user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Arjun Tyagi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWopm7CB27Brsn2nZf_ZcGMYA1rC2xZn0gFS2Ev_B4zUk8mX8MoIQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Love the food here and definitely will be back but most likely grabbing take out over dine in if coming on the weekend. Came here for the first time on Sat, Oct 20th for brunch at 11:15 AM, it was packed and we (2) put our name on the waiting list, it took about 45 mins to get a seat which was the only negative but we figured it must be good considering how busy it was so we waited. The seating is a bit too close for my preference to the point there is no privacy to have a conversation while you eat but I get they are likely trying to maximize the seating, it's also a pay up front before you order type of establishment so just keep that in mind. Not my favourite since I like to tip well but based off the service so in these pre pay scenarios I unfortunately just have to go 15% because I'm hoping it's going to be good, but I don't blame them with all the shady people these days doing dine and dash and etc.

That's where the complaints end, the food was absolutely amazing and the staff are very friendly and welcoming. I will definitely be coming back and seeing if they're a bit less busy perhaps for a later brunch around 1:30-2 PM next time and if not I'll stick to take out.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM4miz5R1JAfwId5oUPDkbUvfO1VKqG9oN3FhiG&fid=0x0:0xaafa76a6be83bd15"],"When":"2024-10-20"},{"Name":"Tyler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV44fpfaEhe-NUZmd0KxbQW5h4ZO24PneHP0Sgtc4_visySni_S=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I can't say enough good things about the food. The bowls are huge and though they seem pricy at first, the amount of food you get is well worth it.

Our first visit came highly recommended by a friend and we were also suggested to try the bowls. We went with the Plant Based bowl and the Brisket Bowl.

The brisket was extremely tasty and delicious. Broke apart with barely a sight of the fork. The combinations were great.

The plant based bowl was equally tasty with the chorizo style no-meat.

The server was very kind and was excited to help us out of provide information.

The problem however, is their pay-at-window system. They require you to pay prior to being served and their system pops up for a tip of 15% or more, prior to having had any service. I voiced my frustration to the server and although she was understanding, this seems to be a growing trend among many small restaurants.

I don't feel comfortable tipping without service first, and especially when ordering food first, you feel compelled to tip so the restaurant gives you good service. This "good tip first = good service" needs to stop.

If not for their tip system, I would easily rate this place above and beyond. It is STILL a must try in Coquitlam.

Don't feel compelled to tip first, tell them right at the window you'll tip after the meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMN-yo_rdnY4iXeMEJun1d0qpS8UBc72wb_7x32&fid=0x0:0xaafa76a6be83bd15"],"When":"2024-2-24"},{"Name":"Amy W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUXW2kFPUz2ZEuA7b5L3P1pRYoMNSxOcfMvE3AI7nWAbheGCBAE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent food and service if you need catering for office lunch or family gatherings. The owner is easy to work with, understands your requests and accommodates well. I’d recommend providing a budget and let them create a fun surprise menu for your event. (Hint: You can order food that is off their regular restaurant menu!) Generous portion size and packaged well for take out. Best to order a few weeks in advance and pick up if you can as it is a busy restaurant!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPwxxVmyjv9uN1f9MMaxfxZM1_hfx8PLZ62oczi&fid=0x0:0xaafa76a6be83bd15"],"When":"2024-3-8"},{"Name":"Neil Westlake","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUkJv3AzW4tBOSLrqh2jethB1xgQxQAL7dV6GEGf7O6ziwbP2c=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food is phenomenally good. The pan fries are perfection,  scumbled until they are floury on the outside, then cooked to a perfect golden brown.

I had the Longanisa patty inside a brioche bun. My wife had the brisket bowl.

The interior is clean and very well designed with live-edge wood accents.
Service is attentive.

Well worth a visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOBdQidu9-LBp2UYGcCi5vlNKrzu1asCqFnSHqw&fid=0x0:0xaafa76a6be83bd15"],"When":"2022-6-23"},{"Name":"Jasmine C (Jasmine)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUl_wTRZRv85CvyyDAN1cvtTS3H_ie2czWqnkRltr5-8JeM_xhQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I understand why they have such high rating now. Their breakfast bowls have a super big portion and honestly taste really good. Very yummy and filling. Good value. Good food.

This was one of the restaurants attached to the bowling place so washrooms are outside to the left and close by.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNUD6OSE3IfIK4WRh44X3OqHrYzMiEXZHC-znyR&fid=0x0:0xaafa76a6be83bd15"],"When":"2023-10-31"},{"Name":"Marley Mckenzie cook","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX5n4XAwgV26WrtDQFOwKexjEHrP8ok0rq2RztGWysEOnM29r4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"First time trying this place, food was decent but that’s not what I find wrong with this place. It is a busy place and I understand they don’t have much seating but to have customers sit in the back where people are constantly walking past you to go to the washroom or take their kids to the bathroom is unpleasant. The back seating is a joke, they have pest control traps on the floor and it’s where  all the recycling is. I find this pretty disgusting and shouldn’t have customers sitting in the back recycling/ trash area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNg2EmY09HpYOYp0h_X9SgkEoIzE6F1a6apmlk&fid=0x0:0xaafa76a6be83bd15"],"When":"2024-5-20"},{"Name":"Madison G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVtZsEld-Yz5a2Swm5LesjF83lo03ZXPGgujeQvQiLn6WLaIuGx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I really wish I could give this place more stars, but the experience me and my friends had here was a hectic one. First, we came on a Sunday around noon for brunch. Sundays are a very busy day, so we expected a waitlist which is totally fine. We waited about an hour for our table. There was so many people leaving, after an hour of not receiving a call we came in again to check how it was going, they apologized said that it was so hectic they were behind with calling the customers. When we finally ordered and sat down, it took quite a while to get our food. I ordered the chicken sandwich, and I was really disappointed when they put pickled peppers and onions on it when it never stated on the menu that it was on the burger. I didn’t bother saying anything because you could see the staff were already really struggling to keep up with all the orders. Second my two friends ordered the acai bowl, and one was completely forgotten all together. We had to go remind them that we never received an order. I do not blame the workers that day, if anything we really felt bad for how stressful everything was. From my understanding aswell is a lot of them were very new, and being new while working a Sunday ,plus understaffed is understandably very overwhelming. We even noticed they were accidently overcharging guests, and not being able to refund them due to the new machine system. One worker really stood out though; I believe her name was Lea. She was so kind and was going above and beyond to try and fix all the problems and issues that the restaurant was having. She was really trying her best and it was lovely interacting with her. She alone made our experience a lot better. The food we received itself was really well made and very delicious. ( Besides having the pickles peppers/onions on my sandwich ) But Like I said before, I had such high hopes for this place, unfortunately due to our experience and the stress it caused us , this place would not be our first choice to come back to. Overall, they need more staff on a Sunday, and better organization","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmqPqRoJVr9_gx0TGti-1enX-R7IWzO0rr5NXI&fid=0x0:0xaafa76a6be83bd15"],"When":"2023-9-13"},{"Name":"Janet","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJLdrp4_-PzGWs8I7cbVIruptxWktGjE-_19gAKtYsnjV7T8DB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Lovely little brunch place in Coquitlam, the staff is friendly and the place is clean, it is on the small side and at rush hour expect line ups. Food was delicious! Be prepared that while they do seat you, you order at the counter so you pay upfront.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPS52NqhoATiiFpOsVT8tFxwp_yGdQbsREFjSfm&fid=0x0:0xaafa76a6be83bd15"],"When":"2024-3-16"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Soren Oakley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUXYOgTeV2_ww6s9tqNXmDRJczT1aljcVqEtrRtUoOfjdBo_zI_bg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This all started with an unexpected encounter. A friend recommended this restaurant, and at first, we thought it was just an ordinary Korean eatery. Little did we know that the dishes here would be so diverse and delightful. From our very first visit, we completely fell in love with this place. Over the next six months, we came back multiple times, mainly to enjoy their udon and creamy udon dishes.

Although there’s quite a distance from where I live to here, I’m more than willing to take the trip just to visit again! Wishing your business continued success, and thank you so much for providing such amazing Korean cuisine.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOi77AO_2BLOY6EeE011HSVXP_TclX9nfsLjD4-&fid=0x0:0x32c61bd38a609209"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"Ellen Tsang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXzoh866OovBfVlMHdFGLQnEdLyB97Utya-3yzGLsM4EYweL6y3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious korean food. Satisfied my tteokbokki craving! Opens till 12am midnight (11:30pm last call), so good for a late night snack 😋","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNCLfzWc6wBHfYjjBI0E250L7lLfFzfWrIKR6Km&fid=0x0:0x32c61bd38a609209"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Daniel Yim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLQasZok9PzRbGWAPT2JykQMeRGEE-9L_G4T1fQkEB1IiM4sw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Their Seafood Tofu Jiggae is a delightful blend of fresh seafood and silky tofu in a rich, flavorful broth. The Kimchi Jiggae is perfectly balanced with just the right amount of spice and tang, making it a comforting and satisfying dish. And for the Spicy Calamari – tender, perfectly cooked, and with a kick that leaves you wanting more. Highly recommend this place for anyone craving authentic Korean cuisine!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMF6zOjsQvY7QmJU3Kjcc-B3XbQkiQAFftzX1ko&fid=0x0:0x32c61bd38a609209"],"When":"2024-12-1"},{"Name":"Ron Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU4C9fuu3Pgu102q3bAxHKivkiOQqwqKjJditkVdy4zIZ628gCE7g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great place to eat, service was great and food was delicious.  It wasn't that busy when we went in which surprised me.

Ordered the pork hock, came with lettuce wraps, kids meal with tonkatsu.  And the carbonara pasta, which was one of the best we've had.  Pasta was done perfectly and came with plenty of sauce.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOh0X3rkZVUzx9xBJp3KQgna03hKjlsXR_TsK1M&fid=0x0:0x32c61bd38a609209"],"When":"2024-7-29"},{"Name":"Stella Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIiz7riC32XwfhlP5DvzuItYRp8oAjyv_k1YErclM-E0H0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our family’s favorite Korean restaurant in the entire Greater Vancouver area. It offers great taste, generous portions, and a clean, pleasant environment for dining in. HIGHLY recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPLiiN-p8xtwA1-uOvZRiGTzsjpYEWyYIDmHA&fid=0x0:0x32c61bd38a609209"],"When":"2024-12-9"},{"Name":"Charlene Alimot","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJK49oevTBzIqwreFOt7DPeIa3qXCXxyJ2zOmFgYQExA20Kp8Nm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really loved my experience at We Grill today! Overall the restaurant is very clean, the staff are polite and friendly and the food portions are so great for the price.

We ordered Beef Bulgogi w/rice, Rose pasta and Carbonara pasta. All of them tasted so so good and we left feeling so full because they have big portions. Our server was so sweet and attentive and made our visit so much better. I definitely recommend going!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3IQXhfGUCqNRd5Gj9XU17frfYRISey9KfOOQj&fid=0x0:0x32c61bd38a609209"],"When":"2024-7-29"},{"Name":"Jannette Salinas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUNCiCjc6eiEYYi_OI3UFBLaZFQh3EJuupDGtLhx3pepo90_Uaq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing! The food is just delicious. We ordered the Spicy BBQ chicken which was so juicy and the barbecue flavor was there with a generous portion of sauce, we algo got the Rose Udon. Just lovely and a very friendly server. Super recommended.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMnhqqqd7CS8BO_4ciVYiecn5bwi4PqDQk1q2At&fid=0x0:0x32c61bd38a609209"],"When":"2024-8-29"},{"Name":"Damilola Ajiboye","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIn5vQKlTs3-hP4RePJHtoDmc3aXrf7dj3dhn4eifq39b6ysA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"All our dishes we really yummy. We had to order one more plate of the grilled chicken. My picky eater kid ate a lot here","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNxcTz4Ydp_ESb0KBby1NLzAjrj8ubDthYCCXe3&fid=0x0:0x32c61bd38a609209"],"When":"2024-12-19"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVJcSTrvAkETp5GS3z8RhAHVaYouKSaPeknm0ZxbLuelbq-2-0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's a great place to try Korean food in various styles. The seafood is fresh, and the food is delicious. Definitely worth a try. The service is good as well. The only thing to note is that we felt really thirsty after the meal. 😂","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMTZPvyF2Tj-s66US3VDJ-XiHdiAW02TVEMXv5r&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-10-17"},{"Name":"Uucky L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUVU-arllP44rVa-XSyXWrd0b-hNq7ECu4284KMlWJ8XxeidF78qg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food taste needs improvement.

Don’t come if you can’t eat spicy at all.
I ordered Beef tartar bibimbap, seafood on rice. Both of them comes with a red sauce, claimed to be non-spicy, but they are actually a little-little spicy.

The beef in Beef tartar bibimbap has some tendon (?) in it, not as soft as I think, so you need to chew a bit more than just swallow it.

Seafood on rice, even added the red sauce, is kinda bland. The rice is a pretty wet/sticky.

Fried oyster & fries only have 5 pieces of oysters.

The server is kind and nice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOD199c5zDxdMM7Ds_dRLkXLpgJnCeuNirilncm&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-11-16"},{"Name":"C L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWFSCt_t74XiqlEdz6jDYOHmtwc4pgb3Fve6nsF3wEBwwz9hl0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This was my first time dining at this restaurant after a strong recommendation from friends who live in the neighbourhood. The experience and food did not disappoint! We held a birthday party for 13 people, which was tricky for the layout of the tables. However, the staff were beyond accommodating and made it work. They could have used a few more servers on a busy Saturday night, but the staff were very friendly and immediately responsive whenever we asked.

We ordered a variety of dishes, including the seafood hot pot, fishcake soup and fried fish. Amazing flavours and textures, with generous portions that are ample for sharing! The fried items were light & crispy. The steaming umami soups had just the right amount of spicy kick. You won't find traditional bibimbap, japchae or pancakes because their menu heavily features innovative takes on fresh seafood - not for those with shellfish allergies! Plenty of Korean spirits to test out & quench your thirst! At first glance the prices seem high but considering that the plates can be shared, the restaurant offers great value. Will definitely be returning to try the other menu items!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO7rbCmBk0xQzNEDNpQI0kMl_DuMnV3myDZBA-X&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"Hyebin Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUjDtbZAwmClVNZWe8in7iKPeuWFpJk3xV63n3oUYqAkU_8FufJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had seafood ttukbaegi and clam bibimbap a few weeks ago. It was a good combination with the soup and the bibimbap. Not that spicy and had perfect level of spiciness for both.
The restaurant was cozy with booths and looked good for having meal + drinking.
The service was also good. I enjoyed their tea comes with a tea pot. I will definitely visit again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPAW_pwiNbZD2uo1clqF1wwWNE4bFs3c-7MXZAm&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-10-20"},{"Name":"Kwang s Koo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJFo3VGQh4dEQHrPSivYNI5XIEy1BykoaCVmEDpxsBAeHTAFA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"From entering to getting our food…was about 1 hour…

The small seafood hotpot…was 90% clams and mussels…maybe 3-4 prawns couple of abalone and a few other things…I do wish there was less clams and mussels…and has some kind of fish…","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNzs80B65n9dqKlhGLZj9jkiEpWUFk5mHNnEtfR&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-11-30"},{"Name":"Toshiyuki Enzo Shirosaki","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUD_24CqvwnpZ272t1lMbFqdPq5Yicn0-6hmHLPLDbUePqw_ASerw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had dinner at a Korean resto bambad the seafood plate was a huge portion for us four people. I like their beef tartare, very soft and tasty.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTthRBMCpezgjbQIAqo9FQZcioh045Rh5XizB7&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-8-12"},{"Name":"Scott Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHpW7vGME__Zs4wKjXR04Upnw88bkVVyz-H2288JsHocq9vI3r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I came away from the restaurant with a great first impression. The food was solid, especially for the price, and the customer service was decent.

I highly recommend that you get their signature steamed seafood pot. We got a small and it was enough for the family of four. They really pack in a ton of high quality seafood in the small pot. The broth at the end is almost like a bonus and it's absolutely killer if you pair it with a shot of soju.

We also got the Korean beef tartar and they give a lot of extra things to eat with the beef like wasabi, and seaweed.

I will definitely be coming back with a designated driver next time so that I can drink.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP_ntt397jhPBf8nD0ABEKZBcIgPksxdsnfOV5G&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-1-23"},{"Name":"Estairia Hong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXmDLygqZ3OT1WagVoz_S7MOF1DNcLc8uEquGumaFc59ZLDHz6l=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I loved the whole experience here. Service was great. The food though! I love that they have whole octopus on the menu but small complaint for me is that it wasn’t cooked long enough for the meat to soften. Even cutting the octopus with the scissors was a bit challenging. But everything we ordered was delish! I def would love to come back here but it’s far from where I live otherwise I would be a regular here (I think) cuz I loveeeee seafood especially octopus and squid and shell fish! And especially having it cooked with Korean flavours!  Yummmmm!! Oh also the kimchi wasn’t to my liking it tasted too sour/vinegary almost like they purposely made it to cater more to a western food palette.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOqfPJtcPGlVRy_w0dsc2HvQy07vmLEXoiyOdZu&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-5-3"}]

title: Pho Super Bowl (Coquitlam)
descriptions: Laid-back operation specializing in pho, plus shared plates, banh mi & other Vietnamese fare.

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Kim Withers","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXKKnnFnw4jT31ns6Kf5JAE_mqFWTs-3cVvpPNOg1rsbgYPYGl3=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The staff are very friendly and the service was fast. The portions are size is huge. Unfortunately, the food was just ok. My beef broth was warm water and the spring roll was abandoned after one bite.  I love Pho with usually great layers of flavour but this was not it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMVHQeNQdBSdRvMLithlCAHQ5clg64xex06Ja41&fid=0x0:0x55e781ca19889a62"],"When":"2024-10-25"},{"Name":"Tyler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX5pgqDcV4jXxCDs44gFpKqBE7-kpDe9pqH0qySpykt9h70rZWn=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited Pho Super Bowl in Coquitlam and decided to try their pork vermicelli (#66), and it did not disappoint! The portion was generous, with a perfectly grilled, tender, and flavorful pork that had a deliciously caramelized edge. The vermicelli was fresh and well-cooked, served alongside crisp vegetables like bean sprouts, cucumbers, and lettuce, which added a nice crunch to the dish. The fish sauce was light and tangy, complementing the savory pork perfectly without overwhelming the flavors.

The balance of flavors in this bowl was spot on, and the accompanying spring rolls were crispy and packed with flavor, a fantastic addition. The presentation was also great—very appetizing with vibrant colors.

Service was quick and friendly despite the restaurant being busy, and the atmosphere was casual and inviting. Whether you’re a fan of pho or looking to explore other options on their menu, I highly recommend giving their pork vermicelli a try!

This captures the key aspects of your experience while emphasizing the flavor and overall atmosphere of the restaurant!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM5qsIkpneH8Vr6cu3bOhK43yolHJZKWNakgeS-&fid=0x0:0x55e781ca19889a62"],"When":"2024-10-11"},{"Name":"Brandon Collins","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJftMou5k5OJyPtZPxUAjCRk0hWFHK-OghGtQJYsSNzGar9YlLzA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Saw this place on an Instagram reel showing of the variety of traditional veitnamese dishes , all of the meals looked amazing so I had to try it for myself . My son ordered a banh mi ga ( veitnamese sub with chicken) it was ok at best I probably wouldn't order it again . My wife ordered the gom ga ( chicken and rice) she said it was ok also.  We ordered the appetizer of chicken wings they were great ! And for myself I ordered the pho thai bo vein ( pho beef ball and steak ) and yes it was definitely a homerun not only a large quantity but good broth and lots of meat . I'd definitely come back but I'd stick to the pho as that's what this place does best at .","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPtldi51cOIJHaWHgfDa1MC5B_neT-gvoQ0M2R3&fid=0x0:0x55e781ca19889a62"],"When":"2024-8-26"},{"Name":"jay Ko","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKx55LCvOrGRPp-bz8WbkRCn4gZDlDBBz0K8yV1EKgnLoTqXw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The food is good and the price is reasonable. BUT I AM NOT COMING BACK, for sure, because they keep messing around with the bill. This is the third time it’s happened to me. Yesterday, I paid, left with my receipt, and noticed something was wrong—they charged way more than the listed prices. I went back to the store with the bill, and they just said, ‘Sorry about that,’ and handed me back $19 in cash. At this point, I have to say this feels intentional because it’s happened three times now.

Be careful about overcharging here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOXU-etp9J401XNl8xOiZZVO7Htrv6WKijYtByj&fid=0x0:0x55e781ca19889a62"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Shivanie Kumar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVFbollGMNfPGQeQeE1iu9uspIWWpZ_q45kMCmZRZ6VvynDEjM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"WORST FOOD EVER!!! Its not even cooked properly. The first wing was okay but others are like they just served it as undercooked tried checking it with fingers before eating. I guess Getting order in 5 mins is no surprise that they serves u raw. And servers are talking to each other and I am seeing the man using his hand to clean his teeth I am not sure if he has tooth pick or what.. NEVER GOING BACK HERE!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMhaby_MvrAfawZ9TQcyI0HYpdTLgg7iknx9dta&fid=0x0:0x55e781ca19889a62"],"When":"2024-12-11"},{"Name":"Jade Chin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLJWSVoZW1CCY-_xhdgdeWOnL28P_e39FAE_t38PKZ_hYo17g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Comfortable dine in experience. Washroom was clean. Food was fantastic. Service was top notch, fast and efficient. Had the beef stew, large, great portions. Reasonable price. The appetizer fried spring roll was done perfectly. The fried chicken wings were fantastic -- crispy, tasty, not overly salty, lots of meat, juicy. Strawberry smoothie was excellent. Nothing bad to complain about.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Huang Recca","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIDF647f8wTC9xYKRRSNQV8CPkQJrc1Y81nFNPZerRiknh_jw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Heard raving reviews about this and came to try. Portion is big. So you might want to have a take away container just in case. Noodles and soup were on the bland side. But to make up for it, the lemongrass chicken was kinda salty. Fried squid tentacles were replaced with non tentacles part and it didnt even fill up the plate that was served with, so lowkey felt scammed. Service was ok, just that had to call out a few times to get too up for tea (as the chicken seems to have overdosed on salt) , it is also in a busy complex so it depends the time you arrive to snag a parking spot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOCYENXaTqEtkYSY2lS33ozYXVgNFIqK7rnSj28&fid=0x0:0x55e781ca19889a62"],"When":"2024-5-5"},{"Name":"Hannah DG","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU037jR4UWeBkpznNrgaH8CsxofxgLROiN8hrJaQSHBDftuIk7R=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"SPOILED MEAT- DO NOT COME HERE AND RISK GETTING FOOD POISONING.
My boyfriend and I have been loyal to Pho Superbowl for over 2 years since moving to the area. I have also been to their new location on Kingsway. We have tried many different dishes from their House special pho, spicy beef pho, house special with saté broth, their rice dishes, vermicelli dishes, chicken wings, salad rolls, and their bahn mi. We have brought our friends and family several times to eat at Pho Superbowl because we loved their food and generous portions.

Today, I ordered #66 grilled pork and spring roll vermicelli which I have had plenty of times before, but for some reason, the grilled pork tasted sour and off, like the meat had already gone bad. I waved down one of the servers to let them know and she was nice enough to offer to change it to a different meat. I picked out all of the spoiled meat into a small bowl which she took back to the kitchen. Then, I heard the head cook angrily yell in the background. Shortly after, a different lady came back with the same bowl with the spoiled pork and said they can't give me a new one because "I already ate it". What do you mean I already ate it? It wasn't like I finished all the food and asked for a new bowl for free! I just took out all of the spoiled pork out of my vermicelli bowl and planned to eat the rest of the food!

I am beyond disappointed especially since we loved coming to eat here and we were always generous with tipping.... but we are not coming back. I understand that restaurants can sometimes have a one-off, and I am usually willing to give another chance. However, since they did not want to fix the issue after I brought it up (especially regarding food safety like spoiled food), Pho Superbowl doesn't deserve another chance.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmdrUm8xnjIm9gt1H0Nz5JcPG-4epoJmnZ1RFQ&fid=0x0:0x55e781ca19889a62"],"When":"2024-4-28"}]

[{"Name":"Chris White","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJzRlBtbLn_MTw22MPSJNZY56aO7efn0TxSkabP8h45RyA7WQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is your quintessential and nostalgic mom and pop Chinese restaurant! I love these people, I walked in last night and it was empty because they were just closing up. The woman asked me if I had been working and I answered yes. She asked me if I was OK with takeout And then asked me what I wanted. I told her I wanted something custom black bean sauce, chow mein, and lots of vegetables as I sat down they were already cutting the vegetables. Such a nice people such great service and the food waswas fantastic. This is a gem,  a little hole in the wall restaurant with great food run by a wonderful and kind family. It’s not brand new, and that’s why it’s so excellent! It’s got character and love. ❤️
Plus the always make me custom veggie dishes!! I will continue to Support this awesome family restaurant ! 🙏","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPSqHLcNQw7FURU6GQgzSziJNsyTBan_mmRNMtj&fid=0x0:0x8d436817161ac08b"],"When":"2024-12-14"},{"Name":"D S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV-PeUVNeu41R0OvIiWLD9zV4iyAZGwVHh3yeozO_e8MkArmt11tg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Been eating here for years. Love the cozy cafe atmosphere. Don’t expect a fancy restaurant, just a simple small neighborhood cafe that serves up good food. The owner always remembers our name and what we love to eat. Makes you feel at home. Excellent prices. Good food. Family owned and operated. Highly recommended for take-out too.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lam Swiss","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKcrpABvkrMV2liUkHTaQXa4k5H2O8MO19I-XneWFRvSSbj_h-o=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious Chinese Hong Kong food
The boss is friendly and nice
They offer delivery service to nearby places
Will come back often","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMshkQv7wsbETvaoVLrWav_SNIzhktOt20eGGZ5&fid=0x0:0x8d436817161ac08b"],"When":"2024-7-20"},{"Name":"Hashan Peiris","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXQS5tXYmTSP8F6gc8CzViRW9uUkD3rHwc2GCIQJ7tX0r6Ne1oo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We ordered a Malaysian fried rice and a chicken chow mein to take away. They only accept cash or debit cards. Place was not busy by the time we went (between 7pm and 8pm). They took only 12mins to prepare the order and portion sizes are good. It could serve 3 people easily. Both te dishes were good and I  would reccomned to eat it with some chili paste and a sauce to have a full flavor. In addiction to that we added some cucumber and onion salad to the dinner. Both dishes were okay for the dinner.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM_XGtomfPWw1JRWm-yyhp7eet446272UZPmOQo&fid=0x0:0x8d436817161ac08b"],"When":"2023-6-16"},{"Name":"Sam Chang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVSeVO8E3yvku7uop8tLoVEGM_NaXzKBAia20QDNEQRDvXqDThPZA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Beef was a bit tough compared to the same dish served in other restaurants. The quantity and prices are better than most restaurants I have been to though. So it's a good deal!
There was only one waitress doubling for cashier too and probably is the chef's wife or daughter or is the owner.
Cash only or debit card. So bring enough with you.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"L Mk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVA11Vll-dqFbuF7cgumBdvAFntLV_6upoinWS5aQlM6PFl-MMS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We ordered $70 worth of food on Wednesday lunchtime.  A combination for one, egg foo young and wonton soup.

Took it back to my office (in the same plaza) and we ate some. Everything was ok, not particularly good but not particularly bad either.

We got quite busy and didn’t have time for more than a few bites each, the leftovers went straight into the fridge. I tell you this because the next day we were planning to have the rest for lunch but when we opened the container with the combination (broccoli, chicken chow mein and bbq pot fried rice) it smelled really bad. My coworker decided that was due to the garlic broccoli and ate anyway.  He got really sick to his stomach a few hours later.  I tried the egg foo young leftovers but immediately it tasted sour.

The majority of the entire order was leftover from Wednesday and had been thrown out Thursday.

Obviously they did not use fresh ingredients.

Usually leftover restaurant food is good at least a few days.

The woman working there was really friendly and sweet so I feel bad writing this but people need to know that the quality isn’t good.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"james corbett","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXORPNpjn99AmypwXC5L8gqaCK1buk43veXhtLSzHUK1ZItjmE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"From the outside, it does not look like much and a place to walk past. This would be a mistake as the food is amazing for both takeout as well as dine in.
I've been doing takeout for years and finally ate in with a friend. Both of us enjoyed the meal and destroyed the house special chowmein. Beef and broccoli were some of the best I have ever had.
This is a great place to try and you won't regret","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Phebe Lai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL-Z1C27OOwYGEF9JwCtvaCRwmMrnupov1bImceSNjwHKI4NA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I like this place, the lady working you can tell shes been in this industry for years. The food portions are pretty decent with the price, and tastewise its pretty good. I ordered the beef black pepper, the cod fish tofu(?) And chicken chow mein. Its enough to feed 4 people I would say.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Nedra Fernandes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIx0UkAMtiKBUUMMcp5qQ_FgjJSnbXAl2FG-yWFWqLLAtkSfw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I thoroughly enjoyed the kebabs paired with fragrant saffron rice. The lamb shank, served with a special spiced rice studded with sweet raisins, was equally delightful. The slow-cooked lamb was incredibly tender, melting in your mouth with each bite, while the rich, flavorful gravy was simply mind-blowing","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMY3_-l8aFfKgsRIbitG_RgovRp_zKCYOJQhFZ1&fid=0x0:0x5efb9a51da1d2e4b"],"When":"2024-12-21"},{"Name":"Morgan Hf","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUg9v8lwsjqUCJSayLNycctRUMA_VacLbUTiQIB7yQTm9fZhysC=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you’re looking for authentic Afghan-Persian cuisine in the Lower Mainland, this restaurant is a must-try! The kobide and kashke bademjan were absolutely delicious—the kobide was juicy, perfectly seasoned, and made with fresh, high-quality meat, while the kashke bademjan had a rich, creamy texture and a perfect balance of flavors.

Beyond the incredible food, the customer service was top-notch, with friendly and attentive staff who made the entire experience even more enjoyable. This spot truly stands out as one of the best in the area for Afghan-Persian dishes. I can confidently say I’ll be coming back for more.
100% recommend it!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMyRYLRaQDas9K-HsPZPgT13dZqSTuEFbwWhHnc&fid=0x0:0x5efb9a51da1d2e4b"],"When":"2024-12-23"},{"Name":"Rick Khan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXgl51VE-11ZQHoLrvu5S0KCm_i6Bwt16vq_3evtPm8uLm2KZK8Jg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is beautiful restaurant with grocery store .. with fresh meats and vegetables fully halal. Friendly staff .. pricing is very good . Very reasonable.. would highly recommend shopping while food is being prepared… one of the hidden jewels in Port Coquitlam..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQsstMM8TU8e8C0MA5ixwngXX2M_MSvzCYCsjF&fid=0x0:0x5efb9a51da1d2e4b"],"When":"2024-10-16"},{"Name":"mahboobeh mahdavi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU3YbWtkkVDpbXqLSJeS30o8XcUIjgFooeX2FQjYfSyesQD4NWO6g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was so good. Everyone was so kind and the food was one of the best we've ever tasted. 10/10 Definitely reccomend the baklava it was so sweet  and tasty.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3LZ_oaOPya4O8Hc4W7U1ziHhIuJVXidGrowE0&fid=0x0:0x5efb9a51da1d2e4b"],"When":"2024-12-4"},{"Name":"Mohammad M Islam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXuRqeYa0qeQvQy57V-9LRvbVMV5FXbbaQqt8771B7XbII3uUko6A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Day 2 Day Halal Restaurant is likely one of the best Persian restaurants in the Lower Mainland I have been to so far. The food was excellent! I ordered the Vaziri, which came with rice, salad, 1 skewer of boneless chicken kebab, and 1 skewer of beef kebab. It was delicious, freshly made, tender, and juicy. Service was a bit slow but understandable, and pricing seems very reasonable.

The decor is casual, with only a few tables, making it a cozy spot rather than a fancy dining experience. However, the focus is clearly on the food quality and taste, which deserves a solid 5 stars.

There's plenty of parking available, and the restaurant is conveniently located behind the "Day 2 Day Halal Grocery" store.

Overall, it's a great option for a satisfying and flavorful halal meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNs-CtF-t8p6d__qbtNWKvWHOGFoIGHiSzG-wTQ&fid=0x0:0x5efb9a51da1d2e4b"],"When":"2024-6-4"},{"Name":"Adam Cartwright","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKsKnCsOP-0T-zwsfA634EBIBcODT2U7_gjSIBsfbKoL7ngRw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Buddy took me here for a bite to eat. I don’t think I have had kabob that was this good. Very juicy and tastes amazing. Great people. I will have to come back here again. Thanks for the good food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPAzZK86icUerGDPYomOJM5jt-d5X6cSzSAy8LX&fid=0x0:0x5efb9a51da1d2e4b"],"When":"2024-7-26"},{"Name":"Ashiya Khan-Sequeira","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUuYMIyIS3X6ZJpbePdnZYMrcPZPFAgtN0wdVtEOXjUQWZ7pnSL=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We did catering for 70 ppl for our stars sweet 16 birthday. Amazing food, very delicious and great service. The food was definitely a hit and our guests could not stop talking about how good the food was.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNzxnjrRRsXIwZtKpSNUtt9t6flrCi99_UsGRUp&fid=0x0:0x5efb9a51da1d2e4b"],"When":"2024-6-17"},{"Name":"Magic Services","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVxyZHpuGhhxdh7d03gYfQmcEonwO1DsIXihj7u5I5HmvwINks=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely! Here’s a glowing review for Day to Day Restaurant in Port Coquitlam:

⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

I recently had the pleasure of dining at Day to Day Restaurant in Port Coquitlam, and I must say, it was a truly delightful experience from start to finish! From the moment I walked in, the warm and inviting ambiance set the tone for a wonderful meal.

All staffs really nice and friendly,Specially Sonia and Hamed 🌹,thank you so much

The food at Day to Day is nothing short of spectacular. Every dish we tried was bursting with flavor and prepared to perfection. It's clear that the chefs use high-quality ingredients, and their passion for creating delicious food shines through in every bite. The menu offers a fantastic variety, ensuring there's something to satisfy every palate.

In addition to the delectable food, the service was outstanding. The staff were incredibly friendly, attentive, and eager to make our dining experience enjoyable. They were knowledgeable about the menu and provided excellent recommendations.

Day to Day Restaurant has quickly become a favorite spot for me in Port Coquitlam, and I highly recommend it to anyone looking for a memorable dining experience. Whether you're there for a casual lunch or a special dinner, you can expect top-notch food and service. I can't wait to return and explore more of their amazing.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipObswPg8l3CZK5x4spVMzuhtyJXbbQV3iGZNT4I&fid=0x0:0x5efb9a51da1d2e4b"],"When":"2024-6-6"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Paulo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJLcA_plm7bkWjnqTJrnEsHhDOSAcI0Thh-Pnw_Wtq2KxuMbiQFg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've passed by this so many times not knowing what it was.
Their reviews are really good.
Finally decided to check it out for myself and this place did not disappoint.

Their ramen was really full of flavor.
The smoked pork was really delicious.
I had the spicy ramen at medium heat, next time I'll try it at the spiciest heat level, then also try the spicy cheese ramen and the boneless chicken.
The atmosphere and setting is really cool.
The staff (he) was really cool too.
Will def come back here again!

My only complaint would be I wish they had some Korean drinks/beers.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMHIG6wJVcQLDYQ7fWFB7e6tVnpou2Hn4VujJwV&fid=0x0:0x1d20f0214579bd6"],"When":"2024-12-13"},{"Name":"Milad Hakimi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJS3tct7xdR_FQg-khxqYfaH1AaaOQttjGkVsM1Uxloq07E-lf=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We got the smoked pork belly and the regular ramen and they were fantastic!
Also I loved the soft noodles. They’re much better than the chewy ones I had elsewhere.

Definitely will come back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN6pdHHXNBI3xPyFjbzvFC5EqeUzZH6kNuWo_WV&fid=0x0:0x1d20f0214579bd6"],"When":"2024-9-22"},{"Name":"Patty B.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXkD4op5IclLwtyGld7EArEDA0uGPTId3d9EWMFqyBZhH5FvL8b=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We discovered this ramen spot through Google, and we’re so glad we gave it a try! Otherwise, we might have just kept walking past this hidden gem. It’s a great reminder not to judge a place by its exterior 😝.

Our favorite ramen spot has always been Honjin Ramen, but now this place has earned a spot on our list. Whenever we’re craving something spicy, this is where we go. We always order their Spicy Ramen but stick to the Medium Spicy option since it can get quite intense. The ramen has a unique flavor with a Korean twist, and it’s done so well—the flavors and aroma blend perfectly.

We’re also big fans of their Takoyaki. Just a heads-up, though—it’s super hot on the inside, so handle with care! Thank you for serving such amazing food. We’ll definitely keep coming back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNoRoYSUtN1oVG2r8rNjdamRdr2vYc5LhslYEPG&fid=0x0:0x1d20f0214579bd6"],"When":"2024-11-22"},{"Name":"Meredith","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJtIhmRfKvKapzOH3Jh8_o3LvCuX7OoNsQCsk7xHgvu0tUTt3o7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Exterior is very unassuming, menu is simple which I personally prefer and the service was quick. The pork belly and ramen had many levels of flavour and was absolutely delicious. I will definitely be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPxtHNPyh8fyBtLRVCUSGWVYF6wIYqpMKPbW5gB&fid=0x0:0x1d20f0214579bd6"],"When":"2024-8-5"},{"Name":"Yumi Chung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVPFqDkxESWXC88SASBBMb5TodqjqiFWci9IiQVgmoclWTpAqs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Smoking pig aka ramengers- Cute little ramen spot in Coquitlam area. We tried their spicy ramen (mild level spice) and really enjoyed it. The chashu  was really tender and tasty, noodles had a nice bouncy texture and, broth was not as salty so it was nice to drink. Honestly, a pretty solid bowl of ramen. Down to try their gukbap next time. They also offer free serve yourself kimchi on the side, which I actually enjoyed quite a bit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP8n9fE6w2-vtJxTThr1Vy5KEMcEqEY4mEbsBOi&fid=0x0:0x1d20f0214579bd6"],"When":"2024-9-21"},{"Name":"A.J. Canadian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU0mITu_1OR_MuXzhVIkPjHjZnimy2Y-mI64r72OA1Zbucah6-N=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Coquitlam's own Smoking Pig ramen restaurant. You have to try the delicious homemade ramen noodles dishes to experience. I love the decor and aesthetic as well. Where else could you enjoy comic book posters, video games, collectibles and models as you wait for your food. I loved to play classic arcade games on the multi game arcade cabinet. No reservations, first come first served. Recommended","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOTJFHUk7lXF1iKVfbuWKiBy6ed1rROg4UzK42x&fid=0x0:0x1d20f0214579bd6"],"When":"2024-7-13"},{"Name":"AJ Brown","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUsu0-zLfdBIi0BMvFkmCrQ7LvpDpcqpsmyMO44b1viyR7y0ygy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Quirky ramen spot with a LOVE for Marvel! Great ramen with amazing smoked pork whose flavour was out standing. The noodles were a bit different than most places but still really good.

Music was a plus, great playlist that just fits the vibe!

Parking is a little tight though so be aware before you arrive.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMaLROeaK6ohawFwgkWlEVtuInCuP_1-bQQ45d8&fid=0x0:0x1d20f0214579bd6"],"When":"2024-6-23"},{"Name":"Jay","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXpO4Bh8DZWAUVAzJ_hJYjoLutXZbl0vSp4y69d3OqZWEClfNlh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best ramen spot, hands down! I've tried so many places, but nothing compares to this one. Seriously, top-tier ramen. I first tried it last year and now I go almost every other week! If I lived closer, I'd be here twice a week for sure.

Perilla Ramen, Spicy Ramen, Spicy Perilla Ramen—everything is amazing, but the Spicy Perilla Ramen is the ultimate winner! The decor is super cool with Gundam figures, Avengers stuff, and even a little arcade machine (bring some coins). The service is great, and the owner and his wife are super friendly. Absolutely recommend this ramen gem!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNWqVgpoNd-kKKnt6p4FtvUCnoPOIKi3JPP_XNZ&fid=0x0:0x1d20f0214579bd6"],"When":"2024-8-10"}]

[{"Name":"ladan ghafouri","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVQKWEx_YV_Uj80v-xctgsLSGRY6V78hw5KMb4aNvRdZAaXJWti=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The venue itself is simple, elegant, and clean. We visited for lunch, and the food arrived quickly and was absolutely perfect. It was delicious, and I especially appreciated the serving plates. The prices were reasonable as well. We thoroughly enjoyed our experience and will definitely return!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMjCsUSBTawbKgXK-huKvzWAvA0uELlp297DnWZ&fid=0x0:0x6820a0261dd95b8c"],"When":"2024-11-11"},{"Name":"Nowell Alcancia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLDqmFfelGK9VUjuTkW_fGkawlR7g8hmDyutgBrf42CtjnR7rw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Indian food can taste quite ordinary but this bistro’s modern take is definitely extraordinary!

I tried the New Zealand Lamb Chops and it tasted really good. The meat was tender and it was perfectly seasoned. The chips / fries on the side were crispy and flavorful. And the coleslaw has a refreshing dressing.

I also tried their Prawn Shahi Masala and it was divine! The curry is rich in flavor and has the perfect blend of spices. Pairing it with their Naan bread, surely satisfied my cravings.

On top of that, their staff are super nice and service is reasonably fast. The vibe of the place is modern and is sparkling clean. Their prices are reasonable as well.

Overall, I enjoyed dining here and I’m looking forward to try their other menu items.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMo0tJDOAyH-59WlS---YVwfDX2KkhivrAIiw4C&fid=0x0:0x6820a0261dd95b8c"],"When":"2024-11-21"},{"Name":"Isha Verma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMJciArOeeSjHndxQ0XoXcUzL8SA1GQlEX1BVvRzfvovE8hbdaUw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"With the rain I was craving some comfort food today!! We decided to stop by naan club in Coquitlam!
It wasn’t busy so we were sat immediately. We started off with the vegetable pakoras, which were hot and fresh! There was a great crunch with each bite and I appreciated the variety of veggies in it! (Sometimes it’s just cauliflower) . This was $6 during happy hour!!

I decided to have the chole Bhature, the chole (chickpeas) was very flavourful. Not overly spicy at all as I requested mild. It came with yogurt, pickled carrots, and some veggies. Overall I’d give it an 8/10, it definitely satisfied the craving. I appreciated the price point of $13.

My boyfriend had the butter chicken with garlic naan, he said he enjoyed it. He specifically mentioned how he like the creaminess of the dish! The naan was a little too crispy for me but I enjoy the tastes I had.

We also finished off with rasmalai (no picture sorry) and it was a perfect end to the meal. Not overly sweet and the cheese patties were soft 🙂

We enjoyed our meal and would definitely come by again as we live near by! It’s nothing super fancy but if you are looking for a more modern setting then this may be the spot!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQCLBGNcZJsKbodPRENw2s2pzS4GJAdKqIyCXF&fid=0x0:0x6820a0261dd95b8c"],"When":"2024-12-14"},{"Name":"Jason Shanks","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqF_09LHcLQUBwa4sJj1J-2wuuUKxQADdaKcyJX3stv4lfuueH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was great.
Some of the best service I've seen in a long time!
Great ambiance, modern interior w/ house music.
One of the oddest things that I've ever made note of in my reviewing history, the takeaway containers have separate compartments so your food doesn't get smushed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPQJA2rnvWepgotpwrVniRhZsu-2Petoe271gpO&fid=0x0:0x6820a0261dd95b8c"],"When":"2024-12-16"},{"Name":"Harjeev Sudan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKr3qEpqTajogs2eW7vWKZEyVziveS5niHBWoWFN0KHBqHSJA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Beautiful ambience, excellent service, and delicious food. Celebrated my parents’ anniversary and they brought out a delicious treat on the house. The owner is welcoming and kind. Great experience, would recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNMvYbmh7n6wfDnZE3LjJmX6VyewdMMpj66hETm&fid=0x0:0x6820a0261dd95b8c"],"When":"2024-12-19"},{"Name":"Geraldine Sangalang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcAsqfNVs6uRfmsJ5FtsU66GdsPGBE4zo_tn8DnG79e7VADqel9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Great spot for a quick bite. This was my first time checking out the restaurant. After a long day of errands in the neighborhood it was a fantastic space to take a break.

We tried the Chole Bhature, a classic family favourite. While less fluffy and thicker than other restaurants in the Tri-Cities, the chole (chickpeas) were seasoned well. It satisfied the craving.

The chili chicken was wonderful. Well balanced flavours and texture. The Chicken Kadhai had wonderful sauce but it was so scorching hot, it almost tasted like it was warmed in a microwave.

I'd skip the Roomali Roti. It wasn't as thin as I expected. The Naan was better.

Surprisingly, the Veggie Pakora was a highlight. Tasty, light and not greasy. The accompanying sauces were delicious.

Quick and responsive service. You can tell there's a hardworking team at this restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMHWyUDQMmK0YVoHaZI6sDWq2llz6oIwRRDm5Bw&fid=0x0:0x6820a0261dd95b8c"],"When":"2024-10-13"},{"Name":"Martin Matahari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAn1gLSlBMeGXZBHUnKkSJRx9LUQmHP9VKEpiPVA6PU8EOwPbl=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had lunch at this restaurant on a weekday. It was pretty quiet. The place is nicely decorated and there’s seating for large groups. They have a selection of alcoholic and non alcoholic drinks. Ordered a starter and few curries. The crispy kebob was very tasty. I like the flavour of coriander that was in the meat and the dipping sauces were flavourful. The palak paneer was nice too, could taste the fresh spinach and it was not too spicy. The chicken dish with creamy sauce was a bit bland. Could have used more salt. Naan was yummy and soft and I loved the texture of the butter naan especially because it’s so rich and fluffy. The staff was pleasant and attentive enough. My wife enjoyed the experience and overall I would say it’s one of the better Indian restaurants in the tri cities area. Would visit again, but not sure how it is if it’s very busy in the evening.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNNPa5Z0VI5Dw53lpt3zlwrnLz0WhkvWT7Ls1ez&fid=0x0:0x6820a0261dd95b8c"],"When":"2024-7-4"},{"Name":"Amanda Green","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWX2-QkU6r0X4DLM6-w27hOoQabXaFOXnHBh92gU3KWWKAd6KWGjA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very pleasant dine-in experience. It was quiet in the evening and service was warm and attentive. Clean and modern atmosphere. Curries were very flavourful and satisfying, and the naan was, of course, fantastic!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOBb5zokjlevGxJEC-fcJbqd4d-2blpdkAkbUDo&fid=0x0:0x6820a0261dd95b8c"],"When":"2024-11-22"}]

[{"Name":"Marisa Lenarduzzi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIbCzpGYeIKBI2SunoaFci_IoZvVVnbxBDnsfb3PLewJQAy3A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was my first time dining at Oz and it did not disappoint! The overall experience was fantastic. We ordered the dduckochi and cheese balls and they were both delicious. The bibimbap and katsu platter were very good as well and super filling. You definitely get your moneys worth here.

It also has a wonderful atmosphere and feeling inside that is cozy and quiet but still lively. I will definitely be coming back again soon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNaqyr8wzBtJ4GhsosyHHMHgfSOor5SZ1FDiSwc&fid=0x0:0x666f1ced9bf985e9"],"When":"2024-11-10"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Korean food here was a bit unimpressive. Maybe because the restaurant didn’t specialize in any particular Korean cuisine and they had a bunch of different items so ultimately, nothing really stood out for me. It was quite busy when we went and they do not take reservations after 6 pm. Luckily, we got the last table available when we went at 7 pm and it was quite convenient to sit at even for a wheelchair user. We were given the menu, water, and the small side dishes. We were able to order relatively quickly and dishes came out one by one and temperature was right.

We ordered kimchi pancake, pork bone soup, and two kinds of Korean fried chicken which were just perfect to feed for adults. Prices were reasonable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPkn-KfcnXIczMTEP2sbylVcKtdoebbH7O2K1t6&fid=0x0:0x666f1ced9bf985e9"],"When":"2024-8-23"},{"Name":"Alan Zheng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL-QmMYfw75kgf5vonVt_7RAAdUJRl5hAF6Ijht6iC6ZE8aPQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I use to live in this area and frequented this place often. I remember trying it for the first time 5 years ago and fell in love with their hot pot soups.

Coming back here to have a meal with friends was nostalgic. We enjoyed the food as always and would recommend this to anyone looking for some Korean food in the coquitlam area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPtfhd5AfTwF9YtaXD3uJCEFkRn80xV1BvdkYOd&fid=0x0:0x666f1ced9bf985e9"],"When":"2024-8-9"},{"Name":"Warner Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDWKsyLtafyGfK7Q7w1ml3mxeAbc-FKoRYJ5e-a9yHsAmwQ441=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Came here on a Sunday mid afternoon post hike. Wasn’t too busy and our party of 3 was able to be seated immediately.

We were able to order off their lunch special menu (forgot to take a picture) which offered a variety of choices from their regular menu at a discounted price or in a “combo” feature (good value).

Food met my expectations and was decent, however it wasn’t over the top amazing. Think: homey comfort food, and it delivered on point. They even provided us a complementary seafood pancake (감사합니다!)

Staff were friendly and food came quickly. Atmosphere was as good as a mid afternoon would feel. Would have to come back in the evening to get a better assessment.

Overall, would recommend a stop by if you’re in the area and craving some Korean comfort food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM10h1t_t07qL6wsIu5gVMXMR7LOB_efmNYcee9&fid=0x0:0x666f1ced9bf985e9"],"When":"2023-11-2"},{"Name":"Zaena","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU0uL5_BX81jM9l56vBhJlVZo9GPHZpZOUMAV-UObxVeXamgoUc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Loved this place! Staff was kind, food was DELICIOUS and great quality. Some of the best tasting tofu I’ve ever had - they even threw in some Korean fried pancakes for free, since we asked them to remove meat!
Would 100% reccomend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPfok_JVO6TJSOXEdrrWTf-yfX2FNdN4gk1d2K1&fid=0x0:0x666f1ced9bf985e9"],"When":"2024-6-27"},{"Name":"Blessed Love Jamantoc","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXiJkDfqK1tLHwmtym7NT7sodUjHvZSVRt9FJ_NqcdWkISaxfG4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"i’m a tough 5 star pleaser and this OZ got me! they had the best soontofu soup I’ve ever tasted.
they served it hot as you can see, NO MSG after taste, and when I asked for no veggie, they just know. I am filled not w preservatives other restaurants does w their food. I am legit stuffed and fully satisfied w the taste and freshness. keep it up you guys!

won’t be surprised if after this review, they’ll order lots of tofu!

Thanks OZ Sunday (08/25/24) team!⭐️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYlkeGSdZKiS0MHeUvlNOykNIPavovUM3fkGYe&fid=0x0:0x666f1ced9bf985e9"],"When":"2024-8-26"},{"Name":"Danna Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUF9zEuY7zqRjRIluv60FcQUIH-EGyvSKkPFdpcqCORZX_gMg4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is a hidden gem by Coquitlam centre. Really cool atmosphere and great food. Only reason I cannot give 5 stars is some foods we ordered were way too spicy like the teokbokki (rice cake) - if you’re not Korean or you’re not used to eating super spicy, it can be hard to eat.

I recommend sticking to other dishes like their fried chicken or katsu and japchae (glass noodles) which were super flavourful. Overall,  a great restaurant to hang out at with friends and it’s opened until midnight.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAk-bHbstZU-CJdI-wvoyKXTIC0WcdxcUcZTIf&fid=0x0:0x666f1ced9bf985e9"],"When":"2024-9-3"},{"Name":"C.K. Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXvliIHOQduurmeC2qNVm7Qqh1DEmhPsO0tu1I7XaICqV5aAbeB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Consistently great fried chicken that is moist and nicely seasoned. We usually get the chicken platter, and add some sides. Service is brisk and friendly. Parking can be a bit tricky, you might have to hunt around to find a spot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMsdST2XkbY_Ery2Zr05phEZIG16lQXm_c-v8R-&fid=0x0:0x666f1ced9bf985e9"],"When":"2024-5-31"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Lyndsay Krause","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUw_d91QaVdyXJ_iD_9n4lPuhHR3K42K7S3ljCJwkny1L-l3IuysA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Mixed feelings on this one.  We went during happy hour for a friend's birthday as a table of four.  Even at the peak during our visit, the restaurant was at max, half full, but they did have a large reservation table of about twenty.  The food was good, but the service was SLOW.
They were clearly short-staffed, as the manager was working behind the bar while we were there, but we had to ask other servers to find our waitress twice and went up to the bar once to order our drinks because we had been waiting for so long.  That being said, they apologized profusely and comped us free desserts and did explain that they were short staffed. However, if you're offering a happy hour with one dollar oysters in a nice, reputable restaurant, then you should be prepared.
We ordered both off the happy hour menu and the regular menu and there was small tweaks. We would have made to each dish, but overall, a pretty satisfying meal.
We will give them another shot to see if the slow service was a one off.
If you park in the underground and register you license plate at the hotel desk, parking is free.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPzq5Fru9vEfYxmcJR5xpopeyv6MziJcBBPsKfk&fid=0x0:0xcea729f7201067c9"],"When":"2024-10-29"},{"Name":"Olivia Ng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUIR4XKe445qsIhcDQSa4vWiOM9DrqY3ui4NVU5_YRxUleaadGk6w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I celebrated my husband's birthday at this restaurant during happy hour. It was great! I really liked the reservation service and the atmosphere in there. The oysters were especially affordable—only $1 each!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOdpEVhtW5DRj8LXHSixV5OtUbkSaXNC_r14vrH&fid=0x0:0xcea729f7201067c9"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"Wonder M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK3hGfH7AOg7pRCDa3Bl6Ihva2AjzSpnVzAGWxFqmscwMF13g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is our second time visiting Wild Fig and it never changed! Still as good as before. We came back for the $1 oysters during happy hours 4-6pm. Still our favorite.
The server, Gaga, was very accommodating and fun. 5 stars for her excellent service!
We will definitely be back with our family.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUKGUqII20gz8cBwmqEzJxiE-UcceFNmhqqtF2&fid=0x0:0xcea729f7201067c9"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Darrin Moench","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLVTIvDThj7TkTP598AOhul-HvnJ48LyKCbcLeGyiMH4FCfSg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Stumbled into the perfect happy hour!  Buck a Shuck Oysters. $4.50 Beers Nuff' said. Fatima was great.  It was very busy with a big birthday party so you could tell they were slammed. But food was great. And waitress went out her way to make rounds and make sure things kept rolling. Food was great 👍","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMMYYch2lk-bCunpYV7YUh7ZvVaUV-eGh72LWsx&fid=0x0:0xcea729f7201067c9"],"When":"2024-12-2"},{"Name":"Jacky Wan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLB3kh5YHFtu97zOxW9maILk0zgbp2Jc2wc2LfnIwMDfF2vFw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently had the pleasure of visiting The Wild Fig Restaurant + Bar, and it was an outstanding experience! The atmosphere is warm and inviting, perfect for a relaxing evening.

I enjoyed six cocktails over three hours, and each one was fantastic. The bartender, Heyson, truly made the night special. His service was exceptional—attentive, friendly, and knowledgeable about the drink menu. He made great recommendations that enhanced my experience.

If you're looking for a great place to unwind with delicious cocktails and top-notch service, I highly recommend The Wild Fig. I can't wait to return!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9SVtfhGWVywzBeZqt6IVTIHOKpPGQUSE0tYi0&fid=0x0:0xcea729f7201067c9"],"When":"2024-9-24"},{"Name":"Simon Reed","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKqDrptZk5K8r7cAAASAK3dUxXTVH7GnPDIaXKpcuAnggfA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went for happy hour and was pleasantly surprised that the music wasn’t blaring. Our server was great, kept checking in with us even as the place started to fill. For the prices the food was great. Side note, the security guard at the entrance was probably the nicest and most professional I’ve ever encountered.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOjdqhF79SAMToD3ZFc3RaKEVz1HLAFAR17piw&fid=0x0:0xcea729f7201067c9"],"When":"2024-9-27"},{"Name":"Sarah E","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIa_jO-vyQRGGDK2y4e7wiYPff_fxb9XQEgCwprbq-00Y5DNQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Sunday Brunch is excellent.  Many choices of food from hot to cold, including an omelette station where you can chose your own ingredients.  Services are great as well,  friendly servers are always around to see if we need a top up on the coffee or take the plates away.  A very enjoyable experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOMRayiGdaH9mB7u_Sn0vun5pfSAHE5bERYS9Zf&fid=0x0:0xcea729f7201067c9"],"When":"2024-7-7"},{"Name":"Genova “Gen” Pangan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXEIdEux0Y6t5oht2jr_SIjM3bcTupGJn9fR2Ts_u19pLcx_Y6eIg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Highly recommend Wild fig , my friends and I had a wonderful experience . Busgirl name ALONA she amazing pretty  , friendly  and accommodating,  The place not  too crowded     , we came in for happy hour the food was great lots of choices. I will surely come back here .  Excellent restaurant I ever visited .","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOIoFtJ6YSzkBGtcxIq36M8YKi02_GiwIqAY6He&fid=0x0:0xcea729f7201067c9"],"When":"2024-10-12"}]

[{"Name":"Chris Yeung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWYOxOPXQOvXbsAix8HXBKL-O5EsvazFehieSJo9pfX1yg67eWh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I tried the Combo A and Donkotsu Noodle set. The combo was creative, though the deep-fried Donkotsu was a bit dry. The Donkotsu noodle soup was rich but not too salty, and the noodles had the perfect texture.

Overall, the food was good, with portions that matched the price. The restaurant was clean, and the service was attentive.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNJiWVqEQUicvnj4UN7aGvW7oAY8Fjii4m-tJn2&fid=0x0:0x2e11a3da16cf2cae"],"When":"2024-12-18"},{"Name":"Hillbillytc","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV833YeKMKJfxtYeKhRHVRSrikZoFOcCapKBwyEFBOnxiCMeXAZ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The atmosphere was very cozy. The food was fresh a few Gluten free options. The server needs more education on food allergies, they said glutenous rice had wheat in it. So be attentive.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipODChokJiwLHw4vic2jPYoca1qkQ10ZDfzgxxzB&fid=0x0:0x2e11a3da16cf2cae"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"Jason Chi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPKMARPtkW-qvBT6AAYyJlEjrXtkzgH4VYcK-ppxLf_WcPXzSE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This culinary establishment presents an array of innovative and delectable dishes, executed with exceptional skill and finesse. The presentation is equally impressive, enhancing the overall dining experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN8rkn3kPpkSxn2cHZrxkRJmK-0gUhZq3DTtPHY&fid=0x0:0x2e11a3da16cf2cae"],"When":"2024-11-1"},{"Name":"Mireile D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJV5u1JVatWPwA7UeTL1oGIrqmoF69ZqjkCiFxVx6vmbalDmuQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Their aburi sushi and special rolls selection are amazing. Truly melts in your mouth. We appreciate the servers always checking on our table to refill our tea. There’s only paid street parking available in the area and it’s full most of the time but you can walk for about 3-5 mins to the Coquitlam mall parking lot and it’s free there.

Highly recommend this place. Will be back again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNLK4Qc4UsRe94mw0Rar1hGYUJQLLgJqck7FEco&fid=0x0:0x2e11a3da16cf2cae"],"When":"2024-9-3"},{"Name":"Aaron MacEwen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV3Ky6ximZkKg4l7lYD2oaitNzrrzF59AoquM1M8Z4is8xtKGnG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food was slightly different than the usual sushi experience.  More traditional style and great flavours.  It’s was $80 for 3 dudes and we all felt legit full.  We splurged and had the cheesesteak roll as well as the Jalapeño roll.  Really good stuff.  I’ll come back 100%","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOcGYn-PSiqBWEcKZFVNUlpOcmj72QZgRuv3Wdf&fid=0x0:0x2e11a3da16cf2cae"],"When":"2024-10-23"},{"Name":"Cindy Toms","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ5HJ-qdATSAgN1_QzZGnkwF-YTSDY4tw_9IAz6BQTPLKu_6Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really great sushi place with different and unique dishes.  Great combos all served with miso soup. Really good quality food at good great prices.  They have a promo at the moment, Mon - Thurs 4-5.30 20% off!!
Great service, friendly staff, nice clean modern decor and bright environment.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO7YpIDP4g2TQLG7FCgCzrp5OKR_Mx2VAHy4jZD&fid=0x0:0x2e11a3da16cf2cae"],"When":"2023-12-14"},{"Name":"Sarah G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW0JyoRjpi5lPBJJkTFOUeaj7BUs1XOGtQmstXEk9_edkm5_Q_H=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I got takeout here and had to do a review because the salmon oshi was 10/10. Very well priced too for oshi. Everything was really good! Super fresh and tasty. I can’t get over how good the oshi was. Definitely recommend this spot! I will be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMzEragvZzg_Yg2jdetGbUQJR-8weKnZSkpR4Sw&fid=0x0:0x2e11a3da16cf2cae"],"When":"2024-11-12"},{"Name":"Justine H (Sunny)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUmvMXm-P_-zaDju2DtLb4mJNuo8OiXNtbw6zPhVOcICWtiAOQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"There's nothing bad to say nor is there anything amazing or special to mention about this place. Maybe the good reviews caused us to have overly high expectations but the food was pretty ordinary and the prices are really standard. We all left still feeling hungry and how we preferred other Japanese restaurants.

Not much service was offered at all besides waiting with our hand up for a while for someone to finally notice we were ready to order. The tables are close together and the group of people seated behind us were incredibly loud and talking about uncomfortable topics, contributing to an overall "meh"  experience that almost leaned towards negative if it wasn't for the nice presentation of the food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNdFohvFV-ToVUZA8IyMBzgz1CZ0GG8KH-KPkmR&fid=0x0:0x2e11a3da16cf2cae"],"When":"2024-3-4"}]
