[{"Name":"Kimiya Namdar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ5NoUG9m0kwHJtkvaDA-UHALghW-sRI1Mo4nWzPLFWn5wQUVw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"For our anniversary, we decided to stay local and chose Cactus Club, and it didn’t disappoint. We arrived 15 minutes early but were seated promptly. Moe, our host, was attentive and made sure we were well taken care of. We both ordered the steak, which was delicious and came in generous portions. When it came time to settle the bill, we were pleasantly surprised to find that our dessert was on the house—a thoughtful gesture for our special occasion. It’s the little touches like these that make all the difference.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOlxtSajFGYkpR7ks7zBaxq3E_Rq1AoW205uJz3&fid=0x0:0x29de451081a450a0"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"Jennifer Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFO0fgPBTIA1yxL3IXSghRJ6EmshLC1YB1a72b-xeg3kpjHx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Date night with my husband. I got the lemongrass prawns and he got the garden burger with Parmesan fries. No picture, but we also got the chocolate peanut butter bar which we love and have ordered several times before. Service was alright but not outstanding.

Edit: we’ve been back several times and always great food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNz5o-NfFrzlsDuL1toQAzF3vym_4Nh0sKHc_Lp&fid=0x0:0x29de451081a450a0"],"When":"2024-7-14"},{"Name":"Jordan Ho","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW11-xeEA0Ih57ocfphXt0C50QwI614ll6t2qknklEqHoDt3aVy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Solid cactus club location; nice atmosphere and decor. Food quality was good, and service was good as well. If you’ve been to a cactus club location, you know everything is pretty consistent in quality, so this location is no exception. Consistent and stable restaurant chain location if you’re looking for food in the area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM7JfFoNjTGrrXQsFLHbl5e01TNdKb9RpDU_IFL&fid=0x0:0x29de451081a450a0"],"When":"2024-10-14"},{"Name":"Karl San Ramon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMltI1k0x7sCrxqWzfGjhhl5muphr65hDnGIRaggxIcR7yfMIR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Cactus Club has a great atmosphere and excellent customer service. There was a small misunderstanding with my order, but the staff quickly corrected it, and I didn’t have to wait long. The portions are very generous, so you’ll leave feeling satisfied. I highly recommend trying the Grilled Dijon Salmon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNl92y_vb_FdIj60kUcUGAjZPOYeXYYPKVGDMhf&fid=0x0:0x29de451081a450a0"],"When":"2024-9-29"},{"Name":"KANVAS","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIc7GQRe5cyMmMtBU7rwkkBMqSxMQC9wVOgxESX-9VBPO4cx_Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Im not one to go chain restaurants, given it was my first time and was highly recommended by friends. Overall the food was beautifully presented and favourites were well balanced. Toronto your better not let me down your new location is next!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMA1QrmgM-GyOZ24ZLj9F_eDXwNVUXstwreB7rT&fid=0x0:0x29de451081a450a0"],"When":"2024-10-1"},{"Name":"L V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKbiBK61CfZsFrw4Y5hmNaYU_dtvifHPnmGFELAVcKqQqcdlg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We did not make a reservation but we did not have to wait too long to be seated. It is a busy location but the ambience and music is great. We had the Hot Chicken and Pickles, Szechuan Lettuce Wraps and Truffle Parmesan Chicken. Love the combination of the spicy chicken and Pickles. The lettuce wraps were a little too sweet for my liking but it is a great portion size. The Truffle Parmesan Chicken is amazing. All in all it was a great meal, excellent service and ambience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNQyUeOozUAESqYwdONgFOXK7yBuKkPRnZnhibN&fid=0x0:0x29de451081a450a0"],"When":"2024-7-4"},{"Name":"MAY 매이 Elford","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUxJVIiA7BVVmzUGqT6sRzP7-hCdYJttIOnYMeIvWOWZPmq7cr7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Celebrated a birthday 🎂 and the birthday card on the table was a lovely touch. The free dessert with a candle was superb! Thank you for making it special.
Our server was friendly and great!
No problem with ordering and food came out quick and perfect.
Even with someone who had a difficult dietary restriction, the server managed to accommodate my friend. She also managed to get my drink request done!
Thank you! Keep up the good work! Hope we can reserve again for our next visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipND9CuiRPSHeu1y7A29JkMA03atMeWruLWhVzkM&fid=0x0:0x29de451081a450a0"],"When":"2024-5-14"},{"Name":"Saveendra Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJZd7txdrRe6l_t6due-EjqsvQvkp8RAB3UXUlYmpEDbtW_Gw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Birthday Dinner main course with a 12oz New York Striploin cooked to perfection served with tasty asparagus and yummy mashed potatoes. Complemented with 2 Servings of the Classic Margarita. Our Server was excellent and she topped it off with a complementary slice of Cheesecake. Fast Friendly Service with a smile. You have outdone yourself again Cactus. Cheers","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMfICdPqlopgvA2tAkHENDQvkdKkjzF0ti8RHye&fid=0x0:0x29de451081a450a0"],"When":"2024-6-11"}]

[{"Name":"Frank Wu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_FRblBfSgHTr-UE0tiLX-XMrs2VlygGYnC4upIgoM9g7vtg6H=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Solid kbbq in Coquitlam. The meat was fresh, and the side dishes were good. We got our food within minutes of ordering, but the stove had to be kept on a very low setting and it took a while for the meat to cook. We didn’t mind it, though, because we used the time to chat and enjoy the side dishes.
Service was decent, as the staff responded right away to the call button. However, the thermos for the hot water was too small for the entire table, and it had to be refilled a few times.
The location is somewhat confusing. From the parking lot, we had to walk past 4 locked doors to the restaurant before finally reaching the correct one. We almost thought that the restaurant was closed and left for something else.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkajA8nD6IHNby0VZDr8e_gafmmLjFgwNAGS22&fid=0x0:0x6e59361dade417d0"],"When":"2024-11-11"},{"Name":"Kevin Luo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWJMxLZr-3YvPOYEYkCwOqoRgX8yyWGLPYZ19IJEKzgIUssXc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"After dining here several times, I definitely owe this place a review. The food here has been excellent every time. Their meat for Korean BBQ is always fresh, marbled, and of the top quality. I had an Anago (eel) combo meal this time, and portions are massive. The eel was tender and super flavourful. The banchan was plentiful and the selection was great. The yogurt was a nice touch as well. I enjoy dining here and would not hesitate to come back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM45iDDA28LOHZSBXEfeQwHa80yiZgDvE1SzOWH&fid=0x0:0x6e59361dade417d0"],"When":"2024-12-7"},{"Name":"K’s coffee lover","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW-385uQOflrqOxsV0QWsdIyhv-rxdZ7rLwLnLPmzpfPGzr9P6Z=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had heard so many positive comments about the lunch set here, so I finally had the chance to visit on a weekday. From the moment I walked in, the service was excellent. I was seated right away, and throughout the meal, the staff checked in regularly to ensure everything was to my liking and even offered refills on the side dishes.

The hot stone rice bowl set menu was especially tempting, with a variety of options including grilled fish, beef short ribs, vegetarian dishes, and even Korean soy-marinated raw crab and shrimp—dishes that were hard to resist. Each hot stone rice bowl set comes with flavorful Korean side dishes and a daily soup, which is always one of the highlights of Korean cuisine. On this visit, I was offered a spicy beef and silky tofu soup, which was both rich in flavor and incredibly comforting.

For the main course, I enjoyed a whole crab and two prawns. To make it easier, they provided disposable gloves for handling the crab shell. Curious about the best way to enjoy the meal, I asked the server for a recommendation. She suggested removing the crab meat, mixing it with the hot, steaming rice, adding an egg yolk and flying fish roe, and then topping it all off with toasted seaweed. The result was fantastic—rich, flavorful, and incredibly satisfying!

Overall, the experience was a perfect blend of great food, attentive service, and a memorable meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOfQ0DUcbW3jtlTCqTJslbdoDJSbOkQ7SoIXn6E&fid=0x0:0x6e59361dade417d0"],"When":"2024-11-8"},{"Name":"Jessameen Dela Peña","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9mRpmL8-ZJUG7UPFcnsjzRdxjABif-MswbO1rxgJyyWfns8Jd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We enjoyed the Kosoo Combo C for 2, which included Beef Short Rib, Marinated Beef Short Rib, and Marinated Pork Galbi. The experience was great with ample side dishes and the ease of ordering via screen. Service was efficient, and though it was a bit pricey, we left feeling fully satisfied. Plus, it's just a 7-minute walk from Lincoln Station, making it very accessible. I highly recommend this place!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP2oI0_Xuy51sCWwB8XTmtNHBjUma0Dudnu4b6Z&fid=0x0:0x6e59361dade417d0"],"When":"2024-8-24"},{"Name":"Jim Fong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV3tXWnX8xFhA_qZcSgIAVcjedjNVtb5Riz6aB4ltUNzTkDmgfU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great place for Korean BBQ in Coquitlam.

Ordered the Kosoo Combo B for 2 and it was more than enough for my wife and I. The Marinated LA Galbi was sooo tender and tasty. We found the Marinated Rib Fingers a little on the chewy side for us.

The Original Boneless Chicken was OK. Tender and crisp but not much flavour to it. Got scared away when the Soy Garlic Boneless Chicken said “mildly spicy”. 😂 I can’t handle anything spicy (even mild) 🤣

They were kind enough to give my wife a side of Kosoo Sweet Chili Sauce for the chicken. 👍

Word to myself: Don’t sit next to the window in the summertime during sunset. The sun coming through the window was pretty hot. Even hotter when you’re doing BBQ. 😂

Will definitely be coming back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMiiZOETe1b9bXadFoLQWTHGT4aVwaNe7n8pjxb&fid=0x0:0x6e59361dade417d0"],"When":"2024-8-5"},{"Name":"Danny Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8eoyUE6az-FmQo7i2mVq5z64Ow48sgKu1EmLZc0zWWN6DMy5asw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A decent experience. Korean-style on-table ordering tablets. The lunch BBQ sets are actually a pretty good deal, but the soups they come with fell a bit flat. The side dishes are unlimited but also tasted a bit too mass produced.

The service was great though and super responsive. The servers helped us navigate the menus and give us the best value which was much appreciated.

Overall food was a bit meh but the meat was good at a good, value price point. Rice is NOT included in the lunch BBQ set so that’s where they kind of get you.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOUuQRlLttE2XKuuZohO8egDeUJkmJtGMowI6W_&fid=0x0:0x6e59361dade417d0"],"When":"2024-6-26"},{"Name":"Selena B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL9oMe3hVhXNDIiZtsRCJWTyPzsoA7vS6BX-uuHALmBEK2jiw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Commuted long to visit this location because it came up on the Instagram reel that they were offering a $15. When we asked about it, the waiter said it was no longer available and that the influencer must have reloaded an old video? Ended up paying $7 more for what was advertised as $15 which is fine but the principle is not clear. I just checked the website
and it says $15 ??? Especially if I could have gone elsewhere closer to home for the same hot stone set meal. Staff are nice and attentive but we felt played to have even come all the way to Coquitlam. Parking is also paid if you park in the lot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOpa7fc6dpQj5YZxvRzY0BVDNQzgj9FFQcXI89p&fid=0x0:0x6e59361dade417d0"],"When":"2024-12-16"},{"Name":"Minjie Woo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9zCbBrt4O1rQ26qjjR37DSEbPG4bZnbwCbIMdl20MdB7NZLPy=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"We went to try their hot stone bowl set that has been advertised online (through their instagram and TikTok) as well as their current menu to have a variety of side dishes.  We ordered the fried Mandu to start and that was very good. For mains, I ordered the bulgogi hot bowl set and my partner ordered the spicy pork hot bowl set. The main bowls were delicious for both sets. However, they advertise this to be with a variety of banchans (Korean side dishes) and to be honest..I was excited for the banchans. To my disappointment, it came with the absolute bare minimum- kimchi, bean spout salad (you can get these for free at literally any traditionally korean restaurant), and cold jeon. I think the salad was just to fill the tray. The “daily soup” was also disappointing; there were literally just slivers of radish and fish cakes. I was expecting something more substantial, even something like 된장찌개. Maybe they felt pity for this sad tray of banchans bc they put a random bottle of yakult on there as well. I really hope that the restaurant takes this review into account and goes back to serving what they advertise online and on their menu.

Please see the sad reality vs online ads of their hot stone bowl sets. Just so sad and disappointing :(","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMAbsIVgMhpHsUr_OPN5y7pGoXy98WT1Ywvh2_Q&fid=0x0:0x6e59361dade417d0"],"When":"2024-12-8"}]

[{"Name":"Geraldine Sangalang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcAsqfNVs6uRfmsJ5FtsU66GdsPGBE4zo_tn8DnG79e7VADqel9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We visited on a weeknight for dinner. There was only us and 1 other table, but the delivery pickups were constant. On a rainy night, I can understand why.

The food is fresh, hot and delicious. Super comforting flavours.

When delivery people arrived without their warming bag, staff would ask them to retrieve it. This ensured the food would stay warm.

I would highly recommend the seasonal specialty, Khao Soi. This was our first time trying it, and I'd definitely order it again. This dish comes with crispy and soft noodles. When you stir it into the sauce, the fried noodles stay crispy, giving you an amazing combination of textures. Beautifully balanced and satisfying dish.

We also enjoyed the crispy wraps, chicken satay and Pa-Nang Curry.

Very relaxing environment, and I'm glad we popped in. Chada Thai is a fantastic local Thai restaurant that has been in the community for many years.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOgs6Rb5cfnF84J2qgMTdFMob8BlMuzG2vmaGLv&fid=0x0:0x2f614226fab6ab26"],"When":"2024-11-2"},{"Name":"Tiffany Yang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVTMFXTr99Nvibpsf_X84FJETCu3bBQbDSclTYmi4Zeid_pQeVX=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely scrumptious authentic Thai food!!! It is a stable restaurant on our family’s go-to bi-weekly!! The air in this local mom-n-pops Thai restaurant is always filled with the most delicious-food-heavenly-aroma flowing from the kitchen :)
Top notch service, monthly and seasonal special menu items, always a good surprise, keeping the customers’ dine in and take out experience exciting!
Love it. Will be back again next week!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN5i0hMWKO1NoxYJ1hz-r9q_LAgP16LoMW8IBlT&fid=0x0:0x2f614226fab6ab26"],"When":"2024-11-8"},{"Name":"Kareen Cadiz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLw3OKuvTnvabIzBQ3y_Jc5m3vIpEHN-6lVpcIUOUmxioiQzg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of our go to places for Thai food in Tri-cities, can’t go wrong with either dine in or takeout. Their lunch specials are such a good deal (pictured here). And of course the food is consistently yummy, fresh ingredients and good portions.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO-5cRjh_efXpw9-7c5P9WAgZ6JpuWrYyw4MPJE&fid=0x0:0x2f614226fab6ab26"],"When":"2024-9-12"},{"Name":"Charmaine Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMK-vcbBIxyt_pQwyKQmCk5dMi5qXNyvwWP-HdCaK4MzQ7dCIb=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love the authentic Thai food here! The Tom yum soup is irresistible. Green curry fragrance is very good that I can finish the bowl of rice. So far this is one of the best Thai cuisine I have in Vancouver. The lunch menu is still very decent in price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOTDJde8-gQXH92NluWv3gqrtQt309FXJTYEGFh&fid=0x0:0x2f614226fab6ab26"],"When":"2024-7-12"},{"Name":"Parichat B.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3tpKxJcU4Lx_ecgrcufj6LfbAj_OdEqTtupyTak05ILPS6QkOMA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best thai food in town, really yummy authentic dishes in affordable prrice.
All staff was so nice, great in recommendation for a menu and spicy level.
The restaurant is clean and easy to access by walikng from Lincolne station.
I definately go there again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPqEm0G5fpF7dbYNyoStcPpYC-5skgUuqbPXtJY&fid=0x0:0x2f614226fab6ab26"],"When":"2024-12-5"},{"Name":"Aidan Siu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWc1EBOVHC3agFY5CmQn_KE37Zb3iZR8UikBgzoOS_YFnx5fxiO=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hidden Thai Gem in Coquitlam! For a delightful Thai culinary experience, try Beef Pad Thai, a perfect balance of savory and sweet with tender beef, stir-fried rice noodles, and crunchy peanuts. Pineapple Fried Rice with Shrimp is another must-try, offering a vibrant mix of succulent shrimp, sweet pineapple chunks, and fragrant jasmine rice. Finally, savor the rich and aromatic Red Chicken Curry, where tender chicken pieces in a creamy, spicy coconut milk sauce infused with red chili. Each dish is a flavorful journey that will leave your taste buds tingling.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNuMZvozTcY-cgvXAYiOFiAAv451NQXKZubUuHV&fid=0x0:0x2f614226fab6ab26"],"When":"2024-6-21"},{"Name":"Dan Peterson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJbNeFUlLkRmjcX25zxpAW7H_0IDjY0P_SfdPGvxnigSNv-OQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Met up for lunch with a friend and we shared two items-shrimp pad Thai ($15 off the lunch special menu) and chicken yellow curry (the sauce was sooo good)
Portions are generous, food was delicious and the service was terrific.
The food was so good that we both ordered additional menu items togo.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPDrQcz7So_FgPV4M_TJ8yvUjsUhEaOgy7ohjCm&fid=0x0:0x2f614226fab6ab26"],"When":"2024-10-18"},{"Name":"Cat King","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVs0w4Gi6wbbwHozHIMXCxGOYXWgHMRV7NGZtPTmRmCUIubsOlj=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is my mother-in-law's favourite Thai food whenever she visits from Ottawa. We've been here a few times already, and we all believe the presentation of the food is on point every time.  Their flavour is great as well. We always order the Thai chilli sauce and crispy wraps. Their noodle soup dish was good too, but I forgot its name😅 unfortunately, this dish was a monthly special. I wish it came back though. Hopefully it will :) The only downside of the restaurant is that when we pick up the food, it  isn't as good as eating in at the restaurant. But that's the case for all restaurants so. Still, I would say the best Thai in Coquitlam. Just make sure to get their coconut rice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOb87rj0mXOnoCwN0B8gg8gk6BIrvt8yWQgk5EI&fid=0x0:0x2f614226fab6ab26"],"When":"2024-7-7"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Jimmy’s Place Restaurant really has the old timey diner feel. Serving breakfast and lunch, it is conveniently located at the plaza with Lifelabs and is easy to find parking. The menu board is all in chalk and it seems like a Korean couple who is running /working this place. We ordered the big breakfast, French toast, and a cup of coffee which came to $35. Food came out within 15 minutes and the plating was nice and neat. With the booths and the older decor, it really felt like a nostalgic diner film scene and a great place to enjoy homey food and catch up with friends.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP6q_0noapEk5_Wf4UXkv8j8w491LWKMjmP7NTY&fid=0x0:0xe9900134f02548b5"],"When":"2024-11-13"},{"Name":"jsflysrc","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX4HguzwfacbLZjrtaRdONz-ndjKHzniCouQ6QvYeTAM2_r7Nk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had the egg benny with ham. I requested egg medium, and it was cooked perfectly. The hash brown was amazing. It was thin and spread out and it was crispy on the outside. The atmosphere was nostalgic and cozy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMSOZ6vilACZEb3ydgCdKEVZ3w2udG1VxhlJQNF&fid=0x0:0xe9900134f02548b5"],"When":"2024-12-14"},{"Name":"Kim N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbdjDpWyXnvjc80j1Uggeb1c_m_wfTt6lOvg1Z_TeE5AinsEnY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The egg benny didn't have enough sauce on it and the amount of toppings kinda overshadowed the egg flavour. However the harsh browns were done perfectly, soft inside, crunchy outside.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMTAmrbxOpmEngo8zpyDzgNfS7zlzrnxop8lJrt&fid=0x0:0xe9900134f02548b5"],"When":"2024-12-11"},{"Name":"Helen D.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXyu5Lt8dplX_J1Zs_BtplHu93y_yusuUNzg33OmEALysRDnBlb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I never would have guessed in a million years that the food at Jimmy’s is this good 👍 I ran out of lunch options and decided to roll the dice - randomly check out a restaurant with decent reviews on google. That’s how i discovered this hidden gem. I ordered club sandwich with a side of fries, perfectly golden and incredibly crunchy! Also 💕 love that menu was hand written with chalks - adding so much charm to this place","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM65HEEiDJvwD9oWXkN5hNgEoYbELib1cZicna7&fid=0x0:0xe9900134f02548b5"],"When":"2024-6-25"},{"Name":"Daisy Shim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL7FlXh5li6Gu28BxP6ht6L_GsITqqbf4cvI2UudicO556H1w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I found this place to be a cozy and warm Western-style brunch restaurant. It feels like a granny's home, with clean and high-quality food that's reasonably priced. I hope they keep the restaurant running forever so I can visit from time to time when I need that cozy and warm atmosphere :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOPKnKkLYPsKxF-BiIKdw6Otwg74DVWf7EpxCyw&fid=0x0:0xe9900134f02548b5"],"When":"2024-7-1"},{"Name":"Zach R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVNyXkBQi0QB1KYWxYBw3_TLlNrsg-jgaNGjTyuUBUiNpV93KBD=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My favourite breakfast place around the hash browns are incredibly delicious, very reasonable prices and quick service I would eat here every single day if I could.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOJ-3-q5CTC-u4Kmgk7xe1_79XDfTVQpsykLq7i&fid=0x0:0xe9900134f02548b5"],"When":"2024-12-21"},{"Name":"Monette Perez Mendoza","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLz9X9ntKCoshwxo5hjj_35EdDYpSvyTQYpdQotXn5no4bDwA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"We were so disappointed with this place. My daughter and I ordered 2 eggs 2 pancakes and 2 sausages. Pancake is very thin and dry and very small. For the price it wasn’t worth it. Another order was French toast which tasted just like toast and bacon which was over cooked and burned. There was no refill on coffee because she never went around. The order cost us over $50. We should have gone to another restaurant.
I’m just sharing how we felt. Maybe we just ordered wrong. Now we know NOT to go back again. Sorry.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOeTp5XuKH0_Uf6BP_Z559hhKuO9HLsJn6W4Zp2&fid=0x0:0xe9900134f02548b5"],"When":"2024-10-21"},{"Name":"Nathan Woods","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWYlKwIGO9PHjqLgc7mRGN7qYIzJ_Yb1JOij4343pL12ye4fG4D-w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Everybody reviewing this place like it's a five star restaurant.

It's a diner.

The breakfast is on the expensive side. Two eggs, two sausages, shredded hashbrowns and a couple pieces of toast. Add a coffee and it's nearly 20$.

I might be inclined to give it another try for a hamburger. But for breakfast, I think I'll pass...","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOrR37BOe0dFo67nOCgCyVZYXFFhAOByccIj-AW&fid=0x0:0xe9900134f02548b5"],"When":"2024-7-31"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Joanna Nguyen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWolcjmld9gF3v6DkaAWVH8shgENhbGrrRuqb_2RSUD8H4muTAvMg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My bf wanted to go to his favourite korean restaurant, and I know why it's his favourite! They place was super busy, the portions are huge, and service was great.

It also came with a side spicy soup which I thought went well with the rice dishes.

Will come back again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO8P6A19olec1UQuceWSKa7rsA9MwRL-aTg-fCh&fid=0x0:0x779eda11561af078"],"When":"2024-12-4"},{"Name":"Foodie Vancouver","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX6n06QAfqStqer1ZgBILsv-fiSHmrGRZuznSS1ny9iQFfb_Ognuw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The set meal portions are quite large, which is great if you're hungry. However, two of the dishes are noodle-based, so there isn’t as much variety as I’d hoped. The dry-fried chicken has a nice, rich flavor and is definitely a highlight, but the noodles with black bean sauce are a bit bland and could use more seasoning to stand out. The service is attentive and quick, which is a plus, and it would be even better if they offered a bit more of the Korean side dishes to complete the meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP_GScEuDlPfEK9PQ0GnMpW96qMFe5EOMUNfp53&fid=0x0:0x779eda11561af078"],"When":"2024-10-25"},{"Name":"Cristina Capacillo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkGswklRJ5A4f5-FOpPqX-C8TZJwW_ylSCJ_G3toUlURFLaPZS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place was highly recommended by a server at another restaurant 😂 and it did NOT disappoint!!!
We had combo A and had plenty of food for 2 people. The star of the show was the Jjam Bong, we didn’t want to get it spicy because it was our first time, but there was chilli powder on the side for us to add to our liking. We were full by the end of our meal, but I could drink that broth forever 🤣
The hype is REAL about this place!!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPnRRs5JdIS3AEZXBpJXeUF3kYGRCziMUJBQfvQ&fid=0x0:0x779eda11561af078"],"When":"2024-10-1"},{"Name":"Y. Cherski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK-7SLlKKRW0Rqcp9wRXFlvt6gbh0rtI7PMIroLgxETtGiPwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Don't let the modest decor fool you, as this restaurant is a place of culinary surprises, where the banchan may not wow, but everything else certainly does. We ordered Combo B and soon realized that 'family combo' means a feast suitable for a small army, not just two people. The sheer volume of food served was staggering, especially considering the reasonable cost. Each dish, especially the Jjam Bong, was flavor-packed, hitting all the right notes. I highly recommend this spot for large groups looking for a meal that's both delicious and abundant without breaking the bank.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPr6-BFJDmzZwPItzwdIB7zkSPxBQwtC7EaC7eK&fid=0x0:0x779eda11561af078"],"When":"2024-5-27"},{"Name":"Scott Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHpW7vGME__Zs4wKjXR04Upnw88bkVVyz-H2288JsHocq9vI3r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is one of few restaurants left in Vancouver area where you can eat good food without breaking the bank. I personally love their black bean sauce noodle which is sweet and savoury noodle, and their spicy seafood soup noodle is also fantastic.

We also had the sweet and sour pork and deep fried gyoza. They are fresh, and very hot, and perfect for larger groups.

It's usually pretty busy so expect to wait but make sure to come with empty stomach because their portions are pretty big.

I highly recommend this place if you want to try Korean-style Chinese food!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPQmCFsEFCEEbUVw9IgJWJ42tlii-KiUtFuKYw9&fid=0x0:0x779eda11561af078"],"When":"2023-12-5"},{"Name":"Tyler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV44fpfaEhe-NUZmd0KxbQW5h4ZO24PneHP0Sgtc4_visySni_S=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We brought a party of 8 and with some notice they were happy to oblige. We had some food to share for the table and dishes each. The portions are large but very welcome. The fried pork and chicken were light, airy and crispy with perfect seasoning. All the Noodle dishes were very tasty. Some were a little too saucy, but I enjoy that. Will definitely return again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Melanie E","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUR0bJcxqNkJt-i1wxCH3EaQXevncA86panZszfT__NAs_0KWRp=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Friends had introduced me to this Korean/Chinese restaurant that they believe is the best Korean mom & pop place for good wholesome food! It was hopping busy and we ended up writing our names on a clipboard by the entrance. Our wait wasn’t too long. Lots of people were doing takeout. They offer a simple menu without a huge list of items to choose from. We ordered Combo E for $137.90 plus an order of the sweet and sour fried chicken. It’s the best value offering a sampling of this and that with tasty food and decent portions.

I was impressed by their huge portions which were enough to feed over 4 people. There was enough leftovers for at least 3 more meals the following day. If you’re looking for a fancy ambience, you won’t find it here. If you’re seeking yummy food, this is it! The service was great too! There’s plenty of free parking in the lot. They’re just across the street from White Spot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPsPJamenm9VuwfHifCGATz5Tu9W-UynfHpb0ME&fid=0x0:0x779eda11561af078"],"When":"2022-6-24"},{"Name":"Kalvin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXYzAZd-0_JeniSNljNxgImCwzlXWbe6PzaDeAXT6_nhg5vP5E=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very delicious sweet and sour pork, soup noodle very tasty and good service. Price is very reasonable and the amount is alot","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNlHpVHyj9nJ1EjorNa_kPv6XbcyIoHlFHfhXwA&fid=0x0:0x779eda11561af078"],"When":"2024-6-13"}]

[{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The restaurant’s set menu is pretty comprehensive with select sliced meats, soup, rice, and salad. We got the couple for two combo despite being three adults as well as a seafood salad and all of that was just the perfect amount of food. The meats were nice and they were easy to cook on the grill. The restaurant had their air con blasting during the summer which helped with all the smoke from the cooking. You can press a button to get a waiter’s attention. All in all, it was an enjoyable experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMdk7YTvQtA4cOKMVVQglSszfKIHYijWA60r2i2&fid=0x0:0x45ad4bc0e24b6787"],"When":"2024-9-21"},{"Name":"Justin J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ9qB0BPnH-SxgmMKD9knqz657T2834b2TJgDxXzOsqhmSY7g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It’s been a while since I last visited, but the entrance decor remain as memorable as ever. The restaurant offers spacious seating, making it very comfortable. Our server was nice and friendly. The food was good, though the portions are smaller than they used to be. Parking during dinner time remains a challenge and likely will continue to be.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMHgVwV-0kvbYUIu3r0xOVfO1OqcnTmIalwcE14&fid=0x0:0x45ad4bc0e24b6787"],"When":"2024-12-5"},{"Name":"Fuzzy Nemo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMhjGNDhI-RZYgIiVRXnRDEQCiyyP-dsVjb7EhBkcymNr9MvYi0A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I haven't been back here for quite a few years, as I was told that this place have been going downhill.  There are quite a few korean bbq places in the same neighborhood,  I have ventured out.

We had combo B for 2, it was $74.99.  Came worth 4 side dishes, lettuce and many sauces.  The portions are smaller than I remember,  but it was enough for 2 people.   The meat was marinated perfectly and very tasty.

Parking was a little bit of a challenge,  but it depends on the time.

Service was pretty good. [{"Name":"Nishad Kumar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXeVfcio4KMpNXlKKqZ_W1exYSM8gXLXL4WvS4fvBt-1U-9f8M97g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Their spicy tuna is a must try. On the house crockets and gyozas tasted good too. Would visit again when in town. Service felt a bit rushed although there was only 2 parties present.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM1M1EinbkAimMvSMSvex0UvsNX4NLGqK8EsFAi&fid=0x0:0x7f9ed62ea165733f"],"When":"2024-7-28"},{"Name":"Ang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUGWb3_O3SimHemt9Y8iH1IlyQ-yatiHpM4XIHBy8hW2ZFZpJcjTA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Super fast and friendly service! 2nd time here and we ordered the chefs boat and it's so yummy!! such good portions and value for the fresh food, genuinely.

They even gave us an on the house appetizer🥹 so sweet","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOV91eWDjKKY1SgnCnMR4z3HVoODoxI60aU2tZD&fid=0x0:0x7f9ed62ea165733f"],"When":"2024-7-8"},{"Name":"Jessameen Dela Peña","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9mRpmL8-ZJUG7UPFcnsjzRdxjABif-MswbO1rxgJyyWfns8Jd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Really had high hopes for this place but left feeling a bit disappointed. We arrived around 8:45 PM, and the service was quite slow, taking 25 minutes to get our meals.

The takoyaki was served cold, and our appetizers arrived after the main courses. On the bright side, the sizzling beef and chicken teriyaki, tuna and salmon sashimi, and California roll were all delicious. Unfortunately, we never received our full order as the rice and ice cream never came.

Given the high prices and the incomplete order, it was a letdown despite the quality of the food. Hoping they can improve their service because the food itself has great potential.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMG6r9BYhd4HoE6LklkdFF6nNhF-MRr2p-wh2Ft&fid=0x0:0x7f9ed62ea165733f"],"When":"2024-6-20"},{"Name":"Dessi Vali","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJLbnNa8FC81KTFWEURLNTbG0_BnJUUgdBXPsBEM8zfX8u28A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Everything about this sushi restaurant is just amazing. From the moment you walk in, you're greeted with a warm smile and friendly staff. The chef's skills are out of this world, creating beautifully presented and delicious sushi rolls. He even has made his own special rolls on the menu. Pae is number 1. And let's not forget about the manager who ensures that everything runs smoothly. It's clear that they truly care about providing an exceptional dining experience! 🍣😄 absolute favourite spot in BC!!! ❤️ They have private rooms and they provide customer comfort and satisfaction. I would recommend everything on their menu but their moody fever is to die for😍","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNO0ZO6M0KnoILEwOj-eDWjbf1TTC7dgghD8Fnh&fid=0x0:0x7f9ed62ea165733f"],"When":"2024-1-26"},{"Name":"Brianna Zavala","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUIf9OdjmIMd3AWmzZ5YjwB3w5wYRGHZIefs8YIoz5D0NWTe24c=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve been going to Nagano since I was 16 and a friend introduced me to the restaurant, the atmosphere has never changed in the 7 years I have been there. The service is always friendly, welcoming, and efficient! The manager Susie is absolutely lovely and is amazing at recommendations! Every time my boyfriend and I come here we always have the freshest seafood, and the most attentive service from the staff members. I couldn’t recommend them more! I always bring all my family members and friends here, it’s a personal favourite!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMAhFR5DgPCNAsm5HNOZpFWkDu0W6IpFtmG5Z5y&fid=0x0:0x7f9ed62ea165733f"],"When":"2024-2-10"},{"Name":"Sarah Hunter","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIVyE789GJWN_zr7DV0XfjroxqIDs6F_d6oaWdcqc-O4m-SHiM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"By far the best food I’ve had!  What  an experience sitting at the sushi bar.  Pai,  the owner and chef is amazing.  He makes it an event.  All the staff is top notch.  There’s something to be said about a place that has been here so many years and keeps their  staff happy .  Will be coming back again!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"David Mak","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJ7vrBokgq5LSIpG2NE2vKzOyvms_kUiL7U4mZHpmIqLf-ArufGg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Last night, we had the pleasure of dining at Nagano Japanese for the first time. The restaurant offers a traditional North American Japanese menu with no fusion or modernized dishes, nor any super high-end options. However, the craftsmanship of the food, its presentation, and the exceptionally friendly atmosphere make Nagano Japanese stand out.

Our meal consisted of several small dishes that we shared, all of which were expertly prepared with fresh ingredients. The raw seafood, including uni, salmon, toro, fish roes, and tuna, was especially delicious and fresh. But it was the cooked dishes that really impressed us. The fried softshell crab had a thin, crispy batter, yet the crab itself was still tender and juicy. The fried salmon cheeks were also fantastic, with succulent, tender meat clinging to the jaw bones. And the grilled mackerel was cooked to perfection, with crispy, thin skin that was perfectly browned and charred.

However, what really made the dining experience memorable was the friendly hospitality of the owner or manager, Susie. She was patient, accommodating, and genuinely made us feel welcome. She made everything great with her personal touches on customer interactions.

It's unfortunate that there have been several negative reviews lately, perhaps due to a shortage of qualified staff or an increase in takeout orders. Nonetheless, some of the best dishes we had could only be appreciated when freshly cooked and served straight from the kitchen.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOgmliG0wkzCCsfYn85x-UYasSgQBkHZy1LkHwG&fid=0x0:0x7f9ed62ea165733f"],"When":"2023-3-19"},{"Name":"Mina A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUa3Ot95qqtO1ooc2Pz-iCEqTxvgYh82KnLf13it1wz8uNx1lvA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This was the second time we ate here. First time was in 2018 or 2019. My partner didn’t want to come back because he insisted the food wasn’t great the last time we were here. I convinced him that every place deserves a second chance, especially after so long! Upon arrival, we were told to seat anywhere we wanted outside as we wanted to be out on the patio. We chose a table far from the other couple that were already eating on the patio (this table wasn’t quite clean and was a bit slanted). A few minutes later the server came with the menus and moved us to another table that was “level”. But this table was not clean either and there were no chairs, so I had to grab my own chair to help the server out. She wiped down the table after we were seated, so 2 dirty tables even though the restaurant was not that busy. There was a sour smell in the patio the moment we sat down (my partner thought it could be dog pee?). No soap in the men’s washroom. Strong urine smell in the women’s bathroom. We ordered 4 items. The crispy shrimp appetizer with salad and sweet chilli sauce was delicious but would have been better if the sauce was served on the side in case someone doesn’t love the dressing. Gomae wasn’t crisp/fresh. Considering the higher prices on the menu compared to other Japanese restaurants in the city, we had higher expectations. For the mains, we got the sizzling scallop and the black cod. The dishes didn’t arrive together. The sizzling scallops were not really “sizzling”. There were 2 scallops with some mushrooms and vermicelli on a shell over a candle. It tasted good but the portion was small and it wasn’t that special for me to want to try it again. The black cod was charred in some areas and the portion was also small for the price, didn’t come with any sides either but at least it tasted good. The sever never came to check on our food or if we needed anything else, only came once to refill the water/tea, and once more, about 5 minutes after we had finished our food to clean the table and bring the bill. She was very nice though. If I only were to rate the food, considering that it was not exceptional and it was pricy, I would conclude that it’s a 4/5. But considering everything else, I have to deduct a point (I wish I could deduct half points, in which case I would have rated it 3.5/5, but because google maps only does full points, and I just can’t see this place as a 4, then it gets a 3/5). Overall, we are still not impressed , maybe even disappointed a little, and will not be returning. Thank you for having us though.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHe6tz4z7F8SQgqo6zMn7pmnL65n6Rp0VzItOq&fid=0x0:0x7f9ed62ea165733f"],"When":"2023-5-21"}]

However, my kids opted for the herb and garlic oil pizza, which unfortunately was quite dry. If you're considering the garlic and oil option, I'd recommend ordering it with marinara sauce to add some much-needed moisture and flavor. Overall, Good experience the staff is friendly and ambiance was nice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM7JBRA_74hqBnICEIXhIIHy57WIC-163xRpLQv&fid=0x0:0xeeb96139e4be3af4"],"When":"2024-6-1"},{"Name":"Sean Bartlette","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLt6yELNcyy9z0uDF0-vlqNgSGzW8ZS_cZzfxnuFF3pI46v3g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I cannot for the life of me understand the positive reviews of this chain.  Their whole thing seems to be lots of low quality toppings, with minimal sauce and cheese.  The crust is a cracker, not even flat bread.  I get if you want to fill up on the toppings and not bread, but $40 for a large of this quality is a bad deal.  The service was great, prompt and attentive, nice location.  The food is a reflection of the chain, not this location.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Joshua (ThickBurger_Bites)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbIhhMlbxk7OIMpcaP-aSx2m75kt8-mqmXoXAJQ5K99gnxiff1zg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great food. Great service. Great location for a quick bite or gatherings.

We had the large gangster pizza and hot wings. Pizza was delicious, well made and didn’t leave a greasy taste in your mouth. Hot wings weren’t hot per-se, barely a kick, but paired with the ranch dip, a must try.

We paid about 60 for the large pizza, wings as well as fountain drinks.

Service was amazing, one server on shift but super attentive and our cups never ran empty.

Would recommend visiting this place with friends and family, or even a date too. Place was relatively quiet with ample tables available on a tuesday evening.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO2d_rsmzyEmHTxa1fMiRvVikIueFIK6Fy_nZJu&fid=0x0:0xeeb96139e4be3af4"],"When":"2023-2-1"},{"Name":"omid piruzan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWIo1fwmgnihU89y2BheYltZR5Di8RxdgtYiIoXg3sm1NX9OE88=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very Cozy and classic interior, takes you back to 80ies. We visit once a year for school fundraiser night.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMTCYWh8BgvpO7pW648FzzDQdHfnhS945AkONcr&fid=0x0:0xeeb96139e4be3af4"],"When":"2022-2-23"},{"Name":"Fhm","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIfpRdgpo_biUMzsiu-CrM0VVbN_mhJeWqgoaHeNPFxNiHSrqE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The crust is perfectly crispy, the toppings are fresh and delicious, and the service is always friendly.

title: Kimbab Cheonguk

But they introduced new item to the menu. Spicy pork kimbap and pork belly rice cake was quite decent. They also added electronic ordering on the table as well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTUurXXkl4fZMmPk10CLLQn1mBx9c5npRMoHcP&fid=0x0:0x79706faa8a6ab9de"],"When":"2024-11-1"},{"Name":"J Mah","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVah5_SCWJ4eK9HwHqcZsHzHe4mysSpCpR9cLFnAvno_cNxE54=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Super dope place for your authentic Korean fixin’. Awesome chilled atmosphere, attentive and friendly service staff and amazing food. Food was fresh and service was fast. We had all kinds of Kimbap and they were all good. Maybe stay away from the beef. The anchovies were the best one! Cold nudes was awesome and the rice dish was great! Highly recommended in the area!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM7Q9WkV38WHwfYa-ej_qa060uFkh1u3JqfwzfC&fid=0x0:0x79706faa8a6ab9de"],"When":"2024-6-13"},{"Name":"OTL","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIDaiwqYX8MNo2iwWjVkU6yJsdN1hsNiutjtTA1StziK05Irw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The tuna kimbab was good, but not super. For the price it’s your best choice at this restaurant.
The AL Bab was not good, the caviar has a fishy smell and doesn’t go well with cheese, the whole meal is lack of flavour which makes that fishy smell kinda stand out more.
For side dishes, they don’t have the potato and kimchi, which are the two basic side dishes for any Korean restaurant. Instead they have a chopped tomato as side dish, I’ve never seen that anywhere else:) that’s so not Korean.
Btw price has gone up compared to 6 months ago.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMyfoqr-_PRaxiIEHi4fUbotT2rep7wOzwj3GNg&fid=0x0:0x79706faa8a6ab9de"],"When":"2024-2-3"},{"Name":"Janice","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVZXVMFXg99DddIAvq90LvFnx8S8T4fPIqVltf27bqW9si-mrdP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I really like eating Korean food, and this restaurant provides traditional Korean soups. The rice cake pot is especially delicious. I have good memories with my friends here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPNL0lWibvbHFiVRPCHDEnzaVoB2oEsVgoKfhhC&fid=0x0:0x79706faa8a6ab9de"],"When":"2024-8-3"},{"Name":"Michael M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL5TtXFD5TFHxA0qFkZvajQi8GxzUmohXsO6CdwixxaYReHIg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Everything was good. We had a beef kimbab and a seafood dok boki with cheese. We chose the mild version dok boki, which I found a bit sweet for my taste but it was tasty. I like that they give a soup vroth to drink with your order very nice for vancouver weather.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOBTSEIKEOqXRQxw93AJi1mZdjoC2vCybtTGmTl&fid=0x0:0x79706faa8a6ab9de"],"When":"2024-9-19"},{"Name":"Jenny T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJQiARxHBX2qOuMFCAcD1158hVepJ33cdQqK4D0HDfs-eTX1g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"delicious Kimbap!! you order from a tablet at the table now. I enjoy their broth that they serve for free from a tea pot!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMXDijL1-i73J7nfcYpwBLWKbJH-Ld6BKnmLGsT&fid=0x0:0x79706faa8a6ab9de"],"When":"2024-12-5"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Izmet Barranco","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXiQo1jy483UmDOGk0DLpOPmwFqDxOxzKBlrj-9MTXzn_Zhoww=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I gave a try to this place through Uber Eats (had a craving for Dim Sum) and I was very pleased with the result. Everything came well packed and hot. Portions are generous (had left overs for 2 more meals) and tasty. I will definitely order again from here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMmD7UXmUboit2xbF_yN5Ys4HOi60O1H1dOHOlJ&fid=0x0:0x2f02bed8d172b222"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"Amy Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXXqddZyajPNoFhSfeKC0jxyRc2Om1n2-N6OKu8IHOhfMDJ3cE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Third time to come this restaurant for lunch. Nobody write down your name or give a number to get a table. That’s not good. Always need to walk to cashier area to ask for table. It’s very noisy inside restaurant and hard to talk with friend to bring along. Th good timing for dim sum is after 2pm, no need like up and more quiet.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMQnvjNsoDWrZlglHOi1dhcGhcoRCXeaAcuWXnW&fid=0x0:0x2f02bed8d172b222"],"When":"2024-7-1"},{"Name":"Stacy Purum Jeon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJokIsJGL-fv0gSK_iI4jQxVk_jmrb_b6s-LN0DAYOqzSpY2xQLw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Wonderful place to have family celebration, big group gatherings. But as a big group, prepare to be hungry a little bit. Serving is not super fast but your stomach will be full for sure!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMdARKT_83o7JGkz1gZt3M9u5asO5tb7xwpZ3CG&fid=0x0:0x2f02bed8d172b222"],"When":"2024-7-22"},{"Name":"Christine W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWKPsEE58m4l7C5YBEcOPLQtBTaYwdBFGzTSKEIraaLnCr6OYcs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We made it just before the lunch rush at noon and only waited about ten minutes for a table of 3.

The hostess asked me if I would like Jasmine tea, I said no and asked for Chrysanthemum tea.  She didn’t understand me and brought me jasmine anyway but it wasn’t a big deal.

We marked off the dim sum we wanted on the paper and the dishes came out relatively quickly considering how busy it was, one at a time.

The food was steaming hot and delicious.  We had the egg tarts, fried tofu, shrimp rice rolls, beef balls, pan fried prawn and chive dumplings, chicken feet and beef brisket rice rolls in a clay pot.

Everything was absolutely delicious, the shrimp rice roll was loaded with prawns!  The servers aren’t the friendliest and don’t hide that they’re annoyed when you ask for other things such as hot sauce or a drink.  I understand that they’re busy though and I’m there for the food so it’s not a big deal.

The hostess also missed one item that I checked off on our order but we were full anyway.

Bottom line, yes I would absolutely return for dim sum!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOnaVG2kGThAKwI_-1GwALL1JRsn48bC2BI75fc&fid=0x0:0x2f02bed8d172b222"],"When":"2024-1-15"},{"Name":"Ngoc Ha","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWBQDR7xuHV7zpmSmm8y3qArF6yv91O7Kuz_kGRJuYZ6FiARojF=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is a 3rd time I am here. There are long line up for brunch. I have never had to pay, so I can't tell about tipping thing. The service has room to improve certainly. For example, when we say today the food seem to be a little bit saltier than the last time we were here, and we ask if they have new chef or what; the server acts like we speak nonsense. I am attaching here the updated menu in case you need to know the increased price. Today is September 30, 2024. I recommend you to bring cash to pay and ask for promotion of cash payment.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNwhQqJazyjZJ780aB1nl5jFq0sJazfM_7PRRv9&fid=0x0:0x2f02bed8d172b222"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Kate Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjE4MSAa0c4Uqc8iOt1LfqIkJDL1ULa2Z17gRh4YDWMExQ1A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"---edit June 2024---
I tried different dim sum dishes.
Deep fried squid tentacles - really good. Portion is a bit small

Beef Rice rolls - good texture.

Shrimp paste on eggplant - came out piping hot

Shrimp patty with chives - this one came out cold... it was good but it probably sat there for a while

Deep fried glutinous rice balls with meat filling - the outside mochi was good but the filling was lacking in flavor and in portion

Beef brisket on chan chuen fan - love the noodles. Can't get this type of noodle in many places. Beef brisket was tough and not much flavor. Would try the pork riblets next time.

-------------
In terms of flavor, this has got to be one of the wosrt ones I have been to.

Century egg and pork congee - flavorless. No salt. No base whatsoever.

Hand shredded chicken salad - extremely small. Most places that give smaller portions have expensive jellyfish in the salad. This place is only chicken and preserved vegetables so there is no need for it to be half the size of the plate, smaller than other specialty chef items.

Deep fried chicken knees - giant pieces only to find out it is 80% batter. The garlic salt and spice just sat at the bottom and the chicken was never stirred with it.

Minced pork fried glutinous rice dumpling - the glutinous rice wasnt very sweetened. The insides were ok. The only good thing is that it came with 4 pieces instead of 3.

Overall, the dimsum dishes were not very good. The prices are high with poor quality dishes. Maybe their dinner menu makes up for it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNRL0bQXOdXOmLCPckVyE40kKNkpOpokL1auaQZ&fid=0x0:0x2f02bed8d172b222"],"When":"2023-5-27"},{"Name":"Brayden M.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVPBZNPVNqHW8dSCFike-NLUMkuCrsmT6ZW7ysivwMhyRbgUxkL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here for lunch again, and it's always a great experience here! Arrived around 2p, so we were seated promptly (wait time ~20 minutes during peak hours).
We ordered the 蝦餃 shrimp dumplings, 牛筋肚 beef stomach tendon, 菠蘿叉燒包 BBQ bun with crispy topping, 鹹水角 'football' pork croquette, and 炸兩腸粉 fried rice roll.
The Pineapple BBQ bun was sold out, so we replaced it with a regular BBQ bun. However our order was not properly registered, and we had to wait around half an hour for it to come out, though our server handled the situation very well.
The shrimp dumplings were large and fresh, the pork bun serving was generous, the croquette was hot and fresh, and the rice roll was super quick to come out.
Overall, we had a great experience, save the minor hiccup with the pork bun, and I look forward to coming back!
Total cost for 5 dishes: $48+tip","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tony","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLe2VHyhSpKyyCfA55fvKWDpIItEGlLqapxQWovhsqs48cXNg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been getting deliveries and take outs from this restaurant during Covid-19. Loved the dishes that I tried before  and finally dined in for dinner. Food tasted so much better at the restaurant. Affordable price. Large portions. My favourite everyday restaurant. Cons: restaurant was quite busy today and 2-3waitress. We were lucky since it wasn’t busy when we arrived. But later, I saw others had to wait for long time to get serviced.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNBZRim4hfHTzin_sh6ZqIL_nKFFOeFZvGJ8GUy&fid=0x0:0x2f02bed8d172b222"],"When":"2022-10-16"}]

[{"Name":"Attila Szamoskozi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW2AAt3w8V6vnjRCqXfUE0xqvAqQuLl4Zs8C3rG6vUvIyME7FzU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very friendly service.  Family run establishment.  Portion sizes are large and flavors are on point.  The only suggestion I would make is for the rice to be a bit warmer.  But the flavor and texture of the rice was perfect.  Appetizer of stewed Eggplant with fried onions was very tasty and a very large portion.  Texture of meats was juicy and perfectly cooked.  Prices very reasonable.  Would definitely return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkEt14ac299DDARyd-SgbrVvDagrTz-2sDL7kR&fid=0x0:0xfe998ac6da7bca88"],"When":"2024-11-11"},{"Name":"Melissa Cabot","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIL0zOTwNlNjn9wGw7Rzo6ydbTGCYv0cdQl9NYnK3iWj33iaQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I've been a customer since the beginning, always good, fresh food. I ordered today, after maybe a month hiatus, and the serving size seems smaller, the chicken seemed like leftovers from the day before and the lemon was old. There are way too many options for good Persian food to be lowering your quality.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLuk86eyrKzFCxN3fjC2Gh7WVgfPs4ac8RQel74iDY6fKVzQA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"amex accepted.  Decent barg/beef steak with rice and shirazi salad. The food is not particularly flavourful but acceptable.  It's a fast food place, so service is minimum. The decoration/atmostphere is better than most middle eastern fast food joint. The old lady at the counter is very friendly. Might come back and try the ground beef kebob.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNs14IYo1pHdekx1j-K9eq221uq_FRoesZnYd7a&fid=0x0:0xfe998ac6da7bca88"],"When":"2024-2-13"},{"Name":"Farid Entezari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV35QQyx2JmA30yOGa4kCXMTDZjBP0mMYjKzM0CL9HNh-FF7LAEEA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The kebob house restaurant in poco is a small nice Persian restaurant. I tried their mix kebab dish which is one skewer of ground beef (Koobideh) and one skewer of steak( barg). Taste was good, portion size was good. Lots of parking in the plaza.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipONMghztr8XUKJnLI08J656NjDz94WXClWyIBRM&fid=0x0:0xfe998ac6da7bca88"],"When":"2023-6-8"},{"Name":"Jason Shanks","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqF_09LHcLQUBwa4sJj1J-2wuuUKxQADdaKcyJX3stv4lfuueH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Go check this place out!!!
What a great little place, we will definitely be back.
1.) Food was great, especially the yogurt for the pitta bread. It was light, fluffy, and had fresh chunks of cucumbers.
2.) Great service, although there was a hockey game on the TV good relaxing music for eating was playing at a conversational level.
3.) Meal for two, we were full upon leaving... just over $35.
3.) Clean kitchen, relatively new renovation making the inside comfortable, happily the renos extended into the washroom... some time these strip mall places can have not so great bathrooms... this was nice.
4.) Strip mall parking = short walk to the restaurant","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOFxEqNuD7DW3qZGM5hzj53ap4gsScn4pVQDJj2&fid=0x0:0xfe998ac6da7bca88"],"When":"2023-11-29"},{"Name":"Holly Hui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWhQD6BQlcWfE694GJOqlMhXMwIQT-rKw4jcG8DlxP8gg2emzY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My favourite persian restaurant to order from on UberEats. I've been ordering since February 2024.

I always order the Vasiri combo with Mast-O-Mooseer (yogurt with shallots), and the Shirazi Salad. The perfect meal! The portions are great, skewers are cooked perfectly and not dry, flavourful. What I appreciate is the consistency, I order quite often from here.

This recent order, the restaurant had contacted me about not having Sprite in stock so I replaced it with Ice tea. When I received my order, they had packaged 2 cans of Ice tea. I really appreciate the complimentary drink. I do want to mention when the lady had picked up the phone, she sounded very pleasant and genuine. One day if I'm in the Port Coco area, I would love to dine-in at this restaurant. Thank you","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Steven H.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXK62iJj1ZUFGa-U3A8AjtI1ckQk60_9MMp9OhTpvv0nDBllSzC=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Been here a couple times.

I've always enjoyed the food and experience here.

[{"Name":"Hanna","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWC8PcJ3VMkwuHFoWwqhZMDiwIhI2-B47BTER2vJc8WkL2eueBj=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went here to try their soup in the cold weather by myself.  It was so good!  The staff were so kind and helpful with the menu, and the portion size and side dishes were very large for the regular size, I was unable to finish but it was very delicious.  The atmosphere is cozy; and I left feeling healthy and warm.  The menu items are listed in Korean but English translations are listed beneath each of them!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM89u577pjysd6Ud2W6s8pOofp4JwwhSGoujW8v&fid=0x0:0x60a421469c3df69c"],"When":"2024-12-16"},{"Name":"Brandon Hwang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXM8uHkSNQ1f67I6kzgiBGArFLjuzwkTWQKJg_2bHlV9k1h7-rn=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"If you're a fan of hearty, flavorful Korean cuisine, Bukchigo Jangguchigo is a must-visit. Specializing in Sundaegukbap (blood sausage soup), this restaurant delivers rich, savory dishes that capture the essence of traditional Korean comfort food. However, for those unfamiliar with offal or sensitive to distinctive food aromas, it might take some getting used to. That said, once you acquire the taste, it becomes incredibly addictive.

Their spicy stir-fried gopchang (intestines) is another standout dish, offering just the right kick of heat. Pair your meal with traditional Korean makgeolli (rice wine) for an authentic dining experience. This is a true gem for those who appreciate down-to-earth, everyday Korean dishes that tug at the heartstrings of home-cooked nostalgia. Whether you're a long-time fan or new to Korean cuisine, this spot is sure to leave a lasting impression.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNmjMSNdMGaNsa1YsVZlsKT7zba-V7Z7hmCXrcu&fid=0x0:0x60a421469c3df69c"],"When":"2024-12-9"},{"Name":"Nhi Hoàng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK1QePYF-UVINbDSSmftKYTXlpwLQZXczMrhEF9IMEzva6RJX0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The restaurant is small, crowded during peak hours but the food quality is still delicious. The fried intestines are soft inside and crispy outside. The pig feet has a chosen level of spiciness, great when eaten with rice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNGkIWrbmWEO1OdW_NkRIbYdeJZX8MTIZvkpR-K&fid=0x0:0x60a421469c3df69c"],"When":"2024-9-24"},{"Name":"Derrick Cheung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWAlQdtNkVOB7lzxgMRguauX1p_mYPY6hJnClVyC3T91iV5mPIL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A hidden gem in Korea Town. Always a line up for dinner. Must try their blood sausage soup. If you’re feeling adventurous…I highly recommend the blood sausage and organs soup.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNht1jFAPS1C1p9_21LN87h7lyTM7NXeh6GrNn9&fid=0x0:0x60a421469c3df69c"],"When":"2024-12-5"},{"Name":"Helen D.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXyu5Lt8dplX_J1Zs_BtplHu93y_yusuUNzg33OmEALysRDnBlb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Authentic korean restaurant with a diverse menu and my go-to for comfort/soupy food. I have ordered many dished on their menu. My favorites are blood sausage soup, cold buckwheat noodle and seafood pancake. Obviously blood sausage and intestines/organs are not everyone’s cup of tea. But you can’t really go wrong with ordering just anything there.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPH0qE2e5GlsDQjEvEqGpsSmWj0y2wjr9JNweSE&fid=0x0:0x60a421469c3df69c"],"When":"2024-6-15"},{"Name":"Alice Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDjZlUFVrVbyNDzA-TlBz2GCFmuAzURRrPGrxlmwdYVifV1EsC=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great Korean restaurant. Not super fancy but All their foods are above average. Place to visit if you want to try out authentic Korean foods rather than k-bbq. Expect to wait if you are dining in, but it totally worth it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOT1gy7WK9SJKQkNcwwyZnATpcpIOn4JQOnzFhi&fid=0x0:0x60a421469c3df69c"],"When":"2024-7-1"},{"Name":"Y S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWTmtWUtCZcs7qDdNKdjVbtcx5f5BcDfDU3YRp4zcFsXHKu1_WS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We came on a Sunday for lunch. This place is packed and you have to write your name down for waitlist. But the turnaround time is fast so we only had to wait for 5 minutes.

Don’t expect fancy decor here. It’s more like a hole in the wall restaurant but the food is amazing and authentic. Service was fast. The food came 10 minutes after ordering and it was steaming hot. Definitely will come again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPHggVOoDno6Z5zaaKgIt4YzH4EPGOx7DN2eHu&fid=0x0:0x60a421469c3df69c"],"When":"2024-3-31"},{"Name":"Iven Tse","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWqYBm_0Md_dEh21ObcpKYh8NezukBMGE0J5wxrlAZNMPCyxCi=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Finally made it to this place, my wife and I had tried four times and each time they were packed and we could not wait that long and we ended up across North Road in some other Korean restaurant. It was worth the experience - finally - and though we may not come again, it is not because of the food being bad, it was very…..interesting. The blood sausage and organ soup was very tasty, a bit spicy, and full of flavour. The sausage was encased in real intestine, which made for a nice chewy texture. The seafood soup had large pieces of soft egg tofu, lots of different kinds of seafood from octopus to mussels to clams and prawns and was perfectly spiced.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOPyFB0gsnpW_oMDQUnmmkpYKwvYKZ3u5MAwJSn&fid=0x0:0x60a421469c3df69c"],"When":"2023-2-12"}]

[{"Name":"Y. Cherski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK-7SLlKKRW0Rqcp9wRXFlvt6gbh0rtI7PMIroLgxETtGiPwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This joint had been on my radar for ages, and I’m thrilled the stars finally aligned for a visit. It's a refreshing detour from your typical breakfast/brunch diner and in the best way possible. The Chicken Cobb salad was amazing. It was exactly my idea of a well-balanced meal, and I’d happily eat it any time. The Bulgogi eggs benedict was a hearty recommendation that hit the mark, though I might pair it with a side salad next time to balance things out.
The Americano was a bit watery for my taste, as I prefer a richer, more rounded brew, but the coffee they use is good, as evidenced by the delicious Affogato. Overall, it was a great experience, and I can easily recommend this place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOBBQBsBVne7CdspMkJ7s050MLquoxqAvgVE9Z0&fid=0x0:0x997a53630888a21b"],"When":"2024-8-2"},{"Name":"James Shu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ-X1zh_92u1cTBADC3dN2MfeBqYQzw8dQmS7J28C0kZ28jdQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great brunch place! Excellent food and service. We sat on the patio on a nice sunny day which added to the experience even more.

Recommend the beef bulgogi, very delicious and they don’t skimp out on the beef!! We ordered the beef bulgogi burrito and the beef bulgogi Benedict.

We’ll definitely be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPDU8aoXbh_75qHSir7NAk-kiwBD-O8oLTW_1fU&fid=0x0:0x997a53630888a21b"],"When":"2024-7-6"},{"Name":"Louise Tuck","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWzJMFzeKH8Wl8xeVohNuiA2sGD_md3syY7itgjQ1C7izfji6QePA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely delicious!! We had brunch here and ordered the bulgogi Benny, the bulgogi burrito and the French toast and they were all incredible.. the flavours were perfect, we loved all of it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNOnQ_aGjXa3bnJAENGotVwmpl115v5BrumOCZY&fid=0x0:0x997a53630888a21b"],"When":"2024-9-12"},{"Name":"jen h","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUhCIsdNpI0zn0ln1R2W8y6FEnO7Rpwo3p2N6L3S94WtNoyzHf7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a really good brunch at Kook’s cook. Parking is a bit limited at the front, but there is some in the back and on the side streets. I had the beef, Bulgogi Benedict and my partner had the chicken and waffles. We also ordered a fruit smoothie to share, but it tasted a bit bitter in my opinion. I like that the chicken and waffles came with fresh fruit. The potatoes were nicely done with the Benedict and my eggs were cooked perfectly. Next time I would love to try the pasta dishes! It is a smaller restaurant so services is quite attentive, but don’t come with a large party unless you’re ok sitting separately.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNNeYBlhrRePVvrA0j0eg0xMCc-IzqUANFfwVGl&fid=0x0:0x997a53630888a21b"],"When":"2024-9-6"},{"Name":"Lisa koebel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLw6QlYwmHtALujBhkwO4UyMcd7F8x7DlhGdHsr9U0G5Mtg1w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"BEST breakfast (I’m sure lunch and dinners are AMAZING too - but I’ve only ate breakfast there).  Every time we are in town… we go to Kook’s Cooks!  It’s a MUST! I order the Bulgogi Benny.  INSANELY DELICIOUS!  Fast and friendly service makes this a 5/5 EVERY TIME.  Not fancy… don’t need it… I’d eat their food on a park bench!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPCcZByvgBVPxWlvPe7jqVulpp7g_ReW9fiW8dP&fid=0x0:0x997a53630888a21b"],"When":"2024-8-23"},{"Name":"Arjun Tyagi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWopm7CB27Brsn2nZf_ZcGMYA1rC2xZn0gFS2Ev_B4zUk8mX8MoIQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was my 4th time here and I’ve always loved it. Haven’t had a bad dish from the chicken and waffles to the frittata and pasta. Thankful to have a wonderful breakfast and brunch spot in the neighbourhood.

Their menu is traditional Canadian brunch style with a touch of Asian (Korean) influence from the owners. Having been to South Korea many times in my life the service and fusion flavours are truly unique but give me hints of neat spots I tried on my travels but with a more North American twist. Will definitely keep coming back and continue to spread the word about this fantastic hidden gem.

They have ample parking, cute indoor diner style seating and a nice patio for sunny days outside. The staff are always friendly and attentive and our server on this visit on Tuesday, July 2nd around 1:30 PM - 2:30 PM was absolutely awesome 👏 as well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYQdhaTl4-Ll1Fxf4u7XfkHDY3RfZ0QU3OQ64e&fid=0x0:0x997a53630888a21b"],"When":"2024-7-3"},{"Name":"Juliana Bergstrom","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV9z_V4_T4Kb4r0iN3AY1nc4y5c0skm3bc-4FOsN5--jOSweZ2U=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great coffee and really good food. I got the “healthy parfait” with a side of eggs and toast, my husband got the “morning plate” and their pancakes, which came with a side of fresh fruit. Nice shaded outdoor seating!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM6yy3ZdenGf8tDJae6oxPIJDqV6bA4w59k_K8D&fid=0x0:0x997a53630888a21b"],"When":"2024-7-14"},{"Name":"A.J. Canadian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU0mITu_1OR_MuXzhVIkPjHjZnimy2Y-mI64r72OA1Zbucah6-N=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a delightful find on Austin street in Coquitlam. A great Asian fusion experience with comfort food, I enjoyed a delicious Sunday breakfast with fresh brewed coffee. You must try if you're in the area. Recommended","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM_4x5X2_7Aq9qOGTPgiKI0aE6Nb0fZI1RSf92V&fid=0x0:0x997a53630888a21b"],"When":"2024-7-22"}]
