[{"Name":"Julia Tallentire","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXn_PwbzuLg5S_bvw5WHe4l0QZc_at0pWbVdGfDZVABBRc3U2Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great food! And friendly staff
We've had and really enjoyed so far: ginger beef, Sichuan string bean, spicy tangy dumplings, and Xiao long bao (not pictured)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOeSIwUywSsyDEQI1Pq27rykd23xsm7ar3ppLqg&fid=0x0:0x9d1f8426af958dd1"],"When":"2024-7-1"},{"Name":"Christopher Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVexNzsO8991iK-9EWX-70Xc57sEkVGaaf84klilDJ3qadcoigBw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great Shanghai food! This place has signature beef rolls and dumplings. But don’t be afraid to try their other dishes. This time I ordered beef noodle soup and deep fried squid. Soup was perfectly flavoured (spicy) and noodles were just the right texture. Fried squid was also spot on, seasoned well and nice and crispy. There are lots of items on the menu I still want to try so I’ll be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMgA2PeHLvPPlkRNTVYhK4DL8hjIT3xoB0l1vFA&fid=0x0:0x9d1f8426af958dd1"],"When":"2023-8-8"},{"Name":"M Carol W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXrApweCZ_o2cDt96mptjdkKLzhWxJGrqd2c_QO9FLaF9_6WY6Yig=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had read my local Peaceful Restaurant (Poco) had very good Szechuan food and I was craving decent soup dumplings. I also ordered Dan Dan noodles, which I’d never had before, but seemed like a good bet. I was very happy with my selections.

The soup dumplings were delicious. The skins were not super thin so you had something to chew, but not thick either that it would be heavy. Each dumpling held a lot of soup which was clear and tasty, not greasy at all like some other places.

My Dan Dan noodles were such a surprise. So delicious - the flavours were well balanced. I would definitely return for another good meal there.

I gave atmosphere a 4 only because some of the seats need repair.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMSTDqMuxZj7V8h9zTazE-awoO9lc6V7tJgHCtX&fid=0x0:0x9d1f8426af958dd1"],"When":"2024-2-3"},{"Name":"Janessa Irene","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWpSbGDk4PCkkLcrRU_e1Ak4moHQg_aEB533erdgDtSMnKW0one=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We have been coming to Peaceful restaurant for years. Being from Edmonton, we only get here when we are visiting the Greater Vancouver area and the food is ALWAYS good and consistent. The noodles are so perfectly fresh and chewy, the beef rolls are crisp and the beef is cooked to perfection, the XLB are the best anywhere and the Dan Dan tastes like an airport hug. Often I find service can make or break a restaurant and the service at this location was phenomenal. Our server was attentive without being too much, friendly and super engaging. It was our first time at the Port Coquitlam location and it definitely will not be our last. Thank you again for the amazing service and food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOIbJhJMOR9aBntLk6tLpaANizaTnPokA81-W-u&fid=0x0:0x9d1f8426af958dd1"],"When":"2023-4-25"},{"Name":"Clara","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJWIwshLULE3B_RdNi9aKWLWw8jS-s52J_rdUUXlZsGL8nMFDg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"At the old Deer Garden location, so same humble Chinese restaurant vibes, which is something I personally like (not even any music). I'm guessing due to the pandemic, it was pretty empty, but our food came really quick and service was polite.

They're known for their Xiao Long Bao (soup dumplings) and those didn't disappoint. We got other standard fare in this category of cuisine to test on this first visit (rice cakes, garlic string beans, Taiwanese beef rolls, Northern pork dumplings), and it was all very flavourful. I could eat the rice cakes all day.

Not a fan of using disposable plates, though. Feels a bit irresponsible, especially with so few customers during the pandemic.

Will definitely return for the food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOV8JXRtTwa8nwu5YuczgGlaoLSjK0H7mGNHMmJ&fid=0x0:0x9d1f8426af958dd1"],"When":"2021-9-15"},{"Name":"Shar E.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUSTTeWSwBUCCTyXplz3ZdtlER3HBP0xmei1e1PbBmts9nKzEHujg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I went to the Vancouver branch some years ago. I remember it being really good, so I visited the Coquitlam branch.  It did not disappoint.

We ordered the beef rolls, pan fried pork, sweet and sour chicken, young chow fried rice, vegetarian noodles, hot and sour dumplings, a s Xiao long bao.  Everything's really good.

The only thing I didn't like about is how cold it is inside the restaurant.  They had portable heaters on but it wasn't enough to make the whole restaurant warm.  Probably their heater wasn't working that day.

But other than that, we enjoyed eating in Peaceful restaurant in Coquitlam.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Fred Z.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKlT70QWwV2DY9EdRG6qQQBK_x9FK_vcq8MKjgCHFTXA_U_2g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is new, but they are good! Fresh ingredients, great menu options, and friendly staff make this a go to!  they are always friendly, easy smiling and helpful explaining everything. There is a friendly & lively atmosphere with great tasting food, quality of the meal was excellent and fully loaded.This place is neat and great, I like it very much. I also feel that their response to Covid-19 is very good I have seen in restaurants setting. I highly recommend you try them out, and you'll keep returning.❤️❤️❤️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMjyp9fVbVXFemLZMfLxEZ-DcRgBBL39O9_k3Cm&fid=0x0:0x9d1f8426af958dd1"],"When":"2020-10-31"},{"Name":"Jennifer H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUEzU9INF1_sZTYVftrDSnlryIgHLw3kMLOe1cm6D0xxwHTb8jqsw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Having been to the other Peaceful Restaurants in Vancouver I was excited to hear that a location opened up so close to home. They seemingly opened quietly during COVID so I wasn't too sure what to expect and I'm sure a lot of people also don't realize that this location is here. So that's why I really wanted to try it out and leave a review, because I think there's great potential here and I hope they get more business!

I've been here twice now, as of this review, and I think this is the type of spot where they do some dishes well, and others not as much. I often find that to be the case for restaurants with larger menus, not every place can do every dish well, and I think that's understandable! So your experience here could definitely vary depending on what you choose to order. The first time we came we ordered the Kung Pao chicken because another review said they enjoyed it, but we found it to be pretty "meh" and just okay. So the next time we came we ordered a different chicken dish, the General Tsao's Chicken, and we like that one much better! Much better flavour!

Other dishes that we enjoyed were the Xiao Long Bao (a dish Peaceful Restaurant is known for), the Beef Rolls (another dish they're known for), the Spicy Gingered Beef, the Vegetable & Tofu Stir-fried Noodles, and the Sichuan Stir-fried Noodles. The broth in the Xiao Long Bao (Shanghai soup-filled dumplings) was delicious and went well with the vinegar they serve it with, the vinegar really helps to cut the richness of the broth and pork filling.

The noodles also had a great texture to them, a nice bounce and chewiness that was satisfying. The Sichuan Stir-fried Noodles were my favourite as they also had a nice light heat to them. I will say that the "Spicy" Gingered Beef isn't very spicy but that may be a good or bad thing depending on who you ask. It's still very tasty regardless of if you're a spice fan or not!

I had family members who visited on a separate occasion from me and they said they wouldn't recommend the fried rice (a category I didn't try on my visits) and that the squid had good flavour but was not crispy enough! So maybe keep those notes in mind when you're deciding what to order!

Now, the ambiance at the restaurant is where I think there could definitely be improvement. It's very clean and quiet in the restaurant, but a little too quiet as there's no music at all! So if you go on a quiet night it's a bit strange having it be so silent. I'd recommend they put some light background music of some kind on and it would be much better.

Also in terms of ambiance, they don't provide regular eating utensils, but plastic cutlery and styrofoam plates and cups. Yes this does upset me as someone who hates single use waste, but I do understand that they opened during covid and it seems to be very quiet for dine in (at least when we've gone). I suspect that they may also be short staffed, so this might be a way for them to keep costs low and keep workloads manageable with only a few staff members.

I definitely hope in future that they will move toward regular cutlery and plates, but if this would be a deal breaker for your dine-in experience, then I recommend trying take out! I did see quite a few take out orders get picked up so that's definitely an option some customers are choosing, and it makes sense.

Aside from the music and dinnerware, the waitress was very friendly and attentive, which we appreciated. Parking is also plentiful so there's no issues there. The price is not bad at all  either, we always get at least another meal or two as leftovers so it's good value! My hope for this place is that it can work toward building a better ambiance and that people will still give it a try as they work toward that transition. I think there's room for improvement but I also think there's definitely some things they're doing well!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP0DwGVQ0f-1evWkGfS9MOh0jP9iL_22siWwZpO&fid=0x0:0x9d1f8426af958dd1"],"When":"2021-9-23"}]

[{"Name":"Dana Sliman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVLCGVuOanB5fZdK4mDXVlNu1FRWwlivE-0dO5Jtxe0XvekGJ21jg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Service was fast and efficient, the place was very clean. Since it’s our first time there, We shared but the tomato beef brisket soup, it tasted a lot like canned soup with no deep beef flavor and very few meat pieces. It wasn’t bad, but have been to other better places nearby…","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMaTBTLQf2FreJIFFH4ImcBvwILoTpIPzyGDLYw&fid=0x0:0x99e640954b54822f"],"When":"2024-11-22"},{"Name":"Elaine","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK3sByrBumaUTi4SsjcCOqzuNL-H25OBzqdKkk5bQB9PSzxRg4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Some of the best rice noodles I've ever had.

Pictured is my favourite Tomato broth with beef brisket rice noodle soup.
The meat is soft and tender, with a rich broth. I recommend asking them to add a bit of spice as well.

Service is great too, it might get busy during dinner hours, but is quite empty when I went late afternoons, so you can just chill and eat!

I also recommend their cucumber salad appetizer, it is refreshing and crunchy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMkHFx1k1gMRMUOu0YXCfIFVdwKNMZ7jr_TRjBk&fid=0x0:0x99e640954b54822f"],"When":"2024-7-2"},{"Name":"Justine H (Sunny)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUmvMXm-P_-zaDju2DtLb4mJNuo8OiXNtbw6zPhVOcICWtiAOQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tasty variety of dishes and great service. The noodles were so soft and unique. I loved the quiet atmosphere and the self serve counter in the centre that allowed people to get chili sauce, garlic, and such by themselves. Will be coming back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNg3vtJEdf60AyLtLjeBg8UDQD1HN0YanOnN8ax&fid=0x0:0x99e640954b54822f"],"When":"2024-5-4"},{"Name":"Jenny A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJRvpNIDvr6_vjm-fMJFybg-lbSH8oM7mSKCGMGU6FC8cVuKGk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I liked this place before, I came here many times and recommended this place to a lot of my friends. A year later-last night , I went there because I missed their soup so much. OMG, the soup is different taste, something off. It's not tasty at all. My husband and I were looking at each other and tasted the same thing..something off. The bowls and wooden spoons looked old, dirty and sorry to say " disq...". So we didn't use the spoons at all.  We won't go there again. We are still talking about it now.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Minipa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXLkpsoXCUt-uCoPDrB_Mv40ZqSioejOqdNEdMQaklHEBDE1W1x=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been coming here with my friends and family for a while now - and I have to say these noodles have basically become the staple hang out. Decent price, decent food, and very fast service too.

There is a little cupboard where you can get garnish like green onions, garlic, chili pepper oil, as well as cilantro.

They put most of their stone bowls in stone pots, which keeps the noodle farm (this unfortunately also keeps it hot for a while for those sensitive to heat).

Definitely give it a go :)

5/5 Food
5/5 Service
5/5 Location","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM7uMnBpK-fAlIo111nc222zMkle2-kVZGDgzbs&fid=0x0:0x99e640954b54822f"],"When":"2023-4-19"},{"Name":"Jo Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW1TqwVe-O5n1d06B2UdI-0JvwJ-TmiUkh94kPgCXIRbaD0Dlbo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"- expect a small wait, when it is busy there is no greeter, just look for the clipboard and write down your name
- there is not a lot of parking in front, but there is also a covered lot in the back
- washrooms are quite small and not the cleanest

I would recommend this place for a relatively budget friendly spot for a quick and filling meal.

Food was good, we had the lamb cross bridge noodle and the noodle pot for 3. It was a lot of food. The broths were flavourful and came out piping hot.

We enjoyed the sauce station in the middle of the restaurant for guests to add extra condiments and garnishes.

Service was mediocre. But it was to be expected I suppose, since the restaurant is newly opened and they are adjusting.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPocHZiM_wZnOiV_xs25BbP60_lO-Hd9PkD-J7Y&fid=0x0:0x99e640954b54822f"],"When":"2018-6-28"},{"Name":"J Yeung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKNJ92b9j3lqmRqAgTBh-3qy3x8VVuxDUGF6GquG2EpmZTw61k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A hidden gem! We recently heard out about this place and decided to check it out and have come back 3 more times.

It's always quiet (during the weekday at least), great for kids and there's lots of variety of soup options. I also find that their prices are very reasonable in relation to their portion sizes.

The first couple times we came, the server was very attentive and we had a very pleasant experience. However the last couple times a different server sat us at a table that hadn't been cleaned, slapped a menu on the table and told us to order online through the QR code. If we were a first-time customer, this definitely would have turned us off so beware if this is your first time.

There is a self-serve station for hot sauce and other condiments at the center of the restaurant

The parking lot looks busy but there is free designated parking in their underground lot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOpMdatJkx8IgU1QxY185jbm7t1ihq4dHz7TJN1&fid=0x0:0x99e640954b54822f"],"When":"2023-7-27"},{"Name":"Nick Wang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK9cUtJY153nRWD4hzNcIo_gDDe44hWUa0zRGkneCYmPYO49A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We’ve been to this restaurant many times throughout the years.  The noodle soup is amazing.  They’re served in a clay pot that keep it hot throughout the meal.  The portion is pretty good too.  What I like the most about this place that differs from other noodle houses is that they provide a self serve condiment section that customers can add green onion, parsley, chopped garlic, chili oil and peppercorn oil.  So customers can adjust the flavor and spiciness for their noodle.  I like garlic, so I would always add a fairly good portion so the smell would last for a few days in my breath 🤣.  Their bubble tea is surprisingly good too for a non-bubble tea place.  The pearl is chewy.  They also have a flavor we enjoy so much and haven’t been able to find it elsewhere (long yan and dates milk tea).  As there is only one server that also acts as a cashier and the bubble tea maker, don’t expect too much service.  I guess the restaurant made it clear of that when they made a QR code menu for you to order from yourself.  What they should do next is, buy a robot to deliver the food so they don’t even need a server.  Overall we enjoy the place for our noodle fix.  But the one thing they should really fix is their washrooms.  Let’s just say if you use it before your meal, you might lose your appetite.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPlFVdvlsgmcnXJ_jDxBVi2k4eyh215XvLBhN5&fid=0x0:0x99e640954b54822f"],"When":"2023-7-12"}]

[{"Name":"William Sun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkmcKL_5RgNxu8KdUWMee6riRTwJvYhXZspxAEntHD8iB9YUqU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best authentic chinese food in Coquitlam.

Price: price is very reasonable. You can expect a full meal for $12.

Food: many selections of delicious food. Their cook is excellent and you can’t go wrong with any options.

Environment: environment is so so. Because the restaurant is located in the food court, I would recommend takeout.

Menu recommendations:
-Beef brisket noodle soup: good portion, beef is savoury and chewy. MUST TRY
-小笼包：juicy and steaming. Good for its price.
-红烧茄子：Soft and savoury. Cooked with ground pork. This is a MUST TRY.
-肉夹馍：beef/pork chinese burger. Not the best I’ve ever had, but it’s good enough for most people.
-煲仔饭：very tasty, you can definitely share this with your family since the portions is good .","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORhTGIrV6zRgMFkYrUVCKWT4lLeDavrzKElBbP&fid=0x0:0xd7c9419f07cf01a9"],"When":"2022-6-23"},{"Name":"Melanie Garnett","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHPmLMDZ_VCJl5XMbN4FJqBi3xOI-bQr5aQXQ9IvxBjUJYirA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hidden gem with DELICIOUS food! Juiciest dumplings I have ever had in my life! The chive and egg pancake is so yummy and tender. The beef brisket soup is beyond words, the meat melts in your mouth. The noodles taste fresh and chewy! I can’t wait to go back and try more items.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPs7k0jXZaX33AzOMLEQsYDERypmxa3IBkVHuk5&fid=0x0:0xd7c9419f07cf01a9"],"When":"2020-11-22"},{"Name":"Al","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKJjil4QRaUHyiXUWGmzZhpLW7QF9mVsl2F5PV_aUQ4TMaKlg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tastes like homecooked Chinese food for reasonable prices! The first dishes I tried was the Wonton soup which was light and comforting and their chicken wings which were super crispy and delicious. I will be back to try their other dishes!

P. S. Went back to try their beef brisket noodles and the meat was tender and overall very delicious soup! They have lots of menu options to choose from so you can build your perfect combo.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNFBMHNaxyGX85r9O7F_ThNP7Ed2H3WdaYQ9AqL&fid=0x0:0xddabc62ff82b8911"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Tried the three item combo with sesame chicken, green beans, and bbq pork and it was surprisingly delicious. The meat was saucy and full of flavour. Could have had more green beans in terms of portions. The chow mein was average. The 3 item combo was $15.99.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPDhY_q7wNn6C60wSOQhG35fTA5YIo2NBLgR04l&fid=0x0:0xddabc62ff82b8911"],"When":"2024-8-12"},{"Name":"Happy Sidhu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLyyMaIgDuAnw55L_QkRaEGKi8IpWnP5jyUOt9IbH6p6YbQSA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food used to be better portions here but still better then the Metrotown, meat used to be towered on-top .","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMsNEaD-n-LgO7C86qrVfasxBiOr0mqRIMlmQG7&fid=0x0:0xddabc62ff82b8911"],"When":"2024-12-14"},{"Name":"Nat A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnjKr4KNFAObzj2bIvH9BRInxwKsSvEg1PM25bKfvhxtWZTWHoog=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good place to go if you are looking for large portion sizes. I had the noodles, green beans, mango chicken and BBQ bourbon chicken. The BBQ bourbon chicken had too much sauce and was a bit on the salty side. I wouldn't order it again. The Mango chicken is always good if you want something a little sweet. Noodles were not bad. Green beans are cooked in butter and were quite good. One of the staff was friendly and offered me to sample the mango chicken. Overall, minus the BBQ chicken it was not bad.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN0KKYLmXhPkMNCc40tZ80L5Y_j9gvcDCFyBLG1&fid=0x0:0xddabc62ff82b8911"],"When":"2023-8-7"},{"Name":"J V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIXubf4BA64V16YiH2FLbFkz0cA-ymFySyrMyQMYlXsSONYar4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food really delicious.  The food was tender and fresh.  I ordered the Honey Garlic Spareribs, Honey Mustard Chicken, and Red Bean Rice with Broccoli.

Service was good.  The people were friendly and nice.

Atmosphere:  the food court was super busy on Black Friday.  The restaurant was clean and organized.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM8Wx8YFvhXPNaaZVmAEiVEMkBiBwRmzoed2Ku0&fid=0x0:0xddabc62ff82b8911"],"When":"2023-11-26"},{"Name":"Ny Richard NY","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVlDNPF-DrbmHT47LTOB7oRHGB09r77OmyZnT1Fbb4vmnk5SD7h=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"What is going on with this place? Is it new ownership, bad training or cheap managers? Have they ever had Bourbon Street Grill before working there? The bourbon chicken used to be saucy and amazing. Now it’s dry with very little sauce. Having rice with it makes it a very dry lunch/dinner. If I don’t have a huge cup of water with this, I’ll get constipated. Why is it in Metro town they give you sauce on the side? The quality of this location in Coquitlam Center dropped and desperately need to do better. Got to keep it real.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM1sveXqEWdh29_NAn_8-ohw_8YiULF9dXzVG3X&fid=0x0:0xddabc62ff82b8911"],"When":"2024-3-15"},{"Name":"Jason James","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXjOeectPZC-yl54vwhkEIEWC7kDb-OthFjAg7Xn6ChCoZ-ooFG=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"My wife and I have been going to Bourbon St. Grill for years. It used to be a real treat for us. Yesterday, we picked up a Combo 3 and took it home. We were so excited to dig in… but the excitement soon faded.

The bourbon chicken no longer tastes like it used to. Weak flavour and barely any sauce. They used to have to spoon the chicken out of the broth, but it was pretty dry and the server almost seemed to be upset at having to drizzle the sauce over our rice. There was so much cartilage in the meat that it was actually becoming annoying and nauseating to eat, knowing you’d bite down into something semi-crunchy. We also got the mango chicken, which didn’t taste like mango and was essentially candied meat. The crunch wasn’t from the breading but from crystallized sugars. And the rice? Where did the veggies go? It used to be loaded with an assortment of veggies and now it’s basically rice with a few veggies peppered in for colour.

It’s sad that something that used to be a fun experience has now become such a disappointment. We won’t be back. 😔","Images":null,"When":""}]

Best I’ve had
Always come back to La Ruota for some great slices
Carne Picante is incredible..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTviU8tBh3XBdEINTzCfpD-_30eazxmTHxKOOV&fid=0x0:0xb28c6c54cf384b07"],"When":"2024-9-21"},{"Name":"Brina Wellington","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW_igXj_VFA6UN-NlH930Gh3dSaeG7ma1g0O3gBgnWDbUwpazzf=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The pizza guy said 20 but it took 40 minutes to get our pizza. To me this is eat it right away pizza it does not benefit from sitting in a box the thin crust gets soggy fast that said it was good we ate in front of the place so it was fresh","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPNyz-K_LOnJEAbWNNubKqUE48RU7cjAZt2ZLIu&fid=0x0:0xb28c6c54cf384b07"],"When":"2024-6-12"},{"Name":"Amy Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVOcU52bOwjYSEbSJ2t4-mBspc4KO3qf3ZMty8mlhHcMGCJeSoC=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Me and my family ordered on too good to go (for those of you who don’t know it’s an app that allows restaurants to serve food that was not sold the previous day for cheap) and we have been on the app for a while enjoying the treats. We’ve also been fans of La Ruota for a while but today when we got our order we were so disappointed with the quality of the pizza. 3 slices of the 6 slices were so burnt that it only makes sense that the workers would have thrown it away but instead they decided to still sell inedible garbage. The only silver lining is that there were 3 slices that were okay, but it’s appalling that these slices were even considered for consumption. I’m all for saving leftovers and food, but this was so disappointing.

UPDATE: I don’t think you guys understand my issue. I’m not talking about how fresh the pizza is, I’m not talking about how the pizza wasn’t the exact same as freshly made pizza, I’m talking about how you guys burnt pizza, and then served it to people. That is unacceptable as a restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN94MzId_piwY4RNlX_BBvjMOOLFgr-N7mGMwNK&fid=0x0:0xb28c6c54cf384b07"],"When":"2024-7-9"},{"Name":"Danny D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVMy7cZTSIOMfwAmDoTnpYDFtZXeJmLNdRr4FkFM73bVHc0TxGV1w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I’ve been ordering and visiting La Ruota Coquitlam since the original Italians opened it many many years ago.  Since these new owners took over the pizza and service have gone down hill tremendously. Quality downhill, price uphill.  I always order additional toppings of arugula for example and I swear it never comes on it. They say they’re busy as an excuse. Maybe if they just read the order like a kindergarten student can and you’ll get the order right. Long time customer. Management and staff need to do better. How hard is it to ask for this? Disappointing is an understatement.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"samuel suarez pineda","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWIHKr-_yToakG57E86Bb_8G5a4CUCMIPQbdus_gWzlhzsNYMeILg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The pizza was amazing, the flavor is really delicious, the people that work here are very kind, the best flavor for me was carne picante","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO9BSzM3S2j1rLZtvxvmYF-OX-Pgde5k5jBXWsP&fid=0x0:0xb28c6c54cf384b07"],"When":"2024-8-18"},{"Name":"Viona Halim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV5PMLEtvgkAwv2IjmL8XXm0-Ly_XpBo5Kd0Hv2pxoQ26_Hfy4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It's a different thin crust option for take out pizza if you don't feel like having more of the doughy usual in the likes of Panago, Dominos, Fresh Slice, etc. But that's just it, it's a take-out quality pizza so don't expect anything mind-blowing.

The venue is definitely a step above your usual pizza joint. It's more modern and cozy looking. By the slice, costs about ~$4 /slice or so. If you just want a few slices to eat there, they would warm up the ones on the display for you. I think because they've been sitting on the display and got warmed up, the dough lost that elasticity and chewiness compared to fresh made pizza, but that's really unavoidable for anything that's been sitting on display counter. So maybe you'll get better ones if you order a whole pan size","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPhpUwfzSgIbma1gXxX-xq7pW3KnglGrDRRkUyK&fid=0x0:0xb28c6c54cf384b07"],"When":"2022-11-5"},{"Name":"Daniel Jung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFE7g6vnjf23CW6mDeh4anchF8fxBs6O5Nsx0bvhepuO3MVzWa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Update:
Was invited back and wow!! I was recommended the Bugogi pizza, and it was heavenly! (Just look at the photo) The ribeye was juicy, and the bugogi flavor was spot on with a kick of heat.. I truly enjoyed every bite and tasted why La Ruota has a high rating. I will definitely be back for the Bugogi pizza and to try the other flavors of their pizzas.

The owner truly cares for the customer's experience and making delicious premium pizzas!

*They also had live music when I came in Friday night. The vibe was 👌🏻

Past post:
Reviews brought me here, but unfortunately, the taste didn't do it for me.. For me, the pizza was so sweet.. The pizza sauce was overwhelmingly sweet for me.. I got the Primo with Vegan cheese.
They were friendly and attentive at the front with good vibes overall.
Maybe I'll try again..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOVTGJKMmI11qtIApn-CzoUNB--3h4I2aIwox5R&fid=0x0:0xb28c6c54cf384b07"],"When":"2023-7-24"},{"Name":"Jessameen Dela Peña","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9mRpmL8-ZJUG7UPFcnsjzRdxjABif-MswbO1rxgJyyWfns8Jd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"All in all, it was a delightful experience. [{"Name":"Peter Ryu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIA1mPJxqbAq3sA5Yx2oELWcSP1BdJp83hRCQqxHH8j4y2zYQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went for breakfast on Tuesday.
Service was good.
The food was so good. We had rice noodle w/ minced beef and parsley. Soup was hitting the spot.
Creamy seafood was good. Added some white pepper for seasoning.
The chicken steak sandwich is so good. Their chicken steak is a must try.
Great price, less than $30 for 3 items.
My gf and I left very full.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN4icTkTUUv9JDkn2JtXGDZMAMx_I3hwCSyteyy&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2024-12-10"},{"Name":"Jessameen Dela Peña","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9mRpmL8-ZJUG7UPFcnsjzRdxjABif-MswbO1rxgJyyWfns8Jd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing customer service—quick and friendly! We ordered the BBQ pork, shrimp fried rice, noodles, and meat poutine, and the generous servings lasted for days. Loved the ambiance and the extensive menu selection. Will definitely come back to try more items!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMv9VLbM7Eayn1Tn58vlSESqVHJeByNmFCEMrlt&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2024-6-13"},{"Name":"Johnny C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMH8aFZIGB5a7CFStbNQ6JGT0sYgxOttD7xMtIebcz8N9tnSzq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Typical Hong Kong style cafe.  Sometimes difficult to find parking because lot is share with other businesses.  Food is OK but prices have gone up a bit since the pandemic.  Food and drink arrive quickly.  There are some elbow room between tables unlike other restaurants that’s elbow to elbow.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPP9Yp6b7U-wMOA3h89pt4AgqSR2112vjBXwLXE&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2024-11-16"},{"Name":"J T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJhlRzWDXzdsN5IEg7ILK_EQ56zA9jcQ-fPPr3cS5cgV1YVlw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Copa (cup) of disappointment…

Picking up something in the Poco area and was deciding on some Korean food or this place. In the end, decided on this place since it’s been decade or longer since I have been to this place.

Upon entering, it seems like the interior went through a bit of change and renovation. The place was pretty empty except for 3 booths seated with customers, maybe it was near closing time (1.5hrs before closing). Everything appeared to be clean throughout the restaurant with a comfortable spacing between the tables and booths.

The service was subpar from the server, maybe she was more focused on cleaning and getting off work. When the owner/ manager took over, it was a lot better and she was more polite.

Here were the food I ordered;

1. Sizzling Hot plate combo B+B (chicken steak & sausages) with borscht soup, spaghetti , cold lemon tea. The chicken was a little dry and the soup was a bit off and warm only. And the hot plate didn’t sizzle at all, maybe a 3 second frisk sound?
2. Sizzling hot place combo A+B (filet mignon & deep fried oysters) with lobster bisque, steamed rice, add lobster tail $23 extra. The filet mignon was horrible, first time ever struggling to chew a filet mignon, it was dry and didn’t taste fresh. The oysters were little midgets. The steamed rice was more like overnight rice just added a bit of water and a quick heat up by the microwave, it was dry and hard. And lastly the lobster tail was horrible; it had that bad fishy taste to it, one tiny bite from that and had to stop cause not worth food poisoning myself from it. And once again the sizzling plate wasn’t even warm!! (Facepalm) The only thing okay was the lobster bisque.

Overall, I was quite disappointed with the food. I don’t remember it being this bad? What happened? Closer to closing time and whoever the cook in the kitchen was didn’t give 2 cents about the food being served? Is it really that hard to hire a decent cook nowadays after the pandemic? And for crying out loud, it only takes 30 seconds to heat up the iron plates and how can one pawn off such a bad bowl of rice in a Chinese restaurant? I honestly would send this cook packing for retirement if working for me, definitely wouldn’t tolerate this kind of bs jeopardizing my business.

I guess I retained my good nature and composure by taking into consideration that the owner/manager was very polite and friendly; very poise and elegant with the services. I guess that’s the only good part of this experience and kept my positivity inlined. Just enjoyed a quick instant noodle when back home lol","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMMcEYpyZUuanHEcQL55fa0WprgsuAX0S3V4h87&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2024-1-25"},{"Name":"Chang Wun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXinnRETbtdmwq0G3dzHpocXq4c0y1kT8tCLTmXT5-MPrsCx3WH9g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went back for the breakfast. There are a lots of people in the breakfast timing, the breakfast set is cost effective! Will revisit!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPglBpXDu8S3-D1K1Vx9zNGj1s7HzGBk70B8aKE&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2024-1-4"},{"Name":"Angie L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKwNm9A8ohrfnu_XFwYhP8N-ACXPuzjT8lHAp_d40ZyvMetcg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is Hong Kong style fusion restaurant. The selection is quite good for anything from appetizers, steak and fries, to noodles, rice, soup, combos and beverages.

There's Western style combo that comes with soup, main and drink & Asian style combo comes with Chinese soup, main and rice, no drink. You may think the price is on the high side but you won't disappoint by the portion.

Service is not bad but when is not busy. They are not dial in.

They charge $0.50 per take out container that I have no complaint to support the environmental recycling.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPDjOVajotJjtkKeh90GhichQoqjYaMOeW4VKP9&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2022-1-2"},{"Name":"Nathan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6aOctokU9KmE5fwo6-6THfOky0imQyJSKP9b0jCAM3iXNSZtK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Low price, good food. What more can I say? I love Hong Kong food. Copa Cafe has good service, the waiters are attentive, friendly, and efficient.

One time, we came here late at night and they still received us and were patient despite us staying beyond their closing time. I’ll always remember the staff’s patience and hospitality.

As you can tell, I really like their noodles 😂🍜","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNmD0avsIDuv7S0oR3k1m2RCOwZwtXixWPr-ed3&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2022-12-15"},{"Name":"Bespoke Happier","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL_JY_sOUqfgLP_sU_CBSIZzGgEmarbG08tg34uKbeN8ljU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Copa Cafe, a popular Hong Kong-style restaurant in Vancouver, is a hidden gem that I frequent when I'm in the mood for a hearty meal. Although there are only two other Hong Kong-style restaurants in Coquitlam, I prefer Copa Cafe for its extensive menu options and exceptional service compared to its competitors. If you become a member, which costs $15 per year, you can enjoy a 10% discount on all orders, which is a great deal.

One of the highlights of Copa Cafe is their breakfast menu, which boasts generous portions that won't hurt your wallet despite the current high prices. On my recent visit, I opted for the satay beef noodle and shared the cheese, spinach, and bacon omelette with my husband. We also ordered two cups of their famous Hong Kong-style milk tea. After applying the 10% membership discount, our bill was a reasonable $23 with the tip included.

Overall, we were pleased with both the quality and quantity of our breakfast. The flavors were satisfactory, and the portions were generous. Copa Cafe is a must-visit spot for anyone who loves Hong Kong-style cuisine and wants to try something new. The ambiance is cozy, and the service is top-notch, making it an ideal spot for a date or a casual gathering with friends.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNSzLi3djIKGAYOhylqv9qdoGJbTHEE6Sfx7hU&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2023-6-17"}]

[{"Name":"Jamie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJbL24nDM0QPqNMyBc2zSr2gn9JuVDfxdsbq9asqnLPrLPLWnyL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The chicken burger was absolutely delicious and fresh. Great value! I also loved the spicy fries. So tasty they didn't even need ketchup!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOupzXR9Znz2moILexerkTwqsTjirx2aPiO1shv&fid=0x0:0x16abda2984fa5eca"],"When":"2024-8-31"},{"Name":"Roozegar Mohammadi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXrQru4VExe7pdnc_LNPc1yA4v-RaJaPJWbL5u-B9MOm7dojm-4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"1- Thank you and a quick question  regarding your meat shop,  Is there any Halal certification accredited by Halal Canada?
2- Your answer: "Response from the owner
Thank you for your inquiry! We’re proud to share that our supplier is one of the best Halal meat providers in the entire country, ensuring the highest quality and adherence to Halal standards.
Regarding your question, yes, our supplier is accredited by Halal Canada, so you can shop with confidence.
By the way, if you’ve enjoyed our services, would you consider giving us a 5-star review instead of 3? Your support means a lot to us, and we’d love to hear what more we can do to earn that extra star from you!"

3- my reply to your reply:"Thank you for your reply. Unfortunately, i have to change the mark to 1 star because of the following objective evidences:
"Although you mentioned that your supplier has an accredited halal certificate, based on my observations during everyday shopping and watching your Deli and Meatshop employees, it seems that you are not adhering to halal provider rules. Specifically, you are selling halal and non-halal meat together and using the same knives and surfaces to cut them. The regulations in this regard are similar to those for allergen and non-allergen items, where cross-contamination is strictly prohibited. Rather than this, open packages of halal and non-halal meat inside the freezer or fridge should be completely separated. I recommend that you read the Halal International Standard requirements for retail stores. Until you are able to meet these standards, please remove all halal signage from your store, as it is misleading to Muslim customers in this regard"","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ali Fasihizadeh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXeEgxRiuCQGGcgBhaC0R0-E7HN9SKaiGfOrL8NTnYlp6WMk2xa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently ordered a birthday cake to Suzan at the bakery and I couldn’t be happier with the result! She made the cake even better than the picture I provided, and the taste was absolutely wonderful. Suzan’s attention to detail and skill are truly impressive. I 100% recommend her to anyone who needs a cake for any occasion. Thank you, Suzan, for making our celebration extra special!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkLGVEJkX7JSqcjBAtyVWyK982WANxb6oPss2F&fid=0x0:0x16abda2984fa5eca"],"When":"2024-12-10"},{"Name":"TNME GROUP","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJqpJf_GmiTs4CToZS-fMCCnxdoqhY1CpAyRnezSuViSn0N0w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had an amazing experience with Urban Gate in Coquitlam! I needed a mocha cake last minute, and Miss Susan came through with a beautiful creation that exceeded my expectations. The cake looked fantastic and tasted even better—rich, flavorful, and a huge hit with everyone. I was so impressed by how quickly they handled my request without sacrificing quality. A big thank you to Miss Susan and the whole team for their exceptional service. I’ll definitely be coming back for more!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mehran bakhtiari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX52_I8QBEvpbwP2DsvccLDQ1hUjTB0qEjwNL_660Q7Wjozcaqk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've been coming here for lunch several times, they have great food at a reasonable price that you can't find anywhere else in Vancouver. Special thanks to Ms. Afsane, who always provides excellent service.
Ms. Afsane is a professional barista and her coffees are wonderful ❤️👌🏻","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO1xMqJRElD_1t8Z-23lkvD_JcHAGaeFjua0Wpn&fid=0x0:0x16abda2984fa5eca"],"When":"2024-6-3"},{"Name":"meow meow","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKrJ-mhNYyKJeNAeH6NNi0zZynSPeNyTmmob3-hI4azgkbLWA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food is always delicious and price is always good! We had a server named Sareh who is very friendly and attentive. She’s also recommended and offered sampling authentic food we’ve never tried before and they taste really good and we all love it! It’sone of the best places to have really good quality food and customer service. In addition the atmosphere is very comfortable and inviting.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Fuzzley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUuQBLG7TksG6wDxiaXxGD7Hm142h_aQxwM9_mE25IYjf3jo0BguA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"As a long-term customer I was very disappointed with my recent experience at Urban Gate. I brought to the attention of the cashier that I had purchased some barbari bread a few days ago, and that I was told these were baked the night before.
Unfortunately when I took the bread home and opened it on the same day, I found both to be rotten and stale. I did not want to drive all the way back for a little refund that. The following week while shopping at the store, I informed the cashier. All I sought was a simple acknowledgment of my concern and an apology for the inconvenience. Instead, what followed was a lengthy justification about how fresh bread can spoil overnight due to moisture. Additionally, the cashier explained their return policy, stating that I should have brought back the receipt and the rotten bread for a refund.
I felt that the response lacked empathy and a proper understanding of customer service. The interaction came off as arrogant, and it left me feeling undervalued as a customer. It is disappointing to know that, as a loyal customer, my concerns were not taken seriously. I hope Urban Gate can improve its customer service training to better handle situations like this in the future.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marjan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJi5kZ8SK7DmiaOMIRuV-4Ttne1NBXp-Dh_P2EIrXoD-QM7Hw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This store has a good selection of products from my home country , especially in the meat department, where the staff are polite and helpful.
However, the customer service at checkout is very disappointing and rude, especially from the cashier ladies. They rarely greet  and often have a negative attitude. For example, one cashier today threw the receipt on the counter, slammed her hand on it, and walked away without saying anything. I even said hello and thank you, but she didn’t respond. When I asked the others if they had the same experience, they said they did.
These interactions make shopping feel unwelcoming. I hope the staff realizes that everyone deserves respect and that good service is important.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Al","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJke_H51lEVtqmQ6Mwhj0R5MqDW7L2xLlIdf0sg4kPFJFF0D9I=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place has a very cold atmosphere but the beef donair was extremely delicious. All ingredients are fresh and very tasty and a bit salty. I enjoyed the taste and definitely would come back for more.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMGGCFF7bdLpzCmj5b6ck--_SmcweTfktCID0uA&fid=0x0:0x646f91ffd4ce0a21"],"When":"2023-9-1"},{"Name":"S D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKJYsqsfylRWb2qB-xJh6bN2jntU-d5BqDo5FMP29y23P0aTA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Donair is okay. Nothing special or out of the ordinary.
Service is okay. The store didn’t look that clean or organized maybe because Indoor dinning is closed and they don’t really do anything inside the area.

I didn’t like the big plastic that was hanging there. Made the place look weird. You can spend a few $$ and get some proper plexiglass. At least you can be safe and the shop won’t look weird.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOwXeWMUSJr6CNiwtmxRWw7f9fmQoPeQ8_BfWbS&fid=0x0:0x646f91ffd4ce0a21"],"When":"2021-4-22"},{"Name":"Shawn B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX7PwLclAbvOTqw2KlQRZ8Yvg7bqh0V4BncKvo3mzD_hm79ivtcQw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Went in to give them another chance cause my experience last time wasn't good. So today they topped it off with an even worse experience. All I did was ask for extra sauce and I'm ready to pay a little extra and she said she can't wrap it and wrapped up my donair without what I asked for. I'll never go back r en the chicken was over cooked mostly.  Better off sultains or tasty honkin donair he's the best gives you whatever you ask for.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jeff Knox","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJDtmd0ktZrdW7ZQ4e6__TmxtiCl53elRkAnNwdw0Kcq6Hx4A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I had the lamb donair and really wasn't a fan. The lamb seasoning was plain, the sauces were bland, the wrap wasn't grilled, and it really could have used more ingredients like pickles.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Gabriel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJU3T5Y0cLHi8J7Os8DiJWRpl1KgnaCw51Vel2SGXrWko70nDE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Ordered a Lebanese Lamb Wrap. It was huge and satisfying. Great taste!

The prices in the photo was old and it has new prices.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNGyVN7sRJtECOJVQcMKCWPvlpcVgJcQP009zSM&fid=0x0:0x646f91ffd4ce0a21"],"When":"2023-12-4"},{"Name":"Din Petrovic","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWrT7VozPd3MVXDzPT2-vY1cOMCRfiKa19M-EZePZQ21aZAPbc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This place used to be much better. I am customer for a few years and getting disappointed with quality. On top of my salad should be feta cheese now you can see only traces of it.
They charge the package to a smaller one (you can see the difference between my picture and other reviews)
but price is still the same.
In salad you get so much more cucumbers and just a few pieces of tomato and peppers.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNqut2rOEmE_EsnN4MAO0k0GIn5oJm4R_wc8ueZ&fid=0x0:0x646f91ffd4ce0a21"],"When":"2020-8-1"},{"Name":"Jayanth Athreya","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUPDghP7-tYKGrUkeWwfSGFAHkcHEY7Ne2gHa-E7_hfAkf-qCM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Absolutely the worst customer service. The lady with short hair is so angry all the time and definitely doesn’t like to work there. Terrible place and the oil used for frying is Black!! Stay away.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cheryl A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocId3JTMrjtqtdmj_0XOBMchbLGhcrTAO0uBPM1jzlHcNAjL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Really good  chicken donair and great lady who served me - 🙂 I’m happily eating while working from home","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPdHUsBqMhSNurjXGXH8TV0g_5z41vGoPB9BuE&fid=0x0:0x646f91ffd4ce0a21"],"When":"2024-1-9"}]

[{"Name":"Andy Chung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWooGSzw1FKhky_mrftz_qLp6fsBzAqJ7JcjT2pde1tUMh4Y9hx8Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Shrinkflation and inflation.

Dishes taste fine but the prices are going up and the portion seems shrinking as well.
I ordered to pick up some dishes. $6.25 for 6 pieces of small spicy salmon roles.
Maybe I’m out of touch these days. $32.25 for takeouts does not go very far these days I guess.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPHN74PVQXn88pZBDO_WRQkASFUILQKLltLDqPH&fid=0x0:0xd5be1ea94eed26b2"],"When":"2024-10-14"},{"Name":"Mohammad Tabesh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUjokXICqa-0DdrHKHh0Wt3GGaHTAC4RDuOqk22M3flRzjmqoKo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good quality food for the price with a nice variety, really quick service and convenient location inside the mall. It's a budget place with disposable plates and chopsticks. Miso soup was plain but tasty.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPL_iRBW2adsUvuZctF90SuqpluYd65jND4m7dv&fid=0x0:0xd5be1ea94eed26b2"],"When":"2024-9-14"},{"Name":"Jessameen Dela Peña","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9mRpmL8-ZJUG7UPFcnsjzRdxjABif-MswbO1rxgJyyWfns8Jd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"My partner works in the mall and grabs lunch here three times a week, especially loving the teriyaki. I had the chance to try the unagi oshi sushi, and it was delicious! The creamy prawn tempura was a fantastic bonus, making the meal even more delightful.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP6on5Y08KZ9VAGnb-Q10oavACH62ly3bxzrkNn&fid=0x0:0xd5be1ea94eed26b2"],"When":"2024-8-24"},{"Name":"Armin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUVKfPvn-jqW8hTOlU1VeElw6vFvjre9PTWSba_96soEJn4hAFVjA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good Sushi for being in the mall! Lots of options to pick and you can order online so you don't have to wait!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN5ux3twBDePDGec0k-4hwPkab1Rd92kFjUs18y&fid=0x0:0xd5be1ea94eed26b2"],"When":"2024-9-19"},{"Name":"I D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJePVcTLvMpAzx-nv1Jiy6G3BSAT8AXC96M8bp3iDt95AnsQw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I wish Coquitlam Centre has better eateries. I ordered the Beef Bento. Price was okay, but the portions were not big. For $15, I only got 4 pieces of California roll instead the standard 6 pieces. I was surprised by the quantity of the beef. It was more than I expected but the beef quality was quite poor. There was also not a lot of rice. Salad was fresh. Service was quick and friendly. It's a small place, and I couldn't find a place to sit, so I had the food to go. I forgot to ask for napkins :(","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alexis Brown","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL4lll3FSw4DuoAXTTSQfNVd2BMOvLsNf0gg2O5LBY3etPVgQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love the prawn tempura and miso soup. For mall sushi, this place is consistently great! I enjoy eating here and will always return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNEOr8Ou4QsT2tC4bIAmYmBwtpMCrNDvv-oKLq1&fid=0x0:0xd5be1ea94eed26b2"],"When":"2024-1-14"},{"Name":"K S H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVUpfuZFJ8RwqNTmsEi_Ve_L99RruCBycZdik5Nf-7YZZhK-hRF=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the Best Sushi places in Coquitlam and very conveniently located in the mall.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPtjlH9F0FcLxhh45QyYB26pLJ8aF_QRpWZxyIU&fid=0x0:0xd5be1ea94eed26b2"],"When":"2024-11-28"},{"Name":"Johnny","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvkqlZ5wz-o7qQiMAPvxq4Uq26umX4_opBke6CDrVfkbGhCeuLaA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"My first time at Togo Sushi was excellent. With exceptional service by the lady employee, I ordered the teriyaki bento box, and I opted for chicken rather than beef. The teriyaki bento box comes with California rolls, salad, gyoza, and miso soup. The teriyaki chicken was, to be honest, disappointing, which I was not expecting. I also ordered yam rolls, which I loved since I love sweet potatoes. Would I go back? Likely not.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Philip Raymond Lim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV5EIBAgpBLsauhPMdjXym7mJ4fA8mtryDtWQIJCZfJxYXxupU8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Hansol seems to be a newer spot in town, offering great value with large portions. The taste, however, can be hit or miss. The beef bibimbap was enjoyable and well-prepared. Katsu is standard. Tempura is good. The bone soup lacked depth of flavor and was overpowered by spiciness. They do offer complimentary pumpkin soup, which was decent but not particularly memorable. Rice is very good. Overall, it’s worth a try for the portion sizes and value, though there’s room for improvement in flavor balance.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP7m7hbyxnfZJxK2Fvd6uuXD0kLrSVu3uRkycl-&fid=0x0:0xf2e1e4462ce2d6e9"],"When":"2024-12-6"},{"Name":"Scott Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHpW7vGME__Zs4wKjXR04Upnw88bkVVyz-H2288JsHocq9vI3r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It was a pretty great Korean restaurant and we were thoroughly impressed by their food and service. They gave us some sweet pumpkin soup as a free appetizer which is always great! The texture was spot on and the flavour was subtle and delicate while being slightly sweet.

The side dishes were also quite tasty with not much to knit pick. The fried shrimps were decent but I could tell that it wasn’t their specialty.

But rest of the dishes were fantastic. My personal favourite was the Korean beef tartare. The beef soup was also very rich and flavourful. Finally, the intestine soup is not for the faint of heart, but it was savoury and spicy, just the way we like it.

Overall, we would definitely come back and try other menu items when we get the chance and we encourage you to try this place out!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPtMBNYjwqeLDnv1NwTnGPEUrJkm6t-6R5v1Wje&fid=0x0:0xf2e1e4462ce2d6e9"],"When":"2024-9-6"},{"Name":"K H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVo2hR2qKHBGSuFyVVc1kqvuNnr23GVLd19IdZCsiU8tz8tbtW-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very impressed with the food here. It tastes like homemade quality and authentic Korean food. We loved the chicken wings and beef bulgogi. Banchan was great too. They are quite small inside and don’t take reservations. It was a longer wait for a 6 table on a Friday night so I would recommend going in smaller groups. But the food is really worth it. The service is by two older Korean man and woman and they work very efficiently and very hard.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMc3HGCCmg40DS3WNjXj6X3-AfC2ZapBmq8JPIm&fid=0x0:0xf2e1e4462ce2d6e9"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Snoopy Kitchen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU3h-I-trbYva-Tzrs-UNhkQe4Nn1jgsblAcoQ0hPrnUWvugM3Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very nice small family restaurant.  I love the beef tartare and portion is very generous.  Spicy tofu soup is great too.

Complementary pumpkin soup is a warmhearted gesture.

Not recommend big party more than 4 people and good to have comfort food in the neighborhood.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNXHyraGjUlZA4zKuHJ5tY_Oagy3_CzwYGg52jH&fid=0x0:0xf2e1e4462ce2d6e9"],"When":"2024-10-16"},{"Name":"Jenn A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVDNY1epuqFb0vEhEwK9bhTQ1dFwhkq_RQVEWkys2fxRxs7SO6V=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Loved this place. Starter soup was delicious and the dishes we had were comforting. Donkatsu was so crispy and sweet potato noodle dish. Wings were a hit. Kimchi pancake had a crunchy crust.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3XJihg4gTXBUng6g9bCnJ9RIXo1l89npXooy3&fid=0x0:0xf2e1e4462ce2d6e9"],"When":"2024-12-20"},{"Name":"Arpitha Rao Annaji","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXrqsdkrs5T063w39fOONriV-UZmIT3JlCpCdqaNPFpHi43Hf6Hew=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a great little Korean restaurant! We ordered everything without meat (vegetarian)  bibimbap hot, tofu and mushroom soup, steam eggs and the best pumpkin soup on the house !! Loved everything so much!

This came with a side of rice and banchan ! (We’re obviously K-Drama and K-Food fans!)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOPpcTDTEJv0T18wz-euaJTIlf74Bg8XyYJJ86b&fid=0x0:0xf2e1e4462ce2d6e9"],"When":"2024-10-8"},{"Name":"justinmctavish","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIEYVdRqmE_3oMTj7PunlTi-aFJRLulUFCNb37Cg7axAP4W=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really like this place. I have been to many Korean restaurants in the area and this is by far the best. Small homey restaurant and super friendly staff. Feels like you are walking into someone’s home for an amazing home cooked meal. Every dish we have ordered has been outstanding!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPQTcpEQfGkAEpAn03EUg0UV4wCAvlwChugK54&fid=0x0:0xf2e1e4462ce2d6e9"],"When":"2024-12-5"},{"Name":"Joe Caldow","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUPY1xctTIatziKXhwQ1piit73bdq1GENeVWggh9AnOsK3UZYpU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food was amazing and service was incredible! Our family of 4 really enjoyed eating here.

I think it is a husband and wife couple that owns and runs it and they are the kindest people. When you get up to leave the hold the door open for their customers. He even held the door open for the Skip the Dishes driver that was there to pick up an order.

Very impressed and we will definitely be back!

Thank you for the great experience!","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Ray Jang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3wj8Ne3ngI4eg9ouEU6zPmvERlQuudbckz4ma4Vg6pfYrsWM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tasty hand pulled traditional noodles typical of Northern China. Tasty sauces and toppings. Generous portion sizes considering the price…the Salt & Pepper chicken was especially large and crisp, and crunchy coating. Service was quick and friendly. Dining area was clean. Count me in for regular repeat visits to satisfy my constant cravings for hand pulled noodles!  Excellent noodle joint that also has offerings in Crystal Mall (Burnaby) and Continental Ctr (Richmond). Love it!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPsLjXKVj5DEZQheCIs65Egsww6E99zXtbIkQlE&fid=0x0:0x25dfa5714ccafc5d"],"When":"2024-11-14"},{"Name":"Jessy J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLHNRFw0Z_JgaU0TxGr1Pv5X-w9V6JzR0bnCuTDlGr_7pfsbx_k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Definitely must try and should you your stable food!

This place offers truly authentic Xi’an Chinese food. You can tell they didn’t cut any corners, from the marinating to the frying and stir-frying of the cumin lamb—it’s full of flavor and cooked to perfection. The hand-pulled noodles are a must-try, with a perfect texture that you won’t find just anywhere. The shredded potatoes are so light, you’d hardly think you’re eating potatoes, as the starch is minimal and the dish feels incredibly delicate.

The service is top-notch! From the warm greeting to expert menu recommendations, attentive tea refills, and thoughtful check-ins, the entire experience was seamless and heartwarming.

Parking can be tricky sometimes, but we had no problem finding a spot on a Saturday night!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNbgFglJr8AcF_s25w0qWaQeaRodunCkpj8UhI7&fid=0x0:0x25dfa5714ccafc5d"],"When":"2024-10-20"},{"Name":"Lee Hwan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL6j8edfdMuAexJg284rJGK3C7SE7k9Zn0kKJfkMwoZJYiFzw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Old Xian delivers an exceptional dining experience with authentic flavors and a warm, welcoming atmosphere. Everything here elevates the meal. Each dish is generously portioned, flavorful, and presented with care, showcasing the chef's dedication to authentic cuisine. The bold, unique flavors make it a standout destination for food lovers, and the reasonable prices only add to its appeal. I highly recommend Old Xian for anyone looking to explore rich, traditional flavors in a comfortable setting.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN_MAhMSr49wODWo1woIpfdP-MBvlqvyMm-SB-n&fid=0x0:0x25dfa5714ccafc5d"],"When":"2024-11-10"},{"Name":"翟媛媛","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL-kPaPCVBzNlAPdOSvP5Xl1gs9d1CJxju74RB4y__Cd8213g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The cold dishes here were fantastic! The flavors were rich and truly authentic, bringing out the best of traditional Chinese cuisine. Every bite reminded me of home, and the seasoning was perfect. If you’re looking for real Chinese taste, the cold dishes are a must-try!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOOG6rFxYhZNzQH7HAl84OBrRs7WjGD8cN-c7RC&fid=0x0:0x25dfa5714ccafc5d"],"When":"2024-9-16"},{"Name":"eric h","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU4wiwKOOLAGG9P3k9zH8vSMybKZzZ7dkhejrfS-DBteL1ZiOwd=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I’m not sure what went wrong, but the XI’an Hand-Pulled Noodles with Hot Spicy Oil was incredibly salty. I tried rinsing my mouth in the washroom, but the saltiness seemed to cling to my tongue. I’ve never experienced anything like it. However, the waitress was very kind and took the dish off my bill, which I appreciated. Honestly, I’m only giving this place two stars because the service was good.

The first photo is the XI’an Hand-Pulled Noodles with Hot Spicy Oil.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNQoSf1RyhCSOs9Hz7S1NEhYJ1EPAaA1JGQmMyZ&fid=0x0:0x25dfa5714ccafc5d"],"When":"2024-8-31"},{"Name":"Tien Lam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUXHCfEOuZX4sAnNQXCtC1HC1c_BtUEmjz0i2XKxPb_xq_Chxo=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good place for Chinese food. Just what I needed to regain my strength. But I got told "don't forget to eat the noodles!" - took two more soups for takeaway. Thank you!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Joshua (ThickBurger_Bites)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbIhhMlbxk7OIMpcaP-aSx2m75kt8-mqmXoXAJQ5K99gnxiff1zg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went there on impulse for a late dinner after reading the reviews.

Food:
Ordered the House Special Pho, large. Was pleasantly surprised to see a bowl that wasn't as big as Pho 99's large. Pho was good, soup was just right, neither too salty or too rich. Noodles came in a good amount. Meats in the House Special Pho left a lot to be desired though. Not as much as I'd expect, half a beef ball, about 2 slices of beef steak, 3 slices of beef flank, tiny bits of beef tendon (which was really soft and delicious to my surprise), and a few bits of tripe here and there. Kinda disappointed with the amount of meat but as it was still pretty delicious,  I'll overlook it.
It comes with tea, beansprouts, basil leaves and lime on the side.
Refer to pictures for more information!

Price:
$10.24++/person

Service:
Nothing special. The lady sounded angry but I guess it's just the way she speaks.

Would I recommend?
Yes, go with family/small groups of friends as the place is rather small. I have not tried the other dishes, but will do so in the future :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQm5L8nR0xCYWH_i_xK2j7rwq5AZRQ2MMi8XQj&fid=0x0:0x136fcd8e7d93f071"],"When":"2017-1-8"},{"Name":"Stan S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJDG5_awNL6dSqZYIF4Ack_45eiH9so1tVgUCK8vlfNcXo0LDN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Not my First time here, busy place seems to be lots on the go even though there's only a few of us sitting down there's plenty of takeout or to go orders and the people are quite friendly and the price is reasonable. With the back door open it is quite cool in here however you do warm up when you're eating your food. I highly recommend this place the food is good the people are friendly service is excellent.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNVX0tlIkif75DPDxyhNi5Wvo2ID-r_1D3o98A6&fid=0x0:0x136fcd8e7d93f071"],"When":"2021-2-13"}]

I really recommend it here!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM93a5T1lvEweZ3KriylvvQg7EM44SFe7IDnpG7&fid=0x0:0xa91f34955da6779"],"When":"2024-8-10"},{"Name":"Haerin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLzvl1TEgLbmLgUGPLTOm6uWgtLU7DgTOaXCc47iibFb2LKWKE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best korean corndog in Vancouver and the redbean walnut pastry was also quite decent but few things you can take into consideration:

- When Customers are taking orders, ask how heavy or light they want the sauces to be on their corndogs. Mine was too saucy and it was overpowering.

- Put sauces on the side by default for takeout orders. My corndog got extremely soggy from all the sauces when I got home.

- The chopstick used for corndogs is too fragile. I ordered potato one and as I was holding it, I felt like the weight of it could easily break the stick.

- I was expecting the red bean walnut pastry to have nice crunch on the outside which was lacking. I hope the texture could improve a bit more since the flavour was totally on point.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPX1VUXigTe1WrB2Uigghzbp44W7mqtTLKOua4Z&fid=0x0:0xa91f34955da6779"],"When":"2024-7-15"},{"Name":"Sue Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXZ2EvZcUR-dfMDNY2VYPR1Z7MkBxqVhywlTTvbNTJFa5OcfSQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is really awesome place for simple but yummy treats located by food court in Henderson mall, Coquitlam.

We will come back again definitely more often for their  delicious foods and services.

[{"Name":"Ping D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV-_KBk5-yIGzGmKAkX1L-6QPRrz_RZKkgRnIY4il5exhoL_sw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Pork burger and cold noodles are pretty good. I think lamb burger has lots of room for improvement. Meat was too hard to chew. In general, it’s nice to have this choice of Chinese street food here in Coquitlam. Keep working on the quality please!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPAPGaY3irSFKuVpKjsYOUBsSZrssFCW0ZgVVDZ&fid=0x0:0x83bf5e63a4ea423e"],"When":"2024-4-13"},{"Name":"Cynthia Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXzeJkq7FGsDfGgQXJWjS-SJOYYhnjPNUtm2wbKTNa_uJ8TyBMm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The burgers (more meat buns in my mind) were delicious and extremely juicy. The price is extremely affordable especially given how  substantial it is. 2 would be too much unless you're starving.

The lamb soup was surprisingly big. I thought it was just the broth, but it's a meal with tofu, lamb meat (a little dry but still good), and a few pieces of noodle to go with the bun.

I'll definitely come back in the future.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Gooseberry Bilberry","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKMJD-L9WmQytMhbODZNa3Nz3Kk8Z3fxnupE5Xvb8JG11rhZQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We ordered the Traditional Pork Belly Burger and the Braised Beef.  The cashier asked us if we wanted onions and chilli and we said no.  It turned out that the pork had no sauce at all and the taste was minimal.  It did not resemble the picture as shown online.  The Braised Beef was a lie (they gave us slices of beef shank instead of chunks of beef).  It was not braised; it was cold. You can check the photos on Uber Eats and Fantuan for the correct version. We were shocked by their misconduct.

Traditional dishes should not be altered and the cashier should not have asked us for modifications. This is a nice no frills place to grab a quick bite if you are in the area. Bonus - the terrace parking is free and it has pretty scenic views of the mountains.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNhKcxCIz-Anvq5ip1ddI-7F5qC7kMykaHZpGAm&fid=0x0:0x83bf5e63a4ea423e"],"When":"2023-1-30"},{"Name":"David Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJQn39r3brDL0VPq82Yr56T560Nm6tJ3AgkaLNo-GnVazotTw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time trying this place and the service attitude is definitely 5 stars.
