[{"Name":"Sarah Okut","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLTH-O9yHrUXXSzwuweULzXw1pBbME2AVL3wPUzYMdoLT_dRg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited Pizza Pietra and really enjoyed their pizza and San Sebastian cheesecake. The pizza had a crispy crust with fresh, tasty toppings. It was delicious! The San Sebastian cheesecake was the best part—it was rich, smooth, and creamy, with a slightly caramelized top that gave it extra flavor. If you love desserts, you should definitely try this cheesecake!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN3wU0_wer5w028bhetbEqdDgTlTPAd9mr8aiH5&fid=0x0:0x4640aee62581d2d2"],"When":"2024-10-16"},{"Name":"Mucahit Mert Alagoz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUlZFzlr8OmJ6ReNSeqILjiXkPYOR-Wi6HlJhjaTTE_xGsRl7kohA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I really loved this small and cozy Turkish café run by two Turkish women. The staff is very warm and friendly. Although the menu is a bit limited, the breakfast options are quite delicious. I loved everything, from the sucuk (Turkish sausage) to the eggs and meat-filled pastries. For four people (we ordered a bit too much), the total was $105.
I definitely recommend it—a lovely café!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOZkVllSrfsqQVnk7-eaCEQy80caDFl6QFecd6N&fid=0x0:0x4640aee62581d2d2"],"When":"2024-11-16"},{"Name":"방새단Jp","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPRFl5X_2oRYVKyp5YOzyZvBiFq4LXRAXvUH4K1gSFuhrTkvIu=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I ordered the poached eggs with avocado.
They took a while to get the plate ready, but it was much better than what I had hoped for. Ingredients were fresh, tasty and I would definitely come back again","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPW5MCUo0Kn75oa42Blt_gR0Ah7EI2gXYUVdZhL&fid=0x0:0x4640aee62581d2d2"],"When":"2024-11-6"},{"Name":"Mahesh Vanga","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_R99DIUm3YNCVBnH6ipuMklk--v4TSFTsQ7Tybr4ECj_qR-ZP9A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is by far the best pizza place I have ever been to in the Mainland area. We explored this place as part of checking regular pizza places around, to our surprise this has been the best random pizza place ever been in fact the best pizza I ever had in the mainland area. Any food/pizza lover cannot miss this place, they got a wide variety of pizzas to offer as well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO263l3lNZQ04gOHPrnihMubx8QyholXqUTO6DE&fid=0x0:0x4640aee62581d2d2"],"When":"2024-9-28"},{"Name":"Graham Sutton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL8UeAA1nmB6Ej3WgCR3VioNDAdhDivzoWDT4UCyjNTsgC4MA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Breakfast was awesome!  Traditional Turkish meals with lovely fresh bread and Turkish tea.  We'll definitely be back on a regular basis.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipODmWArQZDzyV5LCBa5m3uJi_01rXQ5LyF0EMno&fid=0x0:0x4640aee62581d2d2"],"When":"2024-11-20"},{"Name":"Onur Kaan KOÇ","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLl3-LHlkDHqQOafBmwY6xCPBlOCHVa2JkVR6DeNJcaxq3QYw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Clean, Happy and delicious Pizza Pietra, siezed my day 😋

At first I was hesitant because of the mixed reviews but I really wanted to give it a try, especially because of the praised stone oven and authentic dough.

I've been to most regions of Italy, ate a lot of very good pizza and I must say this pizza restaurant reminded me the times I was in Mediterranean.

You must use good quality ingredients and have precise dough craftsmanship, and have the right oven with the correct temperature to make a delicious pizza. But every body knows, in our modern times, this equation is quite impossible in big cities because of the cost and profit concerns.

But in this pizza shop they nearly got the perfect combination.

They have a real stove oven at the right temperature, good quality ingredients and handmade authentic dough.

Both pizza and Foccacia are nicely crusty and juicy. The Tomato sauce is not bitter nor too sweet, just yummy and fresh  ;-).

Toppings and mozzarella have a very good price to quality ratio.

All the ingredients are really really fresh 👍

A suggestion for them, I think you should make a pizza with different ingredients which are hard to find in PoCo

And for me the most important thing , people in this pizza shop are really happy, hospitable, positive and energetic. They really smile to you because they just want to. The total vibe is just like the warm and welcoming family owned pizza shops in Italy too 😍😍.

Ps: I asked the owner to tour the kitchen because of my cleanliness obsession. And yes he let me to quickly tour the kitchen and I'm amazed, this is a really really clean kitchen for BC standarts 😉","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipODw8DnBQZ_EDJZzRNN9UlLF96GZOid--UDy1PJ&fid=0x0:0x4640aee62581d2d2"],"When":"2024-3-28"},{"Name":"Aamir Sheergar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUTKU4wfuc0kwoyEwJxy3N-nmGgBy-VjbHs41hImisM4pU2gpbxyQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great pizza, loved the thin crust. Friendly service from the ladies in the kitchen. One of my new favorite pizza places.

Also tried the cheesecake, it was not too dense and had just the right amount of sweetness, a great balance.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"M. Murat Kucuk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQxmakxls5MdK3S6o9QjUak841XsiEQ7PpJlT7cOAjNN9ECiE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Prepare to be amazed by this extraordinary pizza haven nestled within town. Without hesitation, I wholeheartedly recommend this remarkable establishment to all pizza enthusiasts. During our recent visit, we indulged in their custom 2-in-1 pizza, an exquisite combination that left our taste buds in a state of pure bliss.

The staff at Pizza Pietra were not only kind, but also exceptionally helpful, ensuring that our dining experience was nothing short of perfection. Their attentiveness added an extra touch of delight to an already exceptional culinary adventure.

Do not, under any circumstances, allow yourself to miss out on the opportunity to visit this exceptional pizza establishment. It is an experience that promises to tantalize your senses and leave an indelible impression.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPoC8qGLwQyu83S1THS9PbLQVeSXqTbUxjDY8X&fid=0x0:0x4640aee62581d2d2"],"When":"2023-6-25"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"alex son","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKHu7LRFyxDEmIiDicGOX9Xw2wJytUGtyrAHnY87q_4pR8Nvw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of Doni’s standout features is its dedication to quality ingredients. Each dish is freshly prepared, and it shows. The portions are generous, and the presentation is impressive, especially for a food court setting. It’s clear that thought and care go into every meal, making it feel like you’re dining at a standalone restaurant rather than a quick stop in the mall.

Doni has successfully elevated the mall food court dining experience. With its diverse menu, commitment to quality, and friendly service, it’s a standout option that’s well worth a visit. Whether you’re a regular mall-goer or just passing through, Doni offers a delicious escape from the usual fast food fare. Highly recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMs9cNGsHAmSchoBQxjUsrv8agGYTMoI2S--hcg&fid=0x0:0x5cd9b26c7b81a50a"],"When":"2024-9-24"},{"Name":"Daniel Jung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFE7g6vnjf23CW6mDeh4anchF8fxBs6O5Nsx0bvhepuO3MVzWa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Update: Half & Half Dumplings are spot on, and the Seafood fried rice was delicious with a generous portion! Restaurant quality

Past: The place is pretty solid. I tried it a few days ago for the first time.
Counter service was good, clean space and of course the food tasted great!
Surprised the Seafood Jajangmeon was a little spicy! (Was a good kick just unexpected)
The fried dumplings were awesome!
Great addition to Henderson","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM-zI0R3T-jkGs0KmDo9pLx5dNk7T-q5Ld3D4_I&fid=0x0:0x5cd9b26c7b81a50a"],"When":"2024-2-10"},{"Name":"Snoopy Kitchen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU3h-I-trbYva-Tzrs-UNhkQe4Nn1jgsblAcoQ0hPrnUWvugM3Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good food with value.  Can’t expect more.  Spicy noodle is very hot. Can ask for mild if can’t handle but taste good with spicy especially in cold weather","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNILjIKJkBv16vwWr_GhP6CrP8ogBR_A7AP0_ey&fid=0x0:0x5cd9b26c7b81a50a"],"When":"2024-10-23"},{"Name":"Jason Park","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMhOEKKHXAe86LaxehFj_x7OVFNVhnJ9HjVRBWt_-JiYzZSRxP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I discovered Doni through a Korean community, learning that it had recently relocated from Surrey to Henderson Mall in Coquitlam Centre. Intrigued by the positive reviews, I decided to visit during a weekday at off-peak hours, shortly after 3 PM.

I ordered the spicy pork cutlet, and it did not disappoint. The batter and pork thickness were excellent, and the dish was well-executed. Although the sauce was flavorful and creamy, it wasn't the typical accompaniment for Korean pork cutlets and was spicier than I expected. I didn't quite like the sauce tbh.

However, I loved the texture and the flavour of the rice, and the sliced cabbage was fresh. Next time, I would opt for the non-spicy version, though I couldn't find it on the menu this time.

Located on the 2nd floor of Henderson Mall's food court, the area was clean and well-maintained. Like many Korean restaurants, Doni uses a small remote that rings and buzzes when your order is ready. The employee was kind, and the ordering process was smooth.

Some have complained about long wait times for their orders. Despite there being few customers, my order took about 10-15 minutes, which suggests they fry the cutlet fresh upon ordering. Otherwise, the wait time wouldn't make sense.

Considering the inflated food prices elsewhere, Doni is very affordable. I'm definitely returning to try their Korean-Chinese menu items and dumplings. Keep up the good work!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNFkwX60yoagt8J6S7gtGwralkkMEjZF_TbKQwP&fid=0x0:0x5cd9b26c7b81a50a"],"When":"2024-6-16"},{"Name":"TS OS","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIrxJ8Fjd3bGSI8mWbF186RbFWyg_DW73VTS3OIkFaxPfXFBEQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Price point and taste wise, this is a very good Korean restaurant.  Interior design leaves little to desire but quality of food should make up for it.  We loved the taste of the fried dumplings especially.  Also the noodle soup was excellent.  Soup was rich while the soaked dumplings were awesome.  Stone pot mixed rice tasted great too.  It could be little spicy for some people but sauce was too good.  Squid can be little chewy but they were generous with portion size of squid.  Parking’s plenty in the plaza though it can be busy at times.  Overall, we will definitely return for more.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMFa8mzPd2sVHz-3vms-QQixtWW5Gio1n2t9Yh3&fid=0x0:0x5cd9b26c7b81a50a"],"When":"2023-7-14"},{"Name":"Danny Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8eoyUE6az-FmQo7i2mVq5z64Ow48sgKu1EmLZc0zWWN6DMy5asw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I usually don’t post my pic but I have to because it’s first post :)

After the sudden shutdown of DONI King George left everyone in a tizzy, I am so happy to say that THEY ARE BACK!!

Same great flavour and similar menu as their old location. Same amazing service albeit it’s now in Henderson Mall Foodcourt and served in foodcourt containers. But it’s no less delicious. It tastes the same, people!

They’re running a promotion for their grand opening so come one, come all.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMiKOJv-I9kfzc8hCyxCwU-I90s0w8lkAGjgpQ9&fid=0x0:0x5cd9b26c7b81a50a"],"When":"2024-1-7"},{"Name":"Kane Tan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUEgxeO4rzWbqbMjwUBC8AaFegiYqCe3sPvwn2pXruIC8Du9piLVw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A lovely little corner of the world. It's been a while since I've visited Surrey, and at a friend's recommendation, I came to this little gem of a dumpling and noodle shop.

This is one of those unfussy spots where the owners take great care to provide. Prices are very reasonable, the decor homely and well used, and the food -- it embraces you from the inside.

It's nothing over the top, but the dumplings, noodles and soup (Combo A provides you with a front and centre taste of what this place provides) are hand made, of carefully considered ingredients, and delicious. Grandma made this for you, and happily. Eat up!

Crispy deep fried dumplings with a lacy crust are filled with pork, vegetables and tofu. Light, guilt free, these were my first and last bite of the meal. The soup was light and some of the best I've had, and the soup dumplings were plump and well filled.

Noodles were a little softer than I would have liked, though -- but this dish might call for softer noodles, so I'm not a good judge! They are made of a similar body and texture as the dumpling wrappers, which totally makes sense, but seasoned with spinach.

Seriously considering bringing back some frozen dumps home, but I'll revisit that idea after a walk.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNdh8e7Sdn5N1FK7Hk3SHQTRQ2Ump4r383CRvNV&fid=0x0:0x5cd9b26c7b81a50a"],"When":"2021-3-21"},{"Name":"Michael Xie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUuofARxYvhwxxfylcnz8mBM0K5uLGN7Ke55RRoKhlEZOs358vlwA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The king is dead. Long live the king!

There used to be a Korean restaurant where DONi is now, and that place used to have great Korean food at a great price, and my go to place at this food court. I was sad to see it gone and replaced with DONi, but I still ordered from them anyway. The shrimp fried rice quality was excellent and I think the pricing is not too bad as well!

Will definitely be taking advantage of their grand opening sale and try a few more items! I think this place is my new go to place at the food Court!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM1f7eqHzIreSNqR6TuidZ2UGoJDLTE06qvYI6Z&fid=0x0:0x5cd9b26c7b81a50a"],"When":"2024-1-28"}]

title: Wah Wing Szechuan Restaurant

[{"Name":"Deb PS","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX2JrjvxBJWPrjHCwBxV9NiRybb9V5GJpynDBuSW5sd6snYZiMa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This restaurant is a very unassuming place. I would have never guessed it looked like this inside based on the exterior. It was very clean and the staff was super friendly with a great sense of humour.  The food was also very flavourful.  We all enjoyed our meal very much for not being a high end restaurant. Prices were very reasonable as well. Will be back for sure.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOCVOc1V1GanW0vAfXOMHxUlD7OXgwln2QuHrH_&fid=0x0:0x7c85358e6c767e95"],"When":"2024-10-24"},{"Name":"Ton V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWb4h6oZDMjakZ7o0kpJmjp_i41AvhfJ62KCrl6wCnDvytBpv4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hadn’t been for a while. Food was really good and service super friendly. Good size portions. I would prefer a menu with pictures though.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPxcvuP86fZtjp3Yr1fSFBnF1sXV3XGZII_RYI&fid=0x0:0x7c85358e6c767e95"],"When":"2024-10-10"},{"Name":"Ricardo Amanda Paliotti","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV1-tWR3oImGXb1bh0eJaBkqqB4lKa--eRLaWv99DtP2gOoadI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellently executed every time we visit. Flavors are on point. Always fun times there ! ☆☆☆☆☆ / Dec. 15th Sun 2024","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOFnUCp9_Bgr50_ywSBFmDWPht7MdMv6uwMz8wv&fid=0x0:0x7c85358e6c767e95"],"When":"2024-10-27"},{"Name":"Kate Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjE4MSAa0c4Uqc8iOt1LfqIkJDL1ULa2Z17gRh4YDWMExQ1A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This place has been here since I was a kid. Glad to see it's still here and I'm visiting again after 20+ years. All I remember was that I liked their hot and sour soup.

Not really an authentic Szechuan restaurant. 30 years ago, most chinese cuisines were cooked by hong kongers or south chinese people. So, most of these dishes are going to be a southern take on it.

Hot and sour soup - price is awesome. $11 enough for at least 6 bowls. Souo base is missing a bit of flavor but it is jam packed with ingredients.

Drunken chicken - it was ok. Little on the salty side.

Shanghainese pan fried pork buns - these were probably the worst I've had. Not made in house and not properly pan fried. No juice, super dry, no fried bottom crust.

Bean curd wrapped pork dim sum - surprisingly this came out last. At least 20 min has passed. This is a steamed dish but it came out with dried edges like it was sitting on a dry heater. Taste was ok.

Mapo tofu - asked for extra spicy and extra numbing. Numbing was there but nowhere near real szechuan numbing. Was not spicy at all. Sauce was more oily than saucey.

The price point reflects the quality. Things are either mediocre or a complete miss. Would come again to try only the better stuff. Staff was friendly. Came to try to refill the tea way more times than normal. The iron goddess tea tastes much better than a lot of dim sum places elsewhere.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOsyXtmZVjFTpSM7j5XHpsMqasJjiN51hrkn9sk&fid=0x0:0x7c85358e6c767e95"],"When":"2024-5-14"},{"Name":"Sarah Grace","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0P_FT3n0HZdmLMDEJ6UcRFNPyHbE7QJ8GW3gOL-SGGTFh-sFdQw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very good Chinese food, some of the best we’ve tried! Brought my family of 18 there and everyone had a very positive review to leave. The restaurant is clean, nicely decorated and the service is phenomenal, on top of amazing Chinese food. 100% recommend. Accommodated us no problem and efficiently being a large group.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP4Zm-hsHEcTAf_11Ju8D7ypxHDl4umZ6xffmp0&fid=0x0:0x7c85358e6c767e95"],"When":"2024-5-26"},{"Name":"Marie Amin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIKR0qp3fose5GsYts0dtMeJqwXo1MWNFSPwo4SjCtJGEbgYA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My husband and I have been craving for a good Chinese food. We have done take out here many times before,  it's our first time dining in actually.   I am so amazed on how good the service is at this restaurant. Food came out fast and it was delicious.  Did not disappoint 🙌.  Thank you wahwing, we will definitely dine in again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOVB0fCOEp8ge2kh842Ux2XpFXVwgqLutUtBbEG&fid=0x0:0x7c85358e6c767e95"],"When":"2023-8-5"},{"Name":"Amy Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUamHxgbXpYwrJI1uE5cJUYfe1wmxOQk5ygeSabzKwSDEQZmU3C=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This is my first time to dine in at this restaurant. The service is good but the food need some improvement. I ordered a noodle but the soup base taste salty . Chef should put less salt or no salt since the veggie already taste salty and the Chinese broccoli taste not much flavour.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNCpErihv2HeGr4hQralU6fnwyOSS6XRaqyldOu&fid=0x0:0x7c85358e6c767e95"],"When":"2023-11-15"},{"Name":"Julio Cipriano","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKdiL69VWk_HhrY9vvXJcaFkLa2z0igCrSjghxutPFMYl05ZQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Been going or ordering from here for 20+ years. Can’t remember a less than great meal!  Same applies today for lunch ginger beef, pork buns, even something simple like spring rolls all 5 *.  Tried the fried banana balls  and mango ice cream.  So so good!  Staff went out of their way to make sure my mother (little older) was taken care of. Congrats on 30 years and hope your here for another 30 for my kids to keep coming to!","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Cinthia Carter","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVxCKtnLXcRtOq8N3koaZfmHaE8dGxh16NKhaW2jHYv2KMggWER=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ordered a delivery of the Chicken Briyani and Vegetable Pakora. Sizes are generous and tasteful. Comes with yogurt dip and sweet sauce.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMwQCorKsyXVqRtyeS_eUWRsZNmPiiBLHb7_OF0&fid=0x0:0xb875a0b35cf34e92"],"When":"2024-6-15"},{"Name":"Gen Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL0x4Eq9GRWvX9EA38H3GMWPqz4gj6UZw48zS61frnmQ0-oj3E=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We ordered take out for the first time at Spice Cart Indian Cuisine and we’ll definitely order again! Great service as well, I had a question in regards to ordering and the person I was talking to on the phone and when I picked up our order was very friendly and helpful!

Everything we ordered was delicious and the portions were great! We ordered the mixed grill, jeera aloo, vegetable samosa, vegetable pakora, butter chicken, chicken curry, lamb curry, daal makhani, rice pulao and family size garlic naan. We ordered the rice pulao but the name written on the container was vegetable pulao which was still good but I wanted the flavour of the rice pulao as described in the menu.

We ordered for 6 adults and a few kids and that was plenty with leftovers. Love the option of family size naan too!

Various spice levels to choose from. I personally prefer the mild spice level as there is a bit of a kick to it already but we also tried the mild-medium and medium for a couple of the curries.

I was a little confused with the name though I thought it was Spice Art but found their website as Spice Cart. I had to check a few times before placing my order to ensure I was ordering from the location I wanted. Maybe they’re going through a name change?

Definitely recommend Spice Cart Indian Cuisine!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORhwg6Z106k-utRilMEv5ub_jGowvjp5aiZZSG&fid=0x0:0xb875a0b35cf34e92"],"When":"2023-8-9"},{"Name":"Andrea Montalvo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUM85_tvYyazq3zpCbhXaoxAHQ8AFH9PyvgEoJARteWjTICLgM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing customer service and food is so delicious and fresh. Their lunch special is something u can’t find anymore these days, such a great deal with more than enough food to fill one or even 2 people up!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOGIcZSqsUP5fdacxYTpcTJcbncd7cC6yQtM_U&fid=0x0:0xb875a0b35cf34e92"],"When":"2024-5-27"},{"Name":"Lu Kong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLiVMtuHct0ut1Io0IRXiCox51SyCX5BuI9wBm4XQtwUdKlKQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Awesome!! Garlic naan is a must. Ordered butter lamb and chicken, prawn masala, fish pakora, chilli chicken and chicken roganjosh. Chai and mango lassi to finish.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9ccpxZ5691vQJEqECNY6TQO-pNlZCzh_Dgxm5&fid=0x0:0xb875a0b35cf34e92"],"When":"2024-11-18"},{"Name":"Aliah Penner","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1TDYmKUFrTjDo4d_P5m90F8ZGophb_NfpYjPdV2J8RCVU6pmp=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"These guys are awesome. I consistently get the lunch special which is a good portion size at an exceptional price. Today I took my wife for dinner and we each got a butter chicken along with the "family size" garlic naan.

I was not prepared. Attached is a pic with a full size dinner plate for scale. Words cannot adequately describe this behemoth. It COVERS the lunch tray on which it is served. I'm not the type to take pictures of my dinner, but I was stunned.

Um, so suffice it to say the food is excellent and tasty, the portioning is incredibly generous for the very reasonable prices, and the service is great. Our family loves this place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOlfb_uW48LRZi-xtmIrSzaiHcSmtVDW4FaBnk6&fid=0x0:0xb875a0b35cf34e92"],"When":"2023-3-4"},{"Name":"EVAN ETHAN","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVUx4wFf5gaB1lR1A8XX5kn8xelbVXHG8-xFycDrpZ-n6j0ewpV=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"TRICITIES HIDDEN GEM! Cosy causal Indian restaurant. One of the best in Tricities - Taste, authentic, portions, value & friendly service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN0idsX1GkRrscRGEncB95mVmsU5uPRDgqsye7-&fid=0x0:0xb875a0b35cf34e92"],"When":"2024-3-16"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious food, value for money, and quick service, definitely a must visit. The restaurant has a lunch menu from 12pm-3pm each day with vegetable, chicken, paneer, and lamb combo ranging from $7.99 to $9.99. The combo comes with plenty of naan and a side of rice. The butter chicken was great with three large pieces of chicken and a buttery sauce with a slight hint of spicy. Dine in available. Located within plaza with parking.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOj1P-OKcJcIcVrjY0aY6npDxo6ixOAS77FMnzY&fid=0x0:0xb875a0b35cf34e92"],"When":"2022-12-31"},{"Name":"Dilsher Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJNMNLx9r_56qC0KfTM3Gvi9WvSjeIJDuQMhdv0AgCMlUgAwg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best Indian food in town by far . Spice Cart service and food quality it second to none . Ash and staff are very accommodating and prices are very good . Always make me feel at home and go extra mile . I strongly recommend to try Spice Cart for unforgettable experience. Thank you Spice Cart . Keep up the great work !","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Westcoast SCI","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWpJhoP7-vC8Se5z3JAfb4BRE9JvzaGqnklMMi9D-Mq3-jOlfGK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Such friendly caring staff. Food is always top notch. Been going here for ages and are never disappointed. Great south East Asian food and a local favorite.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNWthTd3sZpy1B6sbOYXmPIwJTJ8MWT6CwPmaQY&fid=0x0:0xcd64adebb2d5434"],"When":"2024-12-8"},{"Name":"Adrienne","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKvS1YiBi1kAYmplCTkzo9NqyjbLMViYayHxaEQA-dKyQUyyA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Service was great, our meals came out quickly. The food was very tasty and well seasoned - we do wish the crispy prawns were crispier, but overall everything was great. Their chili oil had a lot of flavour and is great with pho.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOJCURKxhDsejvYWKZ3B2tGoLFsHmqwT3PbhcwV&fid=0x0:0xcd64adebb2d5434"],"When":"2024-6-1"},{"Name":"Melinda Ng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUMsYIuruesNJ4fTjqy4yNevJthJq9c29QqfPxA8x09D9sg2sf9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Two eggs for the rice combo?! Two thumbs up! All the food we had here was great. I really enjoyed the chicken spring rolls, they’re fried slightly differently and it was so crunchy! It was slightly rainy today so the pho really hit the spot. It was a solid broth. We ordered mostly Vietnamese tonight but there was also tempting Thai food on the menu. Would be interested in coming back to try those.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP8UTX-2aljdQeJ3LYJ7VLvwf206soFVvn3NLF_&fid=0x0:0xcd64adebb2d5434"],"When":"2023-10-17"},{"Name":"Elmira Nazari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUS8psOPde-fgvVYsglTVKj-j9hpNdB1347mGr_T9d11yAStREO4w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Hungry we decided to try this place for pho and wasn't expecting much. Was surprised to see that they also had Thai food. The mango salad had some really unique flavours with spice, sweetness and crunchy textures from the mango and cashews. The pho broth was flavourful and meat seemed fresh. The lemongrass chicken was also well seasoned and one of the best we've had. The shrimp rolls were alright, i wouldn't get them again. The service however, was a bit of a miss with one of our food coming significantly later than the others. Overall good spot to grab a bite!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPiWbheoUAie-TYos2gKT4z4NTT52Q5fBSephfj&fid=0x0:0xcd64adebb2d5434"],"When":"2023-9-2"},{"Name":"Lu Kong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLiVMtuHct0ut1Io0IRXiCox51SyCX5BuI9wBm4XQtwUdKlKQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"For those who want pho and Thai dishes that is really good in one place. This is it. Started on the combo platter then realized should've taken a picture.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNw02Bh1DYLgwrWxEuHwcTOfEyn_D68CfX53A3F&fid=0x0:0xcd64adebb2d5434"],"When":"2024-11-22"},{"Name":"John Harris","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKAq3ml95jHUMxZNKiBUEM24tdpzJMiqP5RJmX8-A4uSjHfIg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Their pad Thai is very good. But why isn't plain chicken pad Thai a regular menu item anymore!? I don't want chicken AND shrimp / to be charged the same price if I want chicken only. I don't want to deal with picking off shrimp shells or skin or whatever the shrimp stuff you can't just eat is.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Blampin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUe_Zl-7bsR_k4aPN0CDrFm3JxQQaY2wgkXgNPVdZQs9NDoFTA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really good food. Appetizers, soups, Mango salads! 🥭  Various spring rolls, Ravens, Noodle dishes and rice dishes.
Quick service.
Lots of parking outside and nice booths yo sit at inside.
I'd go there again for sure to try something new from the menu.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMvp-DNUoHMlkOHc7q4cn6AuP1fZ67JpgES4kr2&fid=0x0:0xcd64adebb2d5434"],"When":"2023-5-15"},{"Name":"Jason York","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW2KL5JJiTZL1QVt_3AcqILQXXBIuqDWdYOdj3lYENvavlAma6S8A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Vermicelli - Grilled beef w/ spring roll
... Got a free beverage for my Google Maps review.
Food was beautifully presented and tasty.  I'm personally not allergic to peanuts and was happy to have that option on the side.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNYpDJ1yDJLzCSeZClsNkf2VsUYfYZe8EnseRp0&fid=0x0:0xcd64adebb2d5434"],"When":"2024-4-26"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Adam M.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXBezQ5u52QUPfNCS-XISW7oETfNlf5RvdoikJTFUzauPV7HEINiA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We recently celebrated Father's Day with a lunch at Kisso Sushi, a spot that has become a bit of a favorite for us. This time, there were six of us, and I had wisely booked in advance, which turned out to be a smart move as the restaurant was nearly full.

This was my third visit to Kisso Sushi, with my previous visits being just my wife and I. This time, we were seated at the booked bench seats, which were comfortable and offered a good view of the restaurant’s charming blend of traditional Japanese ambiance and modern design touches..

One of the standout features of Kisso Sushi is their use of technology. Each table is equipped with a tablet, making the ordering process incredibly convenient. Whether you need to place an order or request service, it can all be done through the tablet.

After placing our orders, we had the unique experience of having our dishes delivered by a robotic server. It was quite a novelty and added a fun element to our meal. As for the food, it did not disappoint. The dishes were delicious, and the portions were generous.

In summary, Kisso Sushi provided us with a delightful dining experience for Father's Day. The combination of tasty food, substantial portions, and efficient service, all set in a beautifully designed space, ensures we'll be back for more. Highly recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPO6u8yWJkEqcwhDv5acWee_n-dpaXn28mvd2l3&fid=0x0:0x8fc73854e26bc0ef"],"When":"2024-6-18"},{"Name":"Jason Tribbiani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXXpvlAY0NULhaj1b4k1yZZtRXFlzsqxg5gIO8-kzQ1-Qy-iq7d=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"**Rating: 4.5/5**

We discovered this restaurant by chance after a stop at Costco for gas and groceries, and it didn’t disappoint! The excellent reviews drew us in for a late lunch, and the atmosphere was warm and inviting. I ordered the miso ramen, which had a generous portion and was a fantastic deal. However, the beef tataki, while decent, could have been fresher and a bit more substantial for $17.

One standout for me was the Japanese black lager—it was hands down one of the best beers I’ve ever tasted. Rich, smooth, and perfectly balanced, it truly elevated the meal.

The service was exceptional, with friendly staff and quick, efficient table service. A fun bonus, especially for families, is the robot that delivers food to your table—kids were absolutely thrilled! Overall, we thoroughly enjoyed our visit and will definitely be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMFuVsWhF70wdcZimTYvIyJbMK6q1HkOqa-SUa8&fid=0x0:0x8fc73854e26bc0ef"],"When":"2024-9-16"},{"Name":"Lillian Lum","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJrY8_dgCjRNM3DfoPeTmvJyXQqnWprjrecffpwFkgSgCFdD7j=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My first time here and the food was very fresh, loved the salmon sushi. The ramen was a nice texture. Chewy. We couldn't finish our meal, as the serving sizes were a good portion. We had a few rolls, presentation was nice. The ambience - comfortable. The music was not too loud, so we could hear each other talk. The servers were attentive to their surroundings. All around, a great experience?! Would definitely come back here. You must give this place a try!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNlLc4F32L3coxlryaEA4E6j-T5DsGgNqR1l2Fi&fid=0x0:0x8fc73854e26bc0ef"],"When":"2024-4-19"},{"Name":"C Kirin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKnBT8Oa_FVHcdDihDKiA_9JO-x7_bvGiDCptW0i5MK-RhAbg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Second time ordering takeout, overall im happy. Very good sushi, average price. Only downside I have experienced so far is getting ginger/wasabi in my order BOTH times when i always ask for neither..thank goodness its not an allergy. I also didnt get chopsticks/soy/napkins this time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMFS1_9-QI1kizcK53owssPV7KjTm0B28wbQdjr&fid=0x0:0x8fc73854e26bc0ef"],"When":"2024-10-4"},{"Name":"Meherin Aupee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXY5oPef8T5X6ZOo5uF-MPpN3GuFeAURkWs8rvqfslB0DHFHA4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I came here first time. The staffs especially servers were very friendly. Most of foods were very fresh and tasted good. I would recommend this place for sure to my friends. Thanks Kisso!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPe4O_ffVKB-Z0FL1avA-B5Hi4--4qWyFAB5F9f&fid=0x0:0x8fc73854e26bc0ef"],"When":"2024-5-8"},{"Name":"Chris Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKL6NY8ujR0ee9OFhMcGaL3sLgJDF84QvHUJHWiYfXacg9U9g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very decent family Japanese restaurant. Food andnpricing is decent. Best value for variety of food with their lunch or bento specials. Seating is a little awkward for bigger groups (we were 8) since most are booth seats so people need to move out to allow inside seaters come out.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPjpKeZ7pNu1E_HZeW2RZ0eIQnibF0_XcFBkN3s&fid=0x0:0x8fc73854e26bc0ef"],"When":"2024-8-19"},{"Name":"Augusto Velez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKapxvbdj8vqqNYigF-wnM0Yr3KpjStzucZu7_xdLasSfSudQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great sushi place.
Their Ramen is just like the one I tried in my recent trip to Japan.
Overall great food","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMevN0fy4JAxApdbJXwXN1WqawAVzp8Lnz4ezsc&fid=0x0:0x8fc73854e26bc0ef"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"Mingyu Hyung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUO4TZih2ZkRTTf-wROrZoFeF_RJiYWREG3DKcg-NG-Bb9E9-Y=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We loved everything. The deluxe assorted sashimi was beyond phenomenal—absolutely outstanding. The servers were attentive and super kind as well. We’re definitely coming back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPHHn88OM3EFfoCUVTm-Vwg-bZTVXDZLNDgfwPf&fid=0x0:0x8fc73854e26bc0ef"],"When":"2024-5-2"}]

[{"Name":"Marissa McKinnon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWBtcJLgdPMQpgMt2XQrlMeQ9B_SDnMecxrkflkfI6-e9ON270=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"sucks that there are such mixed reviews!!! i had the salt and pepper wings with a side of hot sauce and they absolutely hit the spot. the wings were crispy but not too breaded and had lots of meat on them!! tasted so delicious as well as the fries (u might think how can fries be bad) but i have very high fry standards and these were crispy, hot fresh and delicious…not too salty!! They had a delicious garlic dipping sauce that paired perfectly i definitely recommend trying these out!! The space is so gorgeous. It is quite a fancy atmosphere which was a little unexpected for the location, i’d love to come back for drinks as well!! The server was very kind and accommodating :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN3lN4DT_Iycz4TIRz_nUw4Y8sS2jJWKbtd1FJy&fid=0x0:0xa2bd7aba18e32bb6"],"When":"2024-7-19"},{"Name":"tru klass","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJULljo2CZpIBgCzW01ZQWqWOBp8nxIDLyMxp6UUoq4toUJ6Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My mum and I had lunch there on Saturday and everything was perfect. The drinks were delicious, and so were our meals. I had the prawn power bowl and it was so well balanced and I'd definitely recommend. The service was also great.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPlyjqXTgBKhX_ls-QU-rYod3bwan86mGUNs6eh&fid=0x0:0xa2bd7aba18e32bb6"],"When":"2024-7-29"},{"Name":"Grace B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUYzRmU5pRggounfGFdNhaCgFB1i2Hk7bErahU4qwNuN7tYIZyf=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Had read good reviews but this was a disappointing and mediocre experience. Hostess was lovely and the server was trying but had no idea about the food or drink and couldn’t answer any basic questions and didn’t really seem to be trained at all. If craft beer is on the menu either have the details on a board or train your servers to know a bit about your beer and wines.

My heritage is Portuguese and I cannot see how this is in any way Portuguese influenced food. Chicken was clearly reheated with sauce poured over it, grilled veggies and mashed potatoes were ok.  Chicken was extremely dry and rubbery. Arrived way too quickly to be fresh.  We only had two mains;a chicken bowl and grilled chicken meal.  Weren’t compelled to try anything else. Underwhelming. Prices ok but quality not there. Not a good value.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO_28xVzDr6ampMPh-VrxFTVBo9NkMFOOXoOsxE&fid=0x0:0xa2bd7aba18e32bb6"],"When":"2024-6-8"},{"Name":"Andrew J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVVmNa6jisgEJLsGMynHFW0Nb2To-ki1W8gv-mWfe16waRH8-6p=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Not bad! Enjoyed the atmosphere & service here immensely. Food is fine. Wish it was a bit more impressive for thr price. Don't bother with the cesar salad.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNjAwxz4vmvDkzHTbjJ79xAPH5Hv2gweELvkjqP&fid=0x0:0xa2bd7aba18e32bb6"],"When":"2024-11-30"},{"Name":"Kevin Luo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWJMxLZr-3YvPOYEYkCwOqoRgX8yyWGLPYZ19IJEKzgIUssXc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Health food deluxe! I stopped by to grab a quick bite, and I was impressed by its ambience. I had the prawn power bowl, and it was delicious and extremely healthy. The flavour of the fresh vegetables and quinoa is very well balanced by the creamy sauce and shrimp. I'm just not sure how Portuguese it is though. Overall a delightful experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNi9dwa8kkM4BNbDBwDwSuoJTW9Xh-nRrWgwOaX&fid=0x0:0xa2bd7aba18e32bb6"],"When":"2024-3-12"},{"Name":"Adam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXvBO_gAscD4jQgf7WwLgwSNvcd9hd0WZ5uykstCAcxi1lOdl4w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow! I was so surprised that the quality and portion size were spot on the for the price. the food was very tasty and I was happy with everything we got.

The restaurant is also extremely well decorated and comfortable.  They do play music but at a volume that is easy to still have a conversation.

The staff were very friendly and helpful. They had a good knowledge of what they were second and what went into it. Also the different courses are well spaced and seem to appear at just the right time.

I will definitely be going back soon and would recommend to friends and family without hesitation.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPfbzsmuipmh58Tlxh-nSzNEZH3rRQbrO-pzxRa&fid=0x0:0xa2bd7aba18e32bb6"],"When":"2021-7-31"},{"Name":"Adele Watson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLmg9O9eJVdKcgQE9EcLI7KacahS0x1nMw1eZrnJFYsRp_QwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The restaurant was dead, only 2 groups of 4 people. The server did not come to greet us. 15 mins goes by and I had to flag her over. After the food was served she didn’t come by to see how everything was. Again we had to flag her down to get the bill. They did surprise me with a piece of cheese cake saying Happy Mother’s Day. To which I was surprised. That was nice! I think if the staff was more tentative and had more training it could be a better place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM6paIURZCtNemTEJJFNJXiMLROrf43REDF9D_Y&fid=0x0:0xa2bd7aba18e32bb6"],"When":"2024-5-14"},{"Name":"Ryan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW45IYuhuQceepraBGwk75o-s6TtuC_5_eWJedl6juhh8_2uy_gyg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent value! Good food, big portions, attentive service, good drinks and craft beers. There is what looks like a lounge side that is visible from outside and a restaurant side with huge booths that is hidden, so even though it looks empty there may be people sitting in the restaurant side, they should probably be sitting people in the lounge instead as nobody likes going into an empty restaurant and I think seeing people inside would cause more people to come in. So even if it looks empty go in and try it.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Armin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUVKfPvn-jqW8hTOlU1VeElw6vFvjre9PTWSba_96soEJn4hAFVjA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's probably my favorite or second favorite pizza place in Vancouver! Been coming here for more than 15 years.
The foods great, you have to wait a bit but worth it.
It was always expensive but with todays economy the prices have jumped a lot too so I find myself going there a lot less than before. More like an special occasion.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNb7IhsBtrpVD77pxDsLy2RE9hDy8rfFPJZWnaH&fid=0x0:0xa2c542823b0ae144"],"When":"2024-9-19"},{"Name":"todd lazarenko","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXMWhJK6u9XNG2-gmnhPqFucz9pNeWhp5Mzp9oBrrbII94Vr5o9=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This establishment has the best pizza on the planet. If you have never tried it, do yourself a favor and try it. Other menu items worth mentioning are the pastas and the Greek salad. Great atmosphere and top notch service from Rohma.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMfnRmUCKH-ZKcsk7_apXvhch4O2cnPeCf6SA0&fid=0x0:0xa2c542823b0ae144"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Hyeonlee Jeong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcI0gkDJVeRogratAEoVML3D18gR-yt8UO4ru1zdtGUcm039B7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Vee was as fantastic as the food. Highly recommend. She made my birthday!!! ❤️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNCY_BuiLa6w4xcSFs7ypoFqHJdm6eJckzl_WbU&fid=0x0:0xa2c542823b0ae144"],"When":"2024-11-13"},{"Name":"Sahar Taghavi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ8OOT-rS2WgnxA0jJcUc4Eft2oUFCxHr9rO9ZWBW4wrpf0ow=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My family and I had an amazing experience at this restaurant! We enjoyed two awesome cocktails, the garlic bread was absolutely delicious, and the fish and chips were fantastic. Even my 4-year-old daughter loved her meal, which is always a great sign. We really enjoyed the atmosphere—it was warm and welcoming, and we had a great time. Special shout-out to our server, Sharon. She was so kind, lovely, and attentive, especially to my daughter. We will definitely be coming back again!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"B B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIWXkb7cw_G-9xJo_3-zWM41O-N5FcHl5P5HTGctsYs5K7I=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Decent pizza. The Good ... The crust was perfect and the cheese was gooey.

The bad... The toppings were uneven... Way too many (uncooked) chunks of tomatoes, and not much sausage or peppers.
When I'm paying $32 for one medium pizza, the pizza should be loaded evenly with toppings.

Our server was friendly and attentive.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"O'Neil","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWlG_qS4RzoXq0jXYAc_venCNNLYuKBdxhX5Bt4JfwcrWcoZULh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went to this pizza place other night with some friends. They recommend it. I really enjoyed the service. The toppings were really thick and it was very tasty and well put together. Everything thing was wonderful. Price point was fair and portions were good. We ordered a large and 3 of use could not finish it. Also had appetizers were also delicious.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOiDR-RTb1qKIL8QRrBvX1p-oGWlwEhvmurFtru&fid=0x0:0xa2c542823b0ae144"],"When":"2023-2-12"},{"Name":"Candice C.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJwFBBjzDK0K147Ahvw56fgZp0Wzk8W8u0zo_aJQ425Hu_MYA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Mixed review.
Pizza is very good!! I've only ever ordered take out and had no complaints.
The other night I called in and they said I could place a take out order as they were closing in 20min, perfect worked for me. I order the lasagne which I haven't had here before. Well it's literally 90% noodles, 5% cheese and 5% sauce and not good sauce at that, just very bland with little meat and lots of pepper. I won't order it again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOttwakDj7ldqA6GB4WNyu1yGy0wjdN_fIIUjR2&fid=0x0:0xa2c542823b0ae144"],"When":"2023-8-29"},{"Name":"John Harris","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKAq3ml95jHUMxZNKiBUEM24tdpzJMiqP5RJmX8-A4uSjHfIg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you want thin crust, go elsewhere (Emilio Finattis is a good option!). San Remo Pizza is THICC. It's kind of like if 1/3 of a lasagna and a 2/3 of regular pizza had a very delicious baby.

They have beer if you eat in, they've been around since at least the 80s apparently, and I've never had a bad pizza from them.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Debby","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVj1FDmxBaGck5J8K_6foLYNC59Bk0g1TlSH1h2iqnrvGDOlREc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I accidentally tipped twice.
I ordered online and paid in store.
My order already had a tip included, but their machine does not recognize this, so it asks you for a tip. I thought maybe I made a mistake, so I added a tip. When I checked back at my car, I tipped on top of the amount that was already tipped, which means my second tip was based on the previous amount which included the tip. My 2nd tip, although same percentage was higher than the first tip. Not really happy about that, but now I know.

Asides from that, The cheese just is not cheesy. Almost like there is not enough cheese, or not seasoned right.

The presentation looks great.
The pizza was warm, crust was crispy.
Lots of veggies and meat.
My kids were ultimately happy about the pizza.

The staff was friendly.
They labeled the boxes, which I like because my son can't have tomato anything, so he had a separate pizza.

The missing star is because the cheese is just not cheesy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPibqZRuT1yML5oGaW7JRphug16QtnE7ZWFnJHC&fid=0x0:0xcfb41ac83671b9ff"],"When":"2024-8-26"},{"Name":"Phil Dufault","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXddvyUjgQ_YO8GzkQuPay08OzzxyL4QPIRtWGcejX9JSKQFISI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I'm a regular. They've called me before when I have messed up my order, saving me both time and from disappointment.  I love their gluten free pizzas, crust is always crispy and the options are all pretty delicious. I recommend in particular the Chef Created Special, but everything is good.

My kid and wife love their gluteny options, pizza, wings, etc.

Give them a try, you'll be surprised. They make a better pizza than most.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mithila Karnik","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXh7y26jxgrcv2234K17s4LRS1t5EoXQp4TUPik7Ky5HNK7bWg_=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hands down the best pizza I have had in PoCo that has the perfect “desi” flavours - our house favorites are the Three Musketeers and Taste Of India and we always go for adding on cilantro and ginger! The owner is amazing and service is spot on! Our regular and loved pizza place!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chris Tran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVHb3kgAZ1zh7lq6KxmqUUIt5wY73oWFc1xGKx8Xs6V7ttovemaIA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent pizza, tasted fresh, and reasonably priced. Dough was great, toppings were evenly distributed, and even my girlfriend who doesn't like pizza's LOVED it.

My newest go-to pizza place in PoCo","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"lekha chhibba","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ5IZOD4JsMGF5_7w1R7tCN0PqrFQWQWiv9D61QkTEi5u0oCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I had gone in for a meal and I regret it!! The management really needs to work on training the staff on being a lot more respectful and polite! The food tasted unfresh and stale.. the place was extremely dirty.. and at the end of all of it, it's almost like they demand a tip, by repetitively saying, "oh no tip, no tip, sure?"
The place needs to either shut down or hire trained staff.

THERE ARE RODENTS IN THE STORE

It’s just horrible
With extremely disrespectful staff
Unexpected behaviour specially in canada","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dzenan J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXISZzTTcEVuyEWrUryNmL3YO_uwsvWO2Vmr-BxuaFzs5nMBEbgsA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Large variety of pizzas, wings, pasta... [{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Ordered takeout and the pizza was delicious and real tasting. Our favourite was the fungi de Alfredo pizza. The manager’s choice is good too if you like meat and lots going on as toppings for your pizza. The Hawaiian pizza tasted standard. The only thing in my opinion that would make the pizza taste even better is if they applied a little more tomato sauce on the pizzas as the Hawaiian and Manager’s Choice pizza were a little light on the tomato sauce (as seen in the photos) and the tomato flavour was very light and not too prominent.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNDanaQg5OogPQ81J4SQ9fw9ApD-2ZO_W4nlOgX&fid=0x0:0x6203e4dff14a041b"],"When":"2024-8-17"},{"Name":"Bekah French","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJiYLh-7emQ9AthzE2N_CGxwmtRUdZguPeMRuVIWmhyOtllxQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Upon recommendation from a friend we ordered a pizza. We chose the Italian delight but switched the olive oil base for pesto instead. It was delicious and quite affordable. Large (6big slices) for $22. Love the light thin base and great toppings. Easy walking distance from our place. Will be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM7PNveFE7yJk1kR3lFheirfPwsbjs0YO3AvaFT&fid=0x0:0x6203e4dff14a041b"],"When":"2024-10-17"},{"Name":"Marie Amin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIKR0qp3fose5GsYts0dtMeJqwXo1MWNFSPwo4SjCtJGEbgYA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":""Just tried their pizza for the first time, and I highly recommend it! 🍕 Best pizza I've ever had with amazing customer service. Definitely worth a visit!"","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOk6JBQ77EXh9lNodBouxDx5ck25ioObiX2nxxi&fid=0x0:0x6203e4dff14a041b"],"When":"2024-7-24"},{"Name":"Karen R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWDV_xh-2FRTt60Dk8cmOVYbJK862izxJKbtP4b4MrmUNx8NdUF=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’m Impressed!

This place came up on a google search and I was rushed and just went for it, so I didn’t know what to expect. I didn’t even read the other reviews. I went in blind.

The crust was nice and crunchy on the bottom and soft on the top. It is somewhere between the Neapolitan thin-ness and like a “standard pizza”. Best of both worlds.

Toppings were not too heavy but I think there is pizza science out there with a toppings to crust ratio. If you want a stack of toppings add more.

Cheese was light but again I think this is purposeful and it works with the rest of it, but if you need to live the cheezy life, just add more of it.

I was very annoying by accident and I made a few special requests while it was busy on a Friday not knowing this place is actually quite popular and busy. They accommodated my requests anyway.

Online ordering was easy and the timeline was reliable. I waited maybe 2 extra minutes (probably while the accommodated my annoying peak hour requests)

The staff were nice.

It is August and it was hot. I would not recommend sitting inside on a 31 degree August evening to eat your pizza.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPHPjN224PO1yD1vEICW09TRi7_Ob8BC9EHiWeE&fid=0x0:0x6203e4dff14a041b"],"When":"2024-8-10"},{"Name":"Jessica Dhaliwal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOeC5VCbc6g3HH3dxXpDS9bE993HEKMDVI3SjHX2aNdHbQOJHQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice flat pizza with great toppings and aftertaste. Really grateful they have slices available even late","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPdju3xRR9csby2HRwLCeCGjQ8wAdbmHMC6jUyr&fid=0x0:0x6203e4dff14a041b"],"When":"2024-12-21"},{"Name":"Daniel Jung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFE7g6vnjf23CW6mDeh4anchF8fxBs6O5Nsx0bvhepuO3MVzWa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Vegan Cheese option! My friends & I ordered takeout this past Saturday for UFC. Their delivery timing was on point and the pizza tasted really good. I got the Bulgogi Pizza, flavor was spot on with a little kick of heat, crust was so good.
The only thing is the base dough was so thin that when I lifted the pizza.. All the toppings fell off. [{"Name":"Sunny Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI24WPvgM-FfIlJLLr7IedglAHWoUtLRiaKg7As2_gjZs7wTQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I worked at lots of Japanese restaurants all over Canada for all most 15years. I just found my go spot whenever I come to Port Coquitlam. Hands down 👍 😍
If you are sushi lover, won’t be disappointed here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN-vyyowiFAyY0Gcda7FFUG_B6I9YBYmOKTO6-7&fid=0x0:0x29d676848f2eea7f"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"Bill knox","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLSRV11XH3-3P7ySnqI01hySFkx75lkH_2ysCH7LkCeT5zF-A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This should really be a fine dining restaurant. Exceptional food and service. What more can I say? Lots, apparently. Every dish is carefully crafted, not just thrown together. There was a remote-controlled light buried in the ice to high light the sashimi, and the server showed us all the different combinations to the delight of everyone, especially my 6 year old grandson. We're very surprised when  we were presented with deep fried ice cream. Delicious.
Food is key, but for me, service is always the lock that makes the meal. All the servers waited on all the tables. There was never an empty plate on the table and if the food was ready the first available server brought it.
That is what makes a first class restaurant, first class.
I will always go back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPCCHGqeHwmdR-Ci0vBcZx3zIorHb2hjpaNN9iB&fid=0x0:0x29d676848f2eea7f"],"When":"2024-4-18"},{"Name":"Stacey Robinsmith","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_qFQLK010t5gOeaOzVIwWOPcgI7YdNFJni03OtXqoh_08R4sIAQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Kosho Sushi is a littlest treasure out in Port Coquitlam. Beautifully prepared and inventive sushi and sashimi at reasonable prices. I was very pleased with my meal at Kosho.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOdr6lPpr5NkL1VSyjPq5BpayThmxigiz0TjCi_&fid=0x0:0x29d676848f2eea7f"],"When":"2024-6-3"},{"Name":"L Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJQvIh5w41NvNm69uuQ6fEFfx4_xCLgbz-lb793dTjac89L3A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you want fresh sashimi and sushi in Port Coquitlam this is definitely the spot to be at.  The sockeye salmon sashimi was fresh and delicious and presentation here is excellent making the whole experience very enjoyable.  The California roll and spicy salmon rolls were equally enjoyable.  If you come at lunch you can get lunch portions at a reasonable price.  For the price point it definitely is a must try.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPvhX_vpggJiL0Kmp4k48_WtKhbXe1TZ7FJUKeP&fid=0x0:0x29d676848f2eea7f"],"When":"2024-7-18"},{"Name":"Chan Andy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUP8ZIfapwxhfTSOijijHjaOYybbetMTtbDMDr_n7A2U-HLr8E-jA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very good food, very good presentation and very polite staff. Despite a little pricey, we still like the food here. The menu was complicated and had no picture, they promised they will come up with a new menu soon, hope it happens.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMSDe1QEzN-mbqc7yqGx8k7BpaZuG0JEljHCFx9&fid=0x0:0x29d676848f2eea7f"],"When":"2024-9-8"},{"Name":"J T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJhlRzWDXzdsN5IEg7ILK_EQ56zA9jcQ-fPPr3cS5cgV1YVlw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Last man eating…

In the area picking up something from a customer and options for a bite was dwindling down. Finally decided for a revisit to this place which I haven’t been to for years.

Inside is one of those smaller cozy place; clean, typical and nothing too fancy. I was glad the server seated me on a bigger table instead one of those midget size ones. The server informed me they have a Tri-city special set menu for $35, quick glanced and I opted out on that. Here were the food I ordered;

1. Miso soup (complimentary). Pretty basic but thank you, nice to have a hot soup to warm up to from the cold.
2. Appetizer tempura. Pretty basic and as it should be.
3. Oyster motoyaki. I was glad they were on the shell but didn’t know it’s their own version of it; cold, marinated with cold pan fried onions on top. The cold oysters didn’t really do it for me. Is it really that hard to find just the basic fresh oyster motoyaki baked with Japanese mayo anywhere? lol
4. Foie gras nigiri. Okay this is one of those must order item from here. Loved how the way it is put together and seared. Rich, buttery and creamy that literally melts in your mouth. Very nice!
5. Spider roll. A little bit too basic, could be more generous on the soft shell crab.
6. Saba shio yaki. It was okay, pretty straightforward dish.
7. Assorted sashimi. It was okay, the Akami could be a better cut.
8. Chopped scallops, uni, amaebi nigiris. The chopped scallop was fresh, the uni was a generous amount, I like how the amaebi head was prepared so easier to eat.
9. Albacore toro, Akami, chu toro. The albacore toro was a bit dry, the Akami was fresh, the chu toro just make it to the satisfactory level (as you can tell it lost some of its beautiful colour already).

The restaurant is conveniently located on the corner of Lougheed Hwy and Shaughnessy Street in Port Coquitlam. There are plenty of free parkings in the plaza. Inside the restaurant offers a causal comfortable dining atmosphere.

The food was okay, could be better in some departments, but overall satisfactory level.

As for the service, the staffs here were very friendly and welcoming. And quite accommodating to me being the last person left munching away (sorry over stayed 10mins after closing)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMgz35zAf1EBI5VT4-S3OU-XjBlX1JuPyxUP2it&fid=0x0:0x29d676848f2eea7f"],"When":"2024-3-4"},{"Name":"eva lo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLG6_-zQP_odjQCD6-QyiUAohJJqHIlSZOxxzIrErs4yEpQng=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely love this place! Food is great. And their services are amazing as well!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOS83AdNvfEIDJZZkV3DePelW_McN7Tj1FLm851&fid=0x0:0x29d676848f2eea7f"],"When":"2024-11-5"},{"Name":"Shirley Cha","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXpR8FGS-5KuK23fMRpnfaa4vxFgDGeGslPmJNLIpRzEPP553My=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I LOVE this place so much! I’ve been here a lot of times, and each time I’ve had a wonderful experience. Food is beautifully presented, service is exceptional, place is cozy and spotlessly clean, and most importantly the food tastes AMAZING!🍣 It’s always fresh and made with high quality ingredients. Their menu features variety of dishes that are creative and innovative. Whenever I want some sushi, this place is the first one that comes to my mind. I can’t wait to go back and have some more!😍","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNurzGF_ST8dpEReGzlZ8wENSDXHDG8Zh9Wsq65&fid=0x0:0x29d676848f2eea7f"],"When":"2022-10-21"}]

[{"Name":"Golnaz J N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwh094AvMjRiNSQoo9HjnFTPUMh8c3XSGOFZ78okUlI4KLdqnN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The Kaleh Pache was decent, but the experience overall fell short of expectations. The Tah Dig Gheymeh was a letdown – it wasn't crispy as it should be, filled mostly with rice, and had a very small portion of stew that was overly oily. The Persian pizza was just average, lacking any unique flavor that would set it apart. To top it off, the wait time was quite long. Overall, it was an okay experience, but I expected more in terms of quality and service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN-DzvesS71y-fgPB5CjK_5S8bmZDJjWPi46iSO&fid=0x0:0x3c64e6ca184bd7fd"],"When":"2024-10-31"},{"Name":"Ashkan N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKGC9QpVpAYzkuU2nETbRxXDGZW6ZxU4DFK0Bytd5fdamCstw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A nice little local restaurant/ghost kitchen with a solid selection of Persian dishes. The pizzas are decent, though not the best. Their standout item is likely the kale pache, and the tadig khoresht is also quite good.
Service is very slow. But overall I'd give them a 4.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNWxtyTF9I5R2VTJVF2ZMshGzFUPWcZVNlsN-Bi&fid=0x0:0x3c64e6ca184bd7fd"],"When":"2024-12-3"},{"Name":"Aran Owraki","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUMukJTyOYOyVYJHs5NR3brAaT7WkUiw2-ZZJKxdbciL2IrOk1t=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"🌟 A Taste of Home at Ron’s Kitchen! 🌟

I recently had the pleasure of dining at Ron’s Kitchen, and I must say, it was a truly unforgettable experience. From the moment I walked in, the warm hospitality made me feel right at home. The staff were incredibly welcoming and attentive, ensuring that every part of our meal was perfect.

Now, let’s talk about the food—absolutely outstanding! Their nostalgic Pizza and the Tah Dig with Gheymeh took me straight back to the beautiful memories of Iran. The flavors were authentic, rich, and reminded me of the comfort of home-cooked meals from back in our beloved country. It was like taking a delicious trip to Iran without ever leaving Vancouver!

For all my fellow Persians in the area, I 100% recommend that you come and try this place for yourself. Ron’s Kitchen has truly captured the essence of Iranian cuisine, and I can’t wait to return!

Thank you, Ron’s Kitchen, for a perfect meal and for bringing a slice of Iran to Vancouver!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMiXbAVwcP3z55Fs-Xct5p7ayC1xWdYz0NWIKh0&fid=0x0:0x3c64e6ca184bd7fd"],"When":"2024-10-11"},{"Name":"Hamid Hadilou","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ12isydAXwM3ARp62zO3XO3aAlRt1Lz7EzJoHZ_jp5xJJpCg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We have a new Chef in PoCo Town! The food quality, cleanliness, and service were amazing. From the moment we walked in, we were greeted with a warm and friendly atmosphere that set the tone for an exceptional dining and Pick Up experience. Every dish we ordered was a masterpiece, bursting with flavor and presented beautifully. The attention to detail in both the food and the service was evident, making it clear that Ron’s Kitchen is dedicated to excellence. The restaurant was spotless, and the staff was attentive without being intrusive. This is a place where you can tell that passion and care are put into every aspect of the dining experience. We can’t wait to come back and explore more of the menu. Highly recommend to anyone looking for top-notch food in PoCo!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOiNP5H5N26celVarfM24lmbEAtDdYacTyFRrtE&fid=0x0:0x3c64e6ca184bd7fd"],"When":"2024-9-1"},{"Name":"raha jazayeri","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLeHwyKukldVqCQIaW6Hb1fVivrQi2xY8TwgMoYP5s_QjdArw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had the Gheimeh and Fesenjoon with Tah Dig, and they were amazing! The flavors were rich, and everything was perfectly cooked. The place was cozy and had a great atmosphere. We’ll definitely be back to try the Kaleh Pacheh next time. Highly recommend this place 😋","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMP25ckOHlByt-xKZiP9UiHcavjmNJzyWNJpIme&fid=0x0:0x3c64e6ca184bd7fd"],"When":"2024-9-21"},{"Name":"Roozbeh Mahdavian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWlYHlliT96h2CKmEL2OP36V0Ebi4mRPOIoBhegocBDCMV6ZxIC=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a Tahdig and Stew at Ron’s kitchen. The Tahdig was super crispy and a bit oily which good Persian food is. The stews were super delicious . Ghormeh sabzi was slow cooked to perfection and I can bet they used herbs coming from Iran . Gheymeh was also super good with hint of rosewater and cardamom so it makes it a special gheymeh and not a normal eveyday one . The owner was also very friendly and shared a bite of their new Kabob which was really juicy and tender .
The prices were not the cheapest on the market but well worth the quality they offer .","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7h4TsC8YlTv2IibS4gxGrbmh35eO9rWA9vU8t&fid=0x0:0x3c64e6ca184bd7fd"],"When":"2024-11-27"},{"Name":"Behzad S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVdn5sAH4_-94pUgypGL0vz7OLt2p1u7D01QH_tNkAPq1dokklOrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I tried Ron's Kitchen Pizza in Port Coquitlam tonight, and it was a fantastic experience! The pizza was delicious, with fresh, high-quality ingredients and perfectly baked crust. I especially loved their creative topping combinations, which added a unique twist to classic flavors. The service was friendly and efficient, and the atmosphere felt warm and inviting. Whether you're dining in or taking out, Ron's Kitchen Pizza is a must-visit for pizza lovers in Port Coquitlam. Highly recommended.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPzU16bkHjUGWzC-Qm-4RE_98M-r8UJd591fuRN&fid=0x0:0x3c64e6ca184bd7fd"],"When":"2024-12-4"},{"Name":"Negin S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9PFM8OFXz96EGupa46F26TjSmHGXNqJDPVPW5fuudtMqYhMU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Just visited Ron's kitchen and it was by far one of the best persian food experiences I've had. The kalepache is the best in Vancouver, absolutely delicious and the chef is very kind and hospitable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO2GouF2kXIaJ3D4KrtPPpudztewpIYoKWNouA&fid=0x0:0x3c64e6ca184bd7fd"],"When":"2024-10-20"}]
