[{"Name":"Shawn Dean","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJhQHigN_Vr3WjAUcqhl57kBS0p0tQhzE-gVkEnQCJQIcTIhg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What an amazing experience in Japanese culinary arts. Food was beyond amazing. Chef Keith hit all of the dishes out of the park. You never know what you're going to get. Menu is planned around what the chef brings in fresh. If you love metal music and sushi, this is the place to go.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNrrqB8danMCYFz_ZBHayV76VvZX7BE4kxg25aD&fid=0x0:0x6cd92fe57d09de1d"],"When":"2024-9-29"},{"Name":"Katie Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUD_dZl-28hfOStU-qWCDclCtIPBfQUNB_tuHCA1n-Fw92PgZHz=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a really lovely experience at Sushi K. Every bite was DELICIOUS, which can be attributed to the great care taken to make it. The owners are so welcoming and clearly love what they do. I would recommend this to anyone who loves sushi, getting to know new people and looking for a special way to celebrate an occasion or just really good food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPshYFGcPE-fqFXt9LTEhnXQAhJnS4Fx0ySORYr&fid=0x0:0x6cd92fe57d09de1d"],"When":"2024-6-21"},{"Name":"Cindy Leung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWccKoqBV78_5pqbqSMNUcbwBWv49sw1K_gfi_jhr6uX3Zr1z5afQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Sushi K Kamizato is truly a hidden gem! My husband and I have been there multiple times, and each visit leaves us craving for more of their perfect Japanese food experience. The owner is a true perfectionist, and it shows in every detail of the dishes served. Whether it's the impeccably fresh sushi or sashimi, you can always count on them to exceed your expectations. If you're a Japanese food lover like us, do yourself a favor and give Sushi K Kamizato a try - you won't be disappointed!"","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPn7bGPCsiGsQSRivLL7oDbR-cK9R_quJgHjjfJ&fid=0x0:0x6cd92fe57d09de1d"],"When":"2024-6-9"},{"Name":"Kwon Moonjung (Moon)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXs4Y7GxyFnQ_pFO5KYpsasux5QEeBTgXoMas1g-oYYf5BebxX2=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It was a unique dining experience.

My companion and I were tasting exquisite fishes with explanations from the chef Keith, in a friendly atmosphere that they created.

Every piece of sushi they served had different characters and delicate recipes. It was indeed a voyage to Japanese's beloved cuisine.

I would like to visit again in a different season to taste different on-season fishes.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"jen h","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUhCIsdNpI0zn0ln1R2W8y6FEnO7Rpwo3p2N6L3S94WtNoyzHf7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"How lucky are we to have such amazing talent and kind hospitality in a seemingly unassuming plaza housing an omakase restaurant that refuses to sacrifice quality without having to actually travel to Japan?! An absolute A+ to Chef Keith and Chika for their mastery of perfecting a great omakase experience in the tricities.

They are reservations only (and for a good reason!) and this can be done on their new online portal!! by controlling the number of seatings, Chef K and Chika are able to interact and share their craft with patrons in an intimate and personal way. There is no hustle and bustle or fakeness that would otherwise follow some restaurant vibes. There is purely passion for fish, customer service and, of course, metal music! I urge you to dine at the chefs bar and let Chef K tell you his extensive and wonderful background from catering some A list bands, to being on tour, and changing restaurant models all while being fed an amazing feast.

The fish is sourced from Japan and screams quality and flavour. He knows exactly what he’s doing with all the fish profiles and pairing them with a variety of notes like shiso, yuzu and ginger. Between the 14 unbelievably mouth watering and satisfying dishes, Chef K and Chika’s kindness shared the spotlight easily. Humble beginnings have led to an extraordinary and legendary journey for SKK. Some of the special highlights were the blue fin tuna, South American jumbo prawn, Spanish mackerel and the scallops.

I cannot wait to bring my omakase/metal loving friends and family here to join in on the greatness because sharing truly is caring and this gem is too awesome to keep to myself!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOUQxTRcdVg6w2fRGNA2rgJ11LTUVbZ-4-9zpj2&fid=0x0:0x6cd92fe57d09de1d"],"When":"2024-6-10"},{"Name":"RT Q.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJFlx26VZcmF0Oz0NMLS20j-RG2uk3E1hU454Spnz4JmPX1cA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"🤤: finally leaving a long overdue review for this hidden-gem in the Tri-Cities area. quite affordable omakase options without sacrificing quality. we’ve been here multiple times and it never disappoints. Keith and his wife are very accommodating and super friendly (plus, a cool die-hard rock fan). they have varied budget options for first-time visitors, and you can simply call in and let them know your preferences for subsequent visits.

😰: while it’s quite a fusion experience, the nigiri pieces are on the high-quality side. also note that this is a reservation-only place, so plan ahead.

pictures are from my very first visit during winter last year, so the types of fishes will be slightly different. check out their Facebook page for a rough reference on what will be offered that week, as they import ingredients all the way from Japan. omakase price starts at $90 + tax, which includes 10 pieces of nigiri and small bites with miso soup and tuna karaage in between, as well as complimentary umeshu shot at the end.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMMXLygr4HHcwtJU920fWap8tvNod2VBO23-FQv&fid=0x0:0x6cd92fe57d09de1d"],"When":"2024-4-9"},{"Name":"Rosario","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWgGDUvVq0LHcDsGYS5Ajsq7op3PSBcKer8I_HtMpU1JHJRocg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Used to come here 13 years ago when they first opened up and they just recently switched to omakase couple year ago, went tonight give it a try and it was well worth the experience!!! Most of the fish Is imported from Japan weekly or sourced locally, thank you chef Keith for the wonderful dine in experience, looking forward to coming back","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9TiZiyc4023USo1JpvLtXY0wApF5zOoozA-be&fid=0x0:0x6cd92fe57d09de1d"],"When":"2024-5-30"},{"Name":"Sequoia Wiseman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW2XQ92mpE01iZeW7C84Skx_Q0OWX8I2ZLE7hEkPUQ2gnHSduJfeg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Sushi Kamizato is a gem in the realm of Japanese cuisine, helmed by the masterful Executive Chef Keith Kamizato. From the moment we stepped in, we were enveloped in an atmosphere of creativity and rock-and-roll energy. Chef Kamizato's Chef's Choice menu was an enlightening journey through the world of sushi, with each dish meticulously prepared and explained with passion and expertise. The freshness of the fish was unparalleled, a testament to Chef Kamizato's commitment to sourcing only the finest ingredients from the market. Watching him work his magic in the kitchen was a spectacle in itself, adding an extra layer of appreciation to the dining experience. If you're looking for an inventive sushi experience that transcends the ordinary, Sushi Kamizato is a must-visit destination.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3za3LG2IMqsFlI8Of5sj_pjDMjGmUxt1a9wOw&fid=0x0:0x6cd92fe57d09de1d"],"When":"2024-4-22"}]

Free parking lot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPZOep9PY3X_UZZI0gHiWKfkD3_Rwg7S6IlxOXy&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2024-12-2"},{"Name":"shotavi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXNMh1hfEFIJYaCTSLthIdHQ3TANUnSyqWujpD58h8MinLMJyw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was looking for a casual place to grab a drink and found this spot on Google Maps.

The atmosphere was really nice and relaxing, and I thought it would be great to come here on a sunny day.

This time, I only ordered a drink without food, but next time I want to come back for some food and beer.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN8MebbW-WnQTRvvxKA_I0ZvOyBNH4FxfomcuPu&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2024-9-18"},{"Name":"jasonbenj","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXesObwVr-MYoNivn747YIQhYO4b8Vn-9xP5t36MuM6wxR0MRI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"First time back since the renovation. Sadly, it looks like a lot of re-branding of the same old product is 90% of it. Also, they took all the good items off the menu. RIP beer cheese dip, you will be missed. Sorry to say but it's not for me anymore. Also, $13 25 flight before tax !","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOql9qRevUlia8U9C-dRW3PT6r5a5AmKlZ5qwHk&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2024-8-2"},{"Name":"Marisa Lenarduzzi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIbCzpGYeIKBI2SunoaFci_IoZvVVnbxBDnsfb3PLewJQAy3A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great beers and great food for a brewery as well. We got the fries with mango chipotle and it was delicious! There’s also a great atmosphere inside - not too loud, good lighting and very clean. Would go again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7VsLepap0KHEDl1zc5eEsDCQ9ndL4l7M2shto&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2024-10-12"},{"Name":"Christina Faminoff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX12CPz5calL7TtQ0KnMyeMWTusgq3nB56xjWsl60LKS9agnIFQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Just had the burger of the month, the Fall Forage smash with the falafel patty, and a stout. Both were awesome. Falafel was super fresh and tasty. I've tried most of their beers, and kombucha, and I appreciate that they are all really different, and don't all just taste like hops. Love that they added a food menu! Nice to be able to get good hot food instead of just snacks, like a lot of breweries. This is one of my favourite places. Would recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNi9KQYgc3UAPTrvyVhcEulEHKDPEevANrCc4rQ&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Came to this brewery with a meetup group and it was an on experience. There were limited non-alcoholic drinks on the menu, but they had four different craft sodas. I tried the cherry cola craft soda, the taste was interesting, but it wasn’t great, a bit flat. I also tried the pretzel and they were very generous with the mustard, but it was overall still very bland and got too cold too quickly. It’s a nice space to hang out and it can get busy even on weekday evenings.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM5hAZODlvyOhf9B5lJi8jBxhRFGkFm5uo_rePD&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2023-12-21"},{"Name":"Lauren St John","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWi3pWsd_jh8y8V1Pl7XbMiNRgCVHq-YYCdAOx_KkkOFRnXREk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Pass on this one. Unless you're a beer and ale aficionado, keep going. Sorely disappointed in the food. We heard it had improved with new owners but it's obvious that more changes are needed. They charge $17 (plus tax and tip) for 8 chicken wings. That's outrageous. We tried the Jamaican patties and they were ok. The venue is cozy with more outside seating than inside. The service is "meh." The beer was average. There's not a lot for non-alcoholic beverages. The whole experience left us nonplussed. We will not go back or recommend it.  We spent $65 for 2 beers, 8 wings, a can of ginger ale and 2 Jamaican patties. And the pressure to tip 20% even though there's no table service, left us perplexed!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM_Ekb1Paet7mkMRPuwFGpkIuDRB9sqyDH14sUc&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2023-9-8"},{"Name":"E. C Arteaga G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWxwN6PAknbpzp4-FRd4QkWYRhq1QUPT2iG2_oEOzRgEc5F0GVH1w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I was waiting for the perfect opportunity to go try this local brewery and today was the day. We were greeted by our server who was kind and knowledgeable about their beers.  They recommended the Blonde Ale ( Low Gravity Mango) super delicious. But, the food was not what we expected. The fries tasted bland and raw. It tasted like everything was made in an air fryer. The sliders we had were bland and the buns were not toasted. The chicken wings were a hit and miss. Some where nice and fell off the bone and others where hard as a rock. I would definitely try this place again because the beer is their saving grace but I will double think about ordering food again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPN8xjotriAojNGVe5wIIRD29aZaMWIHah5pNDd&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2022-3-30"}]

[{"Name":"Jessameen Dela Peña","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9mRpmL8-ZJUG7UPFcnsjzRdxjABif-MswbO1rxgJyyWfns8Jd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We stopped by 10 minutes before closing, and the staff were incredibly patient and friendly. The House Special had the best broth we have ever tasted, and we never felt rushed despite the late hour. The deep-fried prawns were a delightful addition. The service was outstanding, and the food was so impressive that we returned the very next day. Highly recommended!

UPDATE: We come here twice a month because the food is consistently amazing. The grilled lemongrass pork and chicken have become my new favorites! The owner is incredibly friendly—he always comes by to chat and makes us feel so welcomed. It’s always a great experience!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQKaYfXtWa6v3S8QcyIf-zS2kd1LXEoRfku6oM&fid=0x0:0x84f116fdb154fa91"],"When":"2024-6-9"},{"Name":"Al","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJke_H51lEVtqmQ6Mwhj0R5MqDW7L2xLlIdf0sg4kPFJFF0D9I=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very great food and fresh. The taste was fantastic, and the ingredients were very fresh. You could definitely feel it. Lemon grass chicken was very nice. Service was fast and free parking available.
Place is welcoming and cozy. Price is also affordable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN3EYKVgym_LytOru_9Q0HJh_cQ1QYkmWreO6I4&fid=0x0:0x84f116fdb154fa91"],"When":"2023-11-27"},{"Name":"Edward T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKTItxd4pRAbeGH3PFae1hHHFC3x54f8Em9wKt7VSR6VzWHkQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food is always hitting at this place. 11/10","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPFVA1fayiAxuh1-hkXHnveoU6MVPxaxOHTX3Eb&fid=0x0:0x84f116fdb154fa91"],"When":"2024-11-29"},{"Name":"Joey Yi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXkOn5qmb4YICrtfcwBYOeIF_14yfauICTcRo3rF7abiiQVHvM8-Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place the best Pho restaurant I ve ever been. Owner was really kind and I ate No.11 basic that was awesome.
I was really satisfied soup and food potion.
Definitely recommend this place if you like any kind soup. Two thumbs up","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPb8PvX-2uclDG-XiS60toCBcR3wVYN47gWXwT8&fid=0x0:0x84f116fdb154fa91"],"When":"2023-2-8"},{"Name":"Angela S.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWWq991K5Cn-pfNd9_p_ADAKLGzaUMKQ_C7pVf7isnMpa7MRSeINQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I was hoping to like this restaurant, but unfortunately, the value just isn't there. Do not bother getting the small Pho noodle bowl, it is half the size of a typical small bowl sized portion at any other Pho restaurants. $14 for the tiniest bowl of noodle soup is very disappointing. The noodles had a bit of a plastic old/stale taste to them. I'd say that the Pho is below average, and I can't really give my personal recommendation, but it may be okay for others 🤷‍♀️.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNfoFhNwveSXiakuej-k-EACL5cRZBmIDgPOb_0&fid=0x0:0x84f116fdb154fa91"],"When":"2023-6-4"},{"Name":"Alvin Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUpasldH6X4K8TtkMbIbac-orAN0Eb0jJ-m74oWvWE0xRNC-us=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is a rare gem near the Coquitlam Center, a small but traditional Vietnamese restaurant. Foods are tasty in particular to the house special noodle, pawn salad rolls and grilled chicken and pork rice which are my favorites. Servers are friendly and prices are reasonable too! Patronize as regular customer now😋","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOI23WHEZ1UvyPXbaEapVTN0WEanbkmow2h7wUA&fid=0x0:0x84f116fdb154fa91"],"When":"2021-10-9"},{"Name":"Madison G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVtZsEld-Yz5a2Swm5LesjF83lo03ZXPGgujeQvQiLn6WLaIuGx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of my favourite Pho places. My favourite thing to order is number 31A minced pork, rice and spring roll! It’s always so delicious, always very fresh and everyone is always so kind!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNgjWGTZqX83J-2_ZNQuefKVY6STOD6vJF4N2Yd&fid=0x0:0x84f116fdb154fa91"],"When":"2023-8-29"},{"Name":"Sean Beauchamp","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJiPW0ZmE07r4EhYtr1hlBLWv9eAOAlZGJb33SCXvTfbtA-HQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great place,  my personal favorite.  I drive from langley just to come here.

The owner and his wife are very nice people,  and their employees are always pleasant.
Food is 10/10","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Jodine Morehouse","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWkI3ILmstAY-XeAWqv2CETEpjWiJVODW602jRpnYogrvfslqk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I can’t wait to come back here again! Such fantastic food and a fun environment. The fried chicken was top notch and the waffles were some of the best we’ve ever had. The breakfast truly felt homemade and with care. The kids breakfast was a great size and my kiddo was very happy. Service was okay; you can tell the servers are very busy maintaining a constant flow of customers. It was efficient and we didn’t have to wait overly long for our food. We did have to wait 20 mins to get a table initially, but we wrote our name and number down and were called when our table is ready. There is plenty of free parking around. This has the be the best breakfast I’ve had in the tri cities.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMKJgj8sWDLDS9qegVktaFJLY6wHAIH52u_I1Iw&fid=0x0:0xa167a404bce0a118"],"When":"2024-8-27"},{"Name":"Christina","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVAZU__kcA5bzRg06Xj5DBBJ8cZ62N3LvOHAgj11jS16XxVPZvg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a good brunch. Can’t say anything bad about it. Not to pricey and the serving is neither big or small. Customer service is superb. We’ll definitely go back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPvn0YrbOK9PQexBbmH0uzrLD7g4XyCGtU_9RmR&fid=0x0:0xa167a404bce0a118"],"When":"2024-10-3"},{"Name":"Maria Fernanda Mejia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIuRq66bP7uwZvuWOAzrXMaIaP65fNk1AbmES51ho5i654OFOA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is the best place Ive had brunch in Vancouver. Food was delicious, the place was so cozy and had the perfect temperature. I went with my sister and we share the Benny Eggs with cubed potatoes fries and pan cakes and hot chocolate. Everything was so tasty and well done, the eggs were pefectly done and the pancakes werw so fluffy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMOrT4XQKDGK2dJViD6VsKyNO0Zqf0UnFIb9_9w&fid=0x0:0xa167a404bce0a118"],"When":"2024-10-19"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Korean western breakfast and brunch joint located in downtown Port Coquitlam. Lots of exciting dishes to try with Bulgogi dishes being the most exciting (Bulgogi Benny, Bulgogi pasta, Bulgogi sandwich, etc.). Service was a bit slow as the restaurant was busy. We had to wait around 10 minutes after we put our name and number down to get called. Food was good and presentation was impecable, but the taste was not particularly memorable. The door of the restaurant was open so it attracted a lot of flies from the outside which wasn’t ideal and really made the entire experience not super great.

Interior decor is very interesting with a lot of Lego input.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP4awtX1JY8GFBJy9bWY0sS6Pd9fHU7-n1sKPpK&fid=0x0:0xa167a404bce0a118"],"When":"2024-9-10"},{"Name":"Daniel Jung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFE7g6vnjf23CW6mDeh4anchF8fxBs6O5Nsx0bvhepuO3MVzWa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great brunch spot in the center of Shaugnessy. Came in Sunday around noonish, luckily no lineup. Food took a little bit but was definitely worth it as it tasted great!
Seems like service is team based? It was a little confusing who was taking care of our table. Overall great experience","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPGRk5-xoM7MNas2Lf8X9-8tL5TPa1NyfeG2t5K&fid=0x0:0xa167a404bce0a118"],"When":"2024-7-8"},{"Name":"Helena","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLiYVJyd2ntFwLRumbYS9Kznuj6jXHoPn0UkQ_zdJDM29rWiQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It’s easy to find the small and clean restaurant on main street in Port Coquitlam downtown. We ordered a Bulgogi Benny and a Corned Beef Skillet. The portion size is quite large. I love the soft and fresh eggs that danced in my plate. The pan fried potatoes were crispy on the outside and tender on the inside.  Overall, their food is so delicious and service is great as well. The only downside is that the food is too salty.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOodTPBFYt_-JZobr-pvtMCbt6_xvN_fc6G6khW&fid=0x0:0xa167a404bce0a118"],"When":"2024-6-20"},{"Name":"JESSICA","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVB2i5CpRP7UX8-wv47l2MrFmMz2VuMLPi87EdWVFtliHFbqvwR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Cute spot, warm and cozy. Reasonably priced and tasty. Benny’s made on sweet English muffins/crumpets versus traditional. Potatoes very tasty.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNpj7mBBwvQ0YWcrdYBHVE_81woZdvdFQHDUKKA&fid=0x0:0xa167a404bce0a118"],"When":"2024-12-19"},{"Name":"Mike Liu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL20X_OxbcK6Mq4LfB8wD0MzYN5bZWaRAXw5XJobEo4cGthsw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love how everything is flavored really well and that the Korean fusion element is delicious. I got a simple 2 eggs with sausage and hashbrowns. Everything was done really well. Note that the hasbrowns do have a layer of onions as a filling. The cubed potato’s were delicious.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOzoRfYSvHs4qQ-gqmZ89EYwZ0drtW3HbqfgRVO&fid=0x0:0xa167a404bce0a118"],"When":"2024-7-11"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Joseph","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUXbztcvJy0AIdqJzTOyFSntteOTg-h_qvbqjBrQ7R6H-ALXJr1JA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Of the Uyghur restaurants in Greater Vancouver still in business, this might be the best in terms of food quality and flavors. But there's a big caveat:

Be prepared to wait for a long time! With only one person in front of me, I still waited at least 20 min just to get my order taken and maybe another 20 min to get food. Some people who got in line shortly after me, didn't get to put in their order until sometime after I got my food. Meaning they probably waited 40 min just to order and who knows how long to eat.

This is because there's only one person (owner/operator?) working, who seems to come out to the front to take one or two orders, before disappearing into the kitchen for extended periods of time, hand pulling noodles and ensuring the food is as fresh as can be.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM6WA01U2fkQwvPSsJsMBVWnmcpb8dG78rjzNao&fid=0x0:0x72ec986ae7ae7106"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"Ryan Blight","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbpH73lI2xtK9WJxadw5s8Ist4ItI3NEBYZImc9aopB1Hhs9lf=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"First time here and ordered the lamb shank with naan (menu #5). The lamb was tasty, but small portion. The bread portion was large, but quite hard texture. Fun to try, but wouldn't go out of my way to return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNd7s8qRWgN_NekyShJi_banfr0VF74TJeXzT8X&fid=0x0:0x72ec986ae7ae7106"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Stephen Jackson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWSabsYlgcq7pedZrrlJQtd6yY9XJwQ1Hy3QeRvPyBgE78_whI1Zw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great food that's worth the wait and the setting.

It's set in a food court, so it's not like you're in the greatest of surroundings.  However, the food is more than worth it.  Went for the polo (lamb shank with rice) and a samsa (meat-filled pastry).  The samsa was delicious, and I would happily come again to buy 5 and take them away.  The portion of the polo was huge, the lamb tender, and the rice very flavourful, especially with the spicy cucumber salad mixed in, which added a bit of heat.

Don't come expecting fast food (its setting in a food court is a bit deceptive in this sense).  It does take a little while to get it (probably 15 mins for me, and I came at a quiet time of day).  But, I would much rather wait the time to get good quality food, than get instant food which was reheated / prepared poorly etc.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPI-TbiA148s9Ddb0GyN_XZykDzr3fyxfn9zt4C&fid=0x0:0x72ec986ae7ae7106"],"When":"2024-7-22"},{"Name":"judy wang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJT81G3KLQSjfqtTMAT9IHU_NfAgkAmzPpPLN2CsXTwBRAeBw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a crave for 手抓饭。did some googling and decided to try here which was the best decision of the day. We went a little before lunch time so the wait was not bad at all. 手抓饭 was just fantastic. My husband ordered the soup, bread and lamb leg and it was just beyond the word. We ended up taking extra five bread home to share with friends and families. The owner is doing everything by himself including taking orders, prep of the food and serving it over the counter. So I understand it will take some time if it’s really busy. But definable worth the wait and drive!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNxtxEQF3e3yIGulzImQI98imE328VDkMGYQXUN&fid=0x0:0x72ec986ae7ae7106"],"When":"2023-9-10"},{"Name":"Kevin Luo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWJMxLZr-3YvPOYEYkCwOqoRgX8yyWGLPYZ19IJEKzgIUssXc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Amazing food. Poor experience. The entire operation is done by a single person, who appears to be cooking and on phone the entire time. He seems withdrawn and uninterested in taking orders from anyone. The wait for food is VERY long, almost 30 minutes for a bowl of lamb shank and nan. The lamb shank is super tender and the soup is very flavourful with a hint of spiciness. There could be more meat though. The nan is excellent, especially dipped into the soup. Unfortunately, I can't recommend this place due to the slow service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7TTuDTiSRVzXDv4-dn6uwcTqK7XQnEca6pi5M&fid=0x0:0x72ec986ae7ae7106"],"When":"2024-3-29"},{"Name":"Linda Vu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4Mt-fIM1ZKQuO_Y2ib9yo6xFV3B1mBRBjrbB_M80tp5QNaP0e=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Tried the lamb shank with naan! The soup that comes with it tastes fresh and super hot! Lamb shank is juicy and soft.

The naan was crazy good, it was crispy on the outside and soft inside. Great for dipping with the soup, I wish there was more lamb sauce that came with it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPjybpAz_um9IGqMZH_euQN_2H-1m6cyYW-lZaK&fid=0x0:0x72ec986ae7ae7106"],"When":"2024-1-31"},{"Name":"Murat Arsin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKc6H-T457-oBccqNDru1kc6Jimk0kU403UqpJeWtj4Hgnawg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is real boutique place just for Uyghur cusine, as the owner does everything byhimself, it brings the real taste of Uyghur cusine.
Samsa and Somen is highly recommended.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN9tlahV-8SfTuzYMCibIrLR5vqlxFyRIHuurgZ&fid=0x0:0x72ec986ae7ae7106"],"When":"2024-9-23"},{"Name":"rayyan mansoor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIb6H6Bi4fHrAdb51oLLHmTed679NLLQywCKJ4cPUmMnfR5tA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food is amazing, quality of ingredients as well as just the combination of flavors is awesome and to get anything similar you would have to travel hours.

Anyone complaining about how long it takes should order in advance rather than post invalid reviews, food like this HAS TO TAKE TIME which is why it tastes how good it is, if you can’t wait this long for something out of this world go get fast food.

City is blessed to have such a talented chef willing to share his food.","Images":null,"When":""}]

This place is worth a try!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOOcbsrqo5_g7Li7S7fNKi-xxGk7GkDVD5cM70c&fid=0x0:0x7a37b4d1ff44013a"],"When":"2024-6-29"},{"Name":"jason wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLAr7OPM3u3i7bBkh0r7Q9kS7_8Gu_88Crv223BgydShD66TQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food was ok.. nothing spectacular choose your own meats, veggies abd sauce.. then they put it on the grill and serve it to you with rice","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPA_bj3buHTlpP6KebnHagLO6Ttkh0Ccw-oU61&fid=0x0:0x7a37b4d1ff44013a"],"When":"2024-8-24"},{"Name":"meebo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKZSlLVVD44BlsiEyjhIgD96ZFt0sITGGk4P83OheeAsE3v_3t2=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Ordered through TGTG App to give it a try.
"Great amount of Varieties" XD
A box of fried noodles + plain rice. Oh and i found 2 pieces of meat! LOL","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNTwVYfyQ68m2WXrHsMhZqE-nOS3g0R3c1rLYla&fid=0x0:0x7a37b4d1ff44013a"],"When":"2024-11-11"},{"Name":"Joanne Antoniak","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWTQwhPcO13h_HhVjJVUrwpHjU5MeesKhPrxV5pA1ymdZ1edFkY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Whether it's one bow or all you can eat - this place is amazing.  Fresh ingredients of your choosing - cooked hot in minutes.
Yes it's a little hole in the wall spot ... Decor is meh - but the food is fabulous!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPztp6Zb7B5ZDZDsqo1DS5z8ppNqk-bigqmUC4r&fid=0x0:0x7a37b4d1ff44013a"],"When":"2023-7-15"},{"Name":"Christian Moore","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUVKJ2xG_FIWRFRcDt3VDcD5fpVOT8hPtZ7dimA0A4oc2jlaauY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I don’t have enough good things to say about this place! Awesome and friendly staff, amazing food, great price, and a very home-like atmosphere that makes it a pleasure to eat at. My family and I, as well as my girlfriend and her family come here all the time! 100% recommend!!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Stewart Wright","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVtb_g017F0hKWx4HSHiy2lA9uaFQVSv1vtnSw45Kp3rp_TDvFG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We’ve been going here for over 10 years now every couple months - food is fresh and delicious and service always with a smile. Is it fancy, no, is it delicious and great value, absolutely
Pick your meat and veggies and sauces and they grill it in front of you - my family loves this place and we’re always stuffed afterwards.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Susan Mcrae","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK1cxG9a8HH5Bbts1Y9oNrXAbSMcAg9DQJ3MNJhK91Dys0GLw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"**Absolutely Horrendous Experience – Don’t Waste Your Time!**

I cannot stress enough how utterly terrible Sun Mongolian BBQ is. From the moment you step inside, the service is an absolute disaster. The staff couldn't care less about your experience and seem to take their sweet time with everything. Want a simple question answered? Be prepared to wait ages for a response, and when they finally do get back to you, it's with a dismissive attitude, as if you're bothering them by just being there.

And don’t even get me started on the portions. They are **pathetically inadequate**. You pay a decent price expecting a filling meal, but what you get is a sad, skimpy plate of food that wouldn’t satisfy a toddler. I have no idea how they justify the cost when you’re left still hungry after what should be a satisfying meal.

As if the service and food weren't bad enough, the **clientele is downright trashy**. I’ve never seen such an unrefined crowd in one place. It's like the people who frequent this restaurant have no concept of basic manners or hygiene. The atmosphere feels more like a rowdy dive bar than a place you’d actually want to enjoy a meal.

Overall, Sun Mongolian BBQ is a **complete and total failure** in every aspect—service, food, atmosphere. Save your money and go literally anywhere else. You’ll thank yourself for avoiding this trainwreck of an establishment.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"M Copan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ6IuP11xvJLV_LAcICSOpVAPA2i0lEKHSWUzxGQU3jADCAhg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As someone with food requirement they are attentive and I will continue to come back. Fresh selection of stir fry options. The new owners take the time to prepare everything properly for evening cooking with flavorful sauces. Highly recommend.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Regan Moses","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJWXdmgQOO18drHuZg6oyNK4Pgy4vcsyrzVJVjMl2RQ2P_Akg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very cool brewery! I love the mix of industrial and restaurant vibe. The layout is spacious and there is ample outdoor seating. The food is great! They have a mix of well thought out appez and beer pairing meals. Fav is the wings. The wings are not your traditional wing cut but the whole wing…..Fantastic idea. Most of all they have really good beer. My personal fav is the dark lager. Best thing is, their prices are affordable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPLTuLWnp03j8iDvumuKX5GW_YSx1iAs3YtCppW&fid=0x0:0x168a87ed0c636aaa"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Stuart Xue","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIMJR3m2m3b3A-TFm1gu2Ve7-gZIHc-nb8uoyhBCkgGuF6K=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went for a cool beer after a long hike in a hot day.
Many crafted beers available and the bbq is delicious.
The fries are amazing and it was what fries supposed to be.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOuRTrUalVK76tHhL1gIuolhrviOLplI5oVcJo&fid=0x0:0x168a87ed0c636aaa"],"When":"2024-7-21"},{"Name":"Mary Zhang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU7q3nMNLVt98vdR0lNO5wN9938S_sm6IFSYH1BhPUuDPS0jAvY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The atmosphere, beer, food and service are all 5 stars! Highly recommend the pull pork slider and the two big chicken tigh with 🧇.  Will come back again","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOWJeWXq2cXqVGDIluyRhQeUc3JmnKPXBYXT7RJ&fid=0x0:0x168a87ed0c636aaa"],"When":"2024-6-18"},{"Name":"Brittney Cerritos Kroiss","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUzs74OWdsTEXPNevXDKt4yjRt1tvG8kz7_IZQS_xePF-HLCrj-gA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Decent place but their beer variety has decreased (no soups, no porters, no stout, out of black lager), their dishes have definitely been skrinkfated (chicken and waffles in particular got a lot smaller), and food orders were forgotten. All that said, staff are generally nice, atmosphere is good, and flavourful is decent in most dishes.

They used to be our go to but I think we're going to start considering other options before we come here again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Y. Cherski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK-7SLlKKRW0Rqcp9wRXFlvt6gbh0rtI7PMIroLgxETtGiPwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Before visiting the tasting room, I tried Patina brews in several places. Also, I admire their involvement in the community's life during and after the pandemic, which made the visit so much more special.
The atmosphere is excellent, and the staff is very friendly and helpful. Decent list of beers on tap, including guest collaborations. As I mentioned, I have already tried quite a few of their creations, so there are no surprises – great sought-after product. I regret that we stopped by right after lunch and weren't hungry because some items on the food menu sounded delicious. Well, which adds yet another reason to visit again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO_WkjnxOH4fgfaSRnbA9YornXP5fJcyB7Yk1vn&fid=0x0:0x168a87ed0c636aaa"],"When":"2022-10-21"},{"Name":"Madison G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVtZsEld-Yz5a2Swm5LesjF83lo03ZXPGgujeQvQiLn6WLaIuGx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Super yummy food ! And Lovely atmosphere ! Our server Lily was so fantastic ! She is so welcoming and answered any questions we had. She really made our experience even more better ! They have a pretty big patio , lots of seating ! And a pretty big menu for a brewery ! The meat was very yummy and their fries I would highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMMjkzPkAeubsOD5YfIcjFhLNwLPVqb3wegs64o&fid=0x0:0x168a87ed0c636aaa"],"When":"2023-8-22"},{"Name":"Rick K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV9V4XBFE6pAfU8Athi1_dl9y4vHzN7sHcxVlSWoT-0MyuFcvYE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I'm extremely conflicted with this place. Does it deserve more stars or less stars. Let's start with some positives. Beer is good, unique, and flavorful. Food, flavors are good, sauces are good. However heading to the bad stuff. Quality of ingredients seem low, we are vegetarian/vegan but our table ate a lot of meat and the quality of cuts was very low, the brussel sprouts were tasty but low quality sprouts for sure. Just ingredients seem on the lower end. Also this comment is from my gf (give vegans a carb and they will drink more). The jackfruit vegan dish was literally nothing else but a plate of jackfruit which is pretty close to no calories (don't order this, waste of money). A bun jackfruit sandwich would suffice way better. Service was ok not great. The tofu bites were incredible through and through. Oh dishes are very small don't come hungry. This is a place I'd go to again but I do feel extremely conflicted, it's far from my usual spot visit list and it could be better without much effort, which is also the disappointing part.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPCaj79_IYPrEBLyOLi8PeoirH-nw2qSKi0yPgX&fid=0x0:0x168a87ed0c636aaa"],"When":"2024-4-7"},{"Name":"T U","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0fqYSgi-Oa1ZxHKMAgkTIjdzOCoN9dbq8TIyQm2_XMOry1AQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We stopped in for a quick beer before the Provincial ball hockey tournament - it was fairly busy. Great atmosphere. Next time we are here we will order food as well (looked delicious!). I ordered the Thai Lager.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPj1X_gMZWKh37ZEPBFykTw262WQeea9CbccyPO&fid=0x0:0x168a87ed0c636aaa"],"When":"2024-7-1"}]

[{"Name":"Preethi Nair","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUz8cCAzlnay_PFhvv7Ji00tvlRLoqJA-MhaglfwwGMG6P16JkGug=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice place to hangout. Tried sopes and nachos. Food is tasty and service is quick.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPyJ7EhJfGVDa8ttfSssK_OboVJcjDcZn5LhFh_&fid=0x0:0xcf57a6141d680aaf"],"When":"2024-7-18"},{"Name":"Elena Malkova","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW602f3KiOlmq-3RVv1uCfJgeL2LrWPFJevDjC7s8eC3p665BY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good food, worth to visit. Nacho chips are not house made (packaged). Tacos are really good, a bit dry for me, I like sauce and lime juice on top. As you can see they put only small piece of lime... I like using more with my Mexican food. Also, not enough cilantro taste, again that’s my own preference.
Overall, decent place and nice service, I won’t be back as it’s a bit overpriced and I like more “Californian style” if you know what I mean.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOh3aep59fmlAqp_qkRsELKUJHtgxPnQki7mNeV&fid=0x0:0xcf57a6141d680aaf"],"When":"2020-9-20"},{"Name":"Scott Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHpW7vGME__Zs4wKjXR04Upnw88bkVVyz-H2288JsHocq9vI3r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is a true gem in poco. The food was authentic, and you can tell that it was made by someone who grew up eating the food.

The price was affordable and the service was also quite fast and pleasant. They don’t skimp on portions so one of their burritos should definitely fill you up!

It’s a shame that I couldn’t try their churros but we’ll be back, for sure!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNEjdJ4DF6V0d94iPwCKMeZ2byggZrEQ9pIuqP8&fid=0x0:0xcf57a6141d680aaf"],"When":"2022-2-8"},{"Name":"Susan Rochefort","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL8rVH08cPR6VwUL0HKwjObsOf9gnrVDYn2ehalr65L6-oUpQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was excellent! Fresh made guacamole was amazing. The service was excellent, they accommodated my food sensitivities by ensuring my dish had no spice and no sauces (pork enchiladas). Kind, friendly owners made this a great first visit. We will go back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN0H6u5_AFImO0MYLkLrZG2Vh3F0ABe1ApUWJAH&fid=0x0:0xcf57a6141d680aaf"],"When":"2020-1-3"},{"Name":"Gaurav Khatiwada","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV9esAjLiSzHtBZDV1WCFSvOOCrQ_8ILCJRLORIM1mavbOWu4m3cw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I went there for a quick bite of tacos, I ordered pork belly and chicken tacos with a drink. In a sunny clean weather day you can see mountains in the background in outdoor setting which is a plus. Tacos was great will definitely visit again for more.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOr0f0GhzDrmsUyDbAX3u_DER_njdU2rBZRPgA8&fid=0x0:0xcf57a6141d680aaf"],"When":"2023-4-30"},{"Name":"lea “Lea” howard","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLDu1L_oe7CRcF_qC9V9eWIA_rxaPr1ucAjvHDbhI_ieW2Nkw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Stopped in for a quick bite as we’ve passed by here many times! The place was very clean and welcoming!
We had the shrimp tacos which were delicious and highly recommend! Also had the carnitas tacos which were nice and flavorful and the beef steak tacos which were on the bland side.
Will definitely go back and try some of their main dishes!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNqMAn_weO1d-KnVy0TA8k6q5_8-MmQsyjoTb01&fid=0x0:0xcf57a6141d680aaf"],"When":"2018-4-22"},{"Name":"Jessica M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUHIbOqSbUDgNLlVo2Voj47_sYplTKVpv7ouP7-ReW4GfxYKW6m9w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our favourite Mexican restaurant in poco. Huge portions, affordable prices, and amazing customer service. We came twice last week and can't wait to go back for more! Shrimp taco is a must try","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"E Ip","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVgameZA5Ck3eQuBRGlA8OrqLqldpLX6AMEUMpI-oBZR5E0CU_v=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My favorite was the churos! It was freshly made and the dipping sauce has perfect sweetness. We also tried the poco-burrito, tostada, and tacos. The staff checked on us a few times, very polite and friendly.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMbLNcn1Nt_2n2s5TqxtRfKKInG9quZFd9kfzIx&fid=0x0:0xcf57a6141d680aaf"],"When":"2022-1-24"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"If you try this place out, you have to order the fried chicken wings that are garlic flavoured and crispy on the outside and juicy on the inside. Love the booth seating too. Another highlight is the trio dessert with warm creamy kidney and white beans and green pandan jelly that is mildly sweet and warm on the bottom topped with ice and condensed milk and syrup. The textures, temperature difference, and flavours go together so well in the trio dessert and it was very enjoyable and beautiful to look at in a good sized mug portion. The spring rolls were solid too. The pho dac biet and beef carpaccio were just average. Their sauces are nice and fragrant with lemon grass hot sauce. A good dinner. Would go back for the chicken wings and trio dessert.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMeSPoBD5ayxZ1dsT5JC4iC7lB5DjLNkYVkoEAU&fid=0x0:0x8b84110915097c24"],"When":"2024-12-7"},{"Name":"Adam O'Hara","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWilWKfj4mARbNOIUfPpMaX6ohQ3UW0xGMG7MTlXisTmO2eNVjR=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We order takeout from Mr Pho all the time. The food is excellent and fresh, and it is very consistent. Springs rolls are unbelievable, and the salad rolls are so good too. We enjoy the lemongrass chicken vermicelli and grilled pork vermicelli dishes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOSYqyxiJnWogm_AZoK3WzQJJxKn_ncDVYKHKpD&fid=0x0:0x8b84110915097c24"],"When":"2024-7-19"},{"Name":"Kate Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjE4MSAa0c4Uqc8iOt1LfqIkJDL1ULa2Z17gRh4YDWMExQ1A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"There is a lack of good pho places in PoCo. This place was surprisingly good and for a realistic price. Pho can be from 16-22 nowadays and this place is priced on the low end. The beef broth was extremely well made - super beefy and lots of spice. I would rate the broth one of the top ones in Greater Vancouver. Their vermicelli was ok. Nothing especially delicious about it. I wish they offered lemon grass meat for their vermicelli. Their service is good and they ask you if you want the bean sprouts cooked or not. Lots of places kinda give you the face if you ask for that.

There are limited parking spots here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO-EohuPShCGZKVIfAMpXKwPBFyny9oPbtfr5Q3&fid=0x0:0x8b84110915097c24"],"When":"2024-11-8"},{"Name":"Mei Louis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJgXRRaGeGHZwDQ3Cd4BP54rgwmhE9FWdhKccUqwHk97sb73g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Cozy atmosphere, friendly staffs and delicious food add to a great dining experience. The grilled pork and spring roll vermicelli bowl and spicy Hue beef noodle are flavourful.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOA5n6LNYMV3gxDQoO0WY6CAj1oKNtFbf3nrI_p&fid=0x0:0x8b84110915097c24"],"When":"2024-4-20"},{"Name":"Jack Antos","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI1TGVjeR1aosKpbwp6STozjVfeCGVhxvIWQhreLHIAbO1a8w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing food and customer service. Had food to table during a full house 10 min after ordering. Highly recommend","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPemNh5al-HfCq2g9_8cTqi1M4BBhzQYUmEUoZ_&fid=0x0:0x8b84110915097c24"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"Avis Woo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXh4Pb-SJt2DTMUggN2-tIRxEo8pAErRU5SI_TxM4gC-gvdVBym=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It was our 26th wedding anniversary last night and we wanna celebrate with Vietnamese food! Really follow the 4.6 rating and choose this Mr.Pho and everything was so satisfactory with awesome great taste! 👍🫰🏻😍Even the house tea tasted great! The bill was surprisingly value for money too❤️We definitely will come again and again from time to time! 👍","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Christopher Tan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVTcJAGWdmNZh_350tGgyDVrHJVGD3SOIaxlTnaARTAJEKc5gtr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"You have to try the chicken wings, especially if you like garlic. The wings were incredibly crispy, yet plump and tender on the inside.

The green mango salad was also great, with well-balanced flavours.

We also got the pho, which was good, and had a lot of meat, but we thought that the broth could be a bit stronger (with respect to the spices and herbs).

It's a great addition to the neighbourhood! The chicken wings themselves are good enough to come back for.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOdFqNaI3QMljyDkB5FkwZwpDvFJy124fGvgLXn&fid=0x0:0x8b84110915097c24"],"When":"2022-11-21"},{"Name":"Elysa Jones","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVAo75J_Rtfi9O06eVuLzCtXlTBuV0m9jYy9iywg0OytgDFLbGDzw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Got takeout from here a couple times and was always impressed (not to mention the food travels well).

Today I got the opportunity to go in and fell in love with the place even more. Cute decor with lush live plants all around.

Service was super attentive and food was served quickly.

These are hands down some of the best wings we’ve ever had! The beef carpaccio was perfectly balanced and full of flavour, and both definitely be something we come back for.

Beef ball pho and pork sausage rice plate were both super tasty, and very generous. we definitely left very full and will be back for more - Hands down best Vietnamese in Poco!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPMM7IQOr1JcxG17zGJMTDeRZHIpILQA3LFdp3W&fid=0x0:0x8b84110915097c24"],"When":"2022-12-19"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Faith Oh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIRU1l7lR0St2FKA3sFQRqByUMO0kTpIy7V5hHpzuF2subJjzXD=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious sushi restaurant in poco!! Their complimentary barley green tea was so tasty and it washed down well after each bite so smoothly… The Japanese Pumpkin Korokke appetizer was so mouth watering it was almost the best thing we got here. Must get! We ordered assorted aburi sushi combo, very high quality with good prices (in the photos it shows 8 pieces because we ordered extra! Originally it comes with 7 generous pieces). Hawaiian roll with the deep fried garlic and ponzu sauce was just the perfect roll, also a must get. Godzilla roll was very much like the roll’s name and was so delicious! Such a bang for your buck. All the staff here were so polite and provided sensible service. Prices were so reasonable for the quality and quantity given, which is always great. Definitely will become a regular here and if you haven’t checked Sushi Mi out yet, this is a must visit for sushi!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPzXJo8KsApKoaLia23Wcokx0ss2NEd9bO4nvsl&fid=0x0:0x4c18326833f0f8da"],"When":"2024-12-13"},{"Name":"Keith Eastcott","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXk5BCUEJh42hOpsF-_OoCCbmyygcrHIJcijMiuq6slKML49qmN0g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely love this place. Sushi is great. Chicken teriyaki dinner is great. Definitely check them out, eat in or take out.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMBpR8fJVK14gqnTfKjaq_QAyhepgz0GbWd6Rwy&fid=0x0:0x4c18326833f0f8da"],"When":"2024-12-9"},{"Name":"Joshua (ThickBurger_Bites)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbIhhMlbxk7OIMpcaP-aSx2m75kt8-mqmXoXAJQ5K99gnxiff1zg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went for their lunch special 20% off.

Good food, just slightly small portions.

Food: We had the lunch combos, Dynamite, Mi Special and Aburi Oshi. The rolls and sushi were fresh, packed tight and very delicious. Tempura tasted slightly off with a slightly strong old oil flavour. Spring rolls were so so.

Service: Relatively fast as there were not many patrons around.

Price: Approx 20 per person before tax and tips and after discount.

Would I recommend: Yes. I’d recommend getting their rolls and none of their fried stuff.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOOxATTfNNWlB1NJHdfw7CoJHFjyTtctWHtNZi9&fid=0x0:0x4c18326833f0f8da"],"When":"2024-3-29"},{"Name":"ALFRED CHEUNG","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUIT2FfsIYlcMtZMfx5S50jtyBU4f02MMH3fvMct4kX_yli8F6e5A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We go there for lunch and the lunch special doing a promotion discount. The food is excellent, and the service is fine. Overall experience is excellent. We go down once a month, never disappointed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMrWyBW8pfFf_3jKGuTEkWgRDIZK0B58lSyWkKd&fid=0x0:0x4c18326833f0f8da"],"When":"2024-8-20"},{"Name":"AnnB G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVx_EqQ1Qby9In7pmXay57uqh-S35etSlqf6kLjV8ZKXTATjchx=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had to try this little gem based on the reviews! Delicious food, well presented and value priced! The server was super nice, tiny dining area but clean, modern and pleasant! I had combo, partner had 2 rolls. More than enough! We’ll be back soon! Highly recommend this local family shop!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOCNmXD5cjjUnj5_uuW07A4_qbPajdl5Y7kjixc&fid=0x0:0x4c18326833f0f8da"],"When":"2024-3-13"},{"Name":"Holly Boucher","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-xeDRiO9_ikZrdv5UeZDCWB1UhcifZhsaqcEbQ9q7pMZ_o8M=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Found this place by happy accident today! I’m from out of town but I can definitely say when I drive through I’ll be stopping here from now on. The portions are generous and everything was absolutely delicious. The owners are very friendly and kind. The restaurant itself is quaint and clean. Best of all there’s a 20% discount on the lunch combo’s menu right now. I got the premium lunch combo (miso soup not pictured here, but included) which came to $20 after discount. I’ll definitely be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOjY8lUUeYga91a5_tItB7tXk16ZZ-TlrMU2uFU&fid=0x0:0x4c18326833f0f8da"],"When":"2024-1-4"},{"Name":"Jana Kivi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWLHGq7TC1gz1Wulhf2LuP2-XduKFqa27fK4a5yFBRhWyXreg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"In town for one night, found Sushi Mi and so glad we did. We ordered an assortment of specialty rolls and were delighted with all. The prices are quite reasonable considering the amount and quality of the dishes. Staff are so friendly and welcoming. We received the Jackson roll and pumpkin croquette on the house and they're so yummy! This restaurant deserves all the love! Highly recommend . Excuse the half eaten food photos !😍","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNqQAEzovGPOYMsS4Z7_DuqnVRa3Em3UNW08cs&fid=0x0:0x4c18326833f0f8da"],"When":"2022-12-18"},{"Name":"Fernandawong1 Instagram W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXNFtqoy-cwodQwEn82tgfWyur2vGbFJj5rTY0AvCzEsWJEe71e=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"5 starts to this place is amazing, super clean and amazing food I really enjoyed this place. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Milad Firouzi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWzrgrIGNGbel6o9MR69Ok-V4had6hrv3OGfRkMbkDP6QkTT80y2Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This Korean restaurant offered an exceptional dining experience! The presentation of the dishes was inviting, as seen in the sizzling hot plates surrounded by cheese, corn, and egg, which added interactive elements to the meal. The flavor of the grilled meats was perfectly balanced, complemented by fresh vegetables. The cheese melted to perfection and paired wonderfully with the savory main course.

The servers were attentive and ensured the food was cooked correctly at the table, enhancing the overall experience. The sides, including sweet corn and creamy egg, rounded off the meal beautifully. The atmosphere was cozy and inviting, making it a perfect spot for a fun and satisfying meal. I highly recommend this place to anyone craving authentic Korean flavors with a modern twist!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOXWThLQdXqvFPeTGvwdYt2rhjQ90OeIDfCGpyI&fid=0x0:0xc939c56a24bbbcb3"],"When":"2024-12-9"},{"Name":"Y S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWTmtWUtCZcs7qDdNKdjVbtcx5f5BcDfDU3YRp4zcFsXHKu1_WS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We came on a Friday night for dinner. Like many people have said, parking is limited to the few spots at the front or else you would need to find parking on the back streets. The back street is residential area with no street lights so it can be scary to walk by yourself.

The food was very tasty and good portion. But I found the soup a bit heavy on MSG. Food came out really fast. The side dishes is unlimited refill.

The service was excellent and attentive. The server checked on us every 10 minutes or so. She knew it was our first time trying the hot plate so she helped us quite a bit. She explained how to eat the food quite well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP0tYqFcFaR2HAYAxHucZYUMCbz6cXcwHpSrJWJ&fid=0x0:0xc939c56a24bbbcb3"],"When":"2024-11-16"},{"Name":"X Z","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUXF-fh-XeTsj_eALyZoNQufIdpcqdopw9XVl72CTpZbYMgCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love the cheese grills here. Makes any kind of food more fun when it’s surrounded by cheese.

To top it off, the service is also great. We were seated promptly in a cozy ambient environment surrounded by extra cushions — a hospital touch I personally really appreciate especially on a tired and chilly day.

Great dining experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMHt6kUcIXPux82BDRgZiwo4h1hYcEHpKGo9g&fid=0x0:0xc939c56a24bbbcb3"],"When":"2024-5-26"},{"Name":"Jenevie E","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVce3HruZ31gaGncYHwX95oKzLpg_0g7BO_KicbohIHjs3w6eDj=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Been a few years since I've visited but used to come here all the time when I resided closer to Coquitlam— always been my preferred location! The new renovations are lovely and still has a cozy atmosphere. Food is as good as I remember and I always recommend the spicy octopus hot plate. ❤️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOfsLUOyIbfJI6dWWFL7DkzijmKDsxiWo-5dlEn&fid=0x0:0xc939c56a24bbbcb3"],"When":"2024-5-2"},{"Name":"Kun Ho Yoon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV7a_TkQUEpAcdGGNy9qU2vuDm2_Ypkj7DPW3ASPBDUd0z4TSse=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First of all, my dining experience was absolutely fantastic. Im a big fan of Korean food and have tried every single one and I have to say Tabom’s Dak Galbi and Japchae is one of my favorite of all.

The grill is creative in its way that it comes with egg, corn and cheese (extra). It’s a must-try and Im definitely willing to come again for its food and service. Not to mention that the atmosphere was relaxing and cozy, warm vibe with good service!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM5IWzar2KaZKDx-sht0D8ClCBkSd2pRuZKa2XR&fid=0x0:0xc939c56a24bbbcb3"],"When":"2024-10-11"},{"Name":"Celina Arenillo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLPvcNqjpmtihcb5J8miFlC4lw0H-EdaSQUtLM4u3kh0_GMHA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I had a great dinner at Ta Bom. It was good that they offer live BBQ grill. Servers were friendly and prompt. Restaurant is quite small, but it was clean and doesn’t reek of strong BBQ smoke smell.

I find the dishes to be fairly priced. It was tasty and fresh.

Will definitely dine here again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNKhQouTyWguciGJfX0oQCiZREEdlsjkdVqAHm3&fid=0x0:0xc939c56a24bbbcb3"],"When":"2024-1-21"},{"Name":"Jessica Aranas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUG8N5f3Wd4GKt8zT_qaGsKHP4OREkobtyE2Xefb2cmdEv-KSHu=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Worst korean restaurant we’ve been too. We went there around 4pm and I think they only have 1 server so it took her a long time to get our order (but it is not that busy). Anyway, after we order we’re expecting for some side dishes because every time we eat at a korean restaurant the servers automatically brings you side dishes after you make your order but sadly they don’t do that here and the free side dishes is not enough for two person (3 types and a very small portion, you can refill it max 3x). The corn is too dry, the egg and cheese is so small, there’s even no rice together with our order, everywhere we go there’s always rice that comes with this. The price is not worth it. Not coming back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPz4caRGfDFkaPclS8CZ24ZB97CGURSa8GHWqX&fid=0x0:0xc939c56a24bbbcb3"],"When":"2024-6-13"},{"Name":"Danny Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8eoyUE6az-FmQo7i2mVq5z64Ow48sgKu1EmLZc0zWWN6DMy5asw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Ta Bom was one of the original dak-galbi restaurants way back when Nolbu in Downtown was the only other place to get it.

It’s still one of the standouts for its hot plate shared mains in the area. They also have a number of other Korean classics as well as fried dishes.

Prices are bit on the high side which is what I think keeps it from being more popular.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMR4CCGgkm1CNjYYz-4BuHmgCsq1DCxZP-SPAFC&fid=0x0:0xc939c56a24bbbcb3"],"When":"2024-5-19"}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Fey N.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU3E0rVnOiz07StNteRqZEUIQdMicAfYFGWeEKF3CLBUA95uHdJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I was invited to a teachers and  staff party here and really enjoyed the food. I deeply enjoyed working with the other teachers and the staff and the students during the summer camp. I just wish there were more chairs to sit with my colleagues as I had to bring an extra chair to sit at the table and, there wasn’t enough space for others to go the other side of the place and they bumped into me several times. But overall, the staff were super friendly and helpful, and it was a really memorable night.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMxSPATPoXrPUER9HkFYi65zHBu_UxpQ8-hBGnB\u0026fid=0x0:0xb7f425ff4237c950"],"When":"2024-8-18"},{"Name":"Hailey Jang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLGHzTNWFVEMOYPCgsQqixyQ6UFFIGKdXAQzO83IrNsff_lMg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great for watching hockey and enjoying beer. The atmosphere , food and service were satisfactory. Their happy hour menu was also great. The long island iced tea was a bit disappointing but I quickly switched to draft beers so I am not bothered","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNJ2yydJoQD7OzzU1E1SAKeNXszv-sAmvuMwi3f\u0026fid=0x0:0xb7f425ff4237c950"],"When":"2024-6-19"},{"Name":"helia azad","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVL0oNnAUx_tWjUSI4W6cVxaN-ZKdPS1tV3z8Q09IRAzXgVEW8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been there 4 times, enjoyed the spectacular customer service. Asked my husband if he wants to go to Cactus or Browns for his birthday, he said The Tap House here because of the Customer Service and great burgers, onion rings, etc. Also the game equipments are soooo fun. Our favorite one.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM0py2qMlde_FO_Z7LlpoyZ4Td2EYjbA6EA3nx3\u0026fid=0x0:0xb7f425ff4237c950"],"When":"2024-10-30"},{"Name":"Champagne Kingdom","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWT9L6nbhgKeVF6uvC80gh6he8ZgVExYxBb0bRQFJovbeiruBo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We absolutely love the brunch options here! The Eggs Benedict, specifically the Yorkie Bennys, are absolutely delicious! We also enjoyed playing skier-ball while sipping our drinks","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPdVWNFzIMlOntd15pJqyDW99DKYpC3tuLXKK2_\u0026fid=0x0:0xb7f425ff4237c950"],"When":"2024-9-28"},{"Name":"Moe Tahir","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9iDu-e6jGh4v-LimNB4J6hLIMigr5EdCcxZwrTlr9-nZtYuSxcw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Very, very disappointed.  Seems like they don't take initiative on any of their mistakes. Warm beer in cold glass. Eyes rolled back when I pointed it out. Wings that had all drumsticks. When ask for about that order. I was questioned.  Clearly it should have been mixed wings. And also I was told that I would have to pay for that first mistaken order. If I was going keep this order. I had better service at Samz neighbourhood pub and at Earls. I was going to spend a lot more time here. Not going to come back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNYkoPz6yXRZzy703JQdfKUzSDVtyF0eKPI5_ap\u0026fid=0x0:0xb7f425ff4237c950"],"When":"2024-7-21"},{"Name":"Clint Stewart","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXxh6VsX6hLeU_9_m0ZG1nvLQ2h4LvbdxIxIz9rHEU9MwIOCByM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The staff here are the best I've seen in over 20 years. Every waitress that walked by our table, always looked over to see if something needed attending to. Whether it be an empty plate or a drink that may need to be refilled. Even if it wasn't their table or section. They work as a team. I was very impressed and I'll be back. Food was really good and the restaurant itself was very nice and clean.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cecilia Torres","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXNEEaaadExpk4TXS6qqCV0FmYUxFhqMOus525fmHWN2GQT7vM68g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Bellini Bliss, Dress Code Bummer\nThe Taphouse is my go-to spot for a delicious Bellini, but their dress code is a total buzzkill. I was so excited to go back with my boyfriend, but we were both wearing shorts (on a summer night), and he was told he had to leave after 10 PM. Can you believe it? I'm hoping they loosen up their rules so I can enjoy their amazing drinks without worrying about my outfit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAX2kSioalJrmcBKuNSvagnO2mZyPWLdTENjm1\u0026fid=0x0:0xb7f425ff4237c950"],"When":"2024-9-20"},{"Name":"Sabrina Dean","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIsuNoq0NjIZsw7Q0s08xv-ogcv0ajmV0Oo0HaZ5E_raW8Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Happy hour options and prices are great. We only had the sweet potato fries this time - too salty and not hot! Server was friendly, quick and checked on us multiple times. Washrooms had 5 out of 8 stalls Out of Service - not sure what's happening there.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Grant M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRWL_i5cZiVpXExK1H8xMkwx4_6CHC_xRkP2HoYZIVJehiW1g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Stopped in for the first time in a long time actually. A friend of mine and myself were just going to stop in for a couple quick Beers, but decided on a couple Appetizers as well.

Had the Hot Wings and Salt and Pepper Dry Ribs, and both were actually very good, and great flavors on both of them.

After checking out the menu while having our first beers while waiting for our food to arrive, we definitely noticed that the menu was very nice with lots of different options to it. And lots of Gluten Free options as well since a friend of mine, as well as a few others I know definitely have problems with Gluten. ( Good to see ) As so many places don't really cater to that.

Also Orrange has a nice Gluten Free Beer as well. I had their own House Beer ( Lager ) that was pretty good. They also have Beer Flights and Margarita Flights as well.

Will definitely be back again, and bring some others along with us next time 😀👍👍","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOZGJGATFFuAYpoUIokeK4zkl6r3muGQxnN3Hln&fid=0x0:0xb2e3be892520b306"],"When":"2024-7-20"},{"Name":"Shona Fraser","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX_pDuq2IEOYnuAz5jc_iUm4vZrwZZuuI3aConifzRVQAv9FGWl=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Really enjoyed Orrange! Cute interior, friendly staff and tasty food. Cocktail menu wasn't incredible, but the wine was good. Will come back to try brunch!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMh8Q4co7elXvu8jUVB_NVDD68mvgq9-gXJfW-I&fid=0x0:0xb2e3be892520b306"],"When":"2024-9-5"},{"Name":"Will Desmarais","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVA0w2RDqHZeOd41COAUoFO6hnjotO4YccIPRzQzrfKQTCb31QR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Attended our company Xmas party. Service was good we were well looked after. Would definitely return. There was a shortage of steak and the staff went above an beyond too make it right. I couldn't be happier with the service and communication. Our server also treated the kids at our table with respect and even held the baby at one point. What a great overall experience.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jinnie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK8gqt8IKnCRf4zl37GiLySrzoMAaxn28_yfYYzkVmL6ePwhw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"So I was there for a birthday party. Spent $150 and got the poutine to go…I think I count 6 pieces of cheese on my $15 poutine? I have not been there since it’s grand opening and my review remains the same…abysmal. Ordered deep fried pickles in the restaurant which was great. One server on a Sunday evening. Had to order via the bartender a few times but still got my orders at a timely manner. No complaints with the service…But this to go poutine had me at disgust. Will not be going back anytime soon…or ever.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPwPzSJOyVyteL5QqYO9gjjGdN8MUga4DAgkPQm&fid=0x0:0xb2e3be892520b306"],"When":"2024-9-16"},{"Name":"Zahra Tejpar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL1CTlu2lI8PQ8gnAmixjyIsCtSXmQKDl1rHjt5y812Oda0Ww=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Driven past the restaurant a few times but never really been in to try it out. It’s a very nice, clean restaurant. The ambiance was relaxing and enjoyable for us. We went here for happy hour. The staff were very friendly and helpful. The staff came by a few times to check on us. We tried the yam fries, chilli + lime chicken, and Korean fried chicken. It was really delicious and we left happy. A unique restaurant I would highly recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOqbxFs_8Dnu0wgflWRFLU4ks6a1CCFqJ_MD4AO&fid=0x0:0xb2e3be892520b306"],"When":"2023-4-30"},{"Name":"Kaitlyn Forester","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWkS1mVO5BCaF4vYxZsOQdUzbqxBXZ_kUF1c-SDQ-3HPYw5OR7q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My boyfriend took me here for date night last night and I LOVED it! I honestly don’t enjoy going out much, and although I don’t ever speak up or complain I feel like it’s been a long time since I’ve been to a restaurant and everything’s just been enjoyable all throughout. This was one of those rare nights! The margarita flight was so yum and same with the sangria. The ribs, dill pickles and Yorkshire beef deep were also literally perfect. I wish I got our server’s name because she was SO lovely! Thank you guys again for such a good date night<3","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPVKhowrwMxC8CLpblw1iAfod41RPACmeva-SXP&fid=0x0:0xb2e3be892520b306"],"When":"2024-4-23"},{"Name":"Dan Peterson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJbNeFUlLkRmjcX25zxpAW7H_0IDjY0P_SfdPGvxnigSNv-OQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We went to Orrange for brunch on the long weekend. I had the Yorkshire beef dip with a side of chicken tortilla soup and it was delicious. Its a giant flat Yorkshire pudding roll filled with roast beef. My friend ordered the Nashville chicken eggs Benedict-a classic with a twist! Generous portions and tasty food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN_OIrfroXfRVz3CgWYfzGM-SmVJjsttpGYiL_v&fid=0x0:0xb2e3be892520b306"],"When":"2023-7-10"},{"Name":"Daniel Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAxFTfz_ZYgM60gsStYArKOb4YgmHuHArMEsVm-TJD2WcKuo33=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This dining experience was a delightful surprise! We tried the Old School Spaghetti + Meatballs, Chili+Lime Chicken, Torched Butter New York Steak and Almost Famous Poutine, and they stole the show.

The crispy fries with just the right amount of gravy in the Poutine were a highlight, though a tad more cheese would have perfected it.  The steak was a crispy-tender delight, rivaling those at upscale downtown restaurants.

While the Old School Spaghetti + Meatballs lacked flavor, I wouldn't recommend it to anyone.

Not much to say about the Chili+Lime Chicken, it is a well made dish, but nothing special.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPNrR5Y8VOSYfX-rZRsNhpWYfbjfPvr_uUc1v60&fid=0x0:0xb2e3be892520b306"],"When":"2023-11-5"}]
