[{"Name":"Connie Robson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVcD3CpjQ2KIT9ukXOt3q6p8B8SMkttAVRJsUo328I8e2x3t4I=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I ordered the apple cinnamon French toast but there was not a single piece of apple on it. My friend ordered the same thing and again, no apple. It was still very good but I don’t know if the missing apple was an oversight or if it doesn’t come with it then the description is misleading.

Overall I liked the restaurant - very lively and popular and will come back to try some of the other menu options.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN-O4q7PCGAe_Q_exHXbh66W5xF0fvIy5DjDcX0&fid=0x0:0x23a839fa4c1f06bf"],"When":"2024-11-17"},{"Name":"Nick Wang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK9cUtJY153nRWD4hzNcIo_gDDe44hWUa0zRGkneCYmPYO49A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great place for family!  We came here on a Sunday morning for their Kids Eat Free Special.   Between 7~9am, for every $25 order of an adult meal, you get a kid’s meal for free.  We ordered a Canadian breakfast and Pesto Philly steak, both tasted amazing.  Usually when you order a kid’s meal from restaurants, it’s small portion and not very appealing.  But the free kids’ meal at Pur and Simple, were full size crepes and waffles, filled with banana, chocolate chips, and strawberries.  I also really like the country style decor that they have.  Great vibe, great value and great food!  Definitely worth your visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO2uPEhDiPYzzlUmh-jAKSk098DjZpOsiek7DqQ&fid=0x0:0x23a839fa4c1f06bf"],"When":"2024-6-30"},{"Name":"BABAK TORABI","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXte01Tl3Efa_m0ADFo96Kz1F79A0-Ap8jSjGIMNFygHZjHQcocIQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We recently visited this restaurant again and noticed that the portions of some dishes are quite large for one person. This time, we decided to share, which worked out perfectly.

The food tastes great, the quality is excellent, and the staff is incredibly friendly. The environment is clean, modern, and welcoming. One of the highlights is the open kitchen, which lets you see the chefs at work—always a nice touch.

The only downside is the noise level. The sound seems to reflect a lot, likely due to the ceramic flooring, which is easy to clean but amplifies noise. The ceiling also doesn’t seem to have much for sound absorption.

It was a bit crowded on a Saturday morning, but that’s to be expected for such a popular spot. Overall, a great experience!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN5kNNNIObhREuuSscKObbYbvBBCdaYd8SvrHjg&fid=0x0:0x23a839fa4c1f06bf"],"When":"2024-11-20"},{"Name":"Annie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJAG4UtHNdn-C74S5I053c9lMdRMdh_AH35u090AgjHoFmF2GSW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"So happy to finally have brunch and it did not disappoint!  The location is easy to find and lots of free parking. The atmosphere is easy and friendly and the food and service were excellent. Can’t wait to come back.

Returned with my family and it was even better. Our server Gurleen was an absolute delight while she managed a busy restaurant full of guests. Today was savory and it was amazing. The boys shared the big 3 and it was more than enough. Can’t wait to come back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPiCPG4ng_rPed3P8NoMqKZwG2zyzEYpkFnrOYt&fid=0x0:0x23a839fa4c1f06bf"],"When":"2024-7-12"},{"Name":"Craig’s Food and Fun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUha2Q8WiUjbezKLoCbc8g-ZcFkFuHpjx0PE6RArmNeLmTAwJN4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food was amazing! And the staff was very friendly and professional, definitely coming back! We had the fried chicken eggs Benny and the fried chicken sandwich. The potatoes and fries were tasty and seasoned and the chicken crispy. The eggs were farm fresh and the hollandaise sauce was excellent!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPx6ygBpCV1nh9QvLFAAD3WtpH8Ta9carJ7YKDn&fid=0x0:0x23a839fa4c1f06bf"],"When":"2024-12-4"},{"Name":"Sia Ghaem","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUEMQ83Io5sE_IiypwGW5tpjSnD5RcP1dPzKLkdTOi-SisSW8bCuA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We have been to Pur and Simple a few times and it has been a satisfactory experience every time. They are border line Good/great time restaurant. Not great to blow you away, but good enough to draw you back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO1cabewFzUoYl0Ck3t7YQ0X5raQ_yGu8-dips2&fid=0x0:0x23a839fa4c1f06bf"],"When":"2024-9-23"},{"Name":"Tyler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX5pgqDcV4jXxCDs44gFpKqBE7-kpDe9pqH0qySpykt9h70rZWn=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"During a recent visit to Pür & Simple in Port Coquitlam, my girlfriend and I enjoyed a delightful breakfast experience. The restaurant’s bright and modern ambiance created a welcoming atmosphere, complemented by attentive and friendly staff.

I opted for the Coconut French Toast, which featured thick slices of brioche infused with a subtle coconut flavor, topped with fresh fruits and a light dusting of powdered sugar. The combination of textures and flavors was both satisfying and indulgent.

My girlfriend chose the Gourmet Breakfast, a hearty platter that included perfectly cooked eggs, crispy bacon, savory sausage, and a side of their renowned P&S potatoes. Each component was prepared with care, resulting in a balanced and flavorful meal.

The service was exceptional; our server was attentive without being intrusive, ensuring our coffee cups were always filled and promptly addressing any requests. The menu offered a diverse selection of breakfast and brunch options, catering to various tastes and dietary preferences.

Overall, our experience at Pür & Simple was outstanding. The combination of delicious food, excellent service, and a pleasant atmosphere makes it a top choice for breakfast in Port Coquitlam. We look forward to returning and exploring more of their menu offerings.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOLLZ6a2rGBYbAJu6qxbOFMZlUqdNznKM-GgC9i&fid=0x0:0x23a839fa4c1f06bf"],"When":"2024-11-25"},{"Name":"Nazanin Tehrani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLNvnOcnvQZmQRfgcZ1xIfiff0XhYrv3BK46Bu6rg2GKUDhBQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had an excellent breakfast experience at Pur & Simple. The atmosphere was welcoming, and the food was just what I needed to start the day right. The menu offered a great variety of options, and everything I ordered was fresh, delicious, and beautifully presented.

A special shoutout to our host, Dyson, who provided outstanding service. He was attentive, friendly, and made sure we had everything we needed throughout our meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPtjwERVXfcA2zNYNfAsBJWo_5Pds5RsfhS84G2&fid=0x0:0x23a839fa4c1f06bf"],"When":"2024-8-22"}]

[{"Name":"Zeeshan Sohail","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXQzSgXcEIo5d0fY039IL3LLi7k1i-9eyjB9u0xnur9BQekUdtD=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A decent upscale Syrian restaurant. The food and presentation are really nice and serving size is generous. The Lamb skewer and kababs are current favorites but we will definitely be coming back for more.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMAvckGfl0PoQUcUqY_W5zuNKxZrBZdZ3iBZKGw&fid=0x0:0xe28bd80ba773fc74"],"When":"2024-9-10"},{"Name":"Neda G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXcXBADLi2CMhn5hf9f-JdbOlYYM_LHhdjb9JmX03VjxzMph4k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I had high hopes for this restaurant as it is difficult to find an authentic Arabic Shawarma or Shish taouk in Coquitlam. But unfortunately, this wasn’t it. The atmosphere was nice and quite clean. However, the food and service not quite there. It took almost 30 mins for our food to come and sadly, two customers that arrived and ordered after us, received their food before us. All that aside, the sandwiches was what I was most excited to try. We ordered a beef and a chicken Shish taouk. The beef was quite smelly and I believe they cooked the chicken on the same flat top as the beef, and it smelled similar. Very small portion sizes for the price. The side of fries were also NOT authentic, they were Costco fries. We also ordered an appetizer of falafel, which was just ok. Overall, it did not meet or come close to my expectation.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP1HMefI3ZmMv_z5j-__gdnwx2IpQObi9TKkOH2&fid=0x0:0xe28bd80ba773fc74"],"When":"2024-9-16"},{"Name":"M Ism","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIIouxyfjqFUskw-zPX-rf09-04JaS8UcC8StGLRfSFFg7FyQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"First time dining at the restaurant for a birthday celebration.  I must say the presentation along with the atmosphere was very nice.  The service was okay however, it seems that some of the servers did not have any experience.  The price of the food for what you're getting is unacceptable and not worth it at all.  We ended up ordering the family grill platter with assorted meats from the menu and it  was some of the driest meat that I have ever had.  The lamb, the chicken and beef were all dry and most of all flavorless.  The kunefe was OK and not the best.  The only thing that i could say was enjoyable was the bread and lentile soup.  I dont like giving out bad reviews but after spending over $200,  one would expect to get better food.  This will be the first and last time ever going to that restaurant.  I do not recommend this place at all. Looks good from the outside however overpriced and dry food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNJXbJMGqzFGiMxRFGwWS5nL58REzlIcfHvYXz2&fid=0x0:0xe28bd80ba773fc74"],"When":"2024-6-24"},{"Name":"bahar n","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJmfGtscBDa09dk7b-7RvVKIZH6hneZ4y0b-VObedbjnl-MZvE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Tonight, I went to Ayam Zaman restaurant for the first time. The shawarma had no meat and was just fat, and the food had a strong smell of lamb. The kebab was burnt, and when I mentioned the issues with their food, they said, “I will let the kitchen know.” The burnt kebab should have been replaced, as well as the shawarma, which was just fat. However, they didn’t do anything and gave no response regarding the bad food. It took them an hour to bring the food, and the food was terrible.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPt4dgLGQDg0BkBqsLuehEZZxmn8UW17fMSytSX&fid=0x0:0xe28bd80ba773fc74"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Amitha Thomas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU56Tb4Od8EpwDMLbqdGOzyvHJEOPTjgLc6IBJXDp0kdn-iBMY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went there for our anniversary lunch.
Bought a kebab plate and mandi. Everything was yummy but would have been better if kababs were served with hummus. It's a general Arabic practice. So was surprised when hummus was not given. Everything else was really good. The ambience and the investors were all great.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO8Xyf_-_KUZaF4FlKfOmTWJV4NdOOrn_JYJGKA&fid=0x0:0xe28bd80ba773fc74"],"When":"2024-5-28"},{"Name":"Cassie Meadow","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWsGjxSINOhz43iQl213pjOWfdBb8gBCnc7FoXExHIIE0GlJImo=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"saw some nice google reviews but was EXTREMELY DISAPPOINTED. hummus is actually quite nice but I thought my meal was a joke. I can’t believe I paid actual money for this. i’ve had mana-eesh lebanese style pizza from other places and expected ground/minced meat and spices so ordered the sausage…. it’s HOT DOGS. I’m so mad about this but I guess they need my money more than I do if that’s what they are serving. The chicken shawarma wrap was probably authentic so it’s just a westernized preference of mine - though based on the description of sauce and pickles and based on the price I expected the usual wrap… it was so small the width of a remote control and only seemed to have chicken inside. Sharing my photos so you are more informed than I was before deciding whether or not to purchase. again, really disappointing bc looking at other photos there might be some decent food here and I got very unlucky?","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPViF09VM2CFzCqMCgH1d3NTzsqlRUzTRuIldxW&fid=0x0:0xe28bd80ba773fc74"],"When":"2024-8-6"},{"Name":"Linh Tran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbP3plInkqXVOA2XJc8czoQ80aWBGnT8WS-yMiUPgvNShtt-y90A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a great dinner. We shared falafel, beef skew & a chicken & beef platter and both were happy with the food. It seems to be an authentic Syrian restaurant as staff and most female customers wear head scarves. I assume you may not want to wear appealing clothes in this set up. The Arabian coffee was excellent, love it!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNUsRgw3HmcwN5ov6tmszBiQXQ-EYISZD9CetPW&fid=0x0:0xe28bd80ba773fc74"],"When":"2024-2-12"},{"Name":"kiana Liu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWKoxfjAHBiXenysk2Q-KlulFH1fxjGp6FrGPGGTkK41ibofwbwig=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Let’s start with what was good!
Food: The Iskender dish was good, the yogurt that comes with it was so delicious. The rice came with Lamb Mandy was great, the lamb was tender too. The kibbeh was good as well. Kenefe was good too.
The person who served us was very polite and attentive.

Now let’s talk about the not so positive thing.

Food: the lamb kebab and chicken kebab was super dry and not tasty at all. The chicken shawarma was too dry but still didn’t taste bad just very dry.

The olive oil and viniger bottle was super dirty and hard to use without getting your hands sticky. The dust and hair stick to it, so disgusting.

They make their drinks that needs blender right by my ears, so every 5 minutes there was this super loud noise that was unbearable, we couldn’t talk or hear each other. I left the restaurant with a very bad headache. I took some videos so you can actually hear how loud it is. Normally these equipments belong to the kitchen, no one enjoys hearing ear drilling noise like that while they’re eating food that they didn’t pay cheap money for. I really hope they change this. I was holding my ears not to hear it and still left with a bad migraine.
They were doing their cutlery preparation right by our table that was banging the spoons and forks the rest of the time that was no blender going on. The servants had to go in and out and hit us or our chairs all the time. Overall DON’T SIT BY THE BAR.

I think 2 starts is very generous of me. And that’s for some of the good dishes and our server. I didn’t want to write a review they came to our table with a sign asking to write a review. Here was my honest review in the hopes of things getting better and other customers don’t suffer the way we did.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMz3G_BLekjt5Xx0wNXxZJEDPK-yaQwStO1DFgd&fid=0x0:0xe28bd80ba773fc74"],"When":"2024-5-6"}]

[{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Met a friend at Saku and had a delightful experience. The waitlist link online didn't work but we didn't need to worry about that because there were tables open when we arrived. The atmosphere was both aesthetically pleasing and comfortable with bright, warm lighting, and the two waiters were very polite.
I tried the Saku on Broadway in Vancouver once years ago and loved it and was impressed again here. I got the veggie curry and also their seasonal cinnamon ginger drink. Their curry sauce is earthy and so rich; I am in love. The veggies were fried to be nice and soft inside and not too oily. The sides are also very good. I subbed out the tonjiru for a mini cold udon. The noodles were tender and the broth was also really flavourful. This was my first time trying cold udon and I was pleasantly surprised by how different flavours come out in the cold broth. The cinnamon ginger drink was very unique with the warm cinnamon ginger flavour in a refreshing soda.
My meal with tip was about $40. Although it’s a little expensive, the portions are generous as is and you can stretch the value even more by ordering complimentary refills for your sides. I didn’t need it since I was full with the first round.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO1IZaWTu8bX8SPf3d-L1xEXrV5HEzVX_VUmDVw&fid=0x0:0x63e1fb4e65830f4f"],"When":"2024-12-19"},{"Name":"Paul Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVl2oVxJKLr_k_g4j5wg7lB9NsNfiBzRT5FNAPVPTrX-BeeOxpk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The store isn't very big, but the overall decor feels comfortable. Their deep fried dishes are done quite well—crispy on the outside, tender inside, and not greasy. The other side dishes are also fine. The only slight disappointment is their sauce; in my opinion, it’s a bit too mild, which is a pity given the high quality of their fried items. Overall, it's a pretty good restaurant and worth recommending.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPcCXhtj6e9MzBLZoso4yfUWVGe7VxVYEPfwB97&fid=0x0:0x63e1fb4e65830f4f"],"When":"2024-10-29"},{"Name":"Jooey V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXYFca56bPZafMJtIyMb6Ij_VZ3XATQurm5TlOwXPZrmywf0QM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I'm someone who loves both Korean-style Dongasu and Japanese-style tonkatsu, and this dish is my soul food.

However, I was deeply disappointed by this franchise, which is said to have the best tonkatsu in Vancouver.

A good tonkatsu should taste heavenly even when dipped in just a bit of salt.
But their *Dokujyo rosu katsu*, which is supposed to be a premium menu item, was overly greasy, and the batter crumbled with just a touch of my chopsticks.
Despite being one of the first tables, there was a smell of oil.

Moreover, about a quarter of the *rosu katsu* was fat.
I've never seen this much fat in a pork loin cutlet before.

Both weren’t completely terrible, but for a dish that costs around $30, I would honestly recommend Costco’s frozen stuff instead.

It's a real shame because this place used to be known for its amazing food, but it seems they've completely lost their original touch.

P.s. but the service itself was very nice","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOTqJaHEDApsb1rWimsoqzCEokpp-vyjWlQvLOT&fid=0x0:0x63e1fb4e65830f4f"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Thomas Cyre","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXjxRtq3NoJ3VgRg8YkHsqwg3V2gkoydIp0o9cTSTsZPUk9ApYJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I ordered the Miso Katsu, my wife ordered the Kurobuta Special Katsu. Both were delicious. We really liked the variety of seasonings to eat with the katsu. The tonjiru soup was really good and its great to have free refills of rice, soup and salad. Service was good, will definately go back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMzeaC0Gg7PFJcJ_ODlhxk50bIzzoj9Uaui5yIK&fid=0x0:0x63e1fb4e65830f4f"],"When":"2024-11-25"},{"Name":"B C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIYvDpHvDtMb9gbzsqKNwxqjfCmk7W_UFxEZqOKOCis0fyIO58=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Do not be fooled by the upscaled decor or presentation.

Tried the cheese katsu, which is one of their "signature specials". $27 plus tax and tip for 6 glorified cheese sticks and rice.

In hindsight I should have ordered the regular katsu, as there would be more meat, but even the portion for those looked small.

The taste of everything was fine, but the steep prices for the food you get in return is unjustified.

Would not recommend or return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPEkIJlmYiRZEGYZo_DSHV_g-B95WLRezTU4cI&fid=0x0:0x63e1fb4e65830f4f"],"When":"2024-10-7"},{"Name":"Lucy Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVuwCjTEBDQem6hcfmmxSA0I0nNlJPkS88N0KyjwlMUZAjI_Jdm8w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"So good, one of my favourite katsu places in the city. I’ve been to this place so many times and in many of their locations across the GVA area. I get the premium pork katsu combo most of the time and it’s delicious. Their fried fish one is also really good and I recommend. They also offer free refills on salads, rice and soup which is amazing and fills me up every time. The house made sesame dressing for the salad is the best. Their meat also tastes super fresh and the interior of the restaurants are always clean!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPSTrhy0W_gsEEVrnebp6SUvbS--8lRc8HtdfG8&fid=0x0:0x63e1fb4e65830f4f"],"When":"2024-9-15"},{"Name":"Cat King","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVs0w4Gi6wbbwHozHIMXCxGOYXWgHMRV7NGZtPTmRmCUIubsOlj=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I brought my baby boy and my mother-in-law here for lunch. We ordered the pork and the cheese cutlet. We also got side orders of the ebi tempura and the curry sauce. My mother-in-law was very impressed. The presentation, she thought, was very nice, and the quality of the food was outstanding. She's never had katsu Like this in Ottawa where she is from. The servers were very nice to us as well despite my baby boy making a big mess while he was eating. Overall, food was great . Saku is one of those places that you have to eat at the restaurant. We'll be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMGlAhHO3tUA9ZdkaA8Ci0gSmqrsfJOOAjCYISg&fid=0x0:0x63e1fb4e65830f4f"],"When":"2024-7-7"},{"Name":"Yoshi O","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXXzpF5JXCGmarr1qa55T_-WQSAQqt7aKKnVaI2jByds0GoeWQJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Had their special Kuro buta.
It was too oily as its bottom was still wet by oil even it's laid on a wire rack!! The rice, which I love as I am Japanese, it was bad. Hard, smelled old. No worth $32 before tip plus $5 for parking!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNwIZaPje41m1UK5sCFbCz-T9BJh-ieqeoXYjIl&fid=0x0:0x63e1fb4e65830f4f"],"When":"2024-10-20"}]

[{"Name":"Elmira Nazari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUS8psOPde-fgvVYsglTVKj-j9hpNdB1347mGr_T9d11yAStREO4w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Top 5 Pho places from my experience. Delicious broth flavour which is usually what I look for first. Most pho places have fairly bland broth. The service was kind and prompt. Spring rolls and salad rolls were generously filled and fresh. Venue is not fancy, but everything was solid for a quick bite.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMvcn6yIw2DQtkJaRluT_9hjJOBh6Dz8lZiNwOY&fid=0x0:0x4fc28418f445867"],"When":"2024-12-16"},{"Name":"Jun Jang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL47AHOHCYDKEAbEAKPJ80TxGYhPvE0xJ8NC0flA2gu-YScsEc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Honestly, it's such a nice place to eat. Not too many people and they give so much food when you order a large, and it's delicious! The people here are very nice too!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOIQoXlh2Ile21EfKoc7X2bkzU2S_YAR0KQBAh4&fid=0x0:0x4fc28418f445867"],"When":"2024-9-7"},{"Name":"Mia Phung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUahhblwNBiEAwk94mdJWBHUNijQ6eiD0coiuxNtVCY2uF3K0RbzA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A clean restaurant with friendly staff and good service. They also offer good prices with many combo options, allowing you to enjoy different items in the same bowl. They are kid friendly as well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMnSv1CsIFMgGKRQb3GmRJIMypPEKJZ0VkVoXz-&fid=0x0:0x4fc28418f445867"],"When":"2024-7-6"},{"Name":"Connie Ono","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWu3GznhECwzkHA0nAaCaXgrK62cXqxAJUyd4pU08WzBpBTTJeG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great menu, lots to choose from.

Spring rolls were crispy and delightful with the fish sauce. The Rice with Pork Grilled Chops had the perfect combination of lemon grass and sesame seeds. Moist and flavourful!  Decent size for your buck as well. My husband got the Seafood with Pho Noodles, and the bowl is pretty big for a regular size. (Plus it's filled to the brim).

The owners were really nice! Great service! Close to our hotel we stayed at.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO1eXlq47aU1BKxDH8DB2lg8w_8QaRNjx4ysjMa&fid=0x0:0x4fc28418f445867"],"When":"2023-5-24"},{"Name":"Alice Tan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXSabLEqcemt-2KAauM2vbbDg67dC-dDk8Gyg-Xtd1xlnwMUara=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It was an ok pho place. I wouldn't say it's the best nor the worst. We ordered two pho and a salade roll, the salade roll had hair in it, definitely not pleasant, but they did changed it for us right away. The ingredients weren't fresh, the veggies had black edges. The soup base was ok.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOSd77Sg5MRPM2pPnpzHtp-9ZRd8sdvHJoKJXzx&fid=0x0:0x4fc28418f445867"],"When":"2023-8-15"},{"Name":"Ardalan Audine","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIttLHSciNI5QVvmbvKNCuAe1rkdKd0slBlW9_P847CRy5giA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best Pho place I've been to in Vancouver. Service is super friendly, food is absolutely amazing and I just love these guys.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN4Kd4rYCMLXUx4aDXsApl5YkJhzr-9zqIwDehv&fid=0x0:0x4fc28418f445867"],"When":"2024-5-16"},{"Name":"A T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIgNmuu8n6BZgKwXYt3MmpIV8oem7hLJh3eeyvqe5_e1DpzrQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I’ve been coming here for years even when it was under old ownership. The new owners have been running Friday discount for quite sometime and we decided to go there as kids had a day off which was a big mistake, as it was busy.  We ordered 2 special chicken pho. Depending on the day you go, you get either boiled chicken or grilled chicken🙄. When we received our order, we noticed that it has 2 different broth. One chicken and one beef. On top of that, the noodles weren’t fully cooked. As a non beef eater, I approached the owner and told her. She assured me that it was chicken. It was when I told her to smell it, then she agreed to change it. This wasn’t the first time that it has happened. When she brought out the replacement, I noticed that it wasn’t a whole new order. In fact, it looked like they had drained and rinsed the old noodles and meat and put chicken broth in it. How I knew was that I had already taken a bite out of the chicken. I honestly enjoyed the food here despite of the inconsistency but don’t think I will be going back. Maybe the owners, shouldn’t rush and maybe have more helpers in the kitchen to avoid mistakes.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Andy Chiang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU6Ytd6jvLjiUIKjc2DLdidLuwgHbgPUD4GPhFuPOLEoqlZ2vbh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A good, authentic Pho place tucked in a busy and hard to turn into complex. Many come here for the Korean soup, karaoke, or bar, but there’s a great pho place here called Pho Capital.

They are extremely generous on their portions, and by portions, I don’t mean they give you a large bowl or extra noodles, but they give you a ton of meat! Regardless of small or large bowls, you’re going to get a lot of meat. If you’re not too hungry then a small is more than enough as they give you a huge amount of portion. This is probably the most meat I’ve seen in a pho bowl for a regular bowl of pho.

The food comes out quick, they accept credit cards, and best of all, there’s 15% off on Fridays!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOK6-75GQpmta8oheQv6JKZbt_zMzA2hREfbihy&fid=0x0:0x4fc28418f445867"],"When":"2023-11-19"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Abby Forest","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkVeY5BURjRxxAm-kCjdJ1ykqlqsFIsY5VpRVYmtMueUteyobs6Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best pizza place
Location is convenient, and the staff are friendly and kind

Always smiling

I had ordered the Indian style pizza .
Delicious fresh toppings and a great way to cut the craving, when you want Indian style pizza
Definitely two thumbs up. I ordered this pizza often.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMnlULmoVx_5gm8Bmo08rVTsTELOP4Hno07nBHW&fid=0x0:0xe48dfdd598b8d3ac"],"When":"2024-11-7"},{"Name":"Graham M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKdwLLTjH1ZAFphg34ytA3HLhgZZS3099n8ma3FzbglSlAnpw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best pizza I’ve ever had soo good I would give it a 10 star review if I could","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPajzgn2Ci_2AeNsqzhWpZpTxTo8PQuPZyqNnC6&fid=0x0:0xe48dfdd598b8d3ac"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"S S P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUKMMpxNR6kHBKvWTp7bkyotjXyBOgnR8CIuiSyw9BdjnpY5izU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Best local pizza!

I love this spot. I've been going here for the last 15 years or so. I was introduced to Pizza Factory by a friend telling me about their Monday pizza special a Large 2-Topping pizza for $11.98 (,pick up only) The toppings are premium, the crust is on point, and it's not over cooked. They offer various specials everyday of the week
They also offer Indian dishes, pastas, and wings. I would have given 5 stars but the wings aren't really anything special or memorable but when those improve they will get that 5th star.
The staff are friendly, welcoming and really appreciate their customers.  Give them a try you won't be disappointed!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Zen W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocItsk8TaWY-bgEdARRPgnrRBpwZ2F6MpE5TS8rdDn2mvHmHlQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Today, in the afternoon, I ordered a pizza and was pleasantly surprised to learn that the person ahead of me had already paid for my order. He had left before I entered the restaurant. I am deeply grateful for their generosity; their act of kindness truly brightened my day, making the pizza even more special.

I would also like to extend my gratitude to Gina for her excellent service and for facilitating this unexpected gift.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMKZxRrfm7QrUJXQp_a3iGr51Xh3gdqjtk2JsO9&fid=0x0:0xe48dfdd598b8d3ac"],"When":"2024-3-26"},{"Name":"Gary S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbwfFqaCkOn1VbU76HFhDcbA_7j2OWGRTuW1QlH9kSO3wvLsk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place has become our favourite pizza joint around this neighborhood. We first came here because we had to wait for our food next door then we saw the 9.99 medium 2 toppings walk in special, so we gave it a try.. since then, we had been back almost every week. Pizza is delicious. Perfect crust. Sauce is super tasty. Right amount of cheese and toppings. Jst amazing. We also tried the Indian food one time and they were good. Service is also top-notch. Kudos guys :D","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Evelyn Nie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnnZak8L0h58i8GPwlEL93KsUuO9alR-EbBWfg-W2mWudr8yE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Your pizza is delicious, your service is amazing and it's worth buying back many times","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM-uHPORZ7a7LefDunKZ34cUy1Re8QQwWNy-WDO&fid=0x0:0xe48dfdd598b8d3ac"],"When":"2024-8-13"},{"Name":"Emmanuel Morúa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVgDDr7Bq5maIJYTC_on0x6OlVE8ViM6rt1o7JGzQMU2HdiVQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Super cheap, very delicious, extra hot and super cheesy pizza. I paid no more than $18 and got a whole large pizza, jarritos pop and a dipping sauce, honestly you don’t see prices like these anymore. My pizza was ham and pepperoni, ham was set up in one big piece under the first layer of cheese, never had it like that before, it was odd to me but definitely loved it!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPWy2bIHrcbbq4vp96vJR_PS1FVhsLzufPuMyqU&fid=0x0:0xe48dfdd598b8d3ac"],"When":"2024-5-7"},{"Name":"Brendon Sharma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJwVwAOeHIXcmr9314sP51Aq_8-OvMrjaGARJ6YSAF1fH5wVw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Went in to order our pizza and butter chicken.

Butter chicken was alright but the pizza was overly salted. Called in and spoke with Anmol, she mentioned that they are closed now. So there goes our dinner. Had to order late night food so we spent more on dinner.

Anmol doesn't have the best customer service either. She said to call back and talk to the manager. Basically brushing my concerns off and not giving proper reassurance of what's next.

Probably won't buy from here again. The taste of the pizza really does reflect on there cheap price.

Also pizza places need to stay open longer. Not close at 11pm. Another downside.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Vancouver Foodie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI8w6jkWQhHhs1Z246avVvoKQqrR4N6KZDvvFaklq629YACSQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Average Vietnamese beef noodles.

We ordered their special beef noodles, signature short rib soup noodles, deep fried shrimp spring rolls and Vietnamese coffees.

The noodles are good but the taste is just like any average Vietnamese restaurants.

The seats are small and not very comfortable.
It's also not easy to find parking.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPe5wuB2rkUOyZJne_65HKkXt1YDZUhQVmEqcyy&fid=0x0:0x67373238d75c8118"],"When":"2024-12-9"},{"Name":"Aleah Brown","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVOfmiP6ZZLzOHDPNcx4PgZrUTDT2IUnYpu9vyaqTf1SFX-yNf6=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Never disappoints. I'm hesitant about trying new places but I work close by and was craving pho one day so I ordered from here. Since that day I have eaten here multiple times and get pickup for lunch at least 1-2 times per month (possibly more). Great broth flavor and hits the spot every time!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ray Dubs","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWv4pQtKu2wy66jann-Dj8Exe3FIdSioz5JunQZJxz8XSK1GHcjzg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Review from guy eating his way through the Vietnamese restaurants in the Lower Mainland.

This restaurant is in my neighbourhood and it’s my first time eating here and I’m glad I took a trip to Pho Holiday. It doesn’t look like much from the outside or inside but that’s not usually what you’re looking for anyways at a pho joint.

They’ve got a lot of menu options and some special types of pho. After some debating I settled on the Spicy Peanut Pho. This was really enjoyable to eat as the broth was very flavourful with just enough hints of peanut but not overly spicy (at least to my standards - I eat spicy). The assortment and cuts of beef were great as you get rare slices of beef, brisket and some fatty flank(?) pieces as well. This will be on my “eat again” list.

Other special bowls are the beef rib pho and the smoky beef pho which I will have to come and try on my next Pho Holiday.

Rays Tips:
There’s a few parking spots in front of restaurant.
Parking is available in the back but you’ll have to walk around to the front.
Credit card is accepted here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMd-1VTsEF15quKBk1eyMZRymQdZ900qgP2LLRa&fid=0x0:0x67373238d75c8118"],"When":"2023-8-28"},{"Name":"Alexi Z","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJtyDIWOs-lCvlSbaSncyGpUjQXa0VAI5wpYfXSxXEeur1bqw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The food here is very low quality.  Our noodles were served cold.  No fresh herbs and very little flavour.  Some of the worst Vietnamese food we have ever had.  The service was very poor.  They didn't check on us once nor did they offer to refill our tea.  Servers were on their phones the whole time we were there, and never smiled once.  The atmosphere is awful; the seating looks like it was repurposed from a tear-down.  Muzak was playing...just dull and lame.  The only time the servers smiled was when we paid, obviously looking for a nice tip.  I will never go here again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Joe B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIDpi_rGpZjUyMPy1allklXwcA7eocPaTgiwR-3r8sEtq5q0A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"After enjoying the Rare Beef Pho and famous Spicy Creamy Peanut Pho here for years, I recently tried the Spicy Coconut Curry Pho with rare beef and I absolutely love it! They told me it's been on the menu for a while so I'm surprised I never tried it before. My only regret is that I didn't take a picture of it before I polished off the bowl. I'll definitely do that next time! Pho Holiday has always been my go-to place in Austin Heights for great food and friendly prompt service everytime. :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNVFhY732bD9lfdS5xRbM8v--TtM-9arBdJ7DQT&fid=0x0:0x67373238d75c8118"],"When":"2024-3-25"},{"Name":"chau tran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJdcSjef95Ja-t2NY1EpbZAYMMQl0yANsuKnHISuTj9NgmlLQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Yummy food, cozy place! Curry Veggie noodle soup is recommended 😋","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNa8032K33WTDm7QlKCCRT3AG61uMsQ2QOsUBhu&fid=0x0:0x67373238d75c8118"],"When":"2024-11-23"},{"Name":"Jenni Tran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUfoMGgCjxjNl5-oajeOMf3off2y6SlHFRXa9nWrixIvJpM9ho=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Picked up a vermicelli bowl with grilled chicken and spring rolls and the meat was very dry and bland. The staff wasn't very friendly either. Seems like they had a little bit of attitude when I asked for a small container of chilli oil. Overall, just very underwhelming compared to other Vietnamese restaurants.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alana Cotton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL0BjBagguJl5UqSuBOUicH5WMmdzZe1BphC3SP1FpVGMEXTQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Everytime I've come here, I get exactly what I came for. The staff is super friendly and the food is very tasty and consistent. The fried spring rolls are one of my favorites and I cant find any other place that matches it. I come back here again and again :)","Images":null,"When":""}]

Finally have a chance to visit. Our experience is good. Meat quality is fresh and good cut. Marinated meat taste very good 👍🏻. Love the Korean preserved radish side dish. (We asked for refill). Servers are very nice with smiles always. If they can come to check on us more to refill hot tea and remove extra plate that will be great.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN8WjM559y3VhluTR4eECQe-jmQ0q672d683sJW&fid=0x0:0x2f8ab8e80275082"],"When":"2022-9-13"},{"Name":"Rebecca P.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWOtv1z9oQXsu_j8G9uE8jVQGZlbdGZfOgnrsP8gOev0iFfifM3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very good prices for the quality and quantity of meat! Under $30 for most bbq plates. Heads up, if you want beef belly, there is a requirement to order min 2 plates.

Their pork jowl was very fatty and thick, which was a surprise as most places give you thin pieces. I enjoyed their beef tongue as well. Everything paired up nicely with thier sauce and sides.

1 star off as service was not attentive. We had reservations and took forever for someone to seat us. We had to awkwardly flag a server down to take our order and they never came back to check on us until we were ready to pay.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMCknPI7zYS3JLALNos8BcHsOSPESlo-5WdSFHC&fid=0x0:0x2f8ab8e80275082"],"When":"2023-6-6"},{"Name":"Gina Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWUEH2BZpcTzOQnjuTeyPiJYzBdsA8VUMp3qYAeuxgNC4m6LJux0g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went Haan with my sister today for lunch. They have a Lunch special for $20. I was surprised with all the dishes served. We ordered pork galbi special. There are Japchea ( noodle) and kimchi pancakes and 6 side dishes. All of them tastes good. Japchea was a bit salty. Tofu soup was enough for two people. We ordered veggie wrappers with extra charge but cannot be missed. It served good amount of lettuce and they were fresh. I will be back for Bulgogi special to try on my next day off. Too bad special menu is only for weekdays lunch.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMVLZhiDsqeTrQwaFRuviaOGjZew40zxjUGKvFC&fid=0x0:0x2f8ab8e80275082"],"When":"2023-7-15"},{"Name":"Adrienne","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKvS1YiBi1kAYmplCTkzo9NqyjbLMViYayHxaEQA-dKyQUyyA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We’ve been coming to HAAN’s for the last few years, and we always have a great time! Korean BBQ is great for socializing and it’s a fun experience. Our server was very nice and friendly. We love their beef tartar and cold noodles. The sliced pork belly is also one of our go to’s, but we found it sliced a bit thinner this time. We do find it a little pricey, and they’ve started to charge for lettuce refills.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP5cUEhhBiNS7NzPkL-UHB_O6Ja5DwMWULnGQdc&fid=0x0:0x2f8ab8e80275082"],"When":"2023-5-22"},{"Name":"Kristy Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWEfZ2rjxNiODjhooQ3vu4wU52UFmMssx1nBEw-QrGtiP3D8nPb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The meat here was okay, but nothing special. The side dishes were a tad lacking and there was a weird aftertaste to the soup. The seafood pancake was not great either. I would not recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNR10nrBSV-NSZC5ntuOw2D73lo36RWKfk0gvs5&fid=0x0:0x2f8ab8e80275082"],"When":"2024-3-21"}]

There are lots of seatings and place feels cozy although it’s not modernly decorated.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPVkAABVg4eevF1I6oCFpu0QTXmgyKWVxDOERJQ&fid=0x0:0xb87d13d81937f372"],"When":"2024-10-24"},{"Name":"Justin Pak","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWawP6h5FHOMfa8ZuQwLzoBM7e_krAN0BBa5lEAONbqOUlt2g4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I’ve been going to this place ever since I lived next to this restaurant. I love the way this restaurant is built, looks very authentic.

Their pho is amazing, and I love how they gave us condiments for it.

I definitely would go here again. But it’s just that the prices are a bit expensive.

Overall 8.7/10

Pricing -1.0

Service -0.3","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO2MbkIZRLA3gHRNIGx9m-oFpEhsUrh_UYXkbRs&fid=0x0:0xb87d13d81937f372"],"When":"2024-11-15"},{"Name":"Jacqueline Cheung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIhcQScJBfI45a62J6HUgF8LhdTwX2F9dikSt8Dr0-Uf_ISbg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The smallest chicken wings I have ever seen. It is ridiculously small. It is even smaller than the spoon. Also, the portion of the noodles is small but the price is same as the other Pho with bigger portion. The taste is just ok.
And at last, I have seen the waitress using the broom swept the dirt on the bench. This is ridiculous!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNhQR-43-_7Rr1nsn2MaAvJ7jSrvIZD6IWmd2I8&fid=0x0:0xb87d13d81937f372"],"When":"2024-4-22"},{"Name":"Wida Bakhtary","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKgmsaBPgSGNcigt8T9JkvtwkBaXS-bwAcijbLe8B0cUuiXxw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Let me start from beginning I went with my kids to pho99 school house location.. I ordered #1 large and didn’t even start eating I get a long hair in it…then I sit and wait for them to get the soup away from me then she
offered a new one so I said yes no problem… then she brings another one there was barely any noodles or meat….full of broth  the meat that was inside my soup looked fully cooked to me it felt like they just used the meat from the previous soup I ordered. At the time I went to pay, they didn’t discount the soup with the hair, and charged me fully for it, as well as attitude and no apologies.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Scott Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHpW7vGME__Zs4wKjXR04Upnw88bkVVyz-H2288JsHocq9vI3r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I love the food here and it’s fantastic after a movie marathon.

The staff could be more friendly and the atmosphere is not the greatest but their pho and banh mi can’t be beat!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPES2H9j2hRyuDu8thBRLILS-0YpoxYgp6NvjOU&fid=0x0:0xb87d13d81937f372"],"When":"2023-8-16"},{"Name":"Angela U","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUsJrWHTO99bEAmPV3mlWN7nuQT--scHCqAwCk7vFO3-7Iku-md=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is our family’s go to Pho since 2018! Never gets disappointed with the food!!! The meat is almost always super soft, tender and juicy specially the ones on the rice platter. The soup is always flavourful and the spring rolls are so yummy!! I love their fresh lightly dressed salad too! With regards to the service, I think it’s more a cultural thing. The servers are probably not trained in customer service and I’m guessing it’s not a thing in their culture. But the lady gave us extra bowls and a pair of scissors even without us asking for it. She just did according to our order and seeing our baby!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNJOecSFA3csMi71vdBuzyDpTk4oNDfJWomv9V2&fid=0x0:0xb87d13d81937f372"],"When":"2023-11-13"},{"Name":"Ellen Tsang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXzoh866OovBfVlMHdFGLQnEdLyB97Utya-3yzGLsM4EYweL6y3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good but they got more expensive now.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPsapqGW-tw5Fx8BGp2LKSaN7L1xDH2gLSFWO6W&fid=0x0:0xb87d13d81937f372"],"When":"2024-12-19"},{"Name":"J Cheung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWL0BZ5HaxRtwQYUfB73F38XNmwqlCBtIEfl5nLaJnfdzlxAdl2qA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Food is good but I have been ordering for 4-5 times. Same dish chicken with rice. However this time the vegetables had a really bad fishy smell and taste that was pretty bad. I probably won’t be coming back for a bit… hate to give it low stars as previous times was okay","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Vivek Sharma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJYp1C5l327sjxI5T5cxPgV6Pmx3XlTZGysaP2xspHDo4iWuQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is the best sushi spot people don't know about. The deep fried food is so amazing, warm, crispy, but so fluffy and soft. Its truly an amazing experience. Great prices too. And what a friendly staff. Love to come for a special time whenever I can! Its worth the drive from anywhere to coquitlam! Trust me!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM3OYgYXrygxVSs17ig4YkYFkVdPi4ToboRZEX7&fid=0x0:0x70ede94a38b4b403"],"When":"2024-9-22"},{"Name":"Rusty Johnson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI4ymAI0f0o2WU902QSrg48zXGqcHFwOV2z_Z9nq6__IKEsHA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Big portions, great prices, good service, great food. I'll be back. Haven't been since it changed over from the original Mr. O. My dinner box had Iike everything you would ever want. Kids sushi came with glowing flashlights.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPpWEVDOsEU-_mvrBnWt8WpZNME6uLyTJgjQJJw&fid=0x0:0x70ede94a38b4b403"],"When":"2024-8-23"},{"Name":"Lana Han","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUWcXKPjpw8dJryG_tvzIMFSLPamG9klKTAGOKeFJikbZZWgu3S=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My family and I had a fabulous time at O Sushi.
I ordered Sashimi and Sushi Dinner Set; these days everything is pricier so I didn’t expect a lot but I was pleasantly surprised to see that there still is a restaurant that does not compromise either the portion or the quality (or the price) to provide an awesome dining experience for their customers. The sushi and sashimi were undoubtedly fresh and they were well presented. I was also impressed that there was a good variety of side dishes that offered different textures, acidity, and heaviness to enjoy each item and bring a good balance to the whole meal. I don’t know the names of the dishes but I especially liked the sweet and sour cold noodles with shrimps, lemon, and cucumber slices and the spinach with sesame seasoning. The portion was very generous and despite how delicious they were, I could not finish the dynamite rolls that came with the set.
The owners were very kind and professional; quick to help us when needed and checked up on us regularly to see if anything is needed. I, along with my two somewhat-picky kids and my parents, came out with full bellies and happy hearts after the meal. I truly appreciate their excellent services and food for making our night a very pleasant one.
I would definitely recommend O Sushi to anyone I know and will definitely revisit!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOCN6_rXv_IOLQZ2TxkssBuHlrN07pzgbNZjHV&fid=0x0:0x70ede94a38b4b403"],"When":"2024-7-18"},{"Name":"Mia Banner","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXo3YyYio9vqF7LApz-jbswxOpx_Sp7ljhFEieD1HcoYVfKW2b8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"overall O Sushi was a fantastic experience. the food was exceptional, the service was good and the place looked so cute, plus we got a miso and sunomono soup on the house! we only paid 30$ for 2 rolls and a meal set we almost couldn't finish because of the amount of food, we had a great time and will definitely come back soon :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3UsEnPjogymLXMB7jnrNb5J9kgDL5T-138Fpp&fid=0x0:0x70ede94a38b4b403"],"When":"2024-5-30"},{"Name":"Canada RT","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI4C6qox6x1Wgk4uK2xEpy2ZaXqNe2Qc2I1atkVwI9fwlu7bQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place changed ownership last week and was recommended by a friend,  and the chicken here is the best I've ever had. When I asked why, they told me they use raw chickens, not frozen, and only sell a set amount per day. I am now unable to eat any other ones.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOtAMiKP3OH-inwhPVxeLp99g_OJukJ1EkceEY7&fid=0x0:0x70ede94a38b4b403"],"When":"2024-3-19"},{"Name":"Paula Hlavacek","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXUEHsTUDREBV0VNUK6UGtTRNbBuCTOdBVYyLeZYC7hO1QTx25MLQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was so impressed with this sushi place! The aesthetic and the atmosphere is so nice compared to those average-Joe sushi joints. We had a 2-year old with us (which can be difficult at times) but they were so accommodating and understanding. 10/10 customer service, breath of fresh air when restaurant understands moms do their very best for little ones to behave but sometimes, it can get crazy. I was very impressed with the food; my favorite roll was the veggie roll + gomae roll, the peanut sauce was HANDS DOWN out of this world, I had to ask for extra! Definitely will be coming here again. Thank you","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOExB9Wg6z0ROGF-QGdSn0MYtLFO_GRfMtp1G3T&fid=0x0:0x70ede94a38b4b403"],"When":"2023-7-4"},{"Name":"Nancy Tian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXA9pyhOVC7-Kxqc8CAoujnMvQwIgaCs3eLnr8xR7YuMgUgZRo=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I used to always order food from the old ownership. This is the first time I ordered from the new ownership. The chicken is pretty good. But there is a lid in my sushi when I have the first bite. I probably won’t order from them anymore.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNmm5ZGVowCac-AYt0CK54hJcpUgkaaz0KKwmcd&fid=0x0:0x70ede94a38b4b403"],"When":"2024-4-7"},{"Name":"Angela","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKGRULjSoPL401HdNCtHc43NeCeVNTq215E6FzMkKQFGuH-8w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A true gem!! I got the sushi and sashimi dinner set, which came with ALL of the food pictured for only $23! I was stuffed and had leftovers for lunch the next day. The owners are super sweet and the food was both delicious and fresh. Can’t recommend this place enough. Lots of parking available in the plaza.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPrp8u6Dk73t8iYDEdYGZy6Gca4c-S1UT5vGDf5&fid=0x0:0x70ede94a38b4b403"],"When":"2024-5-1"}]

[{"Name":"Grimoaldo Assuncao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXU2Y0QnGVfV3sT7avvzv_BELncEzuG0SSyXqGRkB5XwNyC_gPK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Good place and ambient.

The double cheeseburger 🍔 is too small for the price. 😞

The shake is worth it and delicious.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMmClUL3KHnRONBOg8srseoN2JHOso2kWbFxKj3&fid=0x0:0x78e85e2236d6e103"],"When":"2024-12-7"},{"Name":"Marcus L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWAm1ka_ESYBlOFfTbfcnGmFcYKuqYakfSxihPN9UkLOeVieLhZ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Fatburger Lougheed
Located beside a bank of Tesla chargers and off highway 1 is one of the better burger locations in the area.
Friendly staff greet you as you walk in and the burgers are a proper burger with a lot of differnt options for toppings.
I wasn’t a fan of the wings lemon pepper and honey garlic bone in….. but then again it’s a burger place.
The restaurant was clean and food was fresh.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOYBeXv83_VEQYdvVSQl5OMDZakx7xZ7Ldz3DzG&fid=0x0:0x78e85e2236d6e103"],"When":"2024-4-22"},{"Name":"Al","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJke_H51lEVtqmQ6Mwhj0R5MqDW7L2xLlIdf0sg4kPFJFF0D9I=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I would call it a real burger 🍔 😋. Delicious taste and fresh ingredients. Medium size is more than enough, let alone the large one. Priced good and fast service. Also, free tiny toys for kids, which make them busy.
Seats are comfortable and are sofa style. They also have stools. You got Tesla? user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Y. Cherski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK-7SLlKKRW0Rqcp9wRXFlvt6gbh0rtI7PMIroLgxETtGiPwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is one of those spots where unassuming interiors hide some seriously tasty cooking. The menu is packed with interesting dishes, including a few uncommon gems—beef stomach and tendons, for instance, were fantastic, with the stomach perfectly tender. Sure, not every staff member exudes warmth, but somehow it adds to the charm, making the experience feel authentic. And the food is good enough to make you laugh it off anyway. With very reasonable prices, there’s no doubt we’ll be back for more.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOJ2e6UYNrIlMh_rgAhhykHS2ETwOpN9i4nrOv9&fid=0x0:0x93a798e9879e846f"],"When":"2024-11-30"},{"Name":"inspiringfoodie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXzYkilODPLPrJrijGHIEENNuCPV7ORM1oJ-GQTIuFySkOHKAh2jA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Stumbled across this little gem at lunch time on a Saturday. This is a no frills, reminds me of my childhood Chinese restaurant my Chinese Nana used to take us to. The portions are large, the food is delicious & the service is friendly.

We ordered the following:

PORK Turnover (aka footballs). This is a must order in our family & I daresay these are some of the best ones we have ever had. Where most places offer 3/serving, here they do 4. They were good sized, non greasy, crispy on the outside, soft & chewy on the inside &  it was full of delicious pork & mushroom filling.

Eggplant w/Shrimp Paste (a customer favourite we're told) & I can see why. The serving came with 3 large pieces that were each cut in half easily making 6 servings. The sauce beautifully complemented the dish without overpowering the shrimp & eggplant.

Pan-Fried Rice Rolls with Sauces. This for me is comfort food. I love the simplicity & soft chewy texture of the rice rolls & how they pair perfectly with the slightly sweet & salty sauces.

Beef Balls. If I had not had beef balls before I would say these were quite good. However, it being a staple on our dim sum table, this one was a little bit of a miss for me. I can't quite put my finger on it as I said they were quite good. I guess they're just a bit different than what I'm used to.

They also have a bakery attached & between the restaurant, bakery & takeout this place was busy!

They do recommend reservations for large parties & did I mention they have ALL DAY DIM SUM!!! Yes you read that right! They also do set menus & they highly recommend checking them out during King Crab season....I think we might just take them up on that. Actually we can't wait to go back & try all their other dishes so I'm sure we'll be back much sooner. We even loaded up on some of their bakery items to have later!

If you're in the Coquitlam area (even if you're not) & are looking for great authentic Chinese food, please check them out! You can thank me later!

@inspiringfoodie","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAt3YGpQFRMWcgR4M1k2pgMfufsHWPQlBa82GZ&fid=0x0:0x93a798e9879e846f"],"When":"2024-9-21"},{"Name":"Vancouver Foodie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI8w6jkWQhHhs1Z246avVvoKQqrR4N6KZDvvFaklq629YACSQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nice to find a HK style cafe in West Coquitlam.  The place is a bit small and old but the food was good. Services were great.

Tried the dim sum, HK style rice/noodles dishes and goodies from their bakery.   Overall, the cafe style food was great. Dim sum was not bad. The bakery food was not as delicious as we expected.

Overall, good experience and will definitely come back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMhJ-3mSMZKBWh9KGQX1RqChUkWw3_rBqGS2_oK&fid=0x0:0x93a798e9879e846f"],"When":"2024-12-9"},{"Name":"Geraldine Sangalang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcAsqfNVs6uRfmsJ5FtsU66GdsPGBE4zo_tn8DnG79e7VADqel9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This family-run Chinese restaurant checks all the boxes! Fresh dimsum and entrees everyday, complete with bakery, roast meats and seafood tanks.

Try the lobster with sticky rice. It's delicious and not commonly found in local restaurants.

Hototai is their House Special Soup. Don't skip it! This soup is a specialty that's hard to find.

Their siopao rivals the most popular Vancouver restaurants. Bonus: their prices are competitive.

If you're coming for dimsum, it's best to make a reservation. Otherwise, be prepared to wait.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM18ynZKtvsGECrxHKuhLwapxdUQ8KwwW4QBW56&fid=0x0:0x93a798e9879e846f"],"When":"2024-10-15"},{"Name":"Jordana","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLJvxqFr8nGL8vok-SCRwxhp2_EJmOiFDFc3qAUH70xw1rrHg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went here for an early dinner. Decent price for the size of serving you get. We got the Combo Dinner B and 3 BBQ meat with rice, and it was a lot of food for 2 people. The place was clean and quiet, and they have a mix of traditional chinese food as well as freash seafood. Definitely recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNB21r90eQph9y_SRlaw8DeP8bXWX2mXuR-Yhlj&fid=0x0:0x93a798e9879e846f"],"When":"2024-9-28"},{"Name":"Edric Hao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLJ29AUKmnqJC9Dxkn_eoSjQQWYbOxYNl_KbM5pBIBqVIvIBQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here to try their dim sum. This is probably the first time on a dim sum menu I saw items that had salt egg yolk so we got the squid with salted egg yolk. Let’s just say it was delicious. The rice roll with bbq pork was great as well. As you can see their rice rolls seem to be made in house fresh vs pre made and just steamed.  The tendon been with sauce was different by just looking at it but once you eat it. It will not disappoint

Needless to say we will return and maybe also come for dinner if they have a set menu","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPDsfnDGUjafpiL_64Jh_3Q1zIl7JRMRQva7UD0&fid=0x0:0x93a798e9879e846f"],"When":"2024-5-18"},{"Name":"Somewhere Out There","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUxyC1orGEQvfd-l7Mx11h63qB1QAGjP_8-pjtC_UJ7TA0EluWn=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"great food and service from the staff.
they have huge portions for the price so it's really a bang for your buck. will be back again some other time to try other dishes on their menu.

we ordered for dine-in beef curry on rice, sweet and sour pork on rice, noodles with beef and spicy fried tofu.

we also ordered from their bakery pork barbeque buns, wintermelon cookies and sesame balls with red bean paste for take out and we all loved them.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPXVTL9Lf5xpbLnWClSMnh_yCC7l7OEizsPRjh2&fid=0x0:0x93a798e9879e846f"],"When":"2024-5-5"},{"Name":"Gasing Yu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWrivAlnO0RJhFNK_ZMNUWHXNEM85KulKojXGTyuzNkPI_dtE8t=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We come here often. Not bad dim sum. The dumplings were average, but the steamed rice noodles were great! The house special chow mein was also great!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNjMWa0Uqo_AWScXIzliTekpfPYCcp69m4oAq7i&fid=0x0:0x93a798e9879e846f"],"When":"2023-12-19"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Pradyumna Gujjar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVHYwZPoeWTWb_r-Pj3URXZmwvjMuE8IJLkPSR4xqAVv86CR0HjQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"One of the better brunch places here in port moody and the neighboring areas.
The food tastes great, good atmosphere and service is fast.
We their the baileys flight, which in my opinion, could be improved. We couldn’t really make out the difference between the different flavors except for the peanut butter one.
The Maui Thai chicken burger was awesome and we was the Yorkshire Benny. I also loved their take on the hash browns.
They could definitely work on the pricing as we found it a bit on the expensive side.
Would def recommend this spot for anyone looking for a good brunch spot!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPToGwTm2g2cjL5bBjFYtzUui484e0jSqqK2tE&fid=0x0:0x4acbc2a73f7224be"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"Aaron Brousseau","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVrpCaHqR-XwUoFEei3pehP3F8y3p8zpxIo1yJXL2DI8WHkRvkE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had an amazing brunch at The Hard Bean Brunch Co. in Port Moody! The food was absolutely phenomenal—every bite was bursting with flavor. The vibe of the place was spot on, cozy yet lively, and the beverage selection was outstanding. Whether you're into coffee, juices, or something a bit stronger, they've got you covered. Our server, Josh, was fantastic—attentive, friendly, and made the experience even better. If you're looking for a brunch spot that nails it on all fronts, this is the place! 10 out of 10 hits all key points for a brunch spots.  Ps the patio was Lovely And is dog friendly which is a huge plus for me.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMNaHI05Lx6EisqaeHHwsYPAftWP6Jdr06aQfbG&fid=0x0:0x4acbc2a73f7224be"],"When":"2024-10-6"},{"Name":"Parneet Kahlon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqz_l5BzN5_mBY3QC7SEZWEVervEPkE_VocF-ECzkBQsGcdPO6=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a nice brunch place in Port Moody.

The place had ample seating and since we had our puppy with us and patio seating was perfect for us.

Food we ordered was very delicious and prepared in a timely manner.

For drinks we ordered coke and mimosa. Mimosa was good but we were expecting a nice tall glass.

Maui teriyaki chicken burger - it was very juicy and delicious…. 10/10 for the flavour

Hard Chicken crunch - Again flavours 10/10 chicken was cooked perfectly

Last but not the least, Hard bean co burger, very nice vegetarian options. Bean patty was very nice not too dry..

Definitely hoping to visit soon, been looking at so many more options to try.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO1KrvVRsRO_zbgmwGyZyuW9bPr71yR3bhKnNq5&fid=0x0:0x4acbc2a73f7224be"],"When":"2024-7-31"},{"Name":"Billy Lam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVSxOBk_c92Ol0FCdQI2uK9UOXNvJt85D76p4UHFqKR_gkp-zYHgw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve been to a lot of brunch places this year and I’ve always been underwhelmed by the concept of brunch. Well, The Hard Bean Brunch Co. broke the mold.

First off, amazing service, people were so friendly and helpful. $6 all day specials as well for drinks.

Ordered the Yorkshire pudding hard ham Benny. Out of this world. Probably will never order a Benny elsewhere ever again. The smashed potatoes were out of this world. Crispy on the outside soft on the inside. Wife ordered the quesadilla and that was equally amazing. One small knock was that ham waffle fries were a bit undercooked but don’t get that anyways, stick with the smashed potatoes!!

We will be back if we’re ever in the neighborhood.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM7JAnb6jeZFhYaQ6sJ8zdxRiRMdkaulczFv38U&fid=0x0:0x4acbc2a73f7224be"],"When":"2024-11-25"},{"Name":"Mandy Sam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWfdcmtmnw1QBUKzc568p_XlShrjauBmzaYnb3AklL4JCX7IFSL3g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"On Sunday, I visited the restaurant with a group of four for a late lunch. Upon our arrival, we were informed that the wait time would be approximately 25 to 30 minutes, which we were happy to accommodate. While waiting, we took a leisurely stroll around the area. After 26 minutes, we received a notification that our table was ready, and we were promptly seated.

The restaurant's interior displayed a lively and welcoming ambiance, creating a wonderful atmosphere and vibe. Our server provided attentive service, checking in on us periodically. However, there were instances when we wanted to place additional orders but had to wait for a while before our server returned. We ordered a diverse selection of dishes, including the rose spaghettini, Julius salad, everything grilled cheese, hard bean co burger, and hard chicken crunch. The handheld dishes were pretty good. The hard chicken crunch lived up to its name, delivering an exceptionally crispy texture. The Julius salad was enjoyable, although the dressing could have benefited from a touch more acidity. Regrettably, the rose spaghettini seemed to lack in terms of flavor.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO2M-uiySMHfptiI6rZzA40nKLqNvQnsjzaLR6d&fid=0x0:0x4acbc2a73f7224be"],"When":"2024-9-9"},{"Name":"Zain Bhanji","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKlgk8aN8btcOJZzZf5wvoL31ZimhDnrY-IWz_-xujZJutZcBjZ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This was an upbeat and lively brunch spot! Great music, cool set up and loved the colour scheme of the place. Service was quick and friendly here, however the serving sizes are quite small and not filling enough. I ordered the steak tacos and although I even ordered a side of fruit at the recommendation of the server, it still wasn’t enough to fill me up. I felt the resto could have been more generous with adding more meat to each of my tacos. Regardless, these tacos were quite small - pretty much a 2 bite eat, which in my opinion isn’t worth the $18 you pay for the plate.
Would consider coming back here but having something else hopefully more filling!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNShnQT9frNbDmQjQgCIY3Hm7YQJsMWry9askrq&fid=0x0:0x4acbc2a73f7224be"],"When":"2024-12-2"},{"Name":"Golnaz J N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwh094AvMjRiNSQoo9HjnFTPUMh8c3XSGOFZ78okUlI4KLdqnN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I tried the yam waffle fries and Bacon Burger with a delicious Green Salad, and it was an exceptional dining experience. The burger, perfectly cooked and topped with crispy bacon, was juicy and flavorful, offering a delightful blend of savory and smoky tastes. I asked for lettuce wrap for the burger. The yam waffle fries were a standout, crispy on the outside and tender on the inside, with a natural sweetness that complemented the burger perfectly. Accompanying the meal was a fresh and vibrant green salad, featuring a mix of crisp lettuce, juicy tomatoes, crumble feta cheese and quinoas. This combination made for a well-rounded and satisfying meal, balancing indulgence with a touch of freshness. Highly recommended for anyone seeking a delicious and hearty bite!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOUaR5a8FLR6B3otK7luPOQG3JxexiCAA5PCQA&fid=0x0:0x4acbc2a73f7224be"],"When":"2024-7-15"},{"Name":"Mounota","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvpiSPg9AtpTNs-8JJvoJHojdmAI1FZcME9pprQbBKumVFhadS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The atmosphere was pleasant. I had their smoothie bowl. It was okay; tasted a little watery. It looked pretty though. I might return and try their other dishes because the reviews are so positive.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMW-NUkGkpjmqUH4iPJ4DTyhMBN9ZyBBys53Ycn&fid=0x0:0x4acbc2a73f7224be"],"When":"2024-11-21"}]
