We went back there yesterday, and the food is still great. However, their prices have become super high, and some items have been removed from the menu.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPITDGlZEnNwHGC10MMb4CZiO8DxdVOnTTK8twl&fid=0x0:0xf02cfebfe9a5a06b"],"When":"2024-9-2"},{"Name":"bharath kumar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWrArQR5CNTfpJ-3PqgBOKGP7IWORRkhblrNfsjo551MSNh-bZl=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A good place if you want to try different varieties in chicken. We ordered full size volcano chicken along with Onion rings. The quality and quantity is so good and we loved the taste. We are family of 5 and we could not complete the volcano chicken basket. At the end we ordered the ice beam with browny which was ok.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNprxo6W-gR8ep02pZ4WEcEcWYtpq1JFBH0nH8a&fid=0x0:0xf02cfebfe9a5a06b"],"When":"2024-5-25"},{"Name":"hedy ekss","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXpcfSDI5FeUZWi4eiiDs727-zJ_KBtUvaWPX2aO9oWvoEwPWb3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great family atmosphere, or friends getting together for some good chicken and beer. They have different selection of Korean style of fried chicken. The Chicken soondal and monster green is our favorite. They also offer complimentary marinated white turnips on the side. I highly recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOK_K1jrLJxFL7GhaFGtcCWZnWMLNFWPSY-th7a&fid=0x0:0xf02cfebfe9a5a06b"],"When":"2024-1-16"},{"Name":"Scott Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHpW7vGME__Zs4wKjXR04Upnw88bkVVyz-H2288JsHocq9vI3r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I used to go here pretty often with friends before we go see a movie across the street. They serve you plenty of food and they're all pretty good. Unfortunately, the pickled radish aren't free, but if you go with Korean friends, they might be able to get it for the table for free ;)

As for the food, I recommend honey garlic fried chicken and kimchi fried rice!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPpuLdsoRzvKhEeBcGXGDgCne4fL72fk9kxfs-Z&fid=0x0:0xf02cfebfe9a5a06b"],"When":"2024-1-23"},{"Name":"Dennis Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJgBHuKaxB6_AGRs3DyAn5DYWAJVYL8OdZQBLbOlZjEJJMR8F5KA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The $9.99 lunch menu has removed some items , added the corn chicken is for $12.95. Here is how small it is in comparison with the radish side dish. Will think twice before coming back","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP1RBgiuWReUzSkm3pgVEgd6VnvsaUKBv6akXTe&fid=0x0:0xf02cfebfe9a5a06b"],"When":"2024-7-2"},{"Name":"Cody Pallin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVPwR3-Lwut2C8ymcu02f-sf0LdgPLffbKzY4RVv8SY-RNuLquS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"So many cocks. I love it.
Didn't take a picture because I didn't want it to be weird but great aesthetic. Loved the food, wasn't busy when we came Wednesday evening which really made it a hidden gem. Will come back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"임지희","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJHHbHVM7xbah01rMS3CXKtRLpC63-Qd0tzO9WR3gTLpDhm-g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"It was my first experience to this restaurant and I am never coming back. I ordered honey garlic chicken and it was the most terrible I’ve ever had. There was no napkin underneath the chicken except only in the take-out box and the chicken was all too greasy, soggy with too much oily sauce a bit  like a porridge. The meat itself didn’t taste good either. Within an hour into serving, it did turn into chicken in a greasy sauce puddle. I felt like it was a total waste of money and time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP_1QP9yV_E5o5tg76DD8HoDQvpIQoZM9tETINZ&fid=0x0:0xf02cfebfe9a5a06b"],"When":"2024-3-31"},{"Name":"Marcus","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUVpAqx3Judbzb0iuJXzx52iIPBZjNV225UkWQ26P-4HM5WbcSiFg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This place is a guilty pleasure for me! The chicken is consistently good across stores today I had the garlic chicken and that's sweet spicy chicken. Both were very good and came out promptly after we ordered it. I think big chicken town is a hidden secret as lineups are not long even though the food is fantastic! I would definitely return and have been telling my friends about this place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPuOU8FN1bJPscBDY3xO7XUXQcWxNd_0JIq9fZE&fid=0x0:0xf02cfebfe9a5a06b"],"When":"2018-6-14"}]

[{"Name":"phung pham","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKPbfrHCpvzKVUr-D7nEtzNxkvlcXQr_EbAjiww4SBYRwVFAw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Fuji Noodle Restaurant is one of the Chinese Restaurants closer to my home.  The foods and service were alright. Many selection choices you can pick and they open late so if anyone need late food you can come to try this restaurant","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNPKGlAvYB8pOCte1iK54kFOI9OIoEiixFk8AXi&fid=0x0:0x8e56f779bf6badbb"],"When":"2024-8-4"},{"Name":"Amy Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXXqddZyajPNoFhSfeKC0jxyRc2Om1n2-N6OKu8IHOhfMDJ3cE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Firs time I try this restaurant at Port Coquitlam. The foods and service were alright. Many selection choices you can pick and they open late so if anyone need late food you can come to try this restaurant","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMkgLXZ8VxQn-rxPXS0DUFtoxMSugLHxi2BzmFP&fid=0x0:0x8e56f779bf6badbb"],"When":"2024-7-27"},{"Name":"Michele L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVAxzJT5HVd70ieWgtRPnBYOI-3WdHBp602F9b2NQ3FhsBevYCm=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here on vacation and went back twice this trip! Super friendly hostess (she and her husband own the restaurant), large group friendly, great prices, and delicious authentic Chinese food! We especially liked the eggplant and green bean dish and the eight treasure duck, which is pretty hard to find. Also loved the desserts. They’re open for late night now as well!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNcysj9p0OG-pLVRPkQm85HbeWtFdNNep5WY0go&fid=0x0:0x8e56f779bf6badbb"],"When":"2023-3-10"},{"Name":"Belinda Jin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVQN2pGhoNzK76Clox_ElaIbflMT40WxZHUMqKpCiI5FtnukLZ6Zw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Fuji Noodle Restaurant is one of the Chinese Restaurants closer to my home.  We haven't had a chance dining at this place due to COVID. But, we always ordered take out from this place.

We already ordered the same food, such as Peking Duck 2 courses, sweet sour pork with pineapple, eggplant with spicy garlic sauce hotpot, beef shank in house special sauce hot pot and  spicy pork floss and string beans. The food very fresh and well cooked. During the holiday, the restaurant also provide free deserve to us.  Very excellent customer services.

The price of the food is a little bit expensive.  Hopefully, we can go dining at this restaurant when everything goes back to normal. I really want to try their noodles.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMKpMM1WFLa4MXEW9d39zC2IPQpkvUCsMvSak9D&fid=0x0:0x8e56f779bf6badbb"],"When":"2021-5-7"},{"Name":"Kevin Luo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWJMxLZr-3YvPOYEYkCwOqoRgX8yyWGLPYZ19IJEKzgIUssXc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great food at a great price! I had Fuqi Feipian and Claypot beef. Fuqi Feipian was warm for some reason instead of a cold dish, and beef cuts were too thick. The flavour was right on though. The claypot beef was great! The ambience is really dated despite the fancy light fixtures. Kudos to the owner for opening late!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMVHs8P1nhtQN_FBW5L-YjeVlQ7sBOg1epu_auH&fid=0x0:0x8e56f779bf6badbb"],"When":"2024-3-21"},{"Name":"DAN NOU","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVpYtBF7XkEge_dJaW_6qxQAvx0BMjlWIVs-s1F2tNjt9jcI0CG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This restaurant is newly renovated.  The service is good.

I order the beef crispy chow Mein with mixed veggies and was somewhat disappointed.  The flavour was bland.

Order the wonton with noodle soup and again the taste...bland

Order the 1/2 bbq duck and that was delicious!

Would I come back?  No, I would try other places.  Let me know your experiences.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP6ZKNCY8H_nnNhuWnMlq0htWxUf2mepI2qkc43&fid=0x0:0x8e56f779bf6badbb"],"When":"2021-8-6"},{"Name":"Andrea Koji","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKm8xDujv3m2blHf2s7xyhtk3tC4OIHJVLzBx6iM1thEBZ-eg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Don't order from this place. Placed an order through Uber and received dishes that barley have any meat in them. My ginger beer and it was filled with more onion than meat. Meat tasted bland and tasted like flour. Also Extremely skimpy on soup ingredients $20 for house special won ton and recieved bland soup with 4 pieces soggy broccoli and one piece of very fatty pork. I called to discuss with the restaurant and they refused to refund despite my offer to return the food myself. Extremely poor service. Don't waste your money.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPqcEZu8QrOhB5cClzpkvGVuNoaRB9qQl7US_s_&fid=0x0:0x8e56f779bf6badbb"],"When":"2023-9-23"},{"Name":"Tommy Joness","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIvM1yb66GYDWFmNjC7izCZ-8qnEQR4tC-Kh4aYxaYhJXkZNwI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This place is dirty and stinks the bleach smell was so strong we all felt sick. I went to the washroom and the lady follows me there and asked me what I was doing right after I asked where the bathroom was. She was rude and short with us ordering food and the food tasted cheep and was small portions my girlfriend found a hair in her food I highly recomend finding another place to eat.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Jay Ram","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJZkA1ehrIA4VnNy0PIxLOt0BXpiMfZdoXQo11n2kz7ZZx0ww=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I used to go to this place all the time when I lived in the area. I stopped by the other day for the first time in a year and the first thing I noticed was the sky high prices. $20 for a large bowl of pho is unacceptable with the amount of meat that was supplied is completely unacceptable. The overall portions have gotten smaller as well. I ended up spending $51 one large house special, one small meatball pho, and one order of spring rolls. I get that inflation is a real thing, but there are other pho options out there with the same, if not better quality, at a more affordable price. I don’t think I’ll ever come back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMTI8GwxOHdZLbG3qDKV924E_r5hll7-dApLXG0\u0026fid=0x0:0xd3b2509383ba609d"],"When":"2024-12-12"},{"Name":"70s Guy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLLpFEkMFgbYDe4BGpd7FdUKJSZCGFJjct_f3_FcWBpZ1Qx4Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great little Vietnamese restaurant across from the courthouse in Port Coquitlam.  Owners and staff are very friendly and attentive.  Food was tasty and prepared quickly.  I enjoyed a vermicelli bowl with grilled chicken and spring roll.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN-GSLwny-1Nf4ZhT2KPb5F0ahiLUwRtavL1tDm\u0026fid=0x0:0xd3b2509383ba609d"],"When":"2024-8-3"},{"Name":"Rayant Yeo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUaSGd8rGguK-MzK7O72I-ocdHyBHvKJG59MOmI710XLPYz1DeB_w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Friendly \u0026 Excellence service; served us with drinks immediately once we gotten a seat. The dishes were delicious especially the Pho; simply authentic.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOHKqK78B6cDzzuiNC10G-fo8KdwReZ3wOrBlom\u0026fid=0x0:0xd3b2509383ba609d"],"When":"2023-12-24"},{"Name":"Autumn_Kiko","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU1zcZdU411-b8f5Fcx7HImynMifJ7qg-_yzjSJzTLgmhJaggW_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Cute little inconspicuous Vietnamese Pho diner that has some Parisian vibes and your basic necessities for soup and vermicelli and rice dishes.  I tried the small sized No. 27 Pho with a side of extra jalapeños since they didn’t have the little red chili peppers.  It was a rainy day and we were hungry after our drive out to Tartan Town nearby and found this place in Google Maps.  For me rainy days and soup make the best pairing.  Especially when it’s a wee bit chilly outside.  I found the soup broth had slightly sweet notes and for a small size I had plenty of meats to go with the sprouts and chili peppers.  Perfectly sized for me and the price was affordable.  Also ordered up some spring rolls that came out hot and fresh and tasty.  No wonder this place is popular with the locals.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNzpbGk7esuvzRZC5gD3wjkp6AnnQHUenGP-f9x\u0026fid=0x0:0xd3b2509383ba609d"],"When":"2024-1-24"},{"Name":"Adrian W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKkC00uJkJsFbk_OdOD9rrYTPpj8QZN9D-8L5mx-4-sXG1BIw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food was perfect and the service was as good as it could be. My only reason for 4 stars is because it was pretty busy and the restaurant was definitely understaffed which resulted in a big bottleneck of service. Management, please hire more staff during busy dinner timeframes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNfglg0dhmsWeP2dhUZn-lsNEIIblpWun2WWJQx\u0026fid=0x0:0xd3b2509383ba609d"],"When":"2022-6-14"},{"Name":"Discovering V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIw0nwNgIa5O9CwW_XBE-aYX1t3_wGZTSaPfaYP36jNTmtocw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hello, i am vegetarian and the Veg Pho was just awesome :P The broth was flavour full and full of veggies and Tofu with a very good presentation. My BF took the beef pho and we both loved it. We also ordered the spring rolls - which were to die for. The chilli oil was the highlight of it all with a lemon grass flavour. We would definitely go again. The service was top-notch.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jason","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXCPn6z0JFTIZPgh1pE-4V1VNSKncUjzbuIqQfQ-OA3rQoJavMZ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely delicious!! Great portion and perfect flavor. Everything was spot on.\nDefinitely recommend this place. 💯","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rob Mckenzie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUKYMc54aGeQ2e0cqU4irUfWRI9HTjwHqMkkeRPSw0YLWi54uo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you like a spicy broth this is your spot. Always fast and super friendly service. POCO has a couple great spots for Pho and this team is the top of that list! I am here almost weekly.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Louisa R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJK3ST9Om4q9TA-nJ0W3Py9B2aqqqJYttJDPV_fbhJn2NszEw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dropped by after visiting the Farmer's Market and was pleased with the decision to visit. The quality and the freshness of the food is good and tasted good. The prices were also reasonable. We had the Chopped scallop roll, Rainbow roll, and the Volcano roll.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNJgYLGWwn1K5JJgBWNAPlA7N1CYkDnjyvSNzQV&fid=0x0:0x1df20d1659b81e20"],"When":"2024-8-16"},{"Name":"Maria Fernanda Guaraná","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU949zWMPKzgd78YIgipV_4PUI5bJb069xY2JNqEIjY4HsjgWnfzQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Found this hidden gem on Google! Food was very fresh and well made, sushi was one of the best I’ve had in a while. We also got some of their spicy fried chicken and it was SO GOOD! Crispy and juicy, the sauce was also pretty good and the level of spiciness was perfect for my taste. The atmosphere is cute and welcoming, our server was really friendly and service was fast..prices are very fair! Would definitely recommend this place and I can’t wait to go back and try other dishes.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"trentongrover","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLVQwBaIjS0DBOqwmNCbk7peJC-3TbK8aNhs0jIXgmSZEYnEw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Passing through the area, I asked trucks Nav for sushi near me. Up pops Awesome Sushi, sounds like I need to try it. The name truly says it all! Great sushi, nice small place with comfortable atmosphere.

Try their Jalapeño poppers!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORZLLEbBpqyDCRUERIoZo7SBaUnU9ejEsUKwbs&fid=0x0:0x1df20d1659b81e20"],"When":"2024-10-18"},{"Name":"Saeid MJ","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXcewSnJcAhACCkEWKUQGjPaBy78cIOsSGEe0B0nR_ARAnMiJU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I ordered smoked salmon cream cheese roll and spicy dynamite roll, which both were delicious and loved it. Just the spicy roll wasn't really spicy. But definitely will try other sushi here again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNUGYY3ulrzAaYBtxDrvqyMiXzkmBw6O8J0jE9x&fid=0x0:0x1df20d1659b81e20"],"When":"2024-9-27"},{"Name":"Martin Matahari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAn1gLSlBMeGXZBHUnKkSJRx9LUQmHP9VKEpiPVA6PU8EOwPbl=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My wife and I enjoyed the yummy sushi here! Miso soup was very flavourful and not too salty. The rolls we tried were very good, sunset roll, red dragon roll and yam roll were excellent. Perfect rice to ingredients ratio. The toppings were very flavourful. I liked the crispy bits on top. Not too spicy at all. There is limited seating inside the restaurant though. I would highly recommend this as a hidden gem in PoCo!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOu5kD4wX2JnZNcUp_ISc_jv_YitcT2GKbZzvxM&fid=0x0:0x1df20d1659b81e20"],"When":"2024-2-19"},{"Name":"Mel “雅慧” Lam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwpbcKV57q67MH16Pap78Z0NPVo3apLaU7yhpxrZCEPOSw4WXktQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was looking to try a new sushi place. This one didn't disappoint. Food and service were incredible. Despite having quite a few takeout orders, our food came out incredibly fast. The server was very thoughtful and pulled over another table to give us more room to sit and eat.  I'm only here visiting for a short time but will make sure to come in and eat here one more time. Highly recommend!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPoBtxF2S7t4aOVEVOr-iNP3XeQxH0BWYN5hBAk&fid=0x0:0x1df20d1659b81e20"],"When":"2024-5-18"},{"Name":"Sarah Woods","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV7JUbYP9UfvKcKjMTVtGVK_u-4I9H-snWOBROylNTcUUw0zoIdXA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"After searching high and low for a local gem, I stumbled upon this incredible spot, and will be my stable sushi to go☺️
From the moment I walked in, I was greeted with warm smiles and attentive staff who made me feel right at home.
The sushi is very fresh and tasty. I
recommend the dynamite roll and Montrose roll 🍣
I love the cute cutlery🍴 I know it might seem like a small detail, but I absolutely adore the attention to detail in every aspect of this place, including the utensils!
I'm already looking forward to exploring more of the fun items on the menu. This place has definitely won me over with its fantastic food, delightful ambiance, and exceptional service. 🎉 It's a gem that I'll be returning to again and again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM0_bB3DiuCW8dER5nMrgh2jMXjV-Na-pG3JKDy&fid=0x0:0x1df20d1659b81e20"],"When":"2024-3-18"},{"Name":"Jimmy Huang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVmaQe2WLp7herqsSS6Qbb3TdkPTjO2rKeO4tgMEL6Gag0kIT7k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Classic bento box (beef): It was delicious. Miso soup was great, tempura was fried well, the portion was right, and I really liked the plates and bowls. It felt good dining at Awesome Sushi.

Chicken teriyaki roll: I liked the sauce, the crunchiness of the chicken, and the taste of it. Really well done!

Thank you Awesome Sushi! Your sushi was awesome.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNPBOvmemlb_YpTGqlDLA3MzyFMppmrHa16bCYZ&fid=0x0:0x1df20d1659b81e20"],"When":"2023-11-20"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Tried the salted crispy chicken with noodle soup, the pan fried vegetable dumplings, and the steamed pork buns. I would say everything was okay but tasted very average and standard. Nothing was spectacular but everything was acceptable. The pan fried vegetable dumplings were unique with lots of veggies inside but the food quality was just okay. The prices are fair.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOEopXt7P9XaO398Ux0W5VH1g9lKsBQCc7hMr8Z&fid=0x0:0xfe65cbbea8e7ea72"],"When":"2024-11-28"},{"Name":"Linda Vu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4Mt-fIM1ZKQuO_Y2ib9yo6xFV3B1mBRBjrbB_M80tp5QNaP0e=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a family-owned Shanghainese restaurant that offers a variety of authentic dishes, including classics like Xiao Long Bao (soup dumplings) and Sheng Jian Bao (pan-fried buns). The food arrived quickly and was served piping hot, showcasing the kitchen’s efficiency.

The Xiao Long Bao were exceptionally juicy, with flavorful broth and perfectly seasoned, firm filling, although it does have thicker skin than Wangs in Vancouver. The Sheng Jian Bao, a delicious pan-fried bun, had a crisp bottom and was packed with savory soup, offering a wonderful balance of textures. Another bonus was, it wasn’t too oily.

I’ve tried the dan dan noodles and the peanuts were crunchy and provided an enjoyable contrast to the softer dishes. The noodles were slightly overcooked.

Bean paste noodles - huge portion and really flavorful.

Overall, the meal was satisfying, and the prices are reasonable for the quality and location.

This restaurant is truly a gem for anyone craving authentic Shanghai-style cuisine in the area. I’ll definitely be returning to explore more of the menu!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNuxP5sLptB9ZcK4lC3Yc_W2-sYcT90eCwG1NlC&fid=0x0:0xfe65cbbea8e7ea72"],"When":"2024-10-11"},{"Name":"Absolut YVR","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVAKKuJBhDjQ2yvrY0bCIOExStNeMzrxg1x0ksL6cHk4jqCNjYH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A very simple , family owned Shanghainess restaurant.  Offering typical dishes like Xiao Long Bao and Seng Jian. (Soup buns and pan fried buns) Plenty of parking in the Henderson mall, this small restaurant is located in the heart of Coquitlam center.
Food came out quickly and hot. XLB was very juicy and tasted good. Stuffing was firm.  Seng Jian is a yeast type of pan fried buns.  Not much juice inside, yet very crunchy bottom. We tried a couple of the appetizers. Both of them are very good. Beef tripes and beef stomach are very tasty with enough spices which are suitable for most customers.  Personally,I can take a bit more heat on these dishe.  Peanuts were crunchy and gave a very good contrast of texture.  Overall, very good meals. Prices are acceptable for this area. One waiter was working during the non peak time. He got it under control. This restaurant definitely is a find of Shanghai style food in these areas. Will come back to try some other dishes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPowPqVAQWIZmJTPGCbcenvK5pqxV7JGG_1LrFs&fid=0x0:0xfe65cbbea8e7ea72"],"When":"2024-6-18"},{"Name":"Eagleridge He","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVyk6k_xeBUj_1KDLC2dilz6BOL-9JcNSoxnyXWuMM0QdJPvjOF=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I’ve passed by this area quite often and only recently realized this place has a new owner. The inside is not quite big but enough to take about two dozens of people at the same time. Typical like many Chinese business makes you feel the floor is sticky and greasy. Server is super nice and friendly.
We ordered the Dan Dan noodle, spicy wonton, cold pig ear appetizer and fried bun. Overall tasty food👍 Dan Dan noodle is not authentic Sichuan style but cooked right with a hint of shrimp sauce. Fried pork bun is very juicy inside with crunchy bottom. Cold pig ear with the garlic sweet and sour sauce is perfectly balanced in flavour and also cooked right to maintain its crispy texture. Spicy wonton is also adequately seasoned and the stuffing inside is tender and moist.
Compare this with the other similar restaurants in the Coquitlam centre area, this one so far I think is my favourite. Highly recommend ✌🏻","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPR7T1HRSYoe7KouNA4KPd0pKLjaJxYJUSpYZ1A&fid=0x0:0xfe65cbbea8e7ea72"],"When":"2023-11-8"},{"Name":"Kate Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjE4MSAa0c4Uqc8iOt1LfqIkJDL1ULa2Z17gRh4YDWMExQ1A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Reminds me of Wang's Shanghai cuisine near Joyce. Affordable meals. Good food.

XLB - the skin is a little thicker but I didn't mind.

Dan dan noodle - gigantic portion. Great value. Not very nutty. The noodle could be less cooked to provide a bouncier texture.

Zha jiang noodle - also gigantic portion. Lots of meat sauce. Same noodle note.

Salt pepper chicken - $15 is pricey for a side dish but it did come with plenty of pieces. Taste was ok but fried very well with light crispiness.

The waitress was super friendly. I would like to come back to try their pan fried buns too.

One thing I am wary off is that they already raised the prices even though they recently opened. I hope this doesnt come frequently.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOBKol3GnJ58qbwEfIbTrQmUDOncPgjvPvAX4ee&fid=0x0:0xfe65cbbea8e7ea72"],"When":"2023-6-12"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Juicy and relatively big xiao long bao (steamed pork bun), I believe it was 6 for $9.99, but a bit lacking in taste. The spicy wonton in chili oil was a bit better and it wasn’t too spicy and much tastier. The beef noodle soup had no much taste but the meat was soft and plenty. Overall, the food and service was just ok. It’s conveniently located by the Coquitlam Library and Coquitlam Centre. There is a covered garage for your parking needs.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNkvj6uE_L1Id5WfwSfKpETnHabM3WaK8bHbCFn&fid=0x0:0xfe65cbbea8e7ea72"],"When":"2024-3-14"},{"Name":"Comic名作復活","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWB807F1BS9C6IboDeJfeD8CJ-GjsvEK8ZHJI2Ry5ZDUkuF8BoWmQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you want to taste delicious and authentic Chinese noodles, this is the best I have tried in the Greater Vancouver area. The owner is very enthusiastic and uses high-quality ingredients. Each person can eat to be really full with an average spending of 15-20 CAD. There is also an indoor parking lot nearby, so you can park your car and walk there within 1 minute. If you don't know what to order, I highly recommend trying the pan-fried dumplings (item A7) on the menu. It's worth driving for half an hour just to have those. The second recommendation is the steamed soup dumplings (item A1). If you like noodles, both the beef noodles (item B4) and the spicy dan dan noodles (item B2) are great choices.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMwlkeNxp8Dh9rLQ8AZ-Cw9Bt5qFimsz2SyzT2I&fid=0x0:0xfe65cbbea8e7ea72"],"When":"2023-10-7"},{"Name":"Sara Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVlSF6ADXHgyatqSj3RdRyjxWuJp2qz8rnQN-QdhLw0IaUlXFq2=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Grand opening, so let’s go

we’ve ordered pork chop noodles, dan dan noodle, salted fried chicken and spring rolls.  The pork chop and chicken is really good, crispy coating with juicy meat, we like the noodle texture is al dente, We would like the dan dan noodle to be more spicy, and the filling of the spring rolls is a bit too wet, other than that, we enjoyed the dinner very much, the lady who serve us are very friendly and helpful, we would definitely refer this restaurant to our friends","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOBf9LHpkK_HZFEZELMjhQL0xT_sUMttsL7dVC-&fid=0x0:0xfe65cbbea8e7ea72"],"When":"2022-10-1"}]

[{"Name":"Dayton Thodos","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJV9JY4oOkjLyO9lR45ss9uXXi5Exxer4saXp5_WEPdsdlZMSI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ate here today. Had the chana masala which was very good. Only $9.99 for all their lunch specials until 2 PM which is a really good price. I appreciated the sign in their window and wanted to give them my business. Glad I did. We could use more people caring for our communities. ❤️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM7P_p5bi-KKlj17E6nrpIy_8Qw1DZ6FIr7Gun5&fid=0x0:0x6a0dbb1d99a6ada2"],"When":"2024-5-18"},{"Name":"JR","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK3_YGWEMNJWYNkYPArm1lJ_HP7RyEaBVSqqscwHuICtS_M=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Absolutely garbage "Greek" food, if you can call it that. I can tell whoever is in the kitchen is guessing at what Greek is supposed to taste like and they have no culinary skill at all, none, zip, ziltch. Stop selling this food immediately. It belongs in the trash. Sorry not sorry you shouldn't be selling this, you're ripping people off.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Byron Lin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI1ZIkhKMx6Jhytrhte_ByMuWA-wf7fxdgXGR0uc8XVcrVhDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great middle eastern food at affordable prices.

Got their beef shami lunch special with a mango lassi for $15.

Tasted great and good portions. Owners were nice as well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOhcQk43-JRrjVLW-AoompYCS-XyyjI2JjL3NO3&fid=0x0:0x6a0dbb1d99a6ada2"],"When":"2023-12-27"},{"Name":"v","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVMalQNO5O3WgU0LxOYrpn0-JYQ9ou7NIB8ukVrbj1B_A3Hleze=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Sorry.......not great. We ordered the butter chicken and naan. The butter chicken had the consistency of tomato soup and frankly the flavour to match. Way to runny. I will say the actual chicken in the dish was nice, not too dry, but they hardly give you any. The naan was a bit on the chewy side. We are going to stick with our old faithful which is strictly Indian food. This place may offer too many styles of food which may mean they are just mediocre making all of them instead of being fantastic with one style. We don't recommend nor will we be ordering anything from them in the future... even though we only had the Indian since it was mediocre we are going to have to assume the rest is as well. I almost forgot... we ordered a piece of cheesecake as well..it was horrible, I actual think it had gone off and they smothered it with all this sweet sauce to cover it up. DISGUSTING. I hope we don't end up sick from the few bites we had before we realized there was something up. If I could give this place zero stars I would.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMnBSkxO-LuBP1CDOgiqV7Ke19lsi_tq2kPrRFW&fid=0x0:0x6a0dbb1d99a6ada2"],"When":"2021-8-9"},{"Name":"Jonathon Gagnon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJWthbVfHKE36MOK846jxUfBzBByHNknTZyAsz0C7lTAOrW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Absolute trash. $30 lamb roast mostly fat. Hard potatoes Rude staff member when I called. We have much better options in the tri cities. Embarrassingly bad","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOOtEEdC0q3sBBCsuthy7Z5uI-yPybnLqY8uC4&fid=0x0:0x6a0dbb1d99a6ada2"],"When":"2024-4-24"},{"Name":"Rachel L Ballard","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWr-srklsKskWjS7X9-4AIJrZem2BuSI0cPQTV50FmTOQvnByZ_=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Calimari meal was awful, only ate it because I ordered through Door Dash and was hungry. Greek salad had no dressing and was half full of white onion. Nothing on the plate tasted like Greek food. Maybe they do other cuisines better, but I would never order Greek from this place at all. Wish I could get my money back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO8BlmH2-mClq09VJ4q5kh6UailoOk9lZYvwcel&fid=0x0:0x6a0dbb1d99a6ada2"],"When":"2023-6-14"},{"Name":"Liam Moss","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWZPZS67TQqx3Uea76ERA7BRjgSHA5yKUONJDHUOaBBanw5cV7a9w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Their curry’s are unbelievable, as a Brit living in Canada I really miss good curry. The Pakistanis and Bangladeshis who run our Indian restaurants in the UK do a great job. The Indians who run the Indian restaurants here do a terrible job both in value and quality. Forgive me if I’m wrong but I believe these guys are Afghan, who have far more in common culinary wise with Pakistan and hence they make much better curry then Sirdaarjii. Bravo, I can’t wait to come back. Amazing value too with the lunch special, great for a work lunch.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tony Cima","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU7L4JEMxZTTSVa9798NKuFVKr18jcX25PgN9UVVk9MTGHQaVg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hidden gem for Middle Eastern and Indian food in Coquitlam.  Delicious food, very reasonably priced, with kind, caring staff.  Highly recommended!","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Tina Leggett","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIckDlE-Iom9xlT8tH-1e6JvJJcuBjfQBSICikXD8S-97S7fA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"TIPS MEANS:  To insure proper service.
This Chinese lady never came to my table ONCE to see if I was ok, to see if everything was ok, or to see if I wanted more water.
THEN I GO TO PAY, and she says…” no tip”
Me: Are you serious?!

NO SERVICE- NO TIP!   Go get some training as a server.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chad Kreschuk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVMSF-OwAx5OyYoFBKxn3JYIW-DaW-P5MyYwUFM9i1vlcx-gQ4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ordered from them last night, they used to be a go-to for Canadian style Chinese in Coquitlam. Dinner for 5 , more like dinner for 2 at any of their competitors restaurants in area. Everything deep fried was burnt and the chow mein had so much cooking oil on it im sick now today. I'm attaching a pic of their burnt up spring rolls. Yes i ate them anyways, less headache than dealing with these clueless people again","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNkfERA87_2y94Kn2xfaVJI6flYnRemU2nxmQNn&fid=0x0:0xa126f7ca0aa61686"],"When":"2020-2-12"},{"Name":"PowerHouse","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKA_tYB3h3knmJGdedxMyYfS5tpwB_va8gZAjAQvvs8knFVaw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Some classic, western Chinese food. Dinner special is a decent portion and selection of stuff I want. Tasted pretty good. Prob the best Chinese food in the area ever since New China Kitchen shut down.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Denise Cimaglia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLLuJRzc6IuSeM3ms2USxbhzUtN6ZoICq1LjQ7_HvGG8-u7QQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Save your money and go elsewhere!!! And definitely DO NOT use their online ordering. You won’t get what you paid for, and the store takes no accountability for it and blames it on the ordering site that THEY choose to use. They used to be good but the food has gone way downhill. It’s like they don’t care anymore. And when you phone there the customer service is terrible. Used to love this place but will never order again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Omar Alsaman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLk50B_a6mK7TKsqwCz87HppcvjGU9HfL1RFJUbVqMEzeuoSw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Literally best Chinese food I've ever had. Very friendly service. Everything looked clean. Food was way beyond my expectations and was super fresh. The price was really good for the portion I got. 10/10 forsure. Highly recommend!!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Randy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQqvVfPd3iWMs1a_CJkDE4WfhWJicNn9XzEw9yv1vaTsMp10rR=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Always  delivered  hot  and fast. Have family  from out  of town that really  enjoy ordering  from jays. Never been disappointed.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"John Petersen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKsTMaN9uPWdZHgIuQ2ywxhyLg2hdDcxnKrn8vr3MhZ5gqK8nvB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The food and atmosphere is mediocre. Also ordered a 3 portion dish to go and upon inspection the quantity was small. When inquired about it she wasn’t willing to adjust the portion or the price. Won’t be going back or recommending. Lost 2 customers.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Meghan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXx-nTmucE2EoJoVZKyDaURTIIYHhu2J5CMiEPqSTwPd9phTwUD5Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tried J's Wok for the first time not that long ago and I have to say it is the best food I have taken out in a long time. I recommend the crispy honey garlic beef! Great food, great service. Parking is a little hard.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Golnaz J N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwh094AvMjRiNSQoo9HjnFTPUMh8c3XSGOFZ78okUlI4KLdqnN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"While the flavors at the restaurant were good/mediocre, I found the portion sizes to be rather small, especially considering the prices. It left me wishing for a more satisfying dining experience in terms of quantity for the cost.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPwrpADd79VB_I10tydfiqVZopI4cNiy_xhuHjt&fid=0x0:0x165fca77eea385b"],"When":"2024-1-5"},{"Name":"Ayrton Reyes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUqaKyysn3U53NAKVb3xU5V20dgqy5rNRa3y-q25zmRfboMLVYC=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I think the restaurant is really good.
A small group of people serve you and they are super friendly.

I’m not to experience in Persian food (actually, is the first time I try it) and I like it. Specially the stew is sooo good, I love it.

So, go and try it, they have good prices and good flavour.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMbQzyJDBPy4CM0XwRO2cgJEuYNWGIuGIKSIwab&fid=0x0:0x165fca77eea385b"],"When":"2023-8-18"},{"Name":"Caspian Painter","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWvx-eR53dJSw__oa-ZvDP8mNQVyf77me-ZC-_9C7210bM7j-Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I order Koobideh with Joojeh,cheken boneless,with rice,was completely cooked and tasty marinated.friendly personal.cozy nice music help to have nice vibe.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN53TeWKSrnWNHLLDjCcPir-aAzAqYi9Vx5Cxov&fid=0x0:0x165fca77eea385b"],"When":"2024-11-9"},{"Name":"Romina K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV-S5jP3_k1CvTHIXok6wJMjW5UHsiiy2y476TICsrgpKIfmmVG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We were disappointed with cost of the food. We ordered Soltani and koobideh, along with zeytoon parvardeh, but found the taste and prices unsatisfactory.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMrbVbkTf4_grwLD3dKeNgT-7V2WiI84WKrqtnc&fid=0x0:0x165fca77eea385b"],"When":"2024-4-22"},{"Name":"Earl Flormata","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUHEYR5crfzT5mFZF5yY6PmVwTawXCmDPm3U8WVZUqH5mb8rOP9MA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Solid food - ok service. Calamari was a little softer than I’m used to but flavour was good (I like it really crispy). Lamb was super tender and delicious but the real MVP was the chicken - cooked to perfection and basically melted in my mouth. I’d visit again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPu-BeMkBT864bVacd4CCZOj0Rotd2hQMPdCcEi&fid=0x0:0x165fca77eea385b"],"When":"2021-7-9"},{"Name":"Reihaneh Kaviani Rad","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMqZSe1qXS1AsTFsph8ACG1GgtS7WyGZHzbxgpPr_5zFJRQUVb=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I recently ordered the Baghali Polo with Lamb Shank from this restaurant, hoping for an authentic Persian meal, but I was extremely disappointed. The lamb shank had an unpleasant smell, and it was undercooked, making it impossible to enjoy. To make matters worse, the rice was also poorly cooked and lacked the fluffy texture that’s expected from Persian rice dishes.

For a restaurant that markets itself as a provider of quality Persian cuisine, this was far from what I anticipated. I won’t be returning, and I certainly cannot recommend this place to anyone","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"n w","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX7UQDByN6t0nePZ4CYWGH0Dj4t17qJ_wKRbK-ykQWwq7mgd96m=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"One of my favourite Persian restaurants in Coquitlam. My go to is the koobideh and it alway delivers! The meat is juicy and flavourful! Sometimes you get lucky and get an extra few itches of meat.

Generous portions, friendly service and reasonable prices…winning formula!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNh5_dvVhZ2WdNhfcPAjtf7aQSYbNBeP0HeQYqR&fid=0x0:0x165fca77eea385b"],"When":"2024-1-25"},{"Name":"Carmen P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU-nb9czyY24UJWiII_N5K8yz1xXvygxnvgXKZGewDZPl_L__eb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A small restaurant that serves delicious and fresh Mediterranean food.  Portion sizes are good. Clean and nice set up. Good customer service.  The place is only a few steps from the Burquitlam Skytrain station. Will definitely go back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNjYw3P2bENtej52N6d1HZrIxpOAcnuITwjV-3Z&fid=0x0:0x165fca77eea385b"],"When":"2022-5-30"}]

Not sure if they changed owner's or what happened. We had family in from out of town and ordered the large family combo dinner. When we brought it home everything was cold, the fried rice had a very long black hair intertwined throughout the dish. The beef and broccoli had a few small pieces of steel wool in it. The portions are a lot smaller and very little meat was in the dishes. For the amount of money we spent for basically a lot of rice and noodles it's hardly worth it. We're now on the search for a new Chinese restaurant.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Hugh McNeney","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVKV9mefEt0CCZbzaaNjDBnhl9Fwv4rM7UfkyZVJX8pG0NVU7C0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Been eating here with my family for years. Summary, guys are nice but they should be so cautious!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMr_RBbyd2Q4ewa_qqazZ8ukJqVQa8MwHgROok\u0026fid=0x0:0x8dffe2c41565deb8"],"When":"2019-6-26"},{"Name":"Christina Holopainen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL7s61XcGxGEmo3hLCedz7DXch_BO6hg4DgSxKujtzSAH3mHw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"1st time customer ordered delivery was prompt . It is our usual Chinese Restaurant to go to when we’re in the area","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNyJm9cjgIqumentOEQkwKbPVzqyjaDu7uJnt5l\u0026fid=0x0:0x8dffe2c41565deb8"],"When":"2019-2-23"},{"Name":"Michelle Owen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUfH8cH2OtuZnx4NPrIqxD_D6XHSeHhhGwzafb2465umOTaDN_etw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely excellent! [{"Name":"Wing Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV3CwQO9cN_VmYBk6QsIpDB_ChUQLMcdHTqcHBMFHLumtEVmGxm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The atmosphere is very modern and clean. Food was good and I enjoyed eating here. I ordered the beef and tendon specialty and jellyfish for the appetizer. I wouldn’t recommend the jellyfish as it seems to just be instant jelly fish, but the noodles were great!

Follow @elliebellyeatss on instagram for more food reviews!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPIvruUosAdX0SHysFBZkltSPaGcIFHc6mblesI&fid=0x0:0xa320f621bcbc4c97"],"When":"2024-6-24"},{"Name":"Jennifer Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFO0fgPBTIA1yxL3IXSghRJ6EmshLC1YB1a72b-xeg3kpjHx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I got a bok choy noodle soup for takeout. Very salty broth but I don’t mind, the flavour was nice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMS7T447pGVXjSBSPW1mkuKeRaqLp_9QmCuP2mU&fid=0x0:0xa320f621bcbc4c97"],"When":"2024-7-19"},{"Name":"James Inouye","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUGMUsvXLijMfgZydLJhU2TpG1bqPFbrelq3iJSQAmmOzYoUfG8Bg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best Taiwanese noodle soup I have had. The broth and noodles are natural and made in-house. I will be coming back over and over again. Thank you.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN_3_4jjhSjc6e_Syz8u_-B2cGGkw8XpUpwgkWz&fid=0x0:0xa320f621bcbc4c97"],"When":"2024-9-9"},{"Name":"Shane Eaton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_agBuvtuLtmuC1xKO030XFkt4ff4uZuyg9JSmMnFCNqfVQepbNA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent beef noodle soup. Ordered extra spicy and my mouth is still tingling 15 min later <3

The dumplings are also excellent.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM8BEwA96Wf866MqKmaC6fU3vHPxO-gtjuBQoyu&fid=0x0:0xa320f621bcbc4c97"],"When":"2024-5-27"},{"Name":"Rebecca Hsu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXINu9_Z4eprUtdsP5cG8WffhMHEVpRJHo4TgiA5TXNfFUvuBY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Quick and friendly service. Good portions for the price. Food was delicious and authentic. Highly recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPXgWYeOWRIt2S3LxAz9idW91cvdeM-Xw1SgFbV&fid=0x0:0xa320f621bcbc4c97"],"When":"2024-10-14"},{"Name":"vivien li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLG2tFt_SO9L_6L1Y0aOdYjmJH9YQZalAnZHIVAe9gCaix6pA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We ordered beef noodle soup and popcorn chicken. Dishes were  so tasty and delicious! ( Prices were reasonable too .)
We Love the clean and relaxing atmosphere . Friendly service, hosts constantly walking around and topping up our tea !
So happy we  found this Taiwanese restaurant near Port Moody . We definitely will go back again and again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Albert Lynn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVDuW2wAraujurHAUmVoLugA8fzryDafkEd9CYWwjjAVSJ8FMLg1A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Gotta love a place where I know exactly what I want without even looking at the menu ❤️ Ding Hao Taiwanese Noodle House. The cooking and flavours here are always spot on, from their handmade dumplings to their signature beef noodle soup with generous portions of tendon. This place feeds my tummy with delicious food and fills my soul with heartwarming nostalgia.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOvJdS-RThFS8K2OeS7n5ydH-1rUMrJtG2yYzir&fid=0x0:0xa320f621bcbc4c97"],"When":"2022-5-17"},{"Name":"n w","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX7UQDByN6t0nePZ4CYWGH0Dj4t17qJ_wKRbK-ykQWwq7mgd96m=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This is not bad for what you can get in the lower mainland. Price is average and you get a lot more meat compared to uno beef noodle in Richmond. The noodles are a bit thin and lack the unique chewiness but still decent. The broth is beefy but could be stronger. I would recommend the signature beef noodle over the tomato broth as it’s lacking beef flavour.

Overall, I would rate it a 7/10 and worth a try if you don’t feel like driving to Richmond for Uno.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTwPlRMXqnJTB-l0r0Bz-NFKwxWr0mFb2PBeLS&fid=0x0:0xa320f621bcbc4c97"],"When":"2023-12-24"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Mina K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIqkiz0bzpa-16Pndf1kiK6M5DS6vr61upv2ilmD1PLQdXAb-I=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really good chicken, crispy and juicy. I ordered 3 flavours. The yangyeom and soy garlic are cover in sauce, it’s so tasty. The creamy onion comes with a small sauce on the side, just wish it has more sauce for that amount of chicken. It’s the best chicken in town so far.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPC3bXMUb8Wgdoo4_FkMUAtaamWzdnoEgX6IE85&fid=0x0:0x4276b8d959ef57bb"],"When":"2024-12-17"},{"Name":"Anna","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX98PrUHxEgks1p_UHXz6OQ_Vovq-hbr6NA6018tymH019sjnz4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went to finally try this place out. I tried the "Big Bang" (sweet and sour chicken with pineapple) their photos and description are a bit misleading. This dish is mildly spicy even though it says "sweet" on the menu, and they use smaller pieces of pineapple instead of the bigger pieces they have in their photos, it still tasted good but I didn't expect for it to be a little spicy. So, I would ask for extra pineapple in the future myself. I would go back to try more of their menu. I wish there was a smaller option for the Big Bang or a combo for one option. Good chicken here","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHN632jLVNxQQVGLcrL1nnVcwd10rxTsA_P2ur&fid=0x0:0x4276b8d959ef57bb"],"When":"2024-11-23"},{"Name":"Minipa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXLkpsoXCUt-uCoPDrB_Mv40ZqSioejOqdNEdMQaklHEBDE1W1x=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing food, made fresh to order. Clerk gave a bottle of water on the house on a hot day too. Very charming and funny man.

Cant wait to come back to try new flavours.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMI6ShFxLapYajTPoq2MC_sArGIkrzCbzLmve4a&fid=0x0:0x4276b8d959ef57bb"],"When":"2024-7-7"},{"Name":"Jag Dhillon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUtpdplh3A6xm-KZ7Hgdk0TvEmNi0MAclqn7NsyIPBJuuFEonw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best fried chicken I have ever had. Nice white tender meat, crispy and non- greasy on the outside. There’s no drenched oil taste or smell. Super tasty seasoning and sauce flavours. I highly recommend and will be back. I wish there were more locations.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kaveesh Kukreja","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXyGM5Wur1OIcPaIKHk8y8hADl72LlmzqOApRwMvp0cKEQAxid2PA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Our Boys at Hens Up Chicken serving up some Delicious Korean Fried Chicken without so much as an Instagram page even.
Honestly, those pieces were FIRE. The sauces could have been better but whatever they lost on the sauce they made up for on the crispiness and tenderness of the chicken.
We ordered the Trips Threat for $32 in which we got the Spicy Yangneom (Not Spicy at all), The Honey Garlic (Your Basic Honey Garlic) and the Pepper ( My favourite)

I also got a Mexi Ranch sauce on the side to dip which was like a mixture of Korean Sauce with Sriracha so added a bit of spice to the mix and it came with coleslaw and what I can only describe as Coleslaw Sauce.
Extra $2 for Pickles if u a radish is a must have guy otherwise I'd skip it.

Clean Place, Quick Service and Good food. If I'm in the area I'd re visit for sure!!

Rating - 8.1","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMXTQwYZvk6mT8chLPPpC85KpFRL3-ws8kYVK9F&fid=0x0:0x4276b8d959ef57bb"],"When":"2024-8-26"},{"Name":"Jimmy Huang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVmaQe2WLp7herqsSS6Qbb3TdkPTjO2rKeO4tgMEL6Gag0kIT7k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Half & Half Chicken (Honey Garlic & Cheesling): I liked the honey garlic, and would recommend having either soy garlic or honey garlic for your chicken. They featured two new sauces for me to try - one is soy-wasabi sauce and one is like a sweet white garlic sauce. I loved it! Thank you Chicken Hens up!

Upon my third visit, I ordered rice and soy garlic chicken. The server was very kind and gave me a side of coleslaw too. I appreciate them!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPRxTpMaPrF8s8qnSdSI3J873ZVw9YhgET7sDGN&fid=0x0:0x4276b8d959ef57bb"],"When":"2024-4-14"},{"Name":"Jason Park","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMhOEKKHXAe86LaxehFj_x7OVFNVhnJ9HjVRBWt_-JiYzZSRxP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing chicken, along with its sister branch in the coquitlam center.

Fried perfectly, and it does deliver the flavour!

The owner is super friendly and goes above and beyond. He recommended the onion sauce to go with the original chicken, gave me a small portion of sample and it was perfect.

I've already ordered twice from here and I'm definitely be coming back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO1K094qyuSjiOqQpK8FYP3M8v-Wi3DZDWMVsfT&fid=0x0:0x4276b8d959ef57bb"],"When":"2023-11-15"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Called to ask whether it was open Boxing Day and luckily it was open. I ordered three whole soy garlic fried chicken and the snow cheese fries. All the food was delicious; however, I wished the soy garlic chicken wasn’t spicy. I also hoped that there was air holes to keep the chicken crispy during transit back if there is take-out involved. Prices are good for the portion size. It is located in a plaza with parking spaces. Negative was I stood waiting for a while for an employee to check up on me at the counter when I first entered the store.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP-S3RgkD6lOgogRVV5ZsDeUSvena19R34XWog2&fid=0x0:0x4276b8d959ef57bb"],"When":"2024-1-8"}]

[{"Name":"Jaewan Cho","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXeeuYxBbYph8XAcixzIm4CirQVDteHcvnNHgfoDFuGgZK4hjwjww=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best Japanese restaurant in the area for sure. They keep it very authentic. I take my clients here for a nice meal all the time and I know I can easily impress them here. Highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNAxHSEoLUBADga6eQCdxbhNQsrfQO_zZv6kUMz&fid=0x0:0xfa83b6009fefb79e"],"When":"2024-10-4"},{"Name":"Nat A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnjKr4KNFAObzj2bIvH9BRInxwKsSvEg1PM25bKfvhxtWZTWHoog=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I ordered Bento Box C lunch special (sashimi) and chose beef teriyaki with it. I didn't realize it was $1.50 extra when choosing beef teriyaki over chicken teriyaki until I saw my bill. Perhaps, I missed it on the menu. They gave a generous amount of tempura. The Sashimi was average. The tables in the the middle of the room are very close together and it feels a bit cramped. The servers were friendly and we did get our food fairly quick. Overall, it was okay.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM2c3MKGcJ2OD3MWY6OooOWjPspY02V2CoGINON&fid=0x0:0xfa83b6009fefb79e"],"When":"2024-12-16"},{"Name":"Karen C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWX8PZExk4CphnQ1v6ysYFCNnt0sZC6YO38ggZ99md7OcXiM6ZP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Their karei karaage bento is amazing, finished every last crunchy bones! Too bad their fish bento is only available during lunch time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMhA3kj3jEa0djOL457-1Bq40MsgSaSRtpb-UuE&fid=0x0:0xfa83b6009fefb79e"],"When":"2024-10-4"},{"Name":"Yumyum","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU2Ps7OMRb5Woekeu-WRhO2P9H6MQ739yHSEC9SvN4CQ52rgx4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hidden Gem!!!!!!!!!!

My friend told me to go Matoi Sushi for real, authentic Japanese food, and she is right! I feel like I’m in Japan again!

Will definitely go back again with family and friends","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORirW4pH-Y6ZKnF183d91JY7k7rytoJFMQuNaX&fid=0x0:0xfa83b6009fefb79e"],"When":"2024-6-27"},{"Name":"Delone Fournier","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXP-RQ8DTT_frU6BvP1FAtyHYm-OkBy2HxJ2hJi66NHk4FrWsbdhg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I was in the emergency needed a epi pen shot on the 18th just before Christmas  if i didn't get that shot  at eagle ridge i not be breathing
I'm highly allergic to red snapper aka TAImy parents are so am i the woman their said my food was safe
I ordered ebi sunomono California rolls oyster motitaki miso Ramen with added chicken and tea left the restraunt throat felt like it was on  🔥 started choking gasping for breath chest was tight could not walk properly was rushed by uber to eagle ridge hospital had the shot with in mins  or I be not here
I had the shot my tempature plummeted my heart rate droped
I started to shake felt frozen but alive one experience I never want again if your allergic to red snapper do not come here your life depends on it unless u got one of those over expensive epi pens that not everyone can afford to get

To the restraunt DO NOT CONTACT ME !","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNX4RyjxrrCMQlkv1r_TWUL_C2Xwtt6DocDRiA0&fid=0x0:0xfa83b6009fefb79e"],"When":"2024-12-21"},{"Name":"Jessameen Dela Peña","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9mRpmL8-ZJUG7UPFcnsjzRdxjABif-MswbO1rxgJyyWfns8Jd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A dependable sushi spot with prompt service and fresh ingredients. The nigiri was particularly enjoyable. It’s a good option if you’re nearby.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPHdUW__KfIobzy74dYr8v_GEGcqf6ShIkPH78Z&fid=0x0:0xfa83b6009fefb79e"],"When":"2024-8-24"},{"Name":"v l","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUdZvJxBhGRMKAh6ZoV-1pNG0RsqEMX0Q7xeTmMWZiQ1-rLiRu7Rg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"TAKE OUT AVAILABLE! New cozy outdoor heated patio. Vegetarian friendly. Come here regularly. Offers traditional japanese foods other than just sushi.  Oden, grilled marinated cod, ramen salad, chawan mushi, tako yaki, skewers..etc. The sushi is very good, too -- profesional sushi chef quality sushi, very traditional style, not"fast food" style.  I would avoid getting the amaebi as they had been ~slimy~ a few times.

It's not a large place so expect a line up, esp. Friday dinner.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNR0W71Q0s3oSJDbf5FTlsdS31b9lHK1sKY5_8t&fid=0x0:0xfa83b6009fefb79e"],"When":"2021-6-6"},{"Name":"Yoon Sean","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWykeIRDaqbY9Qv-u6DC8FhxgkU2wjAEYdo2ac2VeyBIlZtF-_W=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been going here for a long time and I highly recommend it! Every time I go, the service is amazing and the sushi is always the best. Not only that, the hot food is also delicious.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPr5IJmMXCLNgz36x2aN0PwWlIzRSHw5ZdYrwzJ&fid=0x0:0xfa83b6009fefb79e"],"When":"2023-12-9"}]

You can tell they use good ingredients and everything is made fresh for you.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNPhRmgBLqR-_vjkNco41dbUmwiop_iVvBnnBC9&fid=0x0:0x130d623528e88584"],"When":"2024-1-23"},{"Name":"Rob C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVhGlLP_VJpl3qW9qoyQpsesE5pvucyY6kZX0X5h01hxsrvPnlBbg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Edit: I’m unsure how to revise my review. Initially rated 5 stars, but it’s now decreased to 3. The prices have been raised, and I’ve noticed another increase again between January 25th and February 23rd. Paying $18 for a panang curry of this size (its additional $5 for rice, $23 in total) feels too expensive, and unfortunately, my tofu tasted expired. This restaurant used to be my favorite, but the decline in freshness and the price hikes leave me disappointed.

Old review, Nov 2022:
Incredible Vegetable Panang Curry!  I ordered delivery today for the first time and after my first bite I knew this was my new favourite place. I can’t wait to come back.
My food was cooked perfectly. Tasted very fresh and hot: I had Thai level spicy. The Spring Rolls were really good, big and lots of vegetables inside.
Thank you!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP6BbEeS1BuJ7Y8b9VDiNAfiVpfFrnuMT37GnFj&fid=0x0:0x130d623528e88584"],"When":"2022-11-9"},{"Name":"Oindrilla Chatterjee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJm94R0PMP5L1aZDjmRRxz0E0-tAufioZ5Bi0a0wVzXdWXkyQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a small mom and pop store in Coquitlam that we went to after our hike at Bunzten lake. We didn’t know what to expect  as the place didn’t have too many reviews but were pleasantly surprised by the quality of the food. We were a large group and got a variety of items like the vegan and chicken khao suey, panang curry, green thai curry, papaya salad. Everything was very delicious, very well plated and very good quantities too. The server seemed like the owner of the store who was also helping prepare the meals. Very homely and super value for money. Spice level 3 in the appetizers was definitely spicy for us, so we made it 2 for the main course items. Highly recommend if you like Thai food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNnbf-uZeXo_KgjAIwmuXZllYb2LSr71zKgkhxu&fid=0x0:0x130d623528e88584"],"When":"2023-5-15"}]

[{"Name":"TS OS","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIrxJ8Fjd3bGSI8mWbF186RbFWyg_DW73VTS3OIkFaxPfXFBEQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Pretty good value and pretty ok food. I like their original Katsu, reminds me of home cooked Katsu which isn’t easy to make without making a mess. I will try their other menus as well. Last of all, good service by aunty. If you come to Henderson mall food court and feeling hungry, try Tokki for k food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPFE0GO7HbLutkDxsuv5rZzdNG9miEwxLRWrsP&fid=0x0:0xc4d0a3f8d7b70dc7"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"Ryan Blight","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbpH73lI2xtK9WJxadw5s8Ist4ItI3NEBYZImc9aopB1Hhs9lf=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"First time at Tokki. I ordered the Chicken Katsu Curry and it was ok. The curry was underwhelming. The Katsu chicken was cooked which is appreciated, but have had much better elsewhere. Staff is friendly. Fun to try, but won't return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNQsXflDAgPzCtUajtYc6dt5312k08qve-JSBQh&fid=0x0:0xc4d0a3f8d7b70dc7"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Lisa Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU2hRhOWIQf2ren7p1R3F9BVnb3q6vzlyk-JCc_U7cm7KJ7rH11fg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve been coming here for years. They have the best tteokbokki I’ve ever tried. The rice cakes have the perfect level of bounciness and the sauce is delicious. I love pairing it with the original kimbap and fried seaweed roll. I wasn’t a fan of kimbap until I tried it here, it’s the best! And the fried seaweed roll is so crispy and flavourful. This meal was $17 and it fed two people~","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOr0fNuopbSUyix1-aLFtwt3ikvPPsPLt9IZpbJ&fid=0x0:0xc4d0a3f8d7b70dc7"],"When":"2024-8-9"},{"Name":"Jason Park","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMhOEKKHXAe86LaxehFj_x7OVFNVhnJ9HjVRBWt_-JiYzZSRxP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"updated on 25/Mar/24:

I have visited Tokki two more times since my last visit and I can say that the food has been consistent and the quality was amazing.

I tried the spicy pork rice, and it was a great lunch for $12. Flavourful, good portion, fluffy rice and just enough spice.

The plain gimbop I ordered as a side wasn't mushy like last time and it was flavourful. I think the only thing missing was the sesame seeds but that is just for decoration. I'm happy that the quality of rice actually met my expectation.

I can recommend TOKKi to others with confidence, I'll visit again and try different menu in the near future.

===== Original Review =====

Had a high expectation after hearing good things about this restaurant from Korean communities and 4.2 Google review.
I would give 3.7/5.

Visited this place after the lunch hour, so the food court was pretty much empty. The cashier was kind, prompt, and professional. Food came out fast. I really like the 'buzzer' to let you know when the order is ready.

Let's talk about the food.

The rice in Gimbop (김밥) was slightly mushy and not salted enough. This reminded me of my mom making Gimbop for me when I was a kid. She always wanted to take the 'healthier' choice, so she put minimal salt, no MSG and used mushy rice for better digestion. The last time I asked mom to make Gimbop was probably 20 years ago or something :p... I always said NO or had to ask her to make it extra++ fluffy - then she makes rice that I like.

I'll still try their tuna/pork cutlet Gimbops.
Many Gimbop/Ddubokki restaurants in Korea make flavored Gimbops super delicious while leaving their original to taste like meh.

The Ddukbokki (떡볶이) was interesting. Maybe they use anchovy-based broth? It's definitely not my favourite flavour, but I do remember some traditional Ddukbokki places in Korea with such a taste.
Both the rice cakes and the fishcakes had great texture.
My honest opinion would be 3.7/5. Maybe some of my friends or my parents might like this.

The fried squid was pretty good. Decent portion, and the batter wasn't soggy. However, it wasn't crispy either. I always dip these fried items in Ddukbokki sauce and thus all deep fried items need to be extra crispy. If Tokki can make it crispier, it'll be a killer item for sure. Unfortunately, it doesn't have that magic texture yet.
4/5.

Overall, the flavor is rather traditional than what you would normally expect in Korea in 2023. I'm more used to sweet/spicy/clean broth/full of MSG flavour when it comes to Ddubokki.

I see a huge potential but some improvements would easily put them 4.5/5 restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPEuORF2JfYA0K6KvLPnx_jyFApjXWB3K6xx8qo&fid=0x0:0xc4d0a3f8d7b70dc7"],"When":"2023-10-9"},{"Name":"Daniel Jung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFE7g6vnjf23CW6mDeh4anchF8fxBs6O5Nsx0bvhepuO3MVzWa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Kind and friendly service. Delicious Korean food. My favorite is the Chicken Katsu.
Portion is excellent and price is good!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNoBtcK8YwH3acSJud_apsyDDZ9tU3c0IU0kxno&fid=0x0:0xc4d0a3f8d7b70dc7"],"When":"2023-4-10"},{"Name":"P S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW9_SUV2AZEgYqI-iDrgKDEPnF0aGqdTB7j1uqHpOg01SQ7pI2B=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great little korean fast food stall in the Henderson Mall food court. Quite a few flavours of kimbap that is rolled fresh and with a generous amount of filling, and they've had huge Korean Corn Dogs since before it was cool everywhere else at a very reasonable price! Service is always friendly and polite and pretty quick, and the menu is fairly diverse considering how small the stall is. The deep-fried Seaweed Rolls are also stuffed full and very filling, with a nice light batter. My go-to in this food court for sure!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM2OtjwZCddq6Nuh2KdF0clIt2Unk3SxjPi5Sbd&fid=0x0:0xc4d0a3f8d7b70dc7"],"When":"2023-7-20"},{"Name":"Aom Hildebrand","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUqzk0-t2eCJ3dWbzxrmO1EFkEGk94crNKQpEhBC-DrbexpqzAYfw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow, really delicious corn dogs! We just wanted something quick and simple, didn't disappointed us at all. What a good customer service!! I fell in love with their honey mustard, I never tried before which perfect with corn dogs. We all really enjoyed them so will definitely go back to try more in their menus. Highly recommend to try them out. See you again soon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNfbrEDIJrNjI4OVBJiaoD26iB_Kw5aPyXglsw5&fid=0x0:0xc4d0a3f8d7b70dc7"],"When":"2022-10-11"},{"Name":"T L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVlZv7_BS76hKZVl0Wb4gyyjBqUyJq5wa407QgwWRTbVcuuHoaG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"As someone who hasn’t had much Korean food, I can say that this food stall is approachable and also affordable! I’ve been told their food taste like comforting, homemade Korean dishes. I got the Original Kimbop ($5.25) which had a good amount of pieces and flavour, although I do prefer the cheese or tuna ones. I also got the Deep Fried Seaweed Rolls, which had a nice crisp exterior but a mild flavour. Paired nicely with the Original Toppoki sauce, which almost reminded me of spicy, tomato soup (in a good way). As these dishes are “combination” foods, they all pair well alongside each other.

Going back to the prices of their items, I find it encouraging to have cheaper price points, especially as someone from the outside - it removes the worry of spending an excess of money on something you’re uncertain about.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNKDwJpw8x7uKQAuiQmQO9vp_3-OUmFhRnkiQEf&fid=0x0:0xc4d0a3f8d7b70dc7"],"When":"2023-6-30"}]

2) Chopped Scallop
3) Spicy Salmon
4) Spicy Tuna","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMj_Gnd-JFxB5yktq55qwMMqu1xWfurruIYw2jf&fid=0x0:0x2ac8a04fb7238da5"],"When":"2022-1-12"},{"Name":"Joshua (ThickBurger_Bites)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbIhhMlbxk7OIMpcaP-aSx2m75kt8-mqmXoXAJQ5K99gnxiff1zg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Edit: Prices seem to have gone up slightly unfortunately.

Original post:
A gem in the Coquitlam area. New restaurant, and a great place to grab a quick to-go snack.

I’d highly recommend getting the staples; Crab Meat/Tuna/K-Spicy Chicken.

Prices are very very reasonable and two is more than enough for a quick meal meal.

I’ve been there two times in a day because the food is so damn good.

Highly recommended for take-out, celebrations, parties and social gatherings.

Staff are also pretty nice.

Prices range from $2+ to $3+ per Inari.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMeRtlbAVEDJS5WdL4FOM-JfAZKeUfOYjr22lb2&fid=0x0:0x2ac8a04fb7238da5"],"When":"2021-8-23"},{"Name":"Sophia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJYUILCDbu7lIgCx2qRlYTe2WXbAUV3TE2wXr0cfPierSsAVg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is awesome! The inari (sweet tofu) rice rolls remind me of the rolls my mom used to make when I was a little kid. Except the ingredients here are much more luxurious 😁 🍣

I personally recommend the salmon, tuna, and shrimp. The seafood is super fresh. I even loved the scrambled egg, which I was on the fence about at first. They torch the inari slightly on the outside, so it has a nice smokey flavour 🤤

The staff are SUPER friendly. My friend and I talked about how we would come back just for the service. They gave out free samples over the weekend for their soft opening, and I immediately ran to the store to buy and try all the other flavours! Happy to have a new cozy, delicious, friendly little restaurant near my house ❤️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMW-jHeDrfU6bt66mIWu5WsUl-oIrgQTxUDjRnb&fid=0x0:0x2ac8a04fb7238da5"],"When":"2021-6-14"},{"Name":"A Guevarra","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ2mSpAkgi4YrVkipkJUqb8bhzux5sQEQIjAxG93kMJ_HO3Ag=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Favourite spot for Inari. My favorites are the grilled scallop, chop scallop, and spicy pork! This place never fails. Fresh, tasty, and quick options for lunch, dinner or mid day snack. I'd say choose 2-3 inari per person and you're set! Great value, definitely bang for buck.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"O T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXNMZRDyPmCXOIYr2knffcKqnpyxzie7qHVjFWoC2-ZmJX5_do-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We visited this restaurant twice, and unfortunately, both experiences were disappointing. First, the portion sizes were shockingly small. We’re not big eaters, and we don’t expect massive portions, but we did expect enough food to feel satisfied given the prices. Both times, we left still feeling hungry.
On one visit, the server got our order wrong and brought pancakes instead of waffles. We decided to let it slide, but the pancakes turned out to be terrible, so we asked for them to be replaced. To our surprise, we were charged for both meals.
Overall, we were really let down by the food quality, service, and value for money. It’s not a place we’d return to.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPwTnR0sk7n_ze7mP7n_f-jOtfF0efbBswqsPUQ&fid=0x0:0x7ea0a39de7ea97b3"],"When":"2024-11-21"},{"Name":"Jennifer Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFO0fgPBTIA1yxL3IXSghRJ6EmshLC1YB1a72b-xeg3kpjHx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We took my mother-in-law out for a late lunch on a Friday afternoon.
