user_reviews:
[{"Name":"katayoun fathi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIt4RVxDsU0O9i1saXjwxFzJATudNmH_X0AFWg7oJguKfo6fgs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I had a very bad experience at that restaurant. There’s a lady working there as a server – the one with glasses – and she’s extremely rude. While I was eating, I witnessed her behaving very disrespectfully toward a delivery driver. It completely ruined my meal, and I couldn’t even finish it. My spouse and I were sitting there, and we were shocked.

Why should she speak so rudely to a hardworking woman driver, telling her she’s “blocking the way,” when all the driver did was ask why the food was taking so long? I saw the poor lady standing there for 20 minutes. But the server, a very aggressive girl with glasses, treated her terribly. This is the last time I’ll ever go to that restaurant.

The service was also terrible. That server kept us waiting unnecessarily and didn’t handle anything professionally.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sokolov Alexey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUIdRdPWeIS90ph1aeRePZ6G-sdKlolSkkqu7NaJG2zLuN4gz2N=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Calm and nice place. Not crowded, the background music was quiet and not distracting.
Big assortment of fish and seafood.
They serve sushi, nigiri, soup, lots of specialty rolls. Kids bento boxes are available.
I really liked ikura nigiri and rainbow roll.
Roe in ikura nigiri was big.
Staff is friendly but we had to repeat a part of the order a couple of times.
The lunch menu is available only from 15:00.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOtuSD5xezD79_q56e_KtYff_-TzD2Mu7dpwyIV&fid=0x0:0xce9dfb2bfa380a7"],"When":"2023-9-5"},{"Name":"Kevin Kwon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXCYT7BU_V3SI2IMbVzmDmEuQkuaR4AJUdkinmJF25w1grdjOYB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Shrinkflation is real. $16 total for a dynamite roll and spicy chopped scallop roll. What has changed?
1. Yam tempura instead of shrimp tempura. Dynamite rolls used to have 2 shrimp tempura IIRC.
2. Less crabmeat, more cucumber. 50/50 split now.
Overall, it isn't the store's fault that costs have risen so much. However, for $16, I feel like the rolls don't provide as much value.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMn7Vi7jFSuwuaGX_trPox4vdYgyGUXBApvtSbH&fid=0x0:0xce9dfb2bfa380a7"],"When":"2024-1-18"},{"Name":"Christi C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXcgq9JpIfJ5HaJSvpqHkX5vNrbeeAgd7PrWra2BvtkmNmgVJax=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food was tasty. Would get the stand-alone tempura again and look forward to trying more on the menu. Vegetables were fresh and crisp. Tempura in the special roll was soggier than expected.

Child was very pleased with post-meal gesture, and we very much appreciated the pleasant surprise.

Personal preference but I felt a bit rushed when asked quite often whether plates were finished with.

Bathroom needs sorting as woman’s toilet wouldn’t flush and the restaurant’s front door is quite heavy to open.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Henry Yim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXyAeUh2CClKb5j6bPCfm4WTuRVeJI0Sj2rgBonFkle79yB2OU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A pretty nice neighbourhood sushi restaurant. Friendly, Food is delicious especially if you enjoy the “localized” fancy stuff like”fFrench Kiss Roll” etc.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNLkHCqdpt5N8tsA0hz3Dg0FYpPaLFbEEL_1b-P&fid=0x0:0xce9dfb2bfa380a7"],"When":"2023-6-10"},{"Name":"Robert C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWWs1ZuGn1IU9hU9ywiGEtKCQ6RKJwKJrDWc_08WPFhc0a-deo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Our sushi escapade turned out to be more of a comedy than a culinary delight. We ventured into the realm of rolls, bravely ordering a spider roll among others. But alas, as if taking cues from a magician, the sushi rice decided to fall apart before our very eyes. The roll itself seemed to have had an identity crisis, comprising 10% crab, 70% cucumber, and a surprising twist of 20% lettuce. Had I known, I would have simply strolled to Save On, snagged a head of lettuce and a cucumber, and called it a night.

The adventure continued as we discovered that ordering anything with cucumber in this establishment is akin to inviting a vegetable tsunami onto your plate. On the bright side, it's an involuntary dive into your daily greens. Our server, possibly mistaking us for sprinters, could hardly wait for us to finish verbalizing our order before she was off again.

For those seeking real sushi over rabbit food, I'd point you towards Shio Sushi. The quality is night and day and your culinary journey might not feel like a race against time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPuNcE654GNPqVbyj1lDcHP5vwBkA7wbyaXsRmJ&fid=0x0:0xce9dfb2bfa380a7"],"When":"2024-3-5"},{"Name":"Chantelle Ko","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJvymNv8m0OjN24OoAK372hJnR2UcKCian5wKRAnKN34mbq8A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"First moved into the area during the pandemic and religiously and frequently ordered takeout and delivery. The food is about a 4/5 on a good day, sometimes a 2-3/5 on an off day.
I have recently started dining in and the service is absolutely horrendous. The servers are unskilled, inexperienced, rude, and snarky. They asked the only white person in our group if he can use chopsticks before we even sat down. The other server was more than reluctant and rude and snappy when trying ask where our appetizer was (already finished our mains) and for more tea. Then she was suddenly sweet and friendly dropping our bill off and taking payment.

After frequenting this restaurant for the last few years, I won’t be ordering from here anymore.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ariana Abedini","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUKNjWemH3JT4c-lZV9IuSCGGzTuGZDPVm9u6xasU8uvx3gj15E=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love the food! 🍣 It's actually the first place I had sushi at my very first time in Canada 6-7 years ago. I'm a regular ever since! The staff is also very polite.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPgPo61PA7gsO24pWkqGC4rKCuz7qra5_izX0NO&fid=0x0:0xce9dfb2bfa380a7"],"When":"2022-10-1"}]

Really really reasonable considering the quality of ingredient.  If you are in the area, just get it.  Super nice couple was making it in the back, really sweet.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMW9-s-XK5gzEbPRetC0eklx5lIYLXv5PW2JM8E\u0026fid=0x0:0xfc2c4fa1c3b8daa7"],"When":"2024-7-23"},{"Name":"Oye Finks","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUaMWKPLIdfdrlUdKDxK4Ba1O-0IE78b547hP2n5F7soMlgCG3o=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We tried the Capricciosa and the Gyro pizza. Both were not to heavy and baked nicely. The garlic sauce was a hit, really tasty! The pizza wasn't over the top or bad, it was tasty, overall ok. Just a heads up, if ordering through Skip, mods were not recognized on this order, we added onion and pepperoni to the Capricciosa, and unfortunately they were forgotten. Skip has streamlined the complaint process, we were refunded almost instantly for the forgotten items. Posted pics.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO0lIhiyYdt9d0z2w0shqzolW_C7sjeyRC8i6AZ\u0026fid=0x0:0xfc2c4fa1c3b8daa7"],"When":"2020-12-21"},{"Name":"Matthew Tye","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVZarAQ1-ztQzdNskNlTn1QG284VJIfhhqyXKrUc2OXclOuxY4T=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very solid pizza place. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow! All I can say is they serve the perfect piece of pizza. The dough to sauce to topping ratio is just right and the ingredients are fresh and high quality! Will definitely be back. My favourites were the cheese and pepperoni pizza because their tomato sauce is particularly delicious with savouriness and tang. Really impressed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNQoJx7_wzA3EbpOC8_CCBcxmc3Ce8LsytAcHZL&fid=0x0:0xac675e17aa1bdcfc"],"When":"2024-11-25"},{"Name":"W L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK87lyILn2l1GNJGaxosGEolmCjP2Is4zUBq1wgU_yTgsuEnQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Poco is lucky to have this gem of a pizza place. The pizzas are absolutely delicious and you can tell that everything they use is top notch. The dough is light with a slight crisp, not oily and greasy like most places- thank goodness. Generous with the toppings( it’s thin crust pizza so please keep that in mind) and baked in a gorgeous Italian oven. It had the perfect charred crust.
I think a lot of people compare this pizza to the other places next door not understanding that this is a completely different style. This is not your regular conveyor belt pizza with a thick bread like crust.
Was pleasantly surprised to see that they sell beer on tap and wine as well. They have an extensive menu with loads of options to choose from.
Friendly and knowledgeable staff too.
This place is a must try if you like quality pizza. 10/10 Reggianos, will definitely be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOw93I_3pXWCL818Bl_GgwtZK_YbmMbJJm8WPuL&fid=0x0:0xac675e17aa1bdcfc"],"When":"2024-9-22"},{"Name":"Jasmine Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJuOzS967Hz_egt9IQZrMH1_TOYLzJMv0RljQ3XzcQT0pp3BA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"For that size and quality and how soft and chewy it was, was definitely worth the experience! Sometimes other Neapolitan style pizzas in other stores can get too chewy and stiff but this one was perfect to the crust. Will order again for sure to try different kinds!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNNoegTFGywrC7JrR_cikpDdceJJ8eUE6y8PFGO&fid=0x0:0xac675e17aa1bdcfc"],"When":"2024-7-13"},{"Name":"Jennifer Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFO0fgPBTIA1yxL3IXSghRJ6EmshLC1YB1a72b-xeg3kpjHx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was in the area and needed a quick bite between appointments. They had a good selection of pizzas slices available and were also ready to make custom order pizzas. I got the last vegetarian pizza slice and it was good.

The dining room was spotless and they have a funky public washroom (see the video). A great place to get some fresh pizza!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOIrFqONmLFOti0GvALnnj31WmTRqYBB_pYUuyh&fid=0x0:0xac675e17aa1bdcfc"],"When":"2024-3-9"},{"Name":"Kayleigh Chapman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXggIZcln7wZ5SbxNQJuMEWmRbeK0R52nrQoptdEmgNElWW-c4LNg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best pizza place in town. Pizzas baked in the stone oven were delicious. Price was very good - my partner and I spent about $40 and had enough pizza to last 2 days. Service was fast and friendly. They also have a decent selection of good beer to go with. Definitely check this place out if you haven't already.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNmJlPBnmrd7vm1EyFdiehyVzbPEGK-9pin1iYH&fid=0x0:0xac675e17aa1bdcfc"],"When":"2023-7-28"},{"Name":"vanessa lucas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK6tWx3DcZm7qvPeZqBDVhnPAzsGDyE0VLCDhzoWWLQT0ORjw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hopped into this Pizzeria to have a slice of pizza and had a slice of heaven instead. We ordered the Regianno’s Deluxe and it was a sheer delight. The toppings were generous and fresh. It had the right amount of cheese and the crust was one of the best we ever tasted. The staff were friendly and efficient.

Will definitely be having some more. Highly recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP1_3jEEnB25tL_TMPzn40R0ZU8O-Fw0-yN48Dj&fid=0x0:0xac675e17aa1bdcfc"],"When":"2024-2-4"},{"Name":"Alishya Shroff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVzk4pbNxSWWBC4SdXDAth089lM_nR_IuBGHpbAw24vCEK5SjYzzA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had ordered pizza for my kids birthday party recently. The pizza were not only delicious but the quality was excellent. Everyone at the party raved about the pizzas, especially the kids..they thoroughly enjoyed every bite of their pizza. We had ordered margarita, chicken pesto, Fungi and pizza Verde.. all of them were excellent and at a very reasonable price. They even cut slices in such a way so it's easier for kids to eat. They delivered it on time at the park as well which was amazing as it saved time and stress for us.

I highly recommend Reggiano pizza if you want supreme quality and scrumptious pizza!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUss3Xiky_ua2bDX8b8zSa1uC7sAzx8dANwSqBcBq6pELbRRfQi=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We’ve had the Tuscan chicken pizza from here. And it has been very good. The centre is usually soggy which we don’t like and we do wish that could be fixed. Sometimes the bottom is undercooked.  As I move back to being a vegetarian, and then, hopefully, vegan someday, I was excited to see they have a variety of vegetarian pizzas… some with vegan cheese and vegan pepperoni. So I ordered that. Was very disappointed, the middle 3rd to 2/3 of the vegetarian pizza was so soggy, there was hardly any vegetarian pepperoni - maybe one round and a half per large slice of pizza…and where was the cheese? I will never ordered a vegetarian deluxe with vegan pepperoni and vegan cheese on it again. I will give Reggiano’s another chance as I said, we have loved the Tuscan chicken, hopefully the next vegetarian has more toppings on it, and isn’t soggy. See photo …. Litterly a piece and a half of veggie pepperoni on each piece 😕","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP2pBviGtRK3Lc7mIqDsth3Dx18EHRi28ebOY_L&fid=0x0:0xac675e17aa1bdcfc"],"When":"2024-1-24"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Goody Cambay","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVzukNWpr2_Cfsgh7ImX_QEvrvAvvbQ9OIWPLf3WTSrPOFO6uhX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hands down for all you can eat restaurant!

So much food to choose from.  The fridge display is full of food on every shelves.

Love the hot pot.

We went here twice in a week.  We are from Toronto and my 1st time at Happy Lamb is in Vancouver Area.  I would say I can recommend to those people love to cook and eat.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMZnkvj-kldovK5udWZxjr3U9A1qLPaeecBBF4p&fid=0x0:0xf8f3f48c50f9df8c"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Snoopy Kitchen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU3h-I-trbYva-Tzrs-UNhkQe4Nn1jgsblAcoQ0hPrnUWvugM3Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"All you can eat $31 for adult and $19 for 12 and under or senior.  Enough variety to choose from and soup base is $12.  Must eat: egg roll, chicken wings and black sesame ball.
Seafood: crab, prawns
Good for party and they have a vip room for 10 people.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOFHtUxWmb4x4zLfWk985sSSGVsZ8-Ixo8TXZVt&fid=0x0:0xf8f3f48c50f9df8c"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Edgar Ignacio","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV7oexz4qXoBKr6ujKuYxwMvlf16ckv-ovFMKFmC4nzUqeMSoelFA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Happy Lamb Hot Pot offers an incredible dining experience, especially with their lunch specials on weekdays for just $20.99. This price is unbeatable, particularly given the generous offerings that come with it, including free soda drinks and a variety of delightful side dishes like chicken wings, spring rolls, sesame ball treats, and chow mein. The restaurant is well ventilated and fresh air is pump inside the establishment making your experience even better and not smelling like food when youre done dining.

The hot pot itself is a highlight, featuring a wide array of fresh ingredients. Diners can choose from an assortment of meats, seafood, and vegetables to customize their meal. The variety is impressive, allowing you to create a unique flavor profile with every bite.

When it comes to the soups, Happy Lamb Hot Pot excels with their selection. From a rich and savory spicy broth to a soothing herbal option, each soup base adds a distinct character to your meal. The balance of flavors makes every dip in the hot pot a delightful experience, enhancing the taste of the fresh ingredients.

The value for your money is exceptional, considering the quality and quantity of food you receive. With outstanding service—where your drinks are refilled promptly—and the unique touch of an automated robot server delivering your order, it all contributes to an enjoyable dining atmosphere.

Happy Lamb Hot Pot is renowned for its delicious hot pots and efficient service, making it a must-visit for anyone looking to indulge in a hearty meal. I highly recommend it to everyone, whether you’re a hot pot novice or a seasoned enthusiast!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNtxiQCWygwU-yA4b3UYDg0tzGjNISXjzMUzvUK&fid=0x0:0xf8f3f48c50f9df8c"],"When":"2024-12-9"},{"Name":"Audrey T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVt7NSeCmrDxjN6eGFiHdOku-giePvd1JuUbLyAEp6odBtHY6vv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing all you can eat hot pot! You choose a soup base and then you can go off and grab all the food you would like. Great assortment of veggies, meat, noodles, fish balls, seafood, etc. The sauce bar is also stocked with peanut sauce, satay sauce, soy sauce, garlic, green onion, cilantro, etc. Unlimited pop is also included. You have to ask the servers for beef and lamb, but the robot is nice and quick. Ice cream at the end of the meal is a must!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMmYRn5iZrv9XQsnYw5UBD7gz7eu2xSo-K9GYOB&fid=0x0:0xf8f3f48c50f9df8c"],"When":"2024-11-8"},{"Name":"Anthony Plaxen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW0TosyGAQWTqM_XvTHaXfq2jDGHv6ifKWBgTGcJKYnap3ceipL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great all you can eat menu here at Happy Lamb in Coquitlam. The selection is quite good at this location. Similar to Bigway, there are plenty of options to choose from for the AYCE Hotpot.

Really thoroughly enjoyed the options, including the crab fritters, shrimp roll and the fried section that included chicken wings and spring rolls. Good broth, meat portions are quite large especially the lamb hotpot slices. Excellent price as well, about 30$ per person.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNNcjZMK2sZPlpyt8pBCl-Uscvj_Ckz6lMrOkZ-&fid=0x0:0xf8f3f48c50f9df8c"],"When":"2024-11-30"},{"Name":"Sandra Karr","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUWWQsE59qYe8OLpQlduEQcwVVpGB5oywtCQsLnhFibIfRwOKcd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Good AYCE spot (drinks included) unlike their Burnaby location. The servers are friendly (except Kevin, who can be rude) and there’s also a cute robot that brings food to the table. We chose two spicy soup bases and they were both excellent! I also enjoyed the overall atmosphere of the restaurant. Their service used to be a lot better, but I guess it’s more crowded now.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOB7C1c1B5BUHJB62BX3ApYEmYn1cBPU_DgqjnU&fid=0x0:0xf8f3f48c50f9df8c"],"When":"2023-12-18"},{"Name":"Aimi San Felix","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVuaz_nAesiVaBCEvPNDgiT8Hi9tbV_Lq9ORK-eYU4UPo26WalVUw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Me and my family had our tummies full. I love the chicken wings they had. Really good broths and lots of hot pot topping choices. A little pricey but overall great tasting food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMLQhn4J_f-innbI3QaLgrmrhxcJWd0qd5IgGVT&fid=0x0:0xf8f3f48c50f9df8c"],"When":"2024-8-19"},{"Name":"J. P.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIrHbZiN3iiiz0GyNU5ncp-CUVfhI2sIpnnw2Sge7_YT87E=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had 'All You Can Eat' hot pot ($29.99 after 8 pm). The food was good. Various ingridients to choose from and there were even chicken wings. Pops also included. Loved the broth (especially the clear one) so I bought a soup base additionally to take home. One of the servers, who looked to be in her early 40s and had a ponytail, was super nice and caring. We had a great time here!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNkkaGqJ8vLYEfQ103z7YfLuH5hmiUiUbbchTI&fid=0x0:0xf8f3f48c50f9df8c"],"When":"2024-7-28"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"N Bala","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXIn-ixFNj17bJSobYLeT7X0RAI7NKEGNiwAY1UO4Utugg8qdljqQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Awesome place! Limited hours of superb breakfast everyday - 9:30 am to 11:00 am - 7 days a week. Limited menu but very healthy and hearty. The basic breakfast is quite enough and comes with one portion of scrambled eggs, cube-diced hash browns, with either 2 pieces of sausage or few ribbons of bacon for just $3.79. Compare this to outside one for a minimum of $15 at the current inflation. Totally subsidized by IKEA for the customers. A great bottomless coffee comes at $1.50. There are few more items during the breakfast time - vegetarian medallion $1.50, garlic bread slice $0.99, samosa $0.99, vegetarian soup $4.39. Large Cinnamon bun $1.50. Muffin $1.50. My bill came to $9.72 for 2 persons. For other after-breakfast items, please check their menu with their transparent prices. Ample parking space. Excellent view! Fantastic bright and clean ambiance. Simply a heaven!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPXlHRpIbGEQcxCQ39xskWaWmh2Mo9KnnRQLh0b&fid=0x0:0x59278ff7cf09cddf"],"When":"2024-11-24"},{"Name":"Chloe Rachel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWgExGuK1W-XgQc1tPnrQlqQkWxCTaNhdz977uVTTY3zjpsAzs-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Our group had their Swedish Meatballs Meal, Plant Balls Meal and the Vegan Chocolate Torte. The meals are nothing fancy for $8.99 and $7.99, but as diners who visit IKEA once a year, the food has a nostalgic and comforting feel. The mashed potatoes were creamy, and the different balls had good flavour. I was a big fan of their vegan chocolate torte, which was rich and decadent without the use of eggs and gluten! I'd definitely order this again, and appreciate the vegan dessert option! Water is self-serve by the other beverages and is complimentary.

We unknowingly went on Swe-dish Thursdays, so it was packed for the lunch hour with many families in line for food. There was a bit of a wait, but the line moves quickly (finding seating is another question, but we were fortunate to find a table soon after paying). I was looking forward to having their Veggie Balls, but had to settle for the Plant Balls as they weren't serving the Veggie Balls on their menu.

The only minor issue we had was when we were paying full price (because we weren't IKEA Family Members). We were happy to pay full price because we were unaware of the Thursday special and were not signed up for membership, but the cashier had insisted we keep the receipt as they said we'd be able to get a partial refund on that food bill if we became IKEA Family Members at a later date. While we were eating, we signed up for membership, but another staffer in the restaurant area said we could only use it for future meal savings and couldn't get the refund. It wasn't a big issue for us, but we were left questioning why the cashier was insistent about a refund as we hadn't asked for one in the first place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMKuqoOjwtD_cF8WJfhhDxkulxgeMyJ_DngE1Xd&fid=0x0:0x59278ff7cf09cddf"],"When":"2024-8-3"},{"Name":"eddy wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8Fjpj3y8teHQ4LqbC4PHR8whbU4-XOrTXEwklI9bGRqZLRD20=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Friday Friday Friday only this Black Friday! Haha! I was in the area with family and we overheard that there was a special pricing on their breakfast.

99 cents for breakfast. That’s right! Definitely brings back nostalgic times. How can you go wrong with breakfast. Normal price is $3.79 but you’re getting your grub on for 99 cents. It comes with scrambled eggs, chopped fried potatoes, your choice of bacon or sausages.
You have to scan your ikea family membership for a free cup of coffee or tea.

It’s not a glamorous meal don’t be expecting something fancy but where else can you get a traditional breakfast in your tummy for 99 cents? Perfect for all you young bloods that are hung over LOL 😂. Cheers!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNERpfUDm3RduHXYePa14HNCdN3zgNkRpBdXflC&fid=0x0:0x59278ff7cf09cddf"],"When":"2024-11-30"},{"Name":"Fox hmp","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQDamDUP5o_LpyAHYzMLSTM2wh8oeibxwZqA9_fJNfLvrII5o=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very weak management and organization for customer service! After waiting 30 minutes in the line, we found out that half of the menu is sold out or they dont want to make the fresh one! The line organizer stuff was on the right sode of the salon and the employees were trying to move hundreds of people to the other side! But the food still tastes good and fresh.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO04pmEIy6LsLnKRnrJj8xzvQ4M5g8syAr0jzOL&fid=0x0:0x59278ff7cf09cddf"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Tried the haddock and chips and it was extremely mediocre and not the best tasting. The fries were good standard fries but the actual fried fish was super dry, and as seen in the pictures, even had burnt crust that was very hard and abrasive to the mouth. The quality was poor.

The NY cheesecake was barely edible and didn’t taste like real cheesecake at all. It was quite acidic and tasted very processed and not freshly made and had a very preservative heavy taste. Would not recommend the cheesecake.

The wait is insane and they appear extremely understaffed as there was one person serving food in each of the two food lines and one cashier for a giant crowd of people. The workers seem to be doing their best and appear overworked for what they have to do and getting your food is a bit of a chaotic process.

Thankfully there is a lot of seating and the self serve drinks are nice but when we went lots of the syrups for the drinks ran out and weren’t working and many of the drinks were watered down.

The IKEA food box outside is way better if you want food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHu0GnBDezHfCHc_KDB0jv3jW_IuYzxKY62JXs&fid=0x0:0x59278ff7cf09cddf"],"When":"2024-7-31"},{"Name":"S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIlresWC5ihFwmlqPDXUUvDy7NYECPjcTq6PKBfdWyBeF2JHw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The epidemic of mis-advertising has reached to IKEA too.
They show you the picture of their traditional breakfast in a relatively proper portion, but they give you close to half of the amount. I guess they want to make you buy two of them to get a decent portion.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNUcPZCwt8yvpqf3kWazzlcJ9C4F4sZuzLybu7y&fid=0x0:0x59278ff7cf09cddf"],"When":"2024-10-6"},{"Name":"Jennifer Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFO0fgPBTIA1yxL3IXSghRJ6EmshLC1YB1a72b-xeg3kpjHx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It’s cafeteria food, and it’s great for what it is. Cheap and cheerful. Lots of seating available on the Friday afternoon I visited. I appreciate the vegetarian options and I opted for the plant balls with mashed potatoes and peas. I can’t remember the name of the dessert but it was tasty.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAf0J7Q0nNqGngCf_PXziXAdg4I8QU8TlEHW2Z&fid=0x0:0x59278ff7cf09cddf"],"When":"2024-5-26"},{"Name":"Bala888","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKwpXKXLnWVbmRWE49mxf-yYsdsA4jpYsnTuSzc7_Jf6iiW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"First time tried the food here, actually it was not bad with this kind of price tag.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMdxX8oTSR1wNbJqcpwC1NZZd-27jNRyM_08M0&fid=0x0:0x59278ff7cf09cddf"],"When":"2024-12-7"}]

My friend asked for a specific type of wine that seemed to be at a loss for the server (which i can understand) and the bartender did seem to get what she was asking","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mohammadreza Behnejad","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbfFjgusvHBDGevsLnSFlRH6CqkrxaSYgN1dtBgif3eqTdhnw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I really liked the atmosphere and nice staff
Food was very good and we enjoyed it.
Portions are very good too. Small salad was like full size salad in other restaurants

They do not accept telephone reservations and it is first come first serve","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7jGYFtADxotCenEMt2iC3uSu0c7eiVtLF7ck&fid=0x0:0x52719b6f181eb19c"],"When":"2021-2-15"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Diane (Dineoutwithdee)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVJfHVJSjIKAcPEXNIfUcWAtOeYHaXavqJYPtVJZ3lhCbCbpeo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a great place to get authentic Greek food at reasonable prices. Great value here and delicious food, too! The place is busy so best to come early to grab a seat. I recommend the lamb shoulder, calamari and the chicken & beef souvlaki!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP42asUKI5KLp9y9RM9Fit82mrJ9Qd6-ziYb3Sh&fid=0x0:0x9833323042c6301"],"When":"2024-12-13"},{"Name":"Emily Lu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKEvwebxzOOvHfn2UnHwr4i_lsQ_4WBBcdmwEUmGOtZoyfwO9Mg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really good food and great flavour! The pita bread is probably the best in the lower mainland! The portion is also generous. We took the dinner home and that was a whole other meal in and out of itself.
The place is quite bit but it gets 80% full and becomes busy even at 4:30 pm! The space between tables is small so I had to move my chains/out of the way for people/waiters to pass through all the time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP_rakdPK5k-z808EXZ_h6jLZlPrNWM6u9uhOQY&fid=0x0:0x9833323042c6301"],"When":"2024-10-7"},{"Name":"duane r neufeld","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUhhlb1lcJQnDlyAPy1R2d_GOddZm-jMhyJJsiO9YhD02HRj38=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow these folks have it dialed in!!! Do not come here unless you have a LARGE appetite.  Monster serving size and you will love eating it all to the last morsel.  Every aspect of the food is perfect.  Come with your friend with a large appetite.  They will not be disappointed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNDW_s96eeWP-6cW7H05QxCPA7hObO2L0nmcgN1&fid=0x0:0x9833323042c6301"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"Justine H (Sunny)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUmvMXm-P_-zaDju2DtLb4mJNuo8OiXNtbw6zPhVOcICWtiAOQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great place! We ordered the calamari from their dinner menu and their souvlaki. Their calamari was very fresh and crunchy. Their meat was a little hard but you're able to request if you prefer it to be well done, medium rare, etc.

The restaurant is much cleaner than other Greek restaurants we have been to and their prices are standard so we probably keep coming back time to time. :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9BOPAe0Tu_IZ0MhDzHLYvccA1b9J6cef-PjwK&fid=0x0:0x9833323042c6301"],"When":"2024-7-7"},{"Name":"Bella Mills","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV9Ii_MUe1yBHkf4i7hAtgKoYsTZWvSgOMwOkR9qA3QXh9dyYpPrg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We are here at 4:00 pm on Saturday and luck to have table without making reservation.
Food and service are great.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNyHTwJlp2n1QQowmTTyN0vMGdc4AOtJgiUnj4G&fid=0x0:0x9833323042c6301"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Kate Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjE4MSAa0c4Uqc8iOt1LfqIkJDL1ULa2Z17gRh4YDWMExQ1A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good thing I made a reservation cuz wow it was so full on a weekday night. They try to squeeze as many tables in there and my seat bumps into the person behind me. Parking is limited to a few in front and a few on the sides.

We quickly got seated and ordered our meals. Everything was enormous. The mostly I've seen at any greek restaurant. Definitely worth the price.

Calamari was standard. I would have liked it with some seasoning.

The lamb chops were fantastic! I asked for medium rare and it was perfect and tender. There were 6 pieces!

The roast lamb was just ok. My husband likes the Stephos version better. It was a big chunk of meat though.

As with all greek restaurants, the carbs portion is way too much - rice, potato, and pita. The pita not soft unfortunately.

Definitely would come back for the lamb.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOATDXGeayXLsJ-091SfEA30U9Aiv4xc1ccZC0M&fid=0x0:0x9833323042c6301"],"When":"2024-8-9"},{"Name":"Jules Wilkins","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJNCphr6IWBKE7mhK1l34cq3DlSdkR802S6gSUfppAdFS2fhQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Every single item that came was cooked and spiced to perfection. One of the best restaurant steaks I have ever had, the potatoes were surprisingly delicious, the Greek salad had a healthy amount of feta rather than the token shake one normally gets, and everyone else at our table was very pleased with their choices. The price was reasonable and the service friendly. A bit noisy and crowded so nothing to rave about, but nothing to complain about either. The food, being well above average quality, was the reason to immediately leave a well deserved five star review.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"TK FIRE","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUMwgiWW4CWTw18dhib5ASUUbKOwvxPibgN0xFiOf9nH6Ji-EXH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's a great place for Greek food! The atmosphere, and food portions are exactly what I thought of when trying this Greek restaurant and they did not disappoint me at all!

I would recommend this place
The chicken isn't dry it's nice and falvorful. The chicken Santorini is a hearty meal, the beef and chicken souvlaki are great and so is the calamari dinner!

All great foods in a great space! Parking is a bit tricky but there is usually spots available","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMtkT9fytHaneOUKAwGkMRNUwRJnYjKLZx-52V1&fid=0x0:0x9833323042c6301"],"When":"2024-7-14"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"April","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKU_JwwXfd502_5uPpJ0cg8bzuPOCD-lU_roxsnKQpWzN9H4g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This is my second time ordering. Ordered premade seafood bowl last time and the amount of salmon and shrimp in the bowl was so small but thought maybe it’s just one time issue.

Ordered large BYOB today, and added extra salmon based on my experience last time. But the amount of total protein I got is equivalent of one or two scoop i get in different poke store. I tried digging through the salad to see if there are more underneath but what you see in the picture is all I got .. :(

I really hate to leave a bad review but for 25 dollars (doordash did offer 25% off happy hour deal so total was 21 dollars) this is not what I would expect to get :( The ingredients were fresh and loved the umami sauce! Would love yo try out pokerrito but I don’t think I will be going back for poke bowl.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNlWJ7KIrPCdNv1eNvir5VYUxtG4PF0LUe4yGjP&fid=0x0:0xa96818980230a45a"],"When":"2024-9-2"},{"Name":"S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJmvRXPt1uR-h9wzBQ7gvu3Mw7LXVhjVVQ6HaLxs-H4Cg1YdGw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious poke bowl - great size and copious amounts of toppings! the presentation is perfect","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMFEtS1Z3Jolp9wA8YFZG9JVLryd5Q2r5zPEsrE&fid=0x0:0xa96818980230a45a"],"When":"2024-9-5"},{"Name":"M Hamilton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLHG8GdHq5I6-mOUqVi4cC2yNBk1XXSYpaOlZE02ebzKaRnMg8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a delicious quick meal here with very fresh ingredients and really great service! The restaurant is clean and light and bright- we will define back! I’d recommend the roasted chicken bowl 😍 so good!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Scott Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHpW7vGME__Zs4wKjXR04Upnw88bkVVyz-H2288JsHocq9vI3r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It’s a great poke place especially if you’re going to get them delivered. They are quite filling for the price and they allow you to customize your poke to your liking.

I had the aburi bowl and I recommend it to anyone who likes smoky flavours.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNWwAve_yVl1bv6rZiO9kRP66NuJdNdAaXK-NGu&fid=0x0:0xa96818980230a45a"],"When":"2023-1-24"},{"Name":"Y. Cherski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK-7SLlKKRW0Rqcp9wRXFlvt6gbh0rtI7PMIroLgxETtGiPwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Pokerrito was the first place where I tried poke, and it will always stay special for me, so I was excited when the new location opened by my place. I can tell they might not be as busy in Burquitlam as at some other locations, but I hope they stick around as this area is about to get a massive influx of new residents with all the construction around.
I have only good things to say about their food. Great choice of ingredients that are always fresh, a solid lineup of sauces and interesting signature bowls. It took me a while to try, but pokerrito wrap has all rights to be a form of serving poke. After trying out different poke joints, I mostly eat at two chains, and Pokerrito is one of them – a staple of the Vancouver poke scene.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMmx_R7NaCGwb58h-UKB8sNColpip-IDURMEbJK&fid=0x0:0xa96818980230a45a"],"When":"2022-11-5"},{"Name":"Fernanda Nauata","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW9GQdgcgq5IMDtuJ2e1vR0Cjj0qtSmZsKJjBhEGJUsOJDDWOBr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve been coming here for the past two years, and every visit has been fantastic. The poke bowls and pokerritos are consistently fresh and delicious, with high-quality ingredients. Always a great experience!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"michele mateus","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUgFSf1yUGq2xdkVhBjzgbP2Wi4fm50mcfX5yAdtq7l6CG-y9wd5Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We love this place so much. The staff have always been so lovely and the food always taste so fresh! Has quickly become a family favorite.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jeeah Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqgJmPrySY_RgHzxjMFLcdtBqI7sy94lCU5W9nkMpV7ohYK2I9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I absolutely love & and recommend this poke place much better than the poke & co at the Coquitlam Centre Mall Food Court. I absolutely love their service, atmosphere, poke burritos that I made my own version for way less than $17 but for $13.60 to $14. Tiramisu tasted absolutely good & delicious & the cream of the tiramisu is way less sweet & yummy & delicious after I downloaded & signed up for their loyalty program on & Finished my profile on their Pokerrito app.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"yajun guo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLp7wWCAyL8N4BU9YzYEwjUr6kOHsh1skUFpYqXGLOUxa7J9A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I came to eat here for the third time. As a Chinese, I was curious about Korean-Chinese food for the first time. I found it very clean. The fried chicken and dipping sauce were very refreshing, not greasy at all, and felt very healthy. I continued to order fried chicken and special noodles when I passed by for the second time. I tried seafood rice and seafood noodles for the third time. If you like spicy food, you will like it very much. The portion is very large, and each time it is a super large portion.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMTAfTwvHwymurp-J2vwBYPXXMnCbm0sXglvKGA&fid=0x0:0x406e9883b66f164e"],"When":"2024-10-3"},{"Name":"YumYumCha","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK4DHzC88idd6SgF253zU976cjh24MUZrbY8_smo4XhlzY0-Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food is neat, and the seasoning is just right. The crispy fried chicken was perfectly cooked, with a crunchy, tender, and juicy—it was delicious! I highly recommend the fried chicken. The black bean noodles also had chunk pieces of pork and onion, and the shrimp tempura on top was a nice touch. The server was very friendly, and since it was chilly outside, they offered warm tea, showing great thoughtfulness and attention to detail. I’ve been a wanderer among Korean Chinese restaurants, but I think I’ll settle here. Highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPFsLKySnj8L1aFFgrRjiAYfGeU41qRSAV3M0b0&fid=0x0:0x406e9883b66f164e"],"When":"2024-11-2"},{"Name":"Anthony Plaxen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW0TosyGAQWTqM_XvTHaXfq2jDGHv6ifKWBgTGcJKYnap3ceipL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best spots in metro Vancouver for very delicious Korean food. Located in Coquitlam, the restaurant is tucked away in a small strip mall and is a real hidden gem.

We ordered a variety of different dishes for dinner.

The Pan fried black bean noodle was really nice. Quantity wise it was great the portion was massive. The different kinds of seafood, octopus, squid and shrimp really complimented the noodles.

The sweet and sour deep fried pork was also really good. It wasn’t overly greasy or soft, had a nice crunch on the outside and went well with a tangy sauce.

The fried chicken was good. A bit spicy but really solid. Crispy on the outside, soft in the middle and a nice mildly spicy tangy sauce to it with plenty of vegetables and onions. It was delightful.

The real star was the cream saewoo shrimp. They were giant, and the sweet mayonnaise drizzle to it was pleasant.

Overall, I would say that this place has better eats than most of the Korean spots around North road. Nice small location, cozy feeling to the place and the excellent portion sizes really make this a place I would return to and try other dishes at! Pleasantly happy, will come back again.

4.5/5 stars.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNbtAu5tsHye4FviiQk22PenEPzBEp38af73aQe&fid=0x0:0x406e9883b66f164e"],"When":"2024-11-10"},{"Name":"Yuko H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocInqidVGGQTic-c290lK_StdyV7mOrKdBnlV-toPbw96dF0KwA5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"All the foods we ordered in this restaurant were awesome. Sauce and deep fried meats match very well and saltiness was perfect. Spicy noodle soup’s noodle and the soup were very well balanced. I would definitely come here again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNYs9IA9ntiryCf_iH5tf4mZZGPC1UDeToksQ6O&fid=0x0:0x406e9883b66f164e"],"When":"2024-10-5"},{"Name":"Steve B.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLfl0h7LBzTP2I19EaQ980hbd2gVAQ-0Kn286XLsVt3NEFo4W0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Fantastic Korean-Chinese restaurant! I have tried a few well-known Korean-Chinese restaurants (Heeraedeung, Chuihong, Mokran), and this one definitely competes with those that are my favourite. We ordered Ganjjajang, Guobarou and Gunmandu. Jjajang came with a fried egg and a shrimp tempura on top. Sauce was perfectly balances with saltiness and sweetness, lots of crunch onion pieces and big chunks of meat. Guobarou was delightfully crispy and meaty. Wonderful portion size with raw onion and Serrao peppers on the side to cut the richness. The crispi was lasted until my last bite. Gunmandu was crispy and packed with filling. You can tell there's a lot of thoughts went in to enhance flavours and customer experience. This has become one of my favourite spots and we will definitely be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPXlTjvxd7uNO5JvJmPr1YW42O-UXN_nu90dgez&fid=0x0:0x406e9883b66f164e"],"When":"2024-10-31"},{"Name":"Hyeonjin Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWq_5Niw6_vOGJ1t98PmPXGiWLC5QW9gy12k8M5vGC5GBfyBZGn=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We ordered Combo A and it was absolutely delicious! Especially, jjampong was really flavourful with good amount of seafood and spice. The noodles came with prawn tempura on top which was unique. Recommend if you want good korean chinese food in the area!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOCfE9rkdwe366flRsP6tPaSax8nuJDYC-wX630&fid=0x0:0x406e9883b66f164e"],"When":"2024-11-30"},{"Name":"Seunghoon Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJco2avqi0qfqFvGJWQxBmq-mkjU0lhL81N6HBRohekzVHhJw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We recently dined at Hwawon and ordered: Ja Jang Meon, Jjam Bbong, Jab Tang Bab, and Kkan Pung Gi. Each dish was impressively executed, with the Ja Jang Meon offering perfectly cooked noodles in a rich black bean sauce. The Jjam Bbong featured a robust, spicy broth with fresh seafood, while the Jab Tang Bab presented a balanced, savory blend of flavours. Also, the Kkan Pung Gi stood out with its crispy texture and flavorful sauce. Overall, a wonderful dining experience with attentive service. Highly recommended.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNamWDmh0ALoCIN1cQO6MZLAK2XiNepXj1cuRoO&fid=0x0:0x406e9883b66f164e"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"RUBY KIM","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVPj3_c2BjQE_GHSbl5NNgqCC71CfL6cEjGyHAXHVJziWQq0v2A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Both crispy Tang su yuk, Urinki are so amazing!
The stir-fried flavor in the jjampong was bold and spicy, and the jajangmyeon was delicious too.
Good foods, Nice service🩷","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPRTg8cnPArFJO70eCDidGpzmNtfurym94qIuMD&fid=0x0:0x406e9883b66f164e"],"When":"2024-10-20"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Vancouver Foodie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI8w6jkWQhHhs1Z246avVvoKQqrR4N6KZDvvFaklq629YACSQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Love their beef rib kalguksoo - the noodles and the soup base was great.

Also like their rice cakes and sausages

The bulgogi hot pot was good with a lot of meat but it's a bit too sweet.

The seafood pancake was very crispy but not a lot of ingredients

The servers were attentive even though you ordered through the machine

Overall, it's a nice experience and we will come back for more signature food","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN-6WdDAeMZBYmWZJtZPAex39LhAvBj5zRytfUf&fid=0x0:0x86940e9c90894e2f"],"When":"2024-12-9"},{"Name":"Kevin (KC)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVrZpzDcm4xbgvb_oOynyP_bQvwIe7l-wMoPIs8L4UeVZ-waBkO=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Food was just ok for a Korean restaurant. Definitely a lot more expensive for what it is...

I believe the 5 star reviews here is from the promotion they have, however I don't care much about these 'freebies', so I'm here to provide an honest unbiased opinion.

We ordered the following for 6 people:
- spicy chicken (hot grill)
- soy chicken (hot grill)
- rose tteokbokki

The spicy chicken was decent but I honestly feel most Korean restaurants in Metro Vancouver have terrible value when it comes to price and portion. The spicy chicken plate is probably good for like 1.5 people...for 2 guys I would recommend ordering another side to feel a bit more full.

The Rose tteokbokki was just ok. It was basically just rice cakes smothered in KD Mac and Cheese sauce...at least that's how it tasted to me. You're better off just buying a box of KD Mac & Cheese on sale for under 1 dollar and cooking your own rice cakes with this sauce.

Getting a table was also quite difficult on a busy Saturday night. Interior and service was good.

Overall, it's not a bad restaurant, but it didn't blow me away...and for the price, there's definitely more options out there!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOFcKHNNPJK4GNYDXfAdPeGruK_89MtPuDMwSYd&fid=0x0:0x86940e9c90894e2f"],"When":"2024-11-13"},{"Name":"Brittany","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJs_km6RslliP6cTTiQcv7eI3BYv9_LkkJf-8xS0POhDRp70O4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Fast paced, loud but fun, family style dinner environment. Ordered a little of everything to try out this restaurant. Everything was well cooked. My favourite was the seafood pancake. Service was quick but very kind. Place was clean. Wouldn’t mind coming back here!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMeyckBCREpcGOtrV4TiHX_Rg09VVukSQB5j_KR&fid=0x0:0x86940e9c90894e2f"],"When":"2024-8-28"},{"Name":"andrew H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJI2Wi9Ocgr9nl3zo2CZ5YD9JRspbdoiyoPc3OsJIyx9rFIGQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I ordered the octopus/pork grill, katsu, and lunch pork.

The service was excellent—staff were attentive and consistently checked on my table. The prices are reasonable, and parking is convenient since it's in a mall.

The food was average. I had these dishes between lunch and dinner when no one was in the restaurant.
The spicy pork wasn’t hot when served, despite being on a small grill plate. The octopus/pork belly main dish tasted good, but the pork belly was a bit too chewy, likely due to using frozen slices. The portion size for the katsu was generous.

There are many menu options, and I can tell the kitchen staff put in a lot of prep work every day.

Wishing them the best.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOF1V1OgRVObatqtMLnx7ffc0ISBwVvfoJhJOb8&fid=0x0:0x86940e9c90894e2f"],"When":"2024-10-19"},{"Name":"Soung Son","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWHkihcNrKz3Cs19caeCuVOR-Yk29MFxtD_S6stmS9PXtHqts7w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The ginseng chicken soup is a winner on those rainy days and the spicy squid! The fried giant squid is huge! Great appetizer to start the meal! If you guys are looking for a variety of Korean cuisine dishes this is the joint","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNoLb_oLRj-ky5SumYTJ-riXnMxgH6tlde0TVNC&fid=0x0:0x86940e9c90894e2f"],"When":"2024-9-23"},{"Name":"Scott Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHpW7vGME__Zs4wKjXR04Upnw88bkVVyz-H2288JsHocq9vI3r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This was a new restaurant in the Korea town and I wanted to check it out. We ordered two noodles - one with clam broth and another one with beef broth, and a cream cheese corn.

It was very busy with only couple waiters and about 30 minute wait. However, when we sat down, the service was quite fast and the food came out very quickly.

The noodles were hot, and very fresh and I could tell that they were hand made. The broth was savoury, and rich, with clean finish. It was perfect for a chilly day. I preferred the beef broth with the ribs, and my mom preferred the clam broth. They were both delicious.

The beef noodle came with two ribs and soy dipping sauce that was tasty but it was not fall-off-the-bone tender.

Cream cheese corn was fantastic, albeit a bit too rich for me. But I think this will be very popular if you ordered it with a large party.

Overall, it was a very solid first impression and I would definitely be back to try other items on the menu!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPiLrqP_2vPn_Qtd2EmjtT56x4AHUUY9b3pCvR&fid=0x0:0x86940e9c90894e2f"],"When":"2023-11-20"},{"Name":"Michael Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjULDRH9Upm7RaDsdv5-9NJTh_dFOoUW6rNpRJuL2r1G2VRJjaEj=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The amount of food, and  the presentation cannot be better for this price point. The side dishes are also perfect, it is not too sweet or salty.  One of my fav Korean restaurants to go.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNqsXzTrZhhHdBGrVivxjlpNp6v0zhemqmwhbUo&fid=0x0:0x86940e9c90894e2f"],"When":"2024-7-30"},{"Name":"Gina Hong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXfZ29iyi8fMiV-imMeO82LQHxJ5EkG0srkb3BPOZWmXHaP_zQTQg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had an amazing dining experience at Kang's Kitchen when we ordered the King’s Hot Pot! This feast featured an impressive variety of fresh seafood and tender meats, cooked shabu-shabu style right at our table. The broth, enriched with flavors from the veggies, meat, and seafood, was simply divine. Adding kalgooksu noodles to the soup took it to the next level, soaking up all the delicious essence. For a small $5 upgrade, we ended with a comforting porridge made with rice and diced veggies—a satisfying final kick to the meal! The warm hospitality of the owner couple and the attentive staff made the experience even more delightful. Highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMcMMlfye1_bGN1UffGfsHbzBEkfjYmOi7r5mLO&fid=0x0:0x86940e9c90894e2f"],"When":"2024-11-30"}]

[{"Name":"leesa tran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUWsWaHyhzcw7kKPh9V3HkvTK5TTa81TdmCDp9IylYllx4puXIy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I love the atmosphere of the restaurant and the theme with all the decorations. I ordered the beef combo set and thought it was decent. The meat was good, I was just not a huge fan of the smell of certain dishes. For instance I didn’t like how the soybean soup smelled. I also thought that the side dishes that were provided could’ve been fresher. The kimchi tasted like it was about to expire.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNh8dMaX9wSwUxzcRy0JJEX8dOdc3SWHdN5vg2W&fid=0x0:0x92532fcedfcb5927"],"When":"2024-11-9"},{"Name":"Sun Ponzu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVl8cP48Co89qMnCKxozVPzyjjtsGeQaMdziBSwqhO6ZdMcYFPR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We came on a Sunday night, and the restaurant was half full. Service was outstanding as the server came to bbq at our table and waited until we finished each dish before returning to service the next dish. The highlight was defitnely the pork bungs (intestine). Was chewy and full of flavors. Will return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMtgmem7830J8kxKo2tAALXgzElRNt-yiy4Oh6O&fid=0x0:0x92532fcedfcb5927"],"When":"2024-11-18"},{"Name":"MAY 매이 Elford","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUxJVIiA7BVVmzUGqT6sRzP7-hCdYJttIOnYMeIvWOWZPmq7cr7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Keep up the excellent service! The boss and the servers helped out with the grilling, just like in Seoul. Love it! The food was delicious and the price is right. Lots of side dishes, especially the yummy steamed egg with cheese, WoW!!!
We ordered beef combo for 3. Lots of food! Authentic soybean soup was included. 진짜 맛있었어요. 우리는 또 올게요! 감사합니다.

I shared this restaurant with my friends and they’re going to try it this Sunday. Hope they enjoy it as much as I did. 🫶🏼","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMwbOScYY3BXOLGVwHqr3r8Hs8_lB7IY2SjWsPp&fid=0x0:0x92532fcedfcb5927"],"When":"2024-7-13"},{"Name":"Jin P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU5-zvnd8-jTmEBEL4lX2u3pn0_3gO6_vQVuKPoBTwcMzK4jIU1=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"my friend and I ordered the pork combo. The sides were delicious and plentiful. The kimchi stew had an authentic Korean kick, and the BBQ was excellent. The cold noodles were nicely presented and tasted delightful. The staff were incredibly friendly. We're definitely going back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPLX-O17rLspYfnPCl-BT_eYk7UWCeK_S6V09uf&fid=0x0:0x92532fcedfcb5927"],"When":"2024-6-25"},{"Name":"Jason D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV14HLbc6Ze7JZiJufUEhwiQ1I37e9rPxJ7pjEPsypNxuqatRs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Best beef I ever had in Vancouver. I recommend the beef combo and trying to boneless short rib (꽃갈비살). The server cooked it perfectly and it melted in our mouth!

The beef tripe was a bit chewy for our taste even with an extended grilling period, but the portions here are massive for the tripe.

Also the kimchi soup here is delicious, kimchi was soft and broth was deep.

Note that there is a 2 person minimum for an order.

We will be coming back many more times!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOIYmxkhtUYQFDOe_kuZ1XFkSuiNk-KVZqR2yM&fid=0x0:0x92532fcedfcb5927"],"When":"2024-12-16"},{"Name":"Tao Peng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU7GaN1E74aFMPYrHvw_woGDHZsPS-w8gJ1r-3t3I4tVhoKjCg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Was here two day straight! The quality of the meats was outstanding. Manager Chris were extremely attentive and friendly, ensuring our grill was always hot. The ambiance was vibrant and perfect for a fun night out with friends. I can't wait to come back and enjoy another delicious meal. Highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOc7MgVbPtBp2kfDVq53tU8EAf3sj_50n9YxGL3&fid=0x0:0x92532fcedfcb5927"],"When":"2024-7-26"},{"Name":"Hsu Jocelyn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJsQXz5FwnDvlr2SKHzFCqHQW4-Rf_QQEzACV6ESUBZYQcGLg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"They provide really good services.  The garlic beef was so tender.  First time trying the pork intestine. The skin was crispy, and the inside was chewing.  😋
It was a fun experience overall.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipND3ajTO0YKv_ePhPMN0doQ7_8h59lW58L4BH6_&fid=0x0:0x92532fcedfcb5927"],"When":"2024-9-29"},{"Name":"F David","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPg1W2eLpg6YoeWON6SoehGKkexxR9okjddl8ZVlUEvdGMA40=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food was pretty good but a bit more in the higher end price wise. For two it cost us, $110 before tips and we only order 3 different type of meats.

Service is outstanding though. [{"Name":"Shirley Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUtVjCop3ttC98a7Rw2dsGNsPeFIq4SZgEti2_Ra30Oi3BuM7GL=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Came here back in the fall. This is a great spot if you’re looking for a lighter meal that is filling but not heavy.

We ordered the Half & Half Dumplings, Hot Banquet Noodles, and Fish Cake Soup. Each dish was simple and comforting, perfect for dinner on a rainy day.

Service was lovely - the owner was super sweet and always checked on us to make sure we were enjoying the meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNr51A-dFV7PJqVp5fl4mY-esHNHaohHN78hXac&fid=0x0:0xad817352da7db699"],"When":"2024-9-7"},{"Name":"Yumi Chung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVPFqDkxESWXC88SASBBMb5TodqjqiFWci9IiQVgmoclWTpAqs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Came by here for a quick bite to eat, we ordered the half & half kimchi and pork dumplings, bulgogi & rice, and jjolmyun. Dumplings were good, packed to the brim with filling but I can honestly go without the kimchi dumplings. Everything else was very fresh and clean. The owner was really nice and service was quick. Wouldn’t mind coming back here again and trying their other dishes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPrG2EJQPTQVx4X-t_ZzeJbqeGSk2zw7Z_Ne6lG&fid=0x0:0xad817352da7db699"],"When":"2024-9-17"},{"Name":"Jonathan Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJlpk3IkzU6v8a3bWrkRzqWE5VkSKp4KIX1BX7iJPtSIAOmRw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Coquitlam has a lot of great Korean restaurants. If you want to grab a quick snack or lighter lunch this is a great option. The mini kimbap was a big hit with the kids. Fried mandu was crispy and the filling was full of chives and pork. The steamed mandu were only ok. I think they might have changed up the dumplings since the last time we were there because we remembered them to taste better previously. The noodles were pretty standard as well. Overall we would come back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORn27YcFs3RNqqM_B2hI9zOLlCO5NL1yFpNADA&fid=0x0:0xad817352da7db699"],"When":"2024-5-1"},{"Name":"Jason Au","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXuQkBpFBNxfDVCdPMZPlKNkod3AabrNZg7qk8g7qYjlMsYKR78=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love the dumpling soup here. Perfect for a cold and rainy day.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM0CfGkKgQpwdiiAgcdGx3j2SNZkPML1bGJoL76&fid=0x0:0xad817352da7db699"],"When":"2024-12-9"},{"Name":"Ess November","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWuPJ8X9jOZ2CtOO2jCad-r9UmiPcylLXs6WZsf1PzrAZBsBSHw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Tasty little Korean snack bar in Hanin Village. Tight quarters and usually a busy spot, but worth it for the fresh mandu (Korean steamed or fried dumplings). I’ll definitely be back! Highly recommended.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOtGX933PAv8i_W8sTPcdGpMJ_Mj9xyILI7bBF7&fid=0x0:0xad817352da7db699"],"When":"2023-11-7"},{"Name":"Kit Yee Yu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUy4hyLjXryzPjKJf4N3DUJBAsHtZSSuk76pvxFtVmwfHSV1Gtd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This Korean restaurant offers different types of food. Not like a typical one. They sell mandu (with pork and veggies/kimchi flavours) and different types of noodles.

It is a small restaurant running by a few Korean ladies. Once food is ordered, the chef or kitchen prepares and served the food quickly. I love the efficiency here!

We ordered chewy noodles in hot soup with fish cakes, some veggies, and eggs and spicy chewy cold noodles with a lot of veggies. Indeed the portion was quite big but we also ordered kimchi mandu. Each kimchi mandu had a decent size so we were very full. Everything tasted good here.

I would recommend this Korean restaurant if you want to try something different from a typical one. The restaurant is in a shopping complex so it’s attached to a parking lot. Although the parking lot is busy, it’s usually fine to find a parking spot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNd6BDcW-OUIGeFlhR_rwRJpfefMkDiQjazb1qJ&fid=0x0:0xad817352da7db699"],"When":"2023-10-22"},{"Name":"Galvin Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVUbsJhNSaPwctvmImowFs5hMwYYNdL5geQvWjpKuWtpVbHYuVS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My new favourite place. Menu is simple not having to decide too long. Staff are super friendly and welcoming. Food is fantastic! Dumpling soup was great the dumplings are packed with wow! Chewy noodles healthy but yummy and greta texture. The mini kimbaps. I wish I got more
Would definitely recommend to anyone.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tony Lim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUPpfNFEKMn-IMO25HPrOZdTVT7910ijEfpKPzGIkpJLSGoQg6w0g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very good dumplings! I thought I didn't like kimchi dumplings, but this place changed my mind. Apparently I just never had good kimchi dumplings before. The pork dumplings were above average, and the fried seaweed dumplings were also great. Also have to mention that the regular side dish kimchi was one of the best kimchi I've ever had in Vancouver. So good...!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPZuvQsenCd2w19iz9h3SybtGsPwYY5osjVERu3&fid=0x0:0xad817352da7db699"],"When":"2021-12-27"}]

[{"Name":"karl tamondong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLLY0bDAwvCnz6iiK9JJS-w3hLSzr85XHvxgOGetYvjidzhcg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great place to watch the game. Lots of TVs everywhere.

Just note

When you order wings it costs 50 cents extra to get your wings covered in the sauce or spices otherwise it'll come on the side and you'd have to dip and mix it yourself

Also refills aren't free they're $1 per refill.

Other than that my first visit was enjoyable","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOTi7h3FcuLY4U9OVWDfeTAHUBDJ2NkayWR6bdV&fid=0x0:0xee6a49b8baf2cca2"],"When":"2024-10-22"},{"Name":"Antony Nemet","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIpWKCwB0diWt-wfHCUSKBzVZvGKgsK2fD3w_KO1xqO1d58cA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We came by today which is Labour day. Our waitress, Jill was exceptional. Her attentive to our table without being too repetitive was top notch. The breakfast poutine my girlfriend and I had was very good and the wings, delicious. I had the Thai ones which were basically amazing!! If you are looking for an awesome pub that hits the spot this is it. It was my first time here and will be my regular bi weekly choice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMR-L40cVMpDajyg73z7gHRXmrdfEm--xogq_3D&fid=0x0:0xee6a49b8baf2cca2"],"When":"2024-9-2"},{"Name":"Patrick Chin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW9837XYJatBhh8uygAXZ5cFqnhdVU7CsJgBMh-TzrJtW8lVns=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very friendly staff. We got here early and found a cozy table. Our drinks were served almost immediately and our food came out almost immediately too.
The prime rib special was huge!!! And it came with a drink...
Highly recommended!!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOF-Jbcdqgbz0FVpvDE_t3n75W3KzOjtkROWkvR&fid=0x0:0xee6a49b8baf2cca2"],"When":"2024-7-20"},{"Name":"Lori Golden","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV6-VcfVSb5XiaNXuNybTZd8dFS8O8_6G4ifg6tWxwz1edWTIVr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We found this place because we searched for a great french onion soup in the Burnaby area.
We were not disappointed with the French onion, the flavour was amazing. It was lava hot as per usual and a great mix of onion to broth. The only complaint is, it needs so much more cheese. But everything else was spot on in that bowl.  The deep fried pickles are nice and crisp.
Our server was amazing and friendly. She got to our table pretty fast and the place was full. We sure couldn't complain, she was prompt and very friendly.
Three out of the four had the French onion soup and loved it.
Drinks were good even though I ordered a Coors banquet, it's been years.
I highly recommend this place. If you want to catch a hockey game this place has you covered with tvs
Pretty decent atmosphere and great food.
Chairs are a little tight on thick thighs haha but can't fault them for that.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNn6cxw9wCmHRrZgnWL28mahmi5Mgt9BClwZJnA&fid=0x0:0xee6a49b8baf2cca2"],"When":"2024-1-8"},{"Name":"Shaun Hrominchuk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWlIblBNrlAC9AHxGWFOyyH7azlov6mEjdLikax3qgbMNV7WzS-=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great Neighborhood Pub! Woody's Pub has chicken wings on for 0.59 cent each every day of the week at some point of the day and has a great selection of craft beers on tap. I would recommend this pub over chain restaurants. 5 out of 5 stars 🌟🌟 🌟 🌟 🌟","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOcWtdslWIv_lfGuVqDmIK-btk7hQoX6_dY5fH9&fid=0x0:0xee6a49b8baf2cca2"],"When":"2024-4-2"},{"Name":"Andres Noguez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUIhvStnz1ew41IopbO6-izkn-VZbg1362bdZn9Q57hOoMcThFF=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great deal on wings! Flavor of sauces is delicious, there are several options and wings are cooked to perfection. Beers are icy cold and the music is not too loud so you can even hold a normal conversation with friends.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"jason wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLAr7OPM3u3i7bBkh0r7Q9kS7_8Gu_88Crv223BgydShD66TQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good food for Pub.. $0.59 wings all day Monday to Thursday.. cheap breakfast..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNbFMP1Xx0ED3zW6NFylVTKmGQiro88IftIOOZT&fid=0x0:0xee6a49b8baf2cca2"],"When":"2024-1-24"},{"Name":"Rafael Prato","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVmw8x9RDf8apa9mg4sXkmCUBL57rpPrrUqVoRoTSqzlDDkuKry=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The $0.59 wings offer is unbeatable! The chicken was a bit soggy and wasn't crunchy. The atmosphere is decent.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNwvzL0XfyDvN4s4sPWv2fg79cPwcW_AreEWIuG&fid=0x0:0x98d200e4dc4e154e"],"When":"2019-3-3"},{"Name":"Luke Weng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXn1tdfwXfRnZVszKV8bZBNwooyRqfHv0VT8T0EAQWyUrqTrrO6aQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"When my friend and I were in front of the store, we saw the happy hour sign that caught our eye. It said "happy hour from 5-8pm!"

We were excited cause we were pretty hungry food. It was 5:12pm. The with said OPEN and the door was unlocked.

When we walked in,  the tables were completely cleaned up. The chairs were stacked. It looked like it was closing. We thought that they might not be opened yet, but saw that  the staff were chatting with some customers.

They completely ignored us even as we just stood there. It was very awkward. We even waved and walked towards them.

Ignored.

The chef saw us but didn't say anything but minded his own business.

We were so upset that we decided to just leave. I wouldn't want to come back again, not with THAT service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP0WsK7az2XV1KYw9LY0bgNxI-YoCpmbljH94ln&fid=0x0:0x98d200e4dc4e154e"],"When":"2019-3-10"}]
