[{"Name":"SylverscreenArts","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXulb8lBMEyh77llMzSuNBPq0Y3PJ79kx2d0ad9bIm1D3BdKA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing view, great place for meeting, weddings and parties. The outdoor is perfect for that destination wedding, a great bond for nature lovers, a Golfers nest. The staff are warm and friendly, very supportive, positive vibes. Great attention to details. And a great place to relax or hold short meetings outside office. It's indeed a great place to visit. The mountain view and the green vegetation is like a mini paradise.  I will recommend this place any time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNFF7RYptgXdxXmn36_au-zsmp0QBonoGIjljs&fid=0x0:0x585597849144ab14"],"When":"2024-10-18"},{"Name":"T.J. Hatten","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJVOLMVb24vyK1YFvD0fD9FRFgcvInujAC77z1dMK_hF2UlhA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is a great course to golf. Both fun and challenging with some great elevations. The clubhouse is well run, staff are knowledgeable and friendly. Highly recommended this course if you’re looking to have some fun experiencing a new course and challenging yourself and if you have a morning Tee time make sure to get their breakfast sandwich, it’s a great way to start your round.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNX252unc4TTVkrFHvTKjhe9MulxwyzzHFfV11L&fid=0x0:0x585597849144ab14"],"When":"2024-8-19"},{"Name":"William Weissig","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVrNXc3fo0JyuPHUboE7J5f28BCwV75YBHCPbj2rWiKGZWsN4oi=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Sylvia and Jayden helped set things up and coordinated for our wedding. They did a fantasic job and we have remarkable memories for the rest of our lives, thanks to their services.

We would definately recommend them as top workers who are great at wedding planning! Thanks a lot!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMe90ZvOc6zd1SpgYI62qfzfaWEnUaFiTtOqxrB&fid=0x0:0x585597849144ab14"],"When":"2024-11-26"},{"Name":"Jalen Sekhon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVq1XiBH92zFuiFtCb_QVoX4RoDeUFm_uYKWZgjITl7PxOn110=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The “marshall” said “you played a slow round” to me as I finished a sandy golfing experience. He verified that our round was 2 hours to play the 9 hole exec course. We had 4 walkers and we were up against the group in front of us the whole round. The round was fun despite the sandy covering the greens.. but I am shocked that a “marshall” would say that to me when he clearly saw the group in front of us just walk off. I think he would have gotten more data on the pace of play areas of concern by giving feed back to people mid round. I would have wanted a more warm and friendly guest experience than that, and certainly feedback from the “marshall’ about our pace of play that actually made logical sense.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNEEAL9Sl0nR7Hzve6jlrEl6K3yW4ubHTjxZfrW&fid=0x0:0x585597849144ab14"],"When":"2024-9-8"},{"Name":"Ralph McLennan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWrZ02oyygmsqSGGsqmF1szgrz-yPF3IvDkZC4IW16vCFUxAq9t=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We played on Monday morning June 24 2024, pro shop staff and starter were welcoming and informative (warned us we may come across a bear and made sure we had no food in the cart). We did come across the bear on the picturesque 3rd hole ! Course was in great shape, played in less than 4 hours. Had a great time with the twosome we were paired with (Dave & Julie) !! Will definitely be back this summer !! Thanks","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOH7o8PuNHvguzLKrjPNp5HKbR0LFBgo2IonpH3&fid=0x0:0x585597849144ab14"],"When":"2024-6-25"},{"Name":"Dëmin Photography (Wedding Photographer)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWAzZoBizu3g6fBece5zJLjGQxh8xQ2ZfhWDhSKPwt7Zp1Qwkmpow=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had the pleasure of photographing weddings at this stunning venue. The high ceilings in all of the halls and ballrooms create an elegant and spacious atmosphere, and the huge windows allow for natural light to pour in, making for exceptional photo opportunities. The outdoor ceremony options and bride and groom session areas are also fantastic, providing an abundance of picturesque settings.
The staff at this venue are very helpful, going above and beyond to ensure that everything runs smoothly and efficiently. The quality and variety of the food is also outstanding.
Overall, I would highly recommend this venue to anyone looking for a memorable and exquisite wedding experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPuQWHeTjvNDzEbE84r3SjQwMjFNWRMyH6ML_7G&fid=0x0:0x585597849144ab14"],"When":"2023-3-17"},{"Name":"Rob Boyle","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjULkY7_3AudI1Xn76AMW8uXeaTp75rSDuuXFRwd84yupHS7bF7_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I played Westwood Plateau (the full length course) for the first time ever. It was great. Westwood Plateau is literally in the mountains of Coquitlam and the views are amazing. The holes are challenging too. The neat thing is one can choose from a variety of tees. A top pro can choose the back tees at about 6800 yards whereas a newbie can choose the forward tees at about 5000 yards. I went with the middle tees. The conditioning of the course was pretty good for April. A little wet but we played the “preferred lies rule.” They have a super amount of sand bunkers. Unfortunately there were a lot of stones in those bunkers which have to be dealt with. Actually, do you know what the solution is? Don’t hit into them 🤣. There is a hitting cage to warm up but if you want to practice, you’ll have to do that at Westwood’s driving range and Executive course a mile or two away. By the way, the clubhouse is awesome and they have super food.  Overall, it was a very nice experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOeCfz7lBeO0gWdTweXR0qihre3PFlnxgA-qvo_&fid=0x0:0x585597849144ab14"],"When":"2023-4-30"},{"Name":"Philip Bentham","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIvCsZHcboVwOKcvYf3W188SQ0Qr6C6tSw3blyb-BqxpJMhnQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We ordered drinks and one came out after 20 minutes. The second didn't come for another 5-10 minutes. Very strange. We ordered the roasted red pepper queso and 75% of the chips were obliterated to the point where you couldn't even pick them up.

The servers were all lovely.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Veronica Flores","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXIcbpxxY7cEYQkV9Qidh7VmIOnFb2156UDhhTOBNCoTjA-Vac=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our dental team recently had the pleasure of experiencing the exceptional accommodations provided by Westwood Plateau and we couldn't be more thrilled with the experience. From start to finish, everything was perfectly organized and tailored to our needs. The staff went above and beyond to ensure our group felt welcome and well-cared-for. Their attention to detail and accommodating nature truly enhanced our experience. It was clear that they were committed to making our visit as enjoyable as possible. Overall, we had a fantastic time and are already looking forward to our next outing. We highly recommend Westwood Plateau for any group seeking a memorable and enjoyable golfing experience. Thank you Michelle for making our time so special!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ryan Bernard","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIHVVZffy0g5bV6LXjeZ74KJf8NsjvZc2kK4BLvlNCe0Pvn6A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Golfed at this place for over 20 years and suddenly you can't hit drivers at the "driving range" even though it's never been an issue in the past. Save your money and find another one if you dare to want to use one of the funnest clubs in your bag. They say it's so "bc hydro workers might be hit" even though I've never seen one work the tower at the max possible distance a pro could hit the club. No tees and cheap mats make this a regrettable choice for a fun night testing your bag. Not to mention having someone just hired to watch you and make you feel uncomfortable just wanting to hit some balls.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPDMKkuk7fRpL7Xn0PtOr8vMWAq7gZOVEffIdXB&fid=0x0:0xab36c34c09dd5998"],"When":"2024-7-9"},{"Name":"dberN 93","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXe_7kptmUSVUSvtN7m5ewykhfQi21I5xcAmfY0iFgzRSbfbBg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very fun casual golf experience.

The driving range is nice, you can order drinks and they have nice heaters if it gets cold. Only downside is you are limited to 250 yards.

The course is very fun to play, its an intermediate between a pitch and putt and full on golf course. A few short par 4s and a bunch of medium-long par 3s (115 to 185 yards). The main downside for me is the sand traps seem to receive little to no maintenance.

The staff are all very welcoming, generous and easy going. They make the experience even more fun.

There is also a BBQ outside with music and good hot dogs, which adds a great summer party ambiance.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"PG","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJe2tooglWYypE3cK2gMIbwAO5O3gibXEvQYdDuXisb1j7wiw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Just had a great experience at this venue. People in the pro shop were super accommodating, friendly and knowledgeable. From being flexible with our booking in, to retrieving our left behind properly to helping out on apparel in the pro shop They are an absolute credit to the business. Thank you.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kaila Howard","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUnwJ98owpkbOlLEdMzVHaQsqRezAt9Z0GHmAZy57HC7rhXEiK4Yg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"LOVE this course! It's so beautiful, with some incredible views along the way! The staff at the pro shop were amazing, so friendly and very accommodating. We were there a couple weeks ago and played through some crazy rain, one of my favourite days of golf i've ever had. Can't wait to play here again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Eugene S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIZk1vKJ1U5_8VNtqSIoRCc1gmtNBz_t1KtcH8dmyX1r-sI8Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Was at their training academy and it has a great setup. Really suitable for learning. Their cpga pro Ruel was super helpful and knows how to impart the golf knowledge to his students. Definitely a must try.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"S Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUgVRtmLdPczH7Nlq2q53lgx-yg5bLD8oyUEywwI6nugax-q0JM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice 12 hole course. Mostly par 3's but some par 4s. Can use a driver on about 2 or 3 holes. Some challenging shots. $20 to play on weekdays. Power carts are almost a must and they are $18 to rent. Very tiring to walk as it's located on the side of a mountain. At $20 it's good value. Will go again. Has a driving range, golf sims, and a full licensed restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPgJvbPxUAkVULxNYAZ6an7cRAkT5IydaGpv5Iz&fid=0x0:0xab36c34c09dd5998"],"When":"2019-8-30"},{"Name":"Paul Grimes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUh2dcV-KeKiiZJzAfq6rTrjExLXO2hA-dYeYoHESnAxCrNjy8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Staff are awesome. Very accommodating and friendly. The course needs a little work, but is a good 9 hole challenge.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"BSJAGRAON","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKOfDN1EtsV7Y2yZoNNvdw7xP_fnsHs3UTt29GhPENEM8UFoA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a great experience at this pizza spot! Overall, I highly recommend this place if you're looking for fresh, properly cooked pizza in a welcoming environment!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNOXZ71yCKaFdsRqt6qknhFQQrqemmXIHFa--fJ&fid=0x0:0x8115e1a2af5cce77"],"When":"2024-9-13"},{"Name":"prabhjot kaur toor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJsWtQugQdYmXgZHulFiyvXZ-0XtP7mWNSovx2tfkdbBVSv300=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Yesterday I went to subway and I get to know that there is new pizza store opening. I want to try something new so I check the menu as well as the reviews. After reading the reviews i don’t want to order But still my brother, order three pizzas………. Pizzas was soooo sooooo good, i never ever eat pizza like this one. I tried Super Hawaiian, pepperoni and one more…. And their food, service, and atmosphere are unbeatable.
I think someone put fake reviews from fake ids to misguide other people, may be jealo*** factor 🤣🤣🤣🤣.
I will definitely recommend you and 100% sure you will not regret..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPqBWqbDlfL29K3j-AfpwiPIpYFEk_zSfUkMPLB&fid=0x0:0x8115e1a2af5cce77"],"When":"2024-5-18"},{"Name":"Varun V Uppalapati","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0hR2k5UhurSCZ0f1b3vsC5kzt4eLzD-FXYy6uD0N-RZwQC-SL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Walked in to get a pick up special. The place looks absolutely clean.  Since it was our first time, I wasn't sure what to order and was helped by Ritika. She accommodated our request and also gave suggestions. Excellent customer service from her.
The pizza tastes good.

There is also plenty of free parking.

Overall, I will definitely be going back to try their other pizzas.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Zachary Morritt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVRKH7SdPojmEckRqAYwgOckuobhtGVtbG5dmrr8IcoZmzDXDrU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"New place from the Pizza 1 that used to be here. It’s good to have someplace close :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMMgdnpUZI9HwdU8D66Qnhq_cI39gXUw3czU8Qy&fid=0x0:0x8115e1a2af5cce77"],"When":"2024-5-20"},{"Name":"Nd Nd","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV9aAIyoQdMUZKpjAinmtBfvwVxIudCnPnmTIDeiBcffl9essqt=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"It's OK, not as good as the previous Pizza One that used to be in that location. Also they don't have multiple pizza combo specials which is too bad. Very average pizza not very tasty or good quality just very basically will do if your go too place isn't available. Too bad :(","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rob C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVhGlLP_VJpl3qW9qoyQpsesE5pvucyY6kZX0X5h01hxsrvPnlBbg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"A Disappointing replacement for Pizza1.

I’m genuinely disappointed with New West Pizza, the change in owner and menu is not for the better.

First, the pizza itself is a huge downgrade. The ingredient portions are noticeably smaller, not fresh, and the flavor is nonexistent. Instead of the rich, big taste that I expect, what you get is an overly greasy and oily mess. Long wait times for pick-up, even on weeknights.

As a vegetarian, I was particularly disheartened by the lack of freshness and variety in the vegetarian options. The few offerings they have seem like an afterthought, and none of them come close to what Pizza1 used to serve.

On top of that, the customer service is was very bad, I’ve noticed this on several visits when placing an order by phone and picking up my order,

I can’t recommend this place in its current state. It’s truly disheartening to see such a decline in what used to be a local favorite for Coquitlam and Port Moody. I had been a regular customer of Pizza1 since 2009.

However, I’d be more than happy to update this review if things improve on a future visit.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"ABHIR GUPTA","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLg7qltToC35uub3-sdU4FB5qano4DzGiAQsY3A2I6SE3DPlw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tried shahi paneer pizza & loved it .

[{"Name":"Gab Wiessmann","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVCJTnBjHmNVcf6NPJ-Hd6gf8lWFoXmsloOeyZIsL5GoTQ3qtCc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I ordered the tonkotsu ramen with extra noodles and it was one of the best ramen I’ve had in the Coquitlam area. The noodles were perfectly cooked, not too hard, not too soft. The broth was really good too, not too salty like most tonkotsu ramen I’ve had. I also loved the amount of customization you could do when ordering through the kiosk. I will definitely return here next time I’m visiting the area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOVw6_k1kxlVmZKBASUISFP5WwoODLH2Xsb0ijW&fid=0x0:0x9a7fc6ef7ee65139"],"When":"2024-6-23"},{"Name":"Marie Amin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIKR0qp3fose5GsYts0dtMeJqwXo1MWNFSPwo4SjCtJGEbgYA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Today we revisited my favorite spot with the family. Unfortunately, the food quality has declined significantly. The 2 shoyu ramen priced at $17 each and the karage Don at $18 were disappointing in terms of portion size and taste. Was hoping for the great experience we remember, but left unsatisfied. ⭐"  ps. The salad was so dry, gross!
The person with a good review before me, must be a friend or work at this place or he or she doesn't know what real good food supposed to taste like.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO-JioxapoTk3ckQS1ZHI4fDu4tlWI3ZLL_WaYk&fid=0x0:0x9a7fc6ef7ee65139"],"When":"2024-4-6"},{"Name":"Viona Halim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV5PMLEtvgkAwv2IjmL8XXm0-Ly_XpBo5Kd0Hv2pxoQ26_Hfy4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Passed by this stall when we were at the mall and we decided to give it a try. If you've never been here before, the way to order is by self-service touchscreen stations they have on the left side of the counter. We're so used to just ordering to the staff and completely missed the touchscreen stations 😆.

One thing this ramen place has it going is the noodle. They're perfectly cooked with a nice bite and chew to them. You can choose between pork-based or chicken-based broth. We both chose pork-based since we like to base things on traditional first when trying new places. The pork-based is very thick and  creamy. If you're a fan of those really thick and creamy ramen, this place is for you. For us, while we like rich broth, this one is more on the too thick and too rich side of things. I also find for the TanTan ramen, that the broth is too much on the salty side of things. My husband got the chashu ramen and the salt level is much better, just right. Maybe we should've gone with the chicken-based broth instead...

Avg price is somewhere between $13-14/ bowl. You can make it a combo and pick 1 small side dish like gyoza, karaage or donburi, etc. Drinks not included in combo. So for 2 people, if you order 2 combos, expect to pay somewhere along the line of $40 or so. Price-wise, I feel like you can have a better ramen at a sit-down restaurant. You might be paying a little more, but not THAT much more.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOScIYJALBSiF24q2-KcOHh_ChTNlQ-S70oyD2K&fid=0x0:0x9a7fc6ef7ee65139"],"When":"2022-7-29"},{"Name":"Alex Barros","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLbGQfDFyWBFf-SHj8dHqz7fJQ6yDYj9me5-vlKbsRH7vrJMA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The noodles in the Ramen has a strange chemical  smell.  I'm disappointed  with  the food.  The service needs  improvement. Price is reasonable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMu4DPFM0ceUOEV358GE-Www877YZsbj2xHvYVL&fid=0x0:0x9a7fc6ef7ee65139"],"When":"2024-1-24"},{"Name":"Ivan Lin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWAnyoYYXXFP9snQgaU7KUgox1Ss1DMCPvpD-7cL-ggizeHFLh87A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The noodles tasted very good, with a good amount of toppings. Though the price point is a bit on the more expensive side.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPNfayJ7TEep5u_6KWqksKK8Ej6UXvgY-opNj3I&fid=0x0:0x9a7fc6ef7ee65139"],"When":"2024-9-13"},{"Name":"Sally Zeng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXyvG25e-9g8jG0ZfEMdub-S4p2HgxJMLK-NlH0Jp5V2gdVjPNsjg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My son enjoyed very much! I like it too. It’s butter than some  Downtown famous ramen 🍜. I like the Shio, and the chicken base soup tasted not too great. The actual use fire to burn the Chasu meat makes it so delicious. I always go to enjoy it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNlJSGXtQTPWpT_r0LF5x7JXOhuEIKq2fLCXAka&fid=0x0:0x9a7fc6ef7ee65139"],"When":"2024-2-20"},{"Name":"Y. Cherski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK-7SLlKKRW0Rqcp9wRXFlvt6gbh0rtI7PMIroLgxETtGiPwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"In the gastronomical tapestry that is the food court, Menbow Ramen stands not as the gourmet stitch but as the humble, durable thread that holds it all together. Though its ramen won't be ascending to any culinary Mount Olympus, its reliably decent servings manage to stir envy in its broth-boiling brotherhood. Plus, with their takeout packages more secure than a bank vault, others could definitely learn a thing or two about food to-go.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP26cs1Lk5fkGR9pw9_NT-qSYbA_hURSlVx_xXD&fid=0x0:0x9a7fc6ef7ee65139"],"When":"2023-6-22"},{"Name":"Joe B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXgMmsnd7ebO17Gbmka7I7uLdXQJEThrmwrdC1eUggf2HzY-KVbLQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely loved it at the first mouthful. Broth is superb. Noodles chewy.. Pork tender and well charred. In PoCo it's hard to find a good Ramen shop and this one definitely did the trick. Loved it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPwalkgiLrTb2Thx4NXPhDWrFshx7vUoqJLneZm&fid=0x0:0x9a7fc6ef7ee65139"],"When":"2024-2-8"}]
